const PROJECTS = [{"id": "IOT-001", "title": "AI Voice-Controlled Companion Robot for Autonomous Task Execution and Environment Interaction", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Embedded Systems", "nature": "Product", "source": "Orangewood project", "supervisor": "Ch. Ravi Sankar", "sitting_place": "36-203-CH8", "description": "The project aims to develop an AI-driven, voice-controlled robotic system capable of performing autonomous physical tasks and interacting intelligently with its environment. Utilizing the computational power of the Raspberry Pi 5 in combination with the NVIDIA Jetson Nano, the robot integrates multiple sensors, computer vision modules, and natural language understanding (NLU) capabilities to interpret and execute user commands. The system allows users to control and interact with the robot through natural voice commands, such as \"Go to the kitchen and bring me the salt sprinkler.\" The robot processes these commands using onboard speech recognition, NLP-based command interpretation, and path planning algorithms. The vision system, powered by advanced computer vision (CV) models, such as object detection, facial recognition, and environment mapping, enables the robot to perceive its surroundings and make context-aware decisions. By combining AI-based reasoning, speech understanding, and robotic control, this project aims to create a system capable of learning new tasks, adapting to different environments, and operating semi-autonomously without extensive pre-programmed instructions. The robot has a fallback option for higher computational and processing resource-required tasks, such as cloud computing. Low-level controls will be done on the ESP-32, and various sensors, such as the MPU6050, force sensors, etc., will be used for feedback to the control agent. Integration of ROS 2 enables the efficient communication between the different agents."}, {"id": "IOT-002", "title": "AI-based Anti-Cheating Proctoring System", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Embedded Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Manoj Sindhwani", "sitting_place": "36-202 A-WS1", "description": "AI-based Anti-Cheating Proctoring System for university examinations using computer vision and machine learning. The system uses classroom/laptop cameras to monitor students during exams in real time. It detects suspicious activities such as looking away frequently, mobile phone usage, presence of multiple persons, face absence, talking, and unusual movements. Alerts are generated instantly, and all suspicious events are logged with timestamps. The project aims to improve exam fairness, reduce manual invigilation load, and provide automated monitoring with high accuracy."}, {"id": "IOT-003", "title": "AI-enabled Smart Helmet", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Embedded Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Manoj Sindhwani", "sitting_place": "36-202 A-WS1", "description": "An AI-enabled Smart Helmet designed to enhance rider safety using computer vision and IoT. It detects vehicles in blind spots, predicts lane change risks, and provides real time alerts. An inertial measurement unit based accident detection system verifies crash severity, while a belt sensor prevents false triggers. Upon a confirmed accident, the helmet automatically sends an SMS with live GPS location to emergency contacts."}, {"id": "IOT-004", "title": "AI-Enabled Smart Logistics & Supply Chain Automation", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Embedded Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "Live Project", "supervisor": "Ch. Ravi Sankar", "sitting_place": "36-203-CH8", "description": "The project focuses on developing an \"AI-enabled smart logistics and supply chain automation system\" that enhances efficiency, reduces operational costs, and minimises delays. Using AI algorithms for demand forecasting, route optimization and real-time inventory tracking,the system enables data-driven decision-making. It integrates IoT sensors and machine learning models to automate processes, ensure transparency and improve overall logistics performance."}, {"id": "IOT-005", "title": "Al based Real-Time Academic Query Assistant", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Embedded Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "It's a real-life problem which all students are facing during EDU-REV", "supervisor": "Dr. Someet Singh", "sitting_place": "36-203-C1", "description": "The invention addresses a critical gap in academic information delivery within educational institutions. Students and staff currently lack a dedicated, always-available, intelligent system to answer college-specific academic queries such as exam schedules, syllabus details, faculty information, admission procedures, and academic rules. Existing general-purpose AI chatbots (e.g., ChatGPT) are not trained on institution-specific data and cannot provide accurate, contextually relevant answers for a particular college. Manual inquiry counters are time-limited, slow, and inconsistent. There is no system that combines institution-curated knowledge, cloud AI inference, real-time feedback collection, and autonomous knowledge base improvement into a single deployable academic assistant. Furthermore, no existing solution integrates a cloud-deployed chatbot backend with a physical embedded hardware interface (ESP32-S3 + display + keyboard) for offline-style kiosk use on campus."}, {"id": "IOT-006", "title": "Development of Cost-Effective Eco-Friendly Onion Storage Technology for Rural Applications", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Embedded Systems", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH Statement", "supervisor": "Dr. Harpreet Singh Bedi", "sitting_place": "36-202 A-WS4", "description": "This project aims to develop a comprehensive system for analyzing and enhancing the shelf life of onions, employing advanced analytical techniques such as spectroscopy and image processing to assess quality and nutritional content. By integrating cutting-edge technologies with controlled atmosphere storage and ethylene management, the project seeks to create optimal conditions for onion preservation, dynamically adjusting storage parameters based on real-time data to prolong shelf life and minimize waste. Through this interdisciplinary approach, the project aims to contribute to sustainable agricultural practices by reducing post-harvest losses and ensuring a consistent supply of high-quality onions to consumers worldwide"}, {"id": "IOT-007", "title": "Gesture controlled smart home: an IOT and machine learning approach", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Embedded Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Dr. Neha Ahuja", "sitting_place": "36-203-CH15", "description": "This project introduces a novel smart home automation system that integrates gesture recognition, Internet of Things (loT), and Machine Learning (ML) to provide an intuitive and efficient user experience. By utilizing computer vision techniques, the system accurately interprets user gestures, such as swipes, circles, and pinches, to control various home appliances. These gestures are translated into commands that are executed by a microcontroller, which in turn controls devices like lights, fans, and door locks. To enhance system performance and adaptability, ML algorithms are employed to analyze user behavior and environmental factors. This enables the system to learn user preferences, optimize energy consumption, and proactively respond to changes in the home environment. Additionally, loT technology facilitates remote monitoring and control of home appliances, providing users with flexibility and convenience. This research explores the potential of gesture-based interfaces to revolutionize smart home technology. By offering a hands-free and intuitive user experience, this system can significantly improve the quality of life for individuals of all ages and abilities."}, {"id": "IOT-008", "title": "IOT based tyre pressure and temperature monitoring system", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Embedded Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "Not specified", "supervisor": "Dr. Jhulan kumar", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "Description not available for this problem statement."}, {"id": "IOT-009", "title": "IoT-Based Hydroponic System with Autonomous Nutrient Control and Real-Time Monitoring for Precision Saffron Cultivation", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Embedded Systems", "nature": "Product", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2026", "supervisor": "Ch. Ravi Sankar", "sitting_place": "36-203-CH8", "description": "The proposed system presents a distributed and intelligent hydroponic farming system designed to enable precise cultivation of saffron in controlled environments using IoT and embedded systems. The system is built on a multi-node architecture consisting of three ESP32 microcontrollers, where two nodes function as independent slave controllers assigned to separate hydroponic chambers, and one node acts as a master communication unit. Each slave ESP32 is integrated with multiple sensors, including temperature and humidity sensors, a pH sensor, an electrical conductivity (EC) sensor, a light intensity sensor, and a water flow sensor. These sensors continuously monitor environmental and nutrient conditions required for optimal plant growth. Based on real-time sensor data, each slave node performs autonomous decision-making and directly controls actuators such as nutrient dosing pumps, pH adjustment pumps, water circulation pumps, mist makers, cooling modules, and grow lights. The system operates on a distributed control approach where each chamber is independently managed by its respective slave controller without relying on centralized processing. This ensures faster response time and continuous operation even in case of communication failure. The master ESP32 serves as a communication gateway and does not participate in control decisions. It receives processed data from both slave nodes through LoRa communication and transmits it to a cloud-based platform (Blynk) for real-time visualization and remote monitoring. The system handles multiple operational scenarios: Case 1: When environmental parameters such as temperature, humidity, pH, or EC deviate from predefined optimal ranges, the respective slave controller immediately activates the required actuators. For instance, if the EC value drops below the required level, nutrient pumps are activated to restore concentration. Similarly, if pH deviates from the acceptable range, corrective solutions are automatically added. Case 2: If communication between slave and master nodes is interrupted, the slave nodes continue to operate independently using locally stored control logic. This ensures uninterrupted plant growth and system reliability without dependency on cloud connectivity or central control. All monitored parameters and system actions are continuously transmitted to the cloud interface, where users can observe real-time conditions and system performance."}, {"id": "IOT-010", "title": "IoT-Based Polyhouse Monitoring and Automation System for Precision Agriculture", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Embedded Systems", "nature": "Product", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2026", "supervisor": "Ch. Ravi Sankar", "sitting_place": "36-203-CH8", "description": "The prosed system presents an intelligent and automated polyhouse monitoring system designed to improve agricultural productivity using IoT and embedded systems. The system is built using a centralized ESP32 microcontroller that continuously monitors environmental conditions and performs automated control actions. The ESP32 microcontroller is integrated with multiple sensors, including a temperature and humidity sensor (DHT22), a light intensity sensor (LDR), and a soil moisture sensor. These sensors continuously monitor environmental parameters required for optimal plant growth inside the polyhouse. Based on real-time sensor data, the ESP32 performs automatic decision-making and controls actuators such as LED grow lights. For example, when light intensity falls below a predefined threshold, the system automatically activates the LED lighting system to maintain proper illumination for plants. The system operates using a smart IoT-based approach where all sensor data is transmitted to a cloud platform (ThingSpeak) through Wi-Fi connectivity. This allows users to monitor environmental conditions remotely in real time. The system handles multiple operational scenarios: Case 1: When environmental parameters such as temperature, humidity, light intensity, or soil moisture deviate from predefined optimal ranges, the ESP32 automatically performs corrective actions. For instance, if light intensity drops below the required level, LED lights are activated. Case 2: All monitored parameters and system actions are continuously transmitted to the ThingSpeak cloud platform, where users can observe real-time data."}, {"id": "IOT-011", "title": "IoT-Based Smart Energy Monitoring System for Optimizing Power Consumption in Residential and Commercial Buildings", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Embedded Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH 2024 Energy-efficient smart building solutions", "supervisor": "Dr. Suverna Sengar", "sitting_place": "36-203-CH10", "description": "This project develops an IoT-based smart energy monitoring system to track and analyze real-time electricity consumption in residential and commercial buildings. Using sensors, microcontrollers, and a cloud dashboard, it identifies energy wastage, provides usage insights, and supports optimized power management for improved efficiency and reduced electricity costs."}, {"id": "IOT-012", "title": "Optimizing Onion Storage Conditions Using Modern Technological Interventions", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Embedded Systems", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH Statement", "supervisor": "Dr. Harpreet Singh Bedi", "sitting_place": "36-202 A-WS4", "description": "The proposed system employs a combination of gas and temperature sensors to monitor the environment surrounding stored onions. The gas sensor (MQ-135) detects harmful volatile compounds such as ammonia and sulfur-based gases emitted during onion decomposition, while the DHT11 temperature sensor records ambient temperature data. These readings are processed by the ESP32 microcontroller, which compares them against predefined threshold values. If the detected values exceed the set limits, the system identifies the onion as spoiled and triggers an alert through RGB LEDs and a display interface. Conversely, fresh onions are indicated through a green light signal."}, {"id": "IOT-013", "title": "Real-Time Pest Movement Analytics and IoT-Based Field Monitoring using ESP32", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Embedded Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Suverna Sengar", "sitting_place": "36-203-CH10", "description": "Agriculture is increasingly facing challenges related to environmental changes, pest attacks, and inefficient resource management. Continuous monitoring of environmental condi-tions in agricultural fields is essential for maintaining crop health and improving productivity. Traditional monitoring methods rely heavily on manual inspection, which can be time-consuming and may not always provide timely information about changes in field conditions. This research presents a Real-Time Pest Movement Analyt-ics and IoT-Based Field Monitoring System using the ESP32 microcontroller. The proposed system integrates multiple sen-sors, including a soil moisture sensor, DHT22 temperature and humidity sensor, and a gas sensor, to monitor environmental conditions in agricultural fields. The ESP32 microcontroller collects sensor data and processes it in real time. The system displays environmental parameters on an OLED display and provides alert notifications through a buzzer when abnormal environmental conditions are detected. Additionally, the system incorporates an automated irrigation mechanism using a relay-controlled water pump that activates when soil moisture levels fall below a predefined threshold. This automation ensures efficient water usage and reduces the need for manual monitoring. The proposed system provides farmers with a cost-effective and intelligent solution for monitoring field conditions and improving crop productivity through smart agricultural practices."}, {"id": "IOT-014", "title": "Road-Vehicle Magnetic Coupling System for Sustainable Electricity Generation", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Embedded Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "Inductive Energy Harvesting for Smart Vehicles under SIH's 'Clean & Green Technology / Renewable Energy' Theme SIH2023", "supervisor": "Dr. Suverna Sengar", "sitting_place": "36-203-CH10", "description": "The project develops a dual-coil electromagnetic system where one coil is embedded in the road and the other is mounted on a moving vehicle. As vehicles pass over the stationary coil, changing magnetic flux generates electricity. This innovative approach enables clean, continuous, and traffic-driven power generation for smart roads and sustainable urban infrastructure."}, {"id": "IOT-015", "title": "Smart Fuel Measuring System", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Embedded Systems", "nature": "Product", "source": "It's a real-life problem which all faces while refilling the fuel tank", "supervisor": "Dr. Someet Singh", "sitting_place": "36-203-C1", "description": "The smart Fuel measuring system is a modern, IoT-enabled device that helps you keep track of the fuel you pump in real-time. Using a fuel-rated flow sensor and an ESP8266 microcontroller, it accurately measures how much fuel is flowing into your tank. The measured amount is shown on a clear OLED screen, and the data can also be sent to the cloud for remote monitoring. This system not only ensures precise fuel measurement and reduces wastage but also protects users from fuel pump frauds, making it a smart and reliable alternative to traditional mechanical fuel meters."}, {"id": "IOT-016", "title": "Smart Pothole Detection and Response System with Real-Time Alerting and Automatic Road Condition Updation", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Embedded Systems", "nature": "Product", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2026", "supervisor": "Ch. Ravi Sankar", "sitting_place": "36-203-CH8", "description": "The proposed invention sets forth a sophisticated, computerized pothole detection and action system with a purpose to improve road safety and maintenance of infrastructures by means of real-time sensing, machine learning, and intelligent communication technologies. The system utilizes a Raspberry Pi that serves as the master controller with various sensors mounted thereon, such as a stereo camera, ultrasonic sensor, and GPS module to carry out sophisticated pothole detection and decisioning. The system handles two main scenarios: Case 1: When there is detection by both the stereo camera and ultrasonic sensor and when the vehicle is within a preset distance, the system immediately engages the vehicle control module. The vehicle control module actuates the braking or reduces the vehicle speed autonomously. A digital map interface is refreshed in real time to visually identify the pothole and provide better direction and awareness to neighboring drivers. The GPS position of the pothole is communicated to a centralized server through Vehicle-to-Infrastructure (V2I) communication to be logged centrally. Case 2: If the stereo camera cannot detect the pothole (due to lack of vision or blockages, e.g.), the system resorts to the accelerometer as a back-up. The potholes are detected by the accelerometer with abnormal vibration patterns."}, {"id": "IOT-017", "title": "TraceID -- Smart System for Latent Fingerprint Enhancement and Recognition", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Embedded Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "https://www.nec.com/en/global/solutions/biometrics/fingerprint/index.html", "supervisor": "Dr. Rosepreet Kaur Bhogal", "sitting_place": "36-202 A-WS7", "description": "The project is anticipated to produce a functional prototype that will enhance and recognize latent fingerprints with greater accuracy. It will create a system that can automatically enhance poor-quality fingerprint images, extract relevant minutiae features, and match fingerprints against a database in a timely manner. The result will demonstrate the feasibility of combining image processing and machine learning techniques for forensic and security applications along with the accompanying documentation and performance evaluation."}, {"id": "IOT-018", "title": "TraceID: Smart System for Latent Fingerprint Enhancement and Recognition", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Embedded Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "https://www.nec.com/en/global/solutions/biometrics/fingerprint/index.html", "supervisor": "Dr. Rosepreet Kaur Bhogal", "sitting_place": "36-202 A-WS7", "description": "The project is anticipated to produce a functional prototype that will enhance and recognize latent fingerprints with greater accuracy. It will create a system that can automatically enhance poor-quality fingerprint images, extract relevant minutiae features, and match fingerprints against a database in a timely manner. The result will demonstrate the feasibility of combining image processing and machine learning techniques for forensic and security applications along with the accompanying documentation and performance evaluation."}, {"id": "AI-001", "title": "3D Brain Tumor Segmentation Using Deep Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Brats challenge 2024", "supervisor": "Dr. Shallu Duggal", "sitting_place": "38-602-CH7", "description": "This project is about building a smart computer system that can automatically detect and show brain tumors in MRI scans. It's like having a helper for doctors who can look at brain images and clearly mark the exact location of a tumor."}, {"id": "AI-002", "title": "A Multi-Disease Diagnostic Framework Using Feature-Based Routing and Machine Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Self-Initiated", "supervisor": "Ravinder Singh", "sitting_place": "28-204-CH8", "description": "This project develops an artificial intelligence-based multi-disease prediction system for early and efficient healthcare support. It uses a feature-based routing mechanism to select the most relevant prediction model according to the input features provided. The proposed approach eliminates the need to merge multiple datasets into a single unified dataset. The system is designed to support the prediction of diseases such as diabetes, heart disease, and chronic kidney disease (CKD). It also provides explainable results, enabling users and healthcare professionals to better understand the prediction outcomes. The framework is scalable, efficient, and suitable for practical healthcare applications with varying data conditions. In addition, its architecture is well-suited for edge deployment, making it useful for real-time and resource-constrained medical environments."}, {"id": "AI-003", "title": "Adaptive AI-Driven Classroom Attendance and Engagement Analytics System Using Autonomous Pan--Tilt IoT Vision Architecture", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "NA", "supervisor": "Dr. Shilpa( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "Existing attendance systems focus only on physical presence detection using RFID, biometrics, or static face recognition cameras. However, classroom presence does not necessarily reflect cognitive participation or engagement. Traditional systems fail to detect inattentiveness or disengagement, provide behavioural analytics, adapt camera coverage dynamically, or offer multi-level live academic monitoring. This research proposes an integrated system that moves beyond presence verification andintroduces engagement aware attendance intelligence."}, {"id": "AI-004", "title": "AgroVerse -- AI-Integrated Multilingual Agricultural Assistance and Scheme Navigation Platform", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Anuj Sharma", "sitting_place": "34-204-CH3", "description": "AgroVerse is a digital agricultural assistance system designed to support farmers by providing integrated access to crop advisory services, agricultural scheme information, and multilingual voice-based interaction. The platform functions as a centralized agricultural information and support ecosystem that helps farmers make better farming decisions while also enabling them to easily access government and private agricultural schemes."}, {"id": "AI-005", "title": "AI Based Medical Report Analyser", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SCA2502-002", "supervisor": "Priyank Arora", "sitting_place": "38-508-CH9", "description": "The proposed AI-Based Medical Report Analyzer aims to develop an intelligent healthcare decision-support system that can automatically process and interpret unstructured medical reports. With the rapid digitization of healthcare, large volumes of clinical data such as laboratory reports, discharge summaries, and diagnostic records are generated in formats that are often difficult for patients to understand and time-consuming for healthcare professionals to analyze manually. This project addresses these challenges by integrating Optical Character Recognition (OCR), Natural Language Processing (NLP), Machine Learning (ML), and Explainable Artificial Intelligence (XAI) into a unified framework. The system will accept scanned or PDF-based medical reports and convert them into machine-readable text using OCR techniques. NLP methods will then be applied to extract structured clinical parameters such as test values, units, and medical entities. These parameters will be compared with standardized clinical reference ranges to detect abnormalities. Further, machine learning models will be employed to predict potential disease risks based on extracted features and generate probabilistic health insights. To enhance transparency and trust, Explainable AI techniques will provide interpretable explanations of model predictions. The project will primarily focus on laboratory reports including CBC, lipid profile, liver and kidney function tests. A user-friendly dashboard will visualize abnormal values, risk scores, and historical health trends. Overall, the system aims to improve efficiency, reduce manual workload, and enhance patient understanding of medical data."}, {"id": "AI-006", "title": "AI-Based Accident Hotspot Prediction System using GIS and Machine Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Independent Research Idea", "supervisor": "Dr. Sahil Rampal", "sitting_place": "38-603-CH19", "description": "This project develops an AI-based accident hotspot prediction system using GIS and machine learning. DBSCAN clustering is used to detect accident hotspots, and Random Forest predicts accident severity. An Accident Risk Index (ARI) is calculated using severity, accident density, and environmental factors. Results are visualised on an interactive dashboard to help traffic authorities take preventive safety measures."}, {"id": "AI-007", "title": "AI-Based Plant Disease Detection and Quality Analysis System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Collaborative Brainstorming", "supervisor": "Dr. Ramandeep Kaur", "sitting_place": "38-603-CH12", "description": "Agriculture plays an important role in food production and the global economy. However, plant diseases are a major challenge for farmers because they reduce crop yield, damage plant quality, and cause economic losses. Traditionally, plant diseases are detected manually by farmers or agricultural experts through visual inspection. This method is time-consuming, requires experience, and may lead to incorrect diagnosis, especially in the early stages of disease. The proposed project, \"AI-Based Plant Disease Detection and Quality Analysis System,\" aims to develop an intelligent system that automatically detects plant diseases and evaluates plant health using artificial intelligence and image processing techniques. The system will take images of plant leaves or fruits as input and use deep learning models, particularly Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN), to identify plant types and detect diseases. The model will be trained using publicly available datasets such as the PlantVillage dataset, which contains thousands of labeled images of plant diseases. After training, the system will classify whether a plant is healthy or infected and will also analyze plant quality based on factors such as leaf color, disease severity, and overall plant condition. This system will help farmers and researchers detect plant diseases quickly, improve crop monitoring, and support the development of smart agriculture solutions."}, {"id": "AI-008", "title": "AI-Based Smart Classroom Attendance and Monitoring System Using Face Recognition", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "Ministry of IT and ministry of Education", "supervisor": "Neha", "sitting_place": "38-601-CH18", "description": "Attendance management is an essential part of academic institutions, but traditional methods such as manual attendance and RFID-based systems are time-consuming, error-prone, and susceptible to proxy attendance. With the advancement of Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Computer Vision, automated attendance systems can improve efficiency, accuracy, and classroom monitoring. This project proposes an AI-based Smart Classroom Attendance and Monitoring System that uses facial recognition technology to automatically detect, recognize, and record student attendance. The system captures classroom video through a camera, identifies multiple students in real time, and stores attendance data securely in a database while providing monitoring and analytics through a web dashboard. The system aims to reduce manual effort, improve attendance transparency, and introduce intelligent monitoring capabilities in classrooms."}, {"id": "AI-009", "title": "AI-Based Smart Faculty Attendance and Student Duty Leave Management System Using Face Recognition.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Ramandeep Kaur", "sitting_place": "38-508-CH8", "description": "The proposed system is an intelligent and automated solution designed to streamline attendance management and duty leave handling in educational institutions using Artificial Intelligence. Traditional attendance systems are often time-consuming, prone to errors, and susceptible to proxy attendance. To overcome these challenges, this project utilizes face recognition technology to ensure accurate, efficient, and secure attendance tracking for both faculty and students. The system works by capturing real-time images through a camera installed in classrooms or entry points. These images are processed using AI-based face recognition algorithms, which compare the captured faces with a pre-trained dataset of registered users. Once a match is identified, the attendance is automatically marked and stored in a centralized database. This eliminates the need for manual roll calls and reduces the chances of manipulation or human error. In addition to attendance management, the system incorporates a Student Duty Leave Management module. Students who participate in official academic or extracurricular activities can apply for duty leave through the system. Faculty members or authorized personnel can review, approve, or reject these requests digitally. Once approved, the system automatically updates the student's attendance records, ensuring fairness and transparency. The system also provides features such as real-time attendance monitoring, report generation, and data analytics for better decision-making. It can help institutions track attendance patterns, identify irregularities, and improve overall academic management. The primary objective of this project is to develop a smart, reliable, and user-friendly system that integrates attendance tracking with duty leave management. By leveraging AI and automation, the system enhances operational efficiency, minimizes manual workload, and ensures data accuracy. In conclusion, the proposed system offers a modern approach to academic administration by combining face recognition technology with digital leave management. It not only improves efficiency and security but also supports institutions in maintaining accurate and transparent records, ultimately contributing to better governance and student management."}, {"id": "AI-010", "title": "AI-Driven Real-Time Depth-Aware Navigation for Flood Rescue", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon (SIH) 2024.", "supervisor": "Dr. Devender Kumar", "sitting_place": "38-602-CH13", "description": "Aqua-Route is an AI system for flood rescue that generates \"Dynamic Safe-Passage Maps.\" By fusing real-time sonar data with satellite imagery, it identifies safe walking or boating routes. Key features include sonar-to-map synchronization, stability analysis to detect collapsed submerged roads using vibration sensors, and offline mesh-routing via LoRa to guide survivors to shelters without cellular networks."}, {"id": "AI-011", "title": "An AI-Powered Framework for Early Detection and Diagnosis of Crop Diseases Using Multimodal Data", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Ravinder Singh", "sitting_place": "28-204-CH8", "description": "This study proposes an AI-powered framework for the early detection and diagnosis of crop diseases by combining multimodal data such as plant images, environmental factors, and sensor-based inputs. The framework aims to improve diagnostic accuracy, support timely intervention, and help farmers protect crop health, increase productivity, and promote sustainable agriculture."}, {"id": "AI-012", "title": "An AI-Powered Skill Gap Analyzer Integrated with MicroCourses Learning Engine", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "self", "supervisor": "Rohini", "sitting_place": "38-508-CH4", "description": "The global labor market is currently undergoing a seismic shift driven by the Fourth Industrial Revolution. In India, which possesses the world's youngest workforce, this transition presents both a demographic dividend and a significant structural challenge. While millions of graduates enter the workforce annually, a staggering percentage are deemed \"unemployable\" by industry standards. This is not due to a lack of degrees, but a widening \"skill gap\"---the disparity between the static academic curricula provided by educational institutions and the dynamic, rapidly evolving requirements of the modern tech-driven economy."}, {"id": "AI-013", "title": "An Intelligent Graph-Based System for ATS Resume Analysis", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Self Identified", "supervisor": "Dr.Amar Singh", "sitting_place": "38-602-C2", "description": "To develop an intelligent resume analysis system that evaluates resumes against job descriptions using graph-based skill matching and role-aware scoring techniques. To design and implement a full-stack web application that allows users to upload or select resumes, input job descriptions, and receive real-time ATS compatibility scores along with skill improvement suggestions. To build a skill relationship graph that captures connections between related technologies and enables semantic matching beyond simple keyword detection. To implement a skill gap analysis module that identifies missing skills required for a specific job role and predicts how adding those skills would improve the ATS score."}, {"id": "AI-014", "title": "Analyzing seismic patterns to enhance earthquake predictions through time series models", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Coordinating Committee for Earthquake Prediction (Japan)", "supervisor": "Anirban Das", "sitting_place": "38-602-CH17", "description": "Earthquakes, caused by crustal movements, are difficult to predict due to complex tectonic activity. Traditional methods lack precision, while AI and machine learning, especially CNNs and LSTMs, improve prediction accuracy using seismic time-series data. IoT enables real-time monitoring, supporting early warning systems and better disaster preparedness through enhanced predictive modeling."}, {"id": "AI-015", "title": "AOTPRAS Autonomous Orbital Threat Prediction and Risk Assessment System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "N/A", "supervisor": "Sarbjeet Singh", "sitting_place": "38-602-CH14", "description": "Space has become the most important common infrastructure for mankind. Everything from navigation systems that allow autonomous driving to satellite meteorology to provide weather predictions several days ahead of time and broadband constellations to deliver internet to unconnected parts of the world depends on satellites orbiting safely in the scarce and precious resource of Low Earth Orbit. However, LEO is under increasing danger not because of the natural environment there, but because of the ever-increasing amount of man-made debris in orbit. This orbital space is subject to a paradoxical principle of orbital mechanics: while everything that makes LEO suitable for communication purposes and observation -- small distance to the ground, relatively low signal delay, wide swaths of coverage, economical cost of launch -- also means that space is a common pool where anything done there affects everyone's operation. Even an impact of two satellites traveling at 7.5 km per second would release the energy equivalent to several tons of explosives and create clouds of hundreds of thousands of dangerous fragments able to damage other spacecraft. Unlike pollution of the land, debris in orbit does not decay naturally but remains in place for decades or even centuries."}, {"id": "AI-016", "title": "Derma Vision : AI Powered Skin cancer Detection system", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "healthcare", "supervisor": "Dr. Shallu Duggal", "sitting_place": "38-602-CH7", "description": "DermaVision is an artificial intelligence--based system designed to assist in the early detection of skin cancer by analyzing images of skin lesions. Skin cancer is one of the most common types of cancer worldwide, and early detection significantly increases the chances of successful treatment. However, diagnosing skin cancer at an early stage can be difficult without expert medical evaluation. DermaVision aims to support dermatologists and healthcare professionals by providing a fast, accessible, and intelligent screening tool. The system uses deep learning and computer vision techniques, particularly Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), to analyze images of skin lesions and identify patterns associated with different types of skin conditions. The model is trained on a large dataset of labeled dermoscopic images that include both benign (non-cancerous) and malignant (cancerous) lesions such as melanoma. During training, the AI learns to recognize important visual features such as shape, color variation, border irregularity, and texture of the lesion. When a user uploads an image of a skin lesion into the DermaVision system, the image first undergoes preprocessing. This step includes resizing, normalization, and noise reduction to improve image quality and ensure consistency for the AI model. After preprocessing, the trained deep learning model analyzes the image and classifies it based on the likelihood of being benign or malignant. The system then generates a prediction along with a confidence score that indicates how certain the model is about its result. DermaVision can be implemented as a web-based or mobile application, allowing users to upload images easily and receive quick analysis results. This makes the system especially useful in remote or underserved areas where access to dermatologists may be limited. By providing preliminary screening, the system encourages users to seek medical advice when suspicious lesions are detected. The goal of DermaVision is not to replace medical professionals but to assist doctors and improve early screening. The system can reduce the workload on healthcare providers, support faster diagnosis, and raise awareness about skin health. Additionally, the AI model can continuously improve over time as more training data becomes available, making the system increasingly accurate and reliable. In conclusion, DermaVision demonstrates how artificial intelligence can be used in healthcare to enhance diagnostic support and promote early detection of serious diseases. By combining deep learning, medical image analysis, and an accessible user interface, the system aims to contribute to better skin cancer awareness and timely medical intervention."}, {"id": "AI-017", "title": "Driver drowsiness detecting system", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Academic project", "supervisor": "Dr. Amandeep Singh", "sitting_place": "34-204-CH4", "description": "This project is a real-time safety application built using Python and OpenCV. It uses a webcam feed to monitor the driver's facial landmarks and calculate the Eye Aspect Ratio (EAR) to detect signs of fatigue or sleep. The system identifies prolonged eye closure and triggers an audible alarm to alert the driver. It focuses on the practical application of computer vision to improve road safety by preventing accidents caused by drowsiness."}, {"id": "AI-018", "title": "EduCheck -- AI-Based Subjective Answer Evaluation System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Google", "supervisor": "Lakshya Raj Singh Rathore", "sitting_place": "38-602-CH16", "description": "Grading subjective responses such as essays, research papers, and long-answer questions is an integral but challenging aspect of academic assessments. It requires not only careful attention to detail but also the application of subjective judgment, which can introduce inconsistencies, biases, and human error. Teachers are often overwhelmed with large batches of student submissions, making it difficult to provide timely and personalized feedback. Moreover, grading is a labour-intensive process, consuming valuable time that could be spent on more interactive teaching methods. Traditional grading systems often focus on simple keyword matching or surface-level evaluation, which fails to capture the depth, critical thinking, and conceptual understanding 3 \\| P a g e demonstrated by students. These limitations are particularly evident in essay-based assessments where the complexity of student responses can vary widely. The lack of consistency and objectivity in these manual grading methods is a major concern for educators and institutions alike. EduCheck aims to revolutionize this process by utilizing Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Natural Language Processing (NLP) to automate the evaluation of subjective answers. The system integrates machine learning algorithms to compare student answers against both teacher-provided model answers and AI-generated reference answers. This allows the system to focus on the meaning and conceptual relevance of the student's response, rather than just the presence of specific keywords. Through this process, EduCheck enhances grading fairness and consistency while drastically improving grading speed. The use of AI-powered semantic analysis ensures that EduCheck evaluates responses based on their contextual understanding and relevance. By doing so, EduCheck provides a more comprehensive and accurate evaluation of student answers, capturing the nuances of language and the depth of student understanding. The system's ability to compare answers at a deeper, more conceptual level enables it to provide more accurate grades that reflect the true quality of a student's work. The integration of real-time feedback allows students to receive instant insights into their performance. This rapid response helps students understand the strengths and weaknesses in their answers, fostering a continuous learning process. With EduCheck, students can make adjustments to their study strategies while learning from their mistakes without the long waiting periods typically associated with manual grading. This immediate feedback, paired with AI- driven accuracy, creates a more dynamic and efficient learning environment that benefits both students and educators."}, {"id": "AI-019", "title": "Enabled Predictive Asset Monitoring System for Fitness Facility Operations", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Dr. Navpreet Kaur", "sitting_place": "38-602-CH4", "description": "AnEnabled Predictive Asset Monitoring System for Fitness Facility Operations is a data-driven framework that uses IoT sensors, Artificial Intelligence (AI), and Machine Learning (ML) to monitor gym equipment in real-time. Unlike traditional schedules, it identifies subtle signs of wear---such as unusual vibrations or temperature spikes---to forecast exactly when a machine will fail."}, {"id": "AI-020", "title": "E-scholarship Automation System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Project Basket", "supervisor": "Yamini Bhardwaj", "sitting_place": "38-601-CH16", "description": "The E-Scholarship Automation System is a web-based platform designed to simplify and automate the scholarship application and verification process. The system allows students to apply online and upload required documents, while administrators can review and manage applications efficiently. AI-based document verification helps detect fraudulent submissions, improving transparency, reducing manual work, and ensuring fair distribution of scholarships."}, {"id": "AI-021", "title": "Food Hygiene Rating System (IRCTC)", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Aabid Mushtaq Najar", "sitting_place": "38-607-WS3", "description": "Indian Railways is one of the largest public transportation systems in the world. Every day, millions of passenger's travels across different regions of the country, relying not only on transportation but also on catering services provided onboard and at railway stations. The responsibility of maintaining hygiene standards in such a vast ecosystem is immense. Food hygiene is not merely a service quality issue; it is directly linked to public health. Poor hygiene practices can lead to foodborne illnesses, customer dissatisfaction, and reputational damage to the railway system. Therefore, maintaining strict hygiene standards is a priority for IRCTC. Currently, hygiene monitoring follows a traditional model that includes scheduled inspections and complaint-based follow-ups. Although inspections are necessary, they are limited by time, manpower, and geographic coverage. It is practically impossible to monitor every vendor daily through physical inspections. As a result, some hygiene violations may remain undetected. Additionally, complaint-based systems are reactive in nature. Action is usually taken only after an issue has been reported. There is no predictive or preventive monitoring mechanism that identifies declining vendor performance before it becomes critical. With the widespread use of smartphones and digital applications, passengers can now actively participate in service evaluation. A structured digital platform can empower passengers to provide standardized feedback immediately after consuming food. Such a system would create continuous monitoring rather than occasional inspection-based monitoring. The IRCTC Food Hygienic Rating System aims to address these limitations by introducing a digital, structured, and automated hygiene monitoring framework. It integrates passenger participation, inspection oversight, and administrative control into a single ecosystem."}, {"id": "AI-022", "title": "Healthcare Prediction System for Chronic Kidney Disease Using Machine Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "self", "supervisor": "Rohini", "sitting_place": "38-508-CH4", "description": "This project focuses on predicting Chronic Kidney Disease (CKD) using machine learning techniques. It analyzes patient medical data such as blood pressure, glucose level, creatinine, and other clinical parameters to identify patterns associated with CKD. Various algorithms like Logistic Regression, Decision Tree, Random Forest, and Gradient Boosting are applied to classify patients as CKD or non-CKD, helping support early detection and improved healthcare decision-making."}, {"id": "AI-023", "title": "Intelligent Website Development System Using Artificial Intelligence", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Self defined", "supervisor": "Dr. Prince Arora", "sitting_place": "38-516-C3", "description": "This Software Requirements Specification (SRS) document describes the project called \"AI Site Builder.\" AI Site Builder is an automatic web site creation tool that allows users to create any type of web site by simply entering a command into the AI's natural language processing engine. The SRS also includes both functional and non-functional specifications of how the AI Site Builder will function, design limitations, and overall system architecture. The SRS can also act as a legally binding contract between all parties involved in creating the product."}, {"id": "AI-024", "title": "Language Agnostic Chatbot", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "https://www.sih.gov.in/sih2025PS", "supervisor": "Dr. Balraj Kumar", "sitting_place": "38-601-C1", "description": "In modern educational institutions, campus offices are burdened with a large number of repetitive student queries related to fee deadlines, examination schedules, scholarships, timetable changes, and administrative procedures. These queries are usually handled manually through physical visits, phone calls, or emails, leading to long queues, increased workload for staff, and delayed responses. This situation creates communication gaps and reduces overall efficiency. A major challenge arises from language diversity. Many students are more comfortable communicating in Hindi or other regional languages, while most institutional information is published only in English through notices, circulars, or PDF documents. As a result, students struggle to understand important information and repeatedly approach administrative offices for clarification. Although the required information already exists, it is scattered across multiple documents and platforms, making it difficult for students to access quickly. The lack of a conversational and multilingual support system limits accessibility, especially for students from diverse linguistic backgrounds. This gap highlights the need for a digital solution that can provide instant, accurate, and language-independent assistance. To address these issues, a Language Agnostic Chatbot is required that can understand student queries in multiple languages, respond conversationally, and reduce dependency on manual administrative support while improving overall communication and accessibility."}, {"id": "AI-025", "title": "Lightweight Deep Learning Models for Disease Detection on Edge Devices", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Google", "supervisor": "Lakshya Raj Singh Rathore", "sitting_place": "38-602-CH16", "description": "Artificial Intelligence (AI) has transformed healthcare by enabling automated disease detection using deep learning techniques. However, conventional deep learning models are computationally intensive and require high-performance GPUs and cloud servers. This leads to increased latency, privacy concerns, and limited accessibility in remote or rural areas. This project proposes lightweight deep learning models that can operate efficiently on edge devices such as smartphones, IoT medical systems, and Raspberry Pi."}, {"id": "AI-026", "title": "Logistics Optimization using Hybrid GA ACO Framework", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SCA2502-015", "supervisor": "Priyank Arora", "sitting_place": "38-508-CH9", "description": "The project titled \"Logistics Optimization using Hybrid GA-ACO Framework\" aims to develop an intelligent routing optimization system to enhance the efficiency of logistics and transportation operations in dynamic urban environments. Modern logistics networks face challenges such as traffic congestion, unpredictable demand patterns, strict delivery deadlines, and increasing operational costs. These complexities reduce the effectiveness of traditional routing methods, creating the need for advanced optimization approaches. To address these issues, the project proposes a hybrid optimization framework that integrates Genetic Algorithms (GA) and Ant Colony Optimization (ACO). Genetic Algorithms perform global search by exploring multiple route combinations using evolutionary operators like crossover and mutation, while Ant Colony Optimization improves local route refinement through pheromone-based path selection. The combination of these techniques enables faster convergence toward optimal routing solutions and improves adaptability in real-time logistics scenarios. The logistics network is modeled as a Vehicle Routing Problem (VRP) with constraints such as vehicle capacity, delivery time windows, and cost minimization. The proposed system is expected to reduce total travel distance, improve fuel efficiency, and enhance delivery reliability. Additionally, the framework will be validated through simulation and real-world testing, with potential applications in fleet management, emergency routing, and ride-sharing platforms."}, {"id": "AI-027", "title": "MindFlo: Web-Based Mental Health Systems with Anonymous Support", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH : Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Anirban Das", "sitting_place": "38-602-CH17", "description": "Mental health challenges such as stress, anxiety, and depression are rapidly increasing, especially among students and young professionals. Despite the growing need for support, many individuals hesitate to seek help due to stigma, fear of judgment, and lack of accessible resources. Addressing this gap requires a safe, confidential, and easily accessible digital solution. MindFlo is a web-based mental health platform designed to provide anonymous peer support and early intervention tools. It enables users to express their thoughts freely without revealing their identity, fostering a stigma-free environment. The platform integrates features such as mood tracking, AI-based sentiment analysis, and guided self-help resources to detect early signs of mental distress. In critical cases, users can be directed toward professional help or helplines. By combining anonymity, accessibility, and intelligent insights, MindFlo aims to create a scalable mental health ecosystem that encourages open communication and timely support, ultimately contributing to improved emotional well-being and suicide prevention."}, {"id": "AI-028", "title": "Multimodal Deepfake Detection System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SMART INDIA HACKATHON 2026 (Problem Statement 30)", "supervisor": "Gaganpreet Kaur( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This novel multi-faceted system utilizes three foundational artificial intelligence (AI) models integrated synergetically; these three AI models comprise CLIP (Contrastive Language Image Pre-training), which is used to achieve visual-semantic understanding of images and videos; Whisper, which is designed to analyze audio and specifically acoustic-phonetic features within spoken word samples; and Large Language Models that can be used to synthesize and understand contextual-semantic representation of linguistic statements. The result is a comprehensive framework for detecting sophisticated multimodal deepfakes that would otherwise go undetected using traditional unimodal detection systems."}, {"id": "CLD-001", "title": "PowerSync -- Multi Tenant integrated energy-billing, payments and control", "category": "Cloud Computing", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "N/A", "supervisor": "Sarbjeet Singh", "sitting_place": "38-602-CH14", "description": "The primary objective of PowerSync is to design and implement a comprehensive multi-tenant electricity management system that seamlessly integrates IoT-based sub metering with automated billing, payment tracking, and remote power control capabilities. The system aims to replace traditional manual electricity distribution and billing practices with a smart, transparent, and efficient digital infrastructure. By leveraging real-time data acquisition, cloud-based processing, and user-friendly administrative tools, PowerSync intends to minimize billing disputes, improve operational efficiency, and ensure fair electricity usage accountability for every tenant within a shared residential or commercial environment."}, {"id": "CLD-002", "title": "SentinelSaas Multi-Tenant API Based Cybersecurity Monitoring Saas Platform", "category": "Cloud Computing", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "N/A", "supervisor": "Sarbjeet Singh", "sitting_place": "38-602-CH14", "description": "With the rapid growth of internet technologies, web applications have become an important part of modern business and daily life. Organisations use websites and online platforms to provide services, manage customer information and store important data. As the use of online systems increases, the risk of cyber-attacks also increases. Attackers continuously try to find weaknesses in web applications in order to steal information, damage systems or gain unauthorized access. Many companies do not have proper security systems to monitor their applications regularly. Traditional cybersecurity tools are often expensive and require complex setup. Small organisations and developers usually find it difficult to manage security due to limited resources and lack of technical expertise. Because of this, websites remain vulnerable to attacks such as SQL Injection, Cross Site Scripting (XSS), brute force attacks and phishing attempts."}, {"id": "AI-029", "title": "Smart and Intelligent Crop Recommendation Using Machine Learning Techniques T", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Ravinder Singh", "sitting_place": "28-204-CH8", "description": "This project develops an AI-based crop recommendation system using machine learning to help farmers select the most suitable crops. The recommendation is made by analyzing important soil nutrients such as nitrogen (N), phosphorus (P), and potassium (K). It also considers environmental factors including temperature, humidity, pH value, and rainfall for better decision-making. The system uses the Random Forest algorithm, which provides high accuracy in crop prediction. To make the solution practical and user-friendly, the model is deployed as a web application. This enables farmers to receive real-time crop recommendations quickly and efficiently. Overall, the project supports smart farming by improving crop selection and agricultural productivity."}, {"id": "AI-030", "title": "Smart Krishi: AI-Based Crop Recommendation for Farmers", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "SMART INDIA HACKATHON 2026 (Problem Statement 30)", "supervisor": "Gaganpreet Kaur( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "The AI-Based Crop Recommendation System aims to assist farmers in selecting the most suitable crop based on scientific data analysis. By using Machine Learning algorithms, the system provides intelligent suggestions that can improve agricultural productivity and reduce losses. This project supports digital agriculture and contributes toward sustainable farming practices."}, {"id": "AI-031", "title": "Your AI Buddy", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Yogesh", "sitting_place": "38-516-WS4", "description": "Having a conversational partner available at all times provides a unique avenue for emotional regulation and self-reflection. Users often utilize AI friends as a sounding board to process complex motions, practice social interactions before real-world events, or simply unwind after a stressful day without burdening human friends."}, {"id": "DS-001", "title": "AI-Powered Fake News Detection System", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Data Analytics", "nature": "Application", "source": "Self", "supervisor": "Dr. Sartaj Singh", "sitting_place": "38-603-C1", "description": "The AI-Powered Fake News Detection System is a web-based application designed to identify and classify news articles as fake or genuine using Natural Language Processing and Machine Learning techniques. The system analyzes textual patterns, linguistic features, and source credibility to determine the authenticity of news content. Machine learning models such as TF-IDF and BERT are used to process and evaluate the text, providing accurate predictions along with a confidence score. The application also integrates a user-friendly web interface where users can input news content and receive instant verification results. This system aims to help reduce the spread of misinformation and promote reliable information sharing in the digital environment."}, {"id": "DS-002", "title": "AI-Powered Hospital Queue Optimization System", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Data Analytics", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Jasleen Kaur Paintal", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "• An AI-powered smart healthcare management platform designed to optimize patient flow, reduce waiting times, and improve hospital efficiency. The system uses machine learning, predictive analytics, and real-time data processing to intelligently manage queues, prioritize patients based on urgency, and assist hospitals in allocating medical resources effectively. • It enables hospitals to move from manual, inefficient queue handling to automated, data-driven patient scheduling, ensuring faster treatment, improved patient satisfaction, and better utilization of healthcare infrastructure."}, {"id": "CLD-003", "title": "Konnect: A Distributed Microservices Architecture for Real-Time Chat with Multi-Task NLP and Context-Aware Toxicity Dampening", "category": "Cloud Computing", "area": "Data Science and Data Analytics", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH 2024", "supervisor": "Manik Mehra", "sitting_place": "38-603-CH6", "description": "Group messaging has become the default medium for collaboration, socializing, and education. Office teams run daily standups in Slack channels. University cohorts coordinate assignments in WhatsApp groups. Gaming communities organize hundreds of players in Discord servers. What all of these environment's share is that they generate message volumes far beyond what any team of human moderators could review in real time, and they attract exactly the kind of toxic behavior harassment, threats, coordinated bullying --- that destroys communities when left unaddressed. The moderation tooling that exists today tends to solve only part of this problem. Simple blocklists cover only the words their authors anticipated and are defeated by anyone willing to substitute characters or use synonyms. Cloud APIs like Perspective are accurate but introduce external dependencies, round-trip latency, and data governance concerns. Embedded transformer classifiers are the strongest technical option but come with two practical difficulties that have limited their real-world adoption: they are computationally expensive to run per-message, and they produce false positives at rates that erode user trust when deployed without careful post-processing."}, {"id": "DS-003", "title": "Medication Finder", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Data Analytics", "nature": "Application", "source": "Student Idea", "supervisor": "Manik Mehra", "sitting_place": "38-603-CH6", "description": "The Medication Finder is a specialized cross-platform desktop application engineered to provide immediate, offline access to medical information. In an era where digital health literacy is paramount, this project addresses the need for a private, localized repository of medication data and self-care advice. Built using the Electron framework, the application bridges the gap between web-based medical searches and offline utility."}, {"id": "DS-004", "title": "MetaScan (Malware Metadata Scanner)", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Data Analytics", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Anuj Sharma", "sitting_place": "34-204-CH3", "description": "MetaScan is a lightweight static malware analysis system designed for Security Operations Centers (SOCs). Traditional detection systems often rely on file entropy to detect packed or encrypted malware, but many legitimate programs also have high entropy, which leads to false alerts. MetaScan improves this process by combining entropy analysis with structural file features, cryptographic hash reputation, and machine learning models trained on the EMBER dataset. The system analyses executable files and classifies them as benign, suspicious, or malicious while reducing unnecessary alerts for security analysts."}, {"id": "DS-005", "title": "Smart Pantry: AI Food Expiry & Recipe System", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Data Analytics", "nature": "Application", "source": "Self", "supervisor": "Jasleen Kaur Paintal", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "The proposed project, WasteLess AI: Smart Food Expiry Tracker with Recipe Recommendation System, aims to address this issue by providing a web-based platform that helps users track food items stored in their kitchen or refrigerator. The system will notify users about food items that are close to expiration and suggest recipes that utilize those ingredients. By integrating food inventory management, expiry tracking, and AI-based recipe recommendations, the system encourages smarter food consumption habits and helps reduce household food waste. This solution also contributes to sustainable living by promoting efficient use of available food resources."}, {"id": "DS-006", "title": "The Voter ID Application", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Data Analytics", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH 2024", "supervisor": "Manik Mehra", "sitting_place": "38-603-CH6", "description": "The Voter ID Verification App with AI is an intelligent, automated system designed to verify the authenticity of Voter ID cards and validate voter identity using artificial intelligence techniques. In an era where election integrity and secure identification are paramount, this application provides a technological solution to detect forged documents, prevent impersonation, and ensure that only legitimate voters participate in the electoral process."}, {"id": "DS-007", "title": "AI-Driven Public Health Chatbot for Disease Awareness", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Big Data", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "B Monica", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH11", "description": "The project focuses on building a multilingual AI chatbot that delivers accurate healthcare information, disease symptom guidance, vaccination reminders, and outbreak alerts. It will be accessible on messenger app to ensure inclusivity for rural and semi-urban communities where internet connectivity and digital literacy are limited. By integrating with government health databases and APIs, the chatbot will provide real-time updates and reliable information, thus promoting preventive healthcare, reducing misinformation, and ensuring wider access to timely medical awareness."}, {"id": "DS-008", "title": "Al-Based Crop Recommendation for Farmers, Yield Prediction and Optimization", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Big Data", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Veerpal Kaur", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH8", "description": "• The Crop Recommendation System is a machine learning-based application that provides recommendations for suitable crops based on various environmental and soil conditions. It aims to assist farmers and agricultural professionals in making informed decisions about crop selection, optimizing yields, and maximizing profitability. • The system takes into account several factors such as soil type, climate, rainfall, temperature, humidity, and pH levels to determine the most suitable crops for a given region. By analyzing historical data and using predictive models, the system provides personalized recommendations tailored to the specific conditions of a farm or agricultural area."}, {"id": "DS-009", "title": "An integrated IoT-Based Agro-Livestock Monitoring and Intelligent Decision Support System", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Big Data", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart healthcare system using AI and ML", "supervisor": "Aarti Shar", "sitting_place": "34-202-CH7", "description": "This research proposes an Integrated IoT-Based Agro-Livestock Monitoring and Decision Support System aimed at transforming traditional farming into a smart, data-driven process. The system combines crop monitoring, livestock health tracking, and environmental sensing into a single unified platform, addressing the limitations of existing systems that operate independently. It utilizes IoT sensors such as soil moisture sensors, temperature and humidity sensors, and wearable livestock collars equipped with motion and body temperature detection to continuously collect real-time data from the farm. An edge computing device, such as ESP32, processes this data locally to perform filtering and detect anomalies like low soil moisture, abnormal livestock behavior, or sudden environmental changes, enabling instant alerts even in areas with poor internet connectivity. The processed data is then transmitted to the cloud, where machine learning algorithms analyze patterns and generate predictive insights such as irrigation recommendations, livestock health alerts, and climate-based decisions. By integrating multiple agricultural domains and combining edge computing with cloud intelligence, the system improves decision-making accuracy, reduces resource wastage, enhances productivity, and supports sustainable farming practices, making it suitable for both small-scale and large-scale agricultural environments."}, {"id": "DS-010", "title": "Evaluating Machine Learning Strategies for Diabetes Prevalence Prediction", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Big Data", "nature": "Research", "source": "self", "supervisor": "Amandeep Kaur", "sitting_place": "26-205-CH9", "description": "Diabetes Mellitus type 2 (T2DM) has become a problem that is occurring because of the rapid socio-economic transformation and way of life and metabolic. pattern changes. A case of national evidence is mentioned. The fact that there is significant regional disparity and incidence of diabetes, and consequently more of the serious and localized screening. methods are required in order to reduce the rising health care. burden. Nonetheless, there are stringent data privacy laws. and access to big clinical registers is, despite this urgency, One impediment to the creation of indigenous predictive models in the population of Saudi. In order to eliminate this gap in the methodology, the present research proposes an effective developed classification pipeline. a comparative study of classical machine learning. deep learning architectures to algorithms. The model employs proven standardized PIMA Indian Diabetes information set. proxy of modelling metabolic parameters similar to the similar ones. found in Saudi communities. The procedure of preprocessing was very strict. used to enhance the validity of the models, i.e. Z score. Synthetic Minority Oversampling Technique and normalization. which can cause a problem of class imbalance which is addressed by (SMOTE). is a major issue of clinical informatics and is prone to. introduce predictive bias. Comparison was made of three models. similarities of the experiment K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN), Random Forest (RF) and Deep Neural Networks (DNN). The It was empirically found that the Random Forest ensemble was. tends to be more superior to the other types of classifier on all the main measures. of analysis, including accuracy, precision, and F1 score. These findings can be aligned with the existing Saudi-specific predictive age of disease onset and literature on general neural detection."}, {"id": "DS-011", "title": "Machine Learning-Based Models for Crime Prediction and Judicial Decision Support in India", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Big Data", "nature": "Research", "source": "Research", "supervisor": "B Monica", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH11", "description": "This research explores the application of machine learning techniques for crime prediction and decision-making support in the Indian judicial system. It aims to analyze historical crime data, identify patterns, and develop predictive models to assist law enforcement agencies in proactive crime prevention. The study also examines the role of AI-driven analytics in judicial processes, such as case prioritization and sentencing recommendations, while addressing challenges like data privacy, bias, and legal implications. By leveraging machine learning, the research seeks to enhance the efficiency and effectiveness of crime management and judicial decision-making in India."}, {"id": "AI-032", "title": "A Deep Learning-Based Ensemble for Autism Spectrum Disorder Diagnosis Using Facial Images.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Rajeshwar Sharma", "sitting_place": "26-205-CH21", "description": "The research aims to contribute to the development of more efficient and adaptive traffic management systems by providing a comprehensive ML-driven approach to traffic analysis. By offering insights into traffic patterns and enabling real-time decision-making, this study seeks to enhance urban mobility, reduce congestion, and improve overall traffic safety. The successful implementation of machine learning in traffic analysis can revolutionize how cities manage traffic, leading to smarter, more sustainable urban transportation systems."}, {"id": "IOT-019", "title": "A hardware that can detect and prevent unauthorized use of electric fences", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "25077", "supervisor": "Jatinder Kaur", "sitting_place": "27-204-CH3", "description": "The proposed system is a smart automation hardware designed to detect and prevent unauthorized use of electric fences. It integrates current and voltage sensors, microcontrollers, and alert mechanisms to monitor real-time electrical flow. Whenever abnormal usage or illegal tapping is detected, the system triggers an alert to the control unit and automatically isolates the affected section --- ensuring safety, energy efficiency, and operational integrity for electricity boards and rural communities."}, {"id": "OPS-001", "title": "Agile and DevOps Synergy: A Paradigm Shift in Project Management using Left-Shift Testing", "category": "DevOps", "area": "DevOps", "nature": "Research", "source": "Self-Proposed / Research-Based. Aligned with growing industry demand for Agile-DevOps integrated project management frameworks as validated by DORA (Google) and industry case studies.", "supervisor": "Dr. Richa Sharma", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This project studies the integration of Agile and DevOps to improve software development and delivery. Agile enables iterative development, flexibility, and continuous user feedback, while DevOps focuses on automation, CI/CD pipelines, and collaboration between development and operations teams. Their integration helps achieve faster releases, reduced defects, improved system reliability, and better customer satisfaction in modern software projects."}, {"id": "AI-033", "title": "AI Against Suicide: Real--Time Risk Detection from Social Media Texts", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "DevOps", "nature": "Research", "source": "NA", "supervisor": "Tejinder Thind", "sitting_place": "34-203-C2", "description": "The research work on \"AI Against Suicide: Real-Time Risk Detection from Social Media Texts\" focuses on developing an intelligent system capable of identifying suicidal ideation from user-generated content on social media platforms. With millions of posts shared daily, individuals often express emotional distress online, making manual monitoring nearly impossible. This research work leverages machine learning, deep learning, and advanced transformer-based models to automatically detect suicidal intent with high accuracy. Multiple algorithms need to be implemented, including Logistic Regression, SVM, CNN, Bi-LSTM, CNN--LSTM hybrid, and fine-tuned transformers such as RoBERTa and ELECTRA. The system also integrates Explainable AI techniques like LIME and SHAP to highlight influential linguistic cues, ensuring transparency and trust in the model's decisions. A Flask-based web interface enables real-time prediction, allowing users to input text and instantly receive risk categorization. Overall, the work intends to provide a robust, interpretable, and scalable AI-driven solution designed to support early suicide intervention and enhance mental health monitoring through real-time analysis of social media communication."}, {"id": "AI-034", "title": "AI Assisted Cancer Detection Using Medical Imaging and Clinical Data", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "DevOps", "nature": "Research", "source": "Grand Challenges", "supervisor": "Dr. Suchi Jain", "sitting_place": "36-307-CH17", "description": "The cause of cancer is still one of the major causes of death in the world. Early diagnosis contributes greatly to the treatment and survival rates. The conventional methods of diagnosis are based on the imaging, laboratory, and clinical examination by experts. These are however time consuming, costly and in some cases human error prone methods. The current developments in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) have demonstrated that they can potentially assist early cancer diagnosis using enormous amounts of medical data in the form of imaging scans, clinical data, and biomarker information. The existence of AI-based systems allows detecting hidden patterns and anomalies that could otherwise be difficult to detect by human operators, thus enhancing the accuracy and efficiency of the diagnostic process. The proposed dissertation aims at the formulation and assessment of computational methods of cancer detection through machine learning methods applied on medical data. The research question is how the data-oriented models can help healthcare practitioners achieve a better diagnostic performance, detect cancer at an earlier stage and reduce the strain on medical systems."}, {"id": "IOT-020", "title": "AI-Based Rockfall Prediction and Alert System for Open-Pit Mines", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "SIH25071", "supervisor": "Jatinder Kaur", "sitting_place": "27-204-CH3", "description": "Open-pit mining presents inherent safety challenges due to the instability of rock formations and the risk of slope failures. Rockfalls are one of the most hazardous and costly incidents in mining, leading to injuries, equipment damage, and production downtime. Traditional geotechnical monitoring methods --- such as manual inspections or static instruments --- are reactive, often detecting danger only moments before a collapse. To address this, the AI-Based Rockfall Prediction and Alert System was developed to transform mine safety through intelligent, predictive monitoring. This project integrates Artificial Intelligence (AI), Machine Learning (ML), and Internet of Things (IoT) to build a system capable of anticipating rockfall events in real time. Using a network of advanced sensors --- including vibration detectors, LIDAR scanners, and weather stations --- combined with drone-based imaging and visual monitoring, the system continuously collects geological and environmental data. This multi-source data is then processed through noise filtering, normalization, and feature extraction, ensuring that only relevant parameters like slope angle, crack width, and vibration intensity are fed into the AI model. At the core of the system is a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN), which is trained on extensive historical datasets containing both rockfall and stable conditions. The CNN model learns to identify subtle patterns --- such as micro-seismic activity, progressive crack propagation, or temperature-induced stress --- that typically precede rockfalls. Once trained, the AI continuously analyzes live data to compute a Rockfall Risk Score. When this score surpasses a critical threshold, the system automatically triggers alerts via a multi-channel notification system (dashboard warnings, SMS, and emails), enabling timely intervention and evacuation. The overall workflow involves five major stages: 1. Data Collection through IoT devices and drone imagery. 2. Preprocessing to clean and synchronize the data. 3. AI Model Inference to evaluate real-time risk. 4. Alert Generation based on dynamic thresholds. 5. Feedback Integration to refine the AI model continuously using new data. This continuous loop ensures that the system not only detects early signs of instability but also learns and improves over time. The architecture runs on scalable cloud platforms such as AWS or Google Cloud, enabling high-speed computation and real-time analysis. The web interface --- developed using Flask or Django --- allows mine supervisors to visualize live sensor data, monitor slopes, and respond proactively to warnings. By combining real-time monitoring with intelligent analytics, this project introduces a shift from reactive to proactive mine safety management. It creates a safer, more efficient operational environment while demonstrating the transformative potential of AI in industrial risk prevention."}, {"id": "AI-035", "title": "AI-Based Smart Allocation Engine for PM Internship Scheme", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Tanya Gera", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH18", "description": "The PM Internship Scheme is a crucial initiative designed to bridge the gap between academic learning and industry experience for thousands of students. Currently, the immense volume of applicants makes the process of matching candidates to the most suitable opportunities a significant bottleneck. The manual or semi-automated approach often results in suboptimal selections, where highly qualified candidates miss relevant roles, and industries aren't matched with the best talent. This friction leads to delays, reduced scheme effectiveness, and missed potential for both the students and the participating industries. Description This project addresses the allocation challenge by developing a smart, automated system powered by Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning (AI/ML). The engine's core function will be to intelligently match candidates with internship opportunities. The allocation logic will go beyond simple keyword matching, considering a multi-dimensional set of criteria, including: • Core Matching: Skills, qualifications, location preferences, and sector interests. • Inclusivity & Equity: Mandatory accounting for affirmative action (e.g., representation from rural/aspirational districts, different social categories) and balancing past participation history. • Industry Capacity: Ensuring optimal utilization and respecting the stated internship capacity of participating organizations. Objectives of the Project 1. To design and develop an AI/ML-based matchmaking algorithm that achieves the highest possible relevance score between candidate profiles and internship opportunities. 2. To create a functional prototype of the front-end interface that demonstrates the seamless, automated allocation process. 3. To validate the system's ability to handle high-volume data while maintaining fairness and equity in allocation as per scheme guidelines."}, {"id": "AI-036", "title": "AI-Based Threat Detection Application using Machine Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25173", "supervisor": "Lalit Verma", "sitting_place": "27-207-CH15", "description": "With the rapid increase in cyber threats such as malware, phishing, and network-based attacks, organizations struggle to detect and mitigate these threats efficiently. Existing security systems often fail to identify zero-day attacks or evolving threat patterns in real time."}, {"id": "AI-037", "title": "AI-Powered Digital Platform for Centralized Alumni Data Management and Engagement", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr.Varsha", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "Educational institutions face significant challenges in managing alumni relationships due to the absence of centralized data management systems integrated with intelligent automation. Alumni information, including contact details, academic records, career updates, and skills profiles, remains fragmented across multiple platforms or is lost post-graduation. Current alumni engagement relies on manual, informal communication channels such as WhatsApp groups and outdated mailing lists, severely limiting institutional outreach capabilities and preventing intelligent matching of alumni with opportunities. This fragmentation prevents institutions from leveraging AI-driven analytics and machine learning algorithms to identify mentors, facilitate meaningful connections, match internship opportunities, and optimize fundraising initiatives--- representing a missed opportunity for mutual growth and data-driven institutional development."}, {"id": "AI-038", "title": "AI-Powered Digital Platform for Centralized Alumni Data Management and Engagement", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Business Model", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Tanya Gera", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH18", "description": "Problem Statement / Motivation Most educational institutions lack a reliable and centralized system to manage alumni data and foster continuous engagement. Once students graduate, their contact details, career updates, and achievements are often lost or scattered across multiple informal platforms such as WhatsApp groups, outdated mailing lists, or disconnected alumni associations. This results in: • Weak alumni-institution relationships. • Lost opportunities for mentorship, internships, and referrals. • Difficulty in tracking alumni achievements and leveraging them for institutional growth. • Limited fundraising potential due to lack of proper alumni engagement."}, {"id": "DS-012", "title": "AI-Powered Sentiment-Based Trading Signal and Strategy Platform", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Business Model", "source": "Students interest area", "supervisor": "Manjit Kaur", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH5", "description": "This project aims to develop an AI-powered trading and analytics platform that leverages machine learning, social sentiment analysis, and real-time financial data to generate intelligent trading insights. The system collects data from sources like Twitter, Reddit, and financial news APIs to detect sentiment shifts, whale movements, and major macroeconomic trends. Using pretrained NLP models (FinBERT, RoBERTa, etc.) from Hugging Face, the system will classify market sentiment as bullish, bearish, or neutral and correlate it with historical market data. The platform also enables users to create, backtest, and optimize their own trading strategies using a simple chat-based or GUI interface. The backend will process data in real time using Node.js and Redis for caching, while the frontend, built in Next.js, will offer an interactive and responsive dashboard. Additional features include AI-generated trading news summaries \"Trading Journalist\", big-player movement alerts, and global economic news tracking (CPI, interest rates, etc.)."}, {"id": "DS-013", "title": "Automated Student Attendance Monitoring and Analytics System for Colleges", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Amanpreet", "sitting_place": "36-307-CH11", "description": "Attendance tracking in most colleges is still done manually, usually through roll calls or paper registers. This consumes valuable teaching time and often leads to errors such as incorrect entries or proxy attendance. In larger classes, the issue becomes even harder to manage. Additionally, faculty and administrators lack easy access to attendance insights, making it difficult to identify students at risk or to track patterns in engagement. As education undergoes digital transformation, continuing to rely on outdated systems creates unnecessary inefficiencies and delays. There is a clear need for a solution that not only automates attendance but also provides analytics for better academic planning. Such a system should be user-friendly, reliable, and work seamlessly in both in-person and online settings"}, {"id": "DS-014", "title": "Automated Student Attendance Monitoring and Analytics System for Colleges", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Suchi Jain", "sitting_place": "36-307-CH17", "description": "The problem statement focuses on developing an automated system for tracking student attendance in educational institutions, eliminating the need for manual roll calls or paper registers. The system should not only record attendance but also provide valuable analytics and insights, such as identifying patterns, spotting students who are frequently absent, and highlighting those at academic risk. It is expected to function effectively in both in-person and online classes, ensuring flexibility across learning modes. By reducing time wastage, preventing proxy attendance, and enhancing data transparency, the solution aims to support faculty and administrators in better planning, monitoring, and decision-making."}, {"id": "AI-039", "title": "Ayursutra-Panchakarma Patient Management and Therapy Scheduling Software", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Raj Mohan Singh", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH25", "description": "The Panchakarma Management Software will feature automated therapy scheduling and provide notifications to patients regarding the necessary pre- and post-procedure precautions. The software will include Automated therapy scheduling system to plan and manage therapy sessions automatically, Notification system to alert patients about pre-procedure and post-procedure precautions they need to follow, Real-Time Therapy Tracking, Visualization Tools, and Integrated Feedback Loop. The software will address both core functionality and innovative enhancements to ensure usability, efficiency and patient-centric care."}, {"id": "AI-040", "title": "Design and Development of a Hybrid Model for Detecting Social Engineering Attacks Targeting Autistic Individuals", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Research", "source": "Reference Link 1- https://researchautism.org/researchers/graduate-research/ Reference Link 2 - https://www.sfari.org/research/funded-projects/?term=Design%20and%20Development%20of%20a%20Hybrid%20Model%20for%20Detecting%20Social%20Engineering%20Attacks%20Targeting%20Autistic%20Individuals&radio_status=all&award_year=all", "supervisor": "Dr. Arun Malik", "sitting_place": "27-201 A-WW1", "description": "This research work is related to the design and development of a hybrid machine learning model to detect Social Engineering Attacks (SEAs) that disproportionately impact individuals with Autism Spectrum Disorder (ASD). Social engineering attacks exploit psychological manipulation rather than technical flaws, and most existing detection models are optimized for the general population---overlooking cognitive and behavioral differences present in neuro diverse users. This research challenges that status quo by integrating insights from existing SEA models with the nuanced needs of autistic individuals, who may interpret digital communication cues differently and respond atypically to manipulative tactics such as urgency, authority, or reward promises."}, {"id": "AI-041", "title": "Digital Learning Platform for Rural School Students in Nabha", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25019", "supervisor": "Jatinder Kaur", "sitting_place": "27-204-CH3", "description": "The proposed project aims to develop a mobile and web-based digital learning platform specifically designed for rural school students in Nabha and nearby areas. The platform will help bridge the digital divide by providing access to quality educational content, interactive lessons, and digital literacy tools --- even in areas with limited internet connectivity and outdated infrastructure. The system will include features such as: • Offline functionality for uninterrupted access. • Interactive and gamified lessons in local languages to increase engagement. • Digital literacy modules for both students and teachers. • A teacher dashboard to monitor and track student performance. • Optimization for low-end devices and slow networks. This solution will empower students with essential digital skills, enhance learning outcomes, and support teachers with tools for personalized instruction --- ultimately contributing to Smart Education and digital inclusion in rural Punjab."}, {"id": "AI-042", "title": "Disaster Preparedness and Response Education System for Schools and Colleges", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Raj Mohan Singh", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH25", "description": "In India, schools and colleges are often unprepared for natural disasters such as earthquakes, floods, and fires. While emergency guidelines exist on paper, there is a lack of structured disaster management education integrated into the curriculum. Institutions lack digital tools to simulate disaster scenarios or conduct virtual drills to train students and staff on safety protocols. Furthermore, there's a gap in localized awareness---many students are unaware of how to react during disasters specific to their region. Manual drills, where they occur, are infrequent and often poorly coordinated, failing to instill practical preparedness. The goal of this project is to empower young people with this knowledge not only for making campuses safer but also contributing to a more disaster-resilient society. This project aims at providing a digital platform or app that offers interactive disaster education modules, region-specific alerts, and virtual drills."}, {"id": "AI-043", "title": "EduLend: A Decentralized Campus Borrowing and Lending Application", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "Sustainable Development Goal (SDG) 12: Responsible Consumption and Production", "supervisor": "Sukhwinder Kaur( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "The idea for the Campus Borrow and Lend Application originated from real-world challenges faced by university students in accessing temporary-use resources such as books, lab equipment, gadgets, and other academic materials. The concept draws inspiration from the increasing popularity of peer-to-peer (P2P) sharing economy platforms such as OLX, Facebook Marketplace, and Rent mojo, which allow users to borrow, lend, or exchange goods locally."}, {"id": "AI-044", "title": "Evaluating Zero-Shot Generalization in Multimodal NLP: Performance and Fairness Across Text, Images, and Speech with Insights from the Indian Context", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Research", "source": "NA", "supervisor": "Jatinder Kaur", "sitting_place": "27-204-CH3", "description": "my project is about checking how well some AI models---like CLIP, Flamingo, and Whisper---can do tasks across text, images, and speech without any training, using this zero-shot learning idea. I'll test them on things like writing captions for pictures, transcribing audio, and matching text to images, using free datasets like Wikipedia, MS COCO, and Common Voice. I want to see how good they are and if they're fair, especially for Indian things like Hindi speech or our cultural images, by looking at their performance and any biases. It's a cool way to see how these models can work for us here in India."}, {"id": "AI-045", "title": "Freelancing Platform", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH1629", "supervisor": "Dr. Jaspreet Kaur", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH22", "description": "Our freelancing platform not only connects clients and freelancers but also redefines engagement. It introduces AI-powered personalized job matching, skill verification through micro-assessments, and milestone-based secure payments. To make the platform more inclusive, we add regional language support, gamification features (XP points, badges, leaderboards), and a unique 30-second video intro system where employers and freelancers can upload quick reels for job posts, company intros, or mini-interviews --- making hiring faster, more personal, and more engaging."}, {"id": "AI-046", "title": "Gamified Environmental Education Platform for Schools and Colleges", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Raj Mohan Singh", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH25", "description": "The project \"Gamified Environmental Education Platform for Schools and Colleges\" aims to transform traditional, theory-based environmental education into an interactive and engaging learning experience. Current environmental teaching methods in India often fail to connect students with real-world ecological issues or motivate them to adopt sustainable habits. This project proposes a gamified digital platform that teaches environmental concepts through interactive lessons, quizzes, challenges, and real-world eco-tasks such as tree planting. By combining education with gamification, the platform encourages experiential learning, behavioral change, and community engagement."}, {"id": "AI-047", "title": "Healthcare Management System with Disease Detection", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Product", "source": "Sih2024 problem SIH1537Student InnovationHardwareMedTech / BioTech / HealthTechNULLCutting-edge technology in these sectors continues to be in demand. Recent shifts in healthcare trends, growing populations also present an array of opportunities for innovation. AICTE, MIC-Student Innovation", "supervisor": "Tarun", "sitting_place": "27-205-CH4", "description": "The project \"Healthcare Management System with Disease Detection using Machine Learning\" introduces a digital Health Card for every citizen, storing complete medical records from birth to death. It ensures access only to licensed doctors, enhancing security and transparency. Using ML-based disease detection, it predicts illnesses from patient inputs and supports the government in tracking public health data, especially during pandemics."}, {"id": "IOT-021", "title": "Intelligent Renewable Energy Tracking for Microgrids", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Research", "source": "Renewable energy monitoring system for microgrids", "supervisor": "Dr.Varsha", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "Develop an IoT-based monitoring system for solar or wind microgrids in rural areas, providing real-time data on energy generation, storage, and consumption. The system should alert users to inefficiencies or maintenance needs. Expected Outcome A hardware-software prototype improving microgrid efficiency by 15%, with a mobile app for community operators to manage energy distribution. Technical Feasibility Employs affordable IoT sensors (e.g., Raspberry Pi, Arduino) and cloud-based analytics for real-time monitoring, compatible with existing microgrid setups."}, {"id": "AI-048", "title": "KaryFix", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Business Model", "source": "SIH25046", "supervisor": "Arsalan Manzoor Zargar", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH17", "description": "The Smart On-Demand Service Hub is a comprehensive multi-service web platform designed to connect customers with skilled service providers instantly through a single web application. This platform allows users to book doorstep services ranging from repairs, maintenance, entertainment planning, and laundry to recycling waste for cashback---all through a single, easy-to-use interface."}, {"id": "AI-049", "title": "KrishiBandhu: from generic to personalized , transforming agri-advisory in kerala", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Priyanka Mahajan", "sitting_place": "36-307-CH9", "description": "Kerala's smallholder farmers often lack access to personalized, timely agricultural advice. Generic advisories fail to account for local crop choices, weather, soil conditions, or farming practices. Many farmers also don't maintain records of their activities, which limits learning from past seasons and accessing scheme benefits. Build an AI-powered personal farming assistant that acts like a digital companion for each farmer---understanding their specific context, guiding their actions, and learning over time."}, {"id": "AI-050", "title": "lmage based Animal Type Classification for cattle and buffaloes", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Raj Mohan Singh", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH25", "description": "The Image-based Animal Type Classification System aims to automate the evaluation of cattle and buffaloes' body structures using artificial intelligence and image processing. In dairy farming, accurate assessment of physical traits is crucial for predicting an animal's productivity, longevity, and breeding potential. However, the current manual classification method performed by trained personnel is often subjective and prone to human errors, affecting data consistency and reliability. This project proposes an AI-driven solution that analyzes animal images to measure key physical parameters such as body length, height at withers, chest width, and rump angle. Based on these extracted features, the system will generate objective and standardized classification scores automatically."}, {"id": "AI-051", "title": "LPU Smart Helpdesk Chatbot", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "This project aligns closely with Smart India Hackathon (SIH) problem statements under categories such as \\*\\*Smart Education\\*\\*, \\*\\*Digital Campus Solutions\\*\\*, and \\*\\*AI for Governance\\*\\*. Specifically, it matches with themes that seek intelligent chatbots or digital assistants for educational institutions to automate student queries and administrative support systems. The LPU Smart Helpdesk Chatbot addresses these national objectives by promoting digitalization, accessibility, and automation in campus operations.", "supervisor": "Tejinder Thind", "sitting_place": "34-203-C2", "description": "The \"LPU Smart Helpdesk Chatbot\" is an AI-driven conversational assistant designed to provide instant answers to queries from students, faculty, and visitors at Lovely Professional University. It serves as a virtual helpdesk capable of handling questions about academics, hostel facilities, exam schedules, fee payments, and other campus services. The chatbot leverages Natural Language Processing (NLP) to understand user intent and retrieve accurate, pre-trained responses from a dynamic knowledge base. It can be integrated with the LPU website, UMS portal, or mobile applications, ensuring 24×7 availability. The system also features an admin dashboard for managing FAQs and an analytics module to track commonly asked questions, improving administrative efficiency. This solution aims to reduce dependency on manual helpdesks, minimize response times, and enhance the overall student experience through intelligent, accessible campus support."}, {"id": "AI-052", "title": "Mobile application for online learning in rural school", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Suchi Jain", "sitting_place": "36-307-CH17", "description": "This project aims to develop a mobile application specifically designed to enhance online learning in rural schools, where access to quality education and resources is often limited. The app will serve as a low-bandwidth, multilingual, and offline-capable educational platform, enabling students in remote areas to access lessons, videos, assignments, and assessments through mobile devices. The application will feature: • Interactive lessons aligned with local curriculum • Offline access to downloaded content • Voice-assisted navigation for young learners or those with low literacy • Multilingual support to cater to regional languages • Teacher dashboard for tracking student progress and managing classes • Push notifications for reminders and updates By leveraging mobile technology, the project seeks to bridge the digital divide, empower rural students with accessible education, and support teachers in delivering effective instruction even in areas with limited internet connectivity."}, {"id": "IOT-022", "title": "Novel Water quality monitoring and warning system with IOT", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "DevOps", "nature": "Product", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2024)", "supervisor": "Tarun", "sitting_place": "27-205-CH4", "description": "In Novel Water quality monitoring and warning system with IOT will work on a device which can check waterquality and generate warning through IOT message can be generated informing about healt hazards"}, {"id": "AI-053", "title": "Nutrient Deficiency Indicator", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25030", "supervisor": "Arsalan Manzoor Zargar", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH17", "description": "A software that tells us which nutrient is in deficiency for maximum yield."}, {"id": "IOT-023", "title": "Optimizing Doctor Availability and Appointment Allocation in Hospitals through Digital Technology and Al Integration.", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH1383", "supervisor": "Dr. Jaspreet Kaur", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH22", "description": "To develop a digital system that streamlines the appointment scheduling process in hospitals by automating the process of identifying doctor availability and appointment slot allocation. The system will utilize advanced technologies such as RFID, face detection, proximity of Mobile phone, or any other relevant technology to detect the presence of doctors in the hospital. The system will use Artificial Intelligence (AI) to allocate appointment slots based on the doctor's presence and the number of waitlisted patients. This will improve the overall patient experience by reducing the wait time."}, {"id": "AI-054", "title": "Real-Time Public Transport Tracking for Small Cities", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Priyanka Mahajan", "sitting_place": "36-307-CH9", "description": "In small cities and tier-2 towns, public transport systems often lack real-time tracking, leaving commuters uncertain about bus timings and routes. This causes delays, overcrowding, and declining trust in public transport, pushing people towards private vehicles and worsening traffic and pollution. The proposed solution is a web platform with GPS-based real-time bus tracking, showing estimated arrival times and route details. Optimized for low-bandwidth use, it ensures accessibility in smaller towns. This system benefits commuters, local transport authorities, and municipal corporations, improving reliability, efficiency, and promoting sustainable mobility."}, {"id": "AI-055", "title": "Remote classroom for rural colleges.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Suchi Jain", "sitting_place": "36-307-CH17", "description": "This project aims to design and implement a remote classroom system tailored for rural colleges, improving access to quality education through digital means and reducing barriers caused by geographical distance and limited resources."}, {"id": "IOT-024", "title": "Smart AI Enabled Facemask with Predictive Asthma Monitoring, Cough Analysis and Temperature-Controlled Airflow System", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "DevOps", "nature": "Product", "source": "Sih2024 problem SIH1537Student InnovationHardwareMedTech / BioTech / HealthTechNULLCutting-edge technology in these sectors continues to be in demand. Recent shifts in healthcare trends, growing populations also present an array of opportunities for innovation.AICTEAICTE, MIC-Student Innovation", "supervisor": "Tarun", "sitting_place": "27-205-CH4", "description": "The present invention relates to a novel smart AI-controlled wearable facemask designed for proactive and comprehensive asthma management. Its primary inventive concept is a proactive temperature-controlled airflow system that warms cold inhaled air to prevent environmentally triggered attacks. This preventive system is guided by an integrated multi-sensor suite that measures physiological and environmental parameters, such as breathing patterns, heart rate, air pollution, and ambient temperature. This data is processed in real-time by an onboard microcontroller running a machine learning algorithm to predict the onset of an asthma attack. The system's preventive capabilities are further enhanced by a miniature microphone that analyzes cough sounds to distinguish normal coughing from asthma-related symptoms, and a wear-recommendation indicator that advises the user when mask usage is necessary based on environmental conditions. As a fail-safe, upon prediction of an unavoidable attack, the system autonomously activates an integrated vibrating mesh nebulizer (VMN) system to generate and deliver a fine aerosolized medication mist directly through the breathing channel. This invention thus provides a proactive and preventive solution, offering real-time monitoring, prediction, and environmental control to reduce and manage asthma triggers."}, {"id": "IOT-025", "title": "Smart Community Health Monitoring and Early Warning System for Water-Borne Disease in Rural Northeast India", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25001", "supervisor": "Dr. Jaspreet Kaur", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH22", "description": "Our solution is a Smart Community Health Monitoring & Early Warning System for water-borne diseases, designed as a three-tier platform serving Individuals, Health Workers, and Government authorities. The system enables real-time symptom reporting through mobile apps, USSD, or IVR services, ensuring accessibility even in low-connectivity rural areas. Instead of relying on costly IoT devices, it introduces a camera-based water testing approach, where simple test strips can be scanned with a smartphone to detect contamination levels. These inputs are analyzed by an AI-driven risk prediction engine, which generates dynamic risk scores, forecasts potential outbreaks, and issues timely, explainable alerts to both communities and officials. By integrating community participation, medical validation, and government action into one ecosystem, the platform ensures proactive prevention and rapid response against water-borne diseases."}, {"id": "AI-056", "title": "Smart Crop Advisory System for Small and Marginal Farmers", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Suchi Jain", "sitting_place": "36-307-CH17", "description": "We are creating a Smart Crop Advisory System to support small-scale farmers with personalized guidance. By analyzing local weather forecasts, soil health, and crop data, our system delivers specific advice on the best crops to plant, proper fertilizer use, well-organized watering schedules, and pest control methods. The core mission is to empower farmers who have limited resources to increase their crop yields, reduce potential losses, and farm more sustainably."}, {"id": "IOT-026", "title": "Smart Posture Correction Chair Using IoT Technology", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Product", "source": "Students innovation", "supervisor": "Manjit Kaur", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH5", "description": "The Smart Posture Correction Chair using IoT is an innovative yet simple solution designed to improve sitting posture among students and professionals who spend long hours sitting. The chair uses basic, low-cost sensors such as pressure, tilt, and ultrasonic sensors to detect incorrect posture patterns. When poor posture is detected, the system sends an alert through a buzzer or a connected mobile app via Wi-Fi or Bluetooth, reminding the user to correct their sitting position. The data collected can also be stored for posture tracking and analysis over time. This project aims to promote healthy posture habits and prevent back pain, spinal issues, and fatigue caused by long-term poor sitting posture. The entire system is affordable, feasible to build within a university lab, and provides an excellent blend of electronics, IoT, and health monitoring applications"}, {"id": "IOT-027", "title": "Sojh(DIgital Empowerment for rural education)", "category": "IoT-Embedded Systems", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25019", "supervisor": "Arun Prakash K", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH9", "description": "Many rural schools in Punjab face systemic challenges that limit access to quality, modern education. This gap is primarily driven by three factors: infrastructure, content availability, and digital skills. Schools often lack proper computer labs, reliable hardware, and consistent, high-speed internet connectivity, hindering integration of modern teaching methods. Students and teachers struggle to access engaging, updated educational content, leading to reliance on traditional methods and lower engagement rates. The struggle to access modern content perpetuates low digital literacy among students and teachers, widening the educational gap between rural and urban centers."}, {"id": "AI-057", "title": "SurakshaLink: An AI-Enabled Disaster Preparedness and Communication Platform.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH2025 mapped with PS number SIH25008", "supervisor": "Manjit Kaur", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH5", "description": "SurakshaLink is a comprehensive Progressive Web App (PWA) designed to address the critical gap in disaster preparedness. The platform moves beyond static guidelines by offering an interactive and engaging learning environment. Key features include gamified virtual drills to simulate real-world scenarios, offline-accessible educational guides, and a real-time communication suite. An integrated AI assistant, powered by the Gemini API, provides on-demand, contextual guidance. The overarching goal is to instill a culture of preparedness, enhance knowledge retention, and create a safer, more resilient environment through modern, accessible technology."}, {"id": "AI-058", "title": "TypeSense: A Secure Keystroke-Based Mood Detection Mobile Application", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Application", "source": "mart India Hackathon (SIH) 2024 / 2025 problem statements, under the category of Digital Well-Being, Human-Computer Interaction, and AI for Social Good", "supervisor": "Sukhwinder Kaur( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "MoodSense is a real-time mood detection application that analyzes users' typing behavior to determine their emotional state. The application provides a custom keyboard, which can be set as the default input method without interfering with other apps, ensuring privacy and security. The system captures keystroke dynamics such as: Hold time (duration a key is pressed) Flight time (time between consecutive key presses) Latency (response delay between typing events) Typing accuracy These behavioral patterns are processed using machine learning algorithms to classify the user's mood (e.g., happy, sad, neutral, stressed) and provide real-time feedback. The application is designed to be secure, non-intrusive, and scalable, with data stored and processed using Firebase for authentication, database management, and real-time updates."}, {"id": "AI-059", "title": "UniResolve -- Unified AI Solution for Automated Human Task Evaluation", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Program Methodology and Design", "nature": "Business Model", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Tejinder Thind", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "UniResolve is an AI-driven platform that automates repetitive and error-prone processes such as handwritten evaluation, document verification, and content management. It leverages machine learning, computer vision, and NLP to handle tasks like subjective evaluation, MCQ checking, and multi-answer sheet processing with high accuracy. The system minimizes human errors such as mischecking and wrong question mapping. Beyond evaluation, UniResolve provides additional features like automated question bank creation (with difficulty tagging), study material uploads, syllabus management, and e-book integration, making it a comprehensive solution. By reducing manual effort and ensuring unbiased results, UniResolve delivers speed, scalability, and reliability across multiple domains."}, {"id": "DS-015", "title": "A Deep Learning-Based Framework for Real-Time Fraud Detection in Financial Transactions", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "Google Scholar", "supervisor": "Amit Sharma", "sitting_place": "36-307-CH16", "description": "Financial fraud detection is a growing challenge due to the increasing volume of digital transactions and the evolving nature of fraudulent activities. Traditional methods often struggle with detecting sophisticated fraud patterns in real time, leading to high false positives and inefficiencies. Deep learning offers a promising approach by identifying complex transaction behaviours and anomalies more effectively. This research aims to develop a deep learning-based fraud detection framework capable of handling real-time financial transactions. The study will explore methods to improve fraud detection accuracy, address data imbalance issues, and ensure scalability for real-world applications. Finally, the proposed system will be evaluated and compared with existing fraud detection approaches to measure its effectiveness."}, {"id": "DS-016", "title": "AgriXAI: Plant Disease Insights", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "NA", "supervisor": "Savleen Kaur", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH9", "description": "This research focuses on the development of an intelligent system for detecting plant leaf diseases using Explainable Artificial Intelligence (XAI) techniques. Traditional deep learning models, while highly accurate, often function as \"black boxes,\" offering little insight into their decision-making process. In contrast, this study aims to integrate interpretability into disease detection models, allowing users especially farmers and agronomists to understand the why behind each prediction. By leveraging XAI methods such as Grad-CAM, LIME, or SHAP, the system will not only classify diseased vs. healthy leaves but also highlight the key features influencing the model's decision. This added transparency enhances trust, supports better decision-making in agricultural management, and makes AI tools more accessible and usable in real-world farming scenarios."}, {"id": "DS-017", "title": "AgroVision (All in one farmer portal)", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Application", "source": "Industry Requirement", "supervisor": "Sarvesh Chopra", "sitting_place": "33-203-CH24", "description": "Farmers often face significant challenges in identifying plant diseases early due to lack of expert knowledge and delayed access to agricultural support. Additionally, incorrect crop selection based on unsuitable soil nutrients or weather conditions leads to reduced productivity and financial loss. Traditional methods of obtaining farming advice are slow and unreliable, especially in rural regions. Therefore, there is a need for an intelligent, easy-to-access solution that can assist farmers with timely disease diagnosis, crop recommendations, and weather-based decision-making."}, {"id": "DS-018", "title": "AI Mental Health Chatbot with Emotion and Sentiment Detection", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "Research Papers", "supervisor": "Pardeep Kumar", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH3", "description": "The AI Mental Health Chatbot with Emotion and Sentiment Detection is an intelligent, empathetic digital companion designed to support emotional well-being through real-time understanding of human emotions. Using advanced natural language processing and sentiment analysis, the chatbot can detect users' emotional states from their messages and respond with compassion, encouragement, and evidence-based mental health strategies. It offers a safe and confidential space for users to express their thoughts, track mood changes, and receive personalized coping techniques based on emotional patterns. Built on psychological frameworks such as Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) and mindfulness, the chatbot provides practical guidance for managing stress, anxiety, and depression."}, {"id": "DS-019", "title": "AI-Driven Mental Health Support : Sentiment Detection and Safe Recommendation Framework", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Product", "source": "Smart India Hackthon 2025", "supervisor": "Disha Maity", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH5", "description": "The profound global mental health crisis is characterized by pervasive systemic barriers that preclude timely and effective traditional care. These obstacles---including prohibitive costs, extensive wait times, and acute shortages of mental health professionals (averaging just two per 100,000 people in many low-income settings)---have spurred the rapid proliferation of Artificial Intelligence (AI) chatbots as essential first-line resources. The integration of mobile-first AI systems is designed to furnish accessible, confidential, and scalable 24/7 support, fundamentally challenging the stigma associated with seeking human intervention. Modern AI systems represent a significant evolution from earlier, rule-based platforms (e.g., Woebot, Wysa) to sophisticated generative models leveraging Large Language Models (LLMs) and advanced Natural Language Processing (NLP) for real-time sentiment analysis and dialogue creation.1 The explicit objective of these hybrid architectures is to deliver emotion-aware, culturally sensitive support that mitigates initial distress and acts as a vital gateway for referral to formal clinical care. However, the rapid advancement in conversational fluency introduces a critical paradox that structures this analysis. While user engagement metrics and the capacity for sentiment detection are high, empirical data confirms a fundamental safety deficit: the systems demonstrate a catastrophic inability to manage high-risk clinical situations. This report analyzes this complex landscape, reviewing the core objectives, methods, and performance metrics of current systems, identifying critical research gaps, and proposing a technical roadmap toward safer, ethically-aligned, and more effective AI-driven mental health solutions"}, {"id": "DS-020", "title": "AI-Driven Public Health Chatbot", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Vikas Mangotra", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH9", "description": "This research focuses on developing an AI-driven public health chatbot that assists users by providing information about common diseases, their symptoms, and preventive measures. The chatbot uses a pre-collected dataset stored in a structured format and interacts with users through a Python console. It aims to promote health awareness and quick access to reliable disease information using a simple, text-based AI approach."}, {"id": "DS-021", "title": "AI-DRIVEN PUBLIC HEALTH CHATBOT FOR DISEASE AWARENESS", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Review", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Dr. Geetika Chatley", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH7", "description": "This project focuses on developing an AI-powered public health chatbot that helps people get accurate and reliable health information in real time. By studying common health challenges and symptoms, the chatbot provides evidence-based guidance to users. Using Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning, it is designed to give simple explanations, preventive care tips, and support in understanding symptoms. The chatbot also guides users in deciding whether they should consult a doctor, making healthcare more accessible and reducing confusion caused by unreliable sources. With its diverse functionality this project aims to reach a wide range of people and promote better health awareness in the community."}, {"id": "DS-022", "title": "AI-Powered Chest X-Ray Disease Detection Using Transfer Learning and Explainable Visualization", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Product", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Nidhi Arora", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH4", "description": "Early and accurate detection of chest diseases such as pneumonia and tuberculosis is crucial for effective medical treatment and public health management. However, manual examination of chest X-rays is often time-consuming and may lead to diagnostic inconsistencies. This project presents an automated system that leverages artificial intelligence to assist in medical diagnosis. The proposed model employs transfer learning with pre-trained convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to identify abnormalities in chest X-rays efficiently and accurately. Furthermore, the integration of Grad-CAM (Gradient-weighted Class Activation Mapping) provides explainable visualization, enabling healthcare professionals to interpret the model's decision-making process by highlighting the most relevant regions of the X-ray image. The system aims to enhance diagnostic reliability, support medical practitioners in early detection, and make AI-driven healthcare more transparent and accessible.This project aims to develop an AI-based system for detecting chest diseases such as pneumonia and tuberculosis from X-ray images using transfer learning with pre-trained CNN models like ResNet50 or VGG16. The system will be trained on a labeled chest X-ray dataset, preprocessed through resizing, normalization, and data augmentation.Finally, a simple web interface (using Streamlit or Flask) will be built to allow users to upload X-ray images and view both the prediction and the Grad-CAM visualization, making the system accurate, interpretable, and useful for healthcare professionals"}, {"id": "DS-023", "title": "AI-Powered Multilingual and Context-Aware Advisory System for Safe and Personalized Agricultural Decision Support", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Product", "source": "Smart India Hackthon 2025", "supervisor": "Manish Kumar Sharma", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH7", "description": "Agriculture remains the backbone of the Indian economy, with almost half of its population dependent upon it for their livelihood. However, even today, millions of farmers take critical decisions pertaining to irrigation, pest control, and crop management based on incomplete or non-reliable information. Advisory services provided by government institutions or local agents are often plagued with delays, language barriers, and a lack of personalization. The gaps between expert knowledge and the needs of farmers lead to inconsistent yields, overuse of pesticides, and resource inefficiency in many rural regions. Driven by rapid growth in digital communication and artificial intelligence, the urgent need has been felt for intelligent systems that can bridge this information gap by providing real-time, understandable, and contextually relevant agricultural advice. Recent progress in NLP and machine learning has enabled the construction of chatbots and digital advisory systems, but most of the currently available solutions work for a single language or are based on static knowledge bases that cannot adapt to local conditions. Additionally, many AI models are still \"black boxes\" that give recommendations without explainability and safety validation, which is an unacceptable risk in agriculture, given the potentially severe economic or environmental consequences of wrong advice. Multilinguality, proper integration of context, and safety mechanisms remain some of the critical challenges in deploying AI systems in rural India. This project addresses these limitations by proposing an AI-powered multilingual and context-aware advisory system that delivers personalized, safe, and explainable agricultural guidance. The system will make use of multilingual transformer models for understanding farmer queries in English, Hindi, and Punjabi to allow for inclusive communication. It integrates real-time contextual data such as weather, market prices, and soil conditions through external APIs for dynamic and localized recommendations. The system leverages a RAG framework to base responses on grounded verified agricultural knowledge bases to minimize hallucinations and make the system factually reliable. A safety validation module checks chemical dosage and banned pesticides, while explainable AI components provide the reasoning behind every advisory. Multilingual NLP, context fusion, and trustworthy AI together can provide a basis for delivering a scalable advisory digital platform even in low-connectivity environments. The proposed system hopes to go beyond improvement in decision-making and seeks to instill trust among farmers in technology, promote sustainability, and showcase how AI can be a trusted partner in the digital transformation journey of agriculture."}, {"id": "DS-024", "title": "Al-Based Crop Recommendation for Farmers", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH India Hackathon(SIH)", "supervisor": "Amandeep Kaur", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH10", "description": "Agriculture is the backbone of many economies, particularly in countries like India where a significant proportion of the population relies on farming for livelihood. Despite its importance, the sector continues to face persistent challenges such as suboptimal crop selection, inefficient fertilizer usage, disease outbreaks, fluctuating weather patterns, and market price uncertainties. These challenges often result in reduced productivity, economic instability, and increased risks for farmers who largely depend on traditional methods of decision-making. With the rapid growth of Artificial Intelligence (AI), Machine Learning (ML) and Deep Learning (DL), new opportunities have emerged to address these agricultural challenges through data-driven solutions. AI techniques can analyze diverse parameters---such as soil nutrients (N, P, K), pH, temperature, rainfall, and humidity---to generate actionable insights. By leveraging these technologies, farmers can make informed decisions that optimize yield, reduce input costs, and ensure sustainable farming practices."}, {"id": "DS-025", "title": "An Automated Multi-Source Verification System for Student Credential Authentication in Campus Recruitment", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Pritam Sunil Mahajan( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "Organizations hiring students waste significant time and money verifying credentials manually (3-4 hours and \\$50-100 per candidate), while resume fraud remains widespread with 40-60% of resumes containing false information. Students fabricate internships, claim plagiarized projects as original work, and inflate skills, leading to bad hires that cost organizations thousands. Current background verification services are too slow, expensive, and don't verify student-specific claims like GitHub projects, technical skills, or coding contributions.ARBC (Automated Resume Builder & Credential Checker) is a software platform that organizations can use to automatically verify if students are telling the truth on their resumes."}, {"id": "DS-026", "title": "Climate detector for farmers", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science & Big Data", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Sadaf Qureshi", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH13", "description": "The Climate Detector for Farmers is a novel system for farmers that provides them with the necessary information about the changing weather and soil conditions and thus puts them in a better position to handle the changes. The data that the system uses includes temperature, humidity, rainfall, wind speed, and soil moisture among others which are processed to provide farmers with the right information. This in turn helps them in making right crop choices, irrigation scheduling, and securing their farms against adverse weather conditions. The significant aim of this project is to accumulate real-time climate and soil data, analyze it, and offer farmers straightforward advice. The system derives its data from weather websites such as IMD or OpenWeatherMap, as well as sensors which are deployed in the soil. These sensors report on soil moisture, temperature and pH levels. All this data is aggregated and stored in Google Sheets where farmers can visualize it easily in the form of tables and charts."}, {"id": "DS-027", "title": "Data Engineering Pipeline for Medical Imaging", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science & Big Data", "nature": "Research", "source": "Medical Image Understanding and Analysis 2025", "supervisor": "Amandeep Kaur", "sitting_place": "34-207-C2", "description": "DermaMNIST represents a subset of MedMNIST, consisting of dermoscopic images of skin lesions labelled into multiple classes. While a majority of research leans towards training deep learning models for classification, much less effort is directed at building robust, automated data engineering pipelines for such datasets. A data engineering pipeline for DermaMNIST would comprise an automated pipeline that collects, validates, transforms, stores, and delivers the dataset for downstream ML tasks. This creates an environment where reproducible, scalable, and integrable with real-time diagnostic systems are assured."}, {"id": "DS-028", "title": "Deep Learning-Based Prediction of Cardiovascular Risk Factors from Retinal Fundus Images", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH Problem Statements, SIMENS Industrial R&D Problem Statements", "supervisor": "Manpreet Singh", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "Cardiovascular diseases (CVDs) remain a leading cause of global mortality, often requiring invasive or costly diagnostic procedures. The CardioVision project aims to develop a deep learning driven diagnostic framework that predicts key cardiovascular risk factors, such as hypertension, diabetes, and cholesterol level abnormalities, from retinal fundus photographs. Since the retina provides a non-invasive window to vascular health, analyzing its microvascular patterns offers a powerful tool for early risk prediction and preventive healthcare. The proposed system leverages machine learning and neural network models implemented in Python using TensorFlow and OpenCV for image preprocessing, feature extraction, and classification. Traditional techniques such as Decision Trees and Naïve Bayes are used for baseline modeling, while a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) is employed for end-to-end learning and improved accuracy. The dataset of retinal fundus images is preprocessed for normalization, contrast enhancement, and segmentation to identify vascular structures and pathological markers. The model predicts multiple cardiovascular risk factors simultaneously and stores prediction results in a secure database accessible through a lightweight web interface (HTML/Python Flask). This approach reduces dependence on expensive diagnostic methods by providing non-invasive, affordable, and early-stage cardiovascular screening. The system has potential applications in telemedicine, rural healthcare, and public health analytics, enabling proactive interventions and improved patient outcomes."}, {"id": "DS-029", "title": "Design and Development of a Deep Learning-Based Framework for Detecting Manipulated and Deepfake Videos.", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Big Data", "nature": "Research", "source": "Research Literature Review (IEEE / Springer Papers)", "supervisor": "Dr. Geetika Chatley", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH7", "description": "Deepfake videos have emerged as a major challenge to digital media authenticity and information security due to their increasing realism and widespread use in misinformation and manipulation. Detecting such manipulated content has become an important research problem in artificial intelligence and multimedia forensics. This project focuses on the design and development of a deep learning-based system for detecting deepfake videos by analysing visual and temporal inconsistencies in video data. The proposed work will explore advanced deep learning techniques to identify manipulated content and improve the reliability of digital media verification systems."}, {"id": "DS-030", "title": "Design Intelligent Privacy-Preserving Healthcare Framework Using Ethical Machine Learning, Federated Learning, and Power BI", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Big Data", "nature": "Research", "source": "Latest Trends", "supervisor": "Shairy", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH38", "description": "The study is a proposal of an intelligent healthcare system based on the idea of ethical machine learning and federated learning to provide accurate, safe, and privacy-preserving medical data analysis. The system allows several healthcare facilities to jointly train machine learning models that do not involve accessing sensitive patient information, which ensures data confidentiality. Such ethical principles as fairness, transparency, and accountability are included to minimize the extent of bias and increase the degree of trust in predictions. Also, interactive dashboards are created with the assistance of Power BI that help make clinical decisions in real-time. The framework helps to improve diagnostic performance, privacy of data, as well as offer scalable, interpretable, reliable solutions to the contemporary intelligent healthcare systems."}, {"id": "DS-031", "title": "Developing an AI/ML-based algorithm for identifying tropical cloud clusters using half-hourly satellite data from the INSAT.", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "Bharatiya Antariksh Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Shambhu Bhardwaj", "sitting_place": "34-202-CH34", "description": "Tropical Cloud Clusters (TCCs) are very important for Earth's weather and climate because they move heat, air, and moisture upward into the atmosphere. These cloud clusters often lead to the formation of tropical cyclones and are linked with major weather patterns like the monsoon and the Madden--Julian Oscillation (MJO). So, finding and tracking TCCs correctly helps scientists understand how cyclones start, improve weather forecasts, and study changes in the climate. This project aims to develop an AI/ML-based automatic algorithm to identify and analyze Tropical Cloud Clusters over the Indian Oceanic region using half-hourly INSAT-3D Infrared Brightness Temperature (IRBT) data. The algorithm will leverage advanced deep learning and machine learning techniques---such as convolutional neural networks (CNNs) or clustering-based models---to detect cloud clusters from satellite imagery, delineate their boundaries, and estimate key physical parameters including size, centroid location, convective intensity, and cloud-top height. To facilitate this research, a new dataset named the Indian Tropical Cloud Cluster (ITCC) dataset will be generated. The ITCC will serve as a benchmark dataset for analyzing TCC characteristics and their spatiotemporal evolution. By integrating INSAT-3D data with AI-driven analytics, the proposed system will not only automate the identification of TCCs but also enable near-real-time tracking of their movement and lifecycle across the Indian Ocean basin. The outcomes of this study are expected to significantly benefit the tropical cyclone forecast community and meteorological research institutions by providing improved situational awareness and early indicators of cyclogenesis. The developed methodology can also be extended to other geostationary satellite data sources, contributing to global tropical weather monitoring and climate studies."}, {"id": "DS-032", "title": "Development of a Digital Mental Health and Psychological Support System for Students in Higher Education", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Vikas Mangotra", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH9", "description": "The project aims to develop a digital mental health and psychological support system for higher education students. It provides AI-based self-assessment, mood tracking, and virtual counseling to detect early signs of stress and anxiety. The platform ensures 24/7 accessibility, confidentiality, and promotes emotional well-being through educational resources, peer support, and data-driven insights for institutions to enhance student mental health services."}, {"id": "DS-033", "title": "Development of a Digital Mental Health and Psychological Support System for Students in Higher Education", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Review", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Sadaf Qureshi", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH13", "description": "Today, mental health has become one of the most important concerns for students in colleges and universities. Many students struggle with academic pressure, worries about their future careers, financial responsibilities, social expectations, and major life changes. These challenges often lead to stress, anxiety, depression, and emotional burnout. As technology plays a major role in students' lives, there is a growing need for a smart, easy-to-use digital system that can support their emotional well-being anytime, anywhere. This project focuses on developing a digital mental health support platform that helps students stay emotionally strong, build resilience, and get timely help when needed."}, {"id": "DS-034", "title": "Digital Platform for Centralized Alumni Data Management and Engagement", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Sadaf Qureshi", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH13", "description": "The project titled \"Digital Platform for Centralized Alumni Data Management and Engagement\" aims to create a smart, technology-driven system that connects alumni, students, and institutions in one unified platform. Alumni are one of the most valuable parts of any educational institution, they represent its success, contribute to placements, offer mentorship, and strengthen its reputation. However, most universities struggle with managing alumni data due to scattered systems, outdated tools, and poor engagement methods. To overcome these issues, this project proposes an AI-enhanced digital solution that not only centralizes alumni data but also makes interactions more personalized and meaningful. The platform allows alumni to create verified profiles, connect with peers, and take part in mentorship programs. Students can easily find and reach out to mentors who match their career interests, while administrators can view real-time analytics about engagement and alumni activity. A unique addition to this system is the AI-powered resume improvement feature. Students and recent graduates can upload their resumes, which are then analyzed by AI models to provide personalized feedback on content, formatting, and skill relevance. The system identifies missing or outdated skills and suggests improvements based on current industry trends and job requirements. It can also recommend short online courses or workshops offered by alumni or partner platforms to help users bridge their skill gaps and become more employable. This feature not only enhances students' job readiness but also helps alumni mentors provide more focused career guidance. The system is built using React, Node.js, and Google Cloud Firestore, ensuring scalability, security, and smooth performance. What sets this project apart is the use of Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning to make the platform more intelligent. For example, AI algorithms can recommend potential mentorship matches based on shared interests, professional backgrounds, or skill areas. Similarly, the system can analyze engagement data to identify which activities or events generate the most participation. Administrators also benefit from AI-powered analytics that provide deeper insights into alumni behavior, such as identifying the most active regions, popular industries, or successful mentorship outcomes. This helps institutions plan targeted communication strategies, improve placement support, and strengthen overall engagement. By combining centralized data management, AI-based recommendations, and resume enhancement capabilities, the platform transforms traditional alumni systems into an interactive, data-driven community. It not only helps alumni stay connected but also ensures that their contributions whether through mentorship, collaboration, or career guidance are more impactful and aligned with institutional goals."}, {"id": "DS-035", "title": "Disaster and Emergency Detection & Response Predictor", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25008", "supervisor": "Dr. Harpreet Kaur", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-C2", "description": "Natural disasters and emergencies, such as floods, earthquakes, industrial accidents, and pandemics, pose a significant threat to life, property, and infrastructure. Rapid detection and timely response are critical in minimizing damage and ensuring the safety of affected populations. However, traditional emergency management systems often rely on manual reporting, delayed alerts, or fragmented data, leading to slower decision-making and inadequate response. The Disaster and Emergency Detection & Response Predictor aims to leverage real-time data analytics, machine learning, and predictive modeling to detect potential disasters or emergency situations early and recommend the most effective response strategies. By integrating data from multiple sources---such as weather sensors, satellite imagery, social media feeds, and IoT-enabled devices---the system can predict the likelihood, location, and severity of disasters, enabling authorities and responders to take proactive measures. Key Objectives: Early detection of disasters or emergencies using predictive algorithms. Real-time monitoring and integration of multi-source data for situational awareness. Automated recommendation of optimal response strategies to reduce impact. Facilitation of communication between authorities, emergency responders, and the affected publi"}, {"id": "DS-036", "title": "Disaster Preparedness and Response Education System for Schools and Colleges", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25008", "supervisor": "Twinkle Sehgal", "sitting_place": "36-307-CH14", "description": "Problem Description In India, schools and colleges are often unprepared for natural disasters such as earthquakes, floods, and fires. While emergency guidelines exist on paper, there is a lack of structured disaster management education integrated into the curriculum. Institutions lack digital tools to simulate disaster scenarios or conduct virtual drills to train students and staff on safety protocols. Furthermore, there's a gap in localized awareness---many students are unaware of how to react during disasters specific to their region. Manual drills, where they occur, are infrequent and often poorly coordinated, failing to instill practical preparedness. Impact / Why this problem needs to be solved Lack of awareness and preparedness leads to panic, chaos, and potentially fatal outcomes during emergencies. By integrating disaster education into regular learning, institutions can equip students and staff with life-saving knowledge and skills. This is especially critical in areas prone to natural calamities. Empowering young people with this knowledge not only makes campuses safer but also contributes to a more disaster-resilient society. Expected Outcomes • A digital platform or app that offers interactive disaster education modules, region-specific alerts, and virtual drills. • Gamified learning experiences to improve engagement. • Emergency contact directories and real-time communication tools during disasters. • Dashboards for school administrators to track preparedness scores and drill participation. Relevant Stakeholders / Beneficiaries • Students (K-12 and higher education) • Teachers and administrative staff • Educational institutions and local disaster response teams • Parents and guardians • Government departments (NDMA, Education Ministry) Supporting Data • NDMA reports show low awareness levels in schools despite India's high disaster vulnerability index. • UNDRR has recommended integrating disaster risk reduction in education policies (Ref: National Disaster Management Authority)."}, {"id": "DS-037", "title": "Disaster Preparedness and Response Education System for Schools and Colleges", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Sadaf Qureshi", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH13", "description": "This project focuses on building a digital system that helps schools and colleges prepare for and respond to disasters like earthquakes, floods, or fires. In many places, disaster drills are either not taken seriously or are not done at all. Students are often unaware of what actions to take when a real emergency happens. To fix this, we designed a platform that not only sends alerts during a disaster but also teaches students how to stay safe using videos, quizzes, and regular practice drills. It combines learning, real-time alerts, and emergency planning into one easy-to-use platform. The aim is to protect lives and build a safety-first mindset in schools using smart technology."}, {"id": "DS-038", "title": "EcoGeoGuard: A Dual Approach to Environmental Safety and Crop Yield", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Sheetal Chauhan", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH22", "description": "EcoGeoGuard is an intelligent AI- and IoT-driven ecosystem designed to enhance disaster resilience, smart agriculture, and human-- animal safety in India's hilly and rural regions. The system integrates geo-sensors, soil and weather analytics, and machine learning models to deliver continuous situational intelligence and predictive alerts. It monitors ground vibration, rainfall, and soil moisture to forecast landslides, enabling timely evacuation, rescue, and protection of humans and animals. For agriculture, EcoGeoGuard uses AI-based soil and crop analysis to guide irrigation, fertilizer use, and harvesting, reducing crop and livestock losses while improving yield and income stability. A dedicated animal-rescue module with geo-tagged trackers safeguards livestock during disasters.By merging these domains, EcoGeoGuard creates a unified, data-driven safety and productivity network, fostering climate resilience, sustainable rural development, and aligning with Digital Bharat and the SDGs --- Climate Action, Life on Land, and Innovation in Infrastructure."}, {"id": "DS-039", "title": "EduSync: AI-Powered Smart Attendance and Goal-Based Learning System", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025 Topic No 11", "supervisor": "Sandeep kaur", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH39", "description": "EduSync is an AI-driven platform that automates attendance through QR or face recognition and utilizes students' free periods for goal-based learning. It provides separate teacher and student dashboards, creates personalized timetables, and offers gamified micro-learning tasks, tests, and AI-generated cheat-sheets to improve productivity and engagement while aligning with academic goals. The project will be implemented using Angular/React for Frontend, Python libraries for machine learning , Python (Flask, Django, FastAPI) for backend."}, {"id": "DS-040", "title": "Enhancing cardiac diagnostics: A deep learning ensemble approach for precise ECG image classification", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "SpringerOpen - Journal of Big Data (https://doi.org/10.1186/s40537-025-01070-4)", "supervisor": "Anchal Kaundal", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH8", "description": "Cardiovascular diseases remain one of the leading causes of death worldwide, emphasizing the need for early and reliable diagnostic methods. This research aims to develop a deep learning--based system capable of automatically analyzing electrocardiogram (ECG) images to identify and classify heart conditions. By leveraging image-processing and pattern-recognition techniques, the model detects abnormalities in heart rhythms and assesses their severity. In addition to classification, the framework provides preventive healthcare guidance by offering personalized recommendations for early-stage irregularities and generating alerts for critical cases. The approach enhances diagnostic accuracy, enables faster medical decision-making, and promotes proactive cardiovascular health management."}, {"id": "DS-041", "title": "Fake news detection using machine learning models and frameworks.", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "Google Scholar/Springer(https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10115-024-02321-1)", "supervisor": "Anchal Kaundal", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH8", "description": "This research studies fake news occurrence in contemporary digital networks with special attention to its effects on social understanding. Fake news detection is a crucial area of text classification, focusing on distinguishing real news from deceptive content designed to mislead audiences. The domain has witnessed excellent performance from ML-based models/Frameworks. The research adopts these models to make fake news detection systems more precise and dependable. Standard evaluation metrics used to assess the effectiveness of the approach in a complete measure of model performance."}, {"id": "DS-042", "title": "Hybrid Approach for Heart Disease Prediction: Synergizing Deep Learning and machine learning Techniques.", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "It is novel idea.", "supervisor": "Priyanka Kumari", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH11", "description": "This research explores hybrid models combining deep learning and machine learning techniques for heart disease prediction. By synergizing convolutional neural network (CNN) with random forest (RF), Recurrent Neural Network (RNN) with gradient boosting , the approach leverages the powerful feature extraction."}, {"id": "DS-043", "title": "Intelligent Diagnostic System for Early Chest Cancer Detection using Radiological and Clinical data", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Dr. Vipin Kumar", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH20", "description": "Chest cancers remain one of the leading causes of mortality worldwide, and early detection significantly improves survival rates. Current diagnostic practices rely heavily on radiological expertise and clinical judgment, which may be time-consuming and prone to variability. This project introduces an AI-powered intelligent diagnostic system that integrates radiological imaging features and structured clinical data for more reliable and interpretable cancer detection. The system leverages machine learning models (SVM & XGBoost) alongside interpretability tools (Grad-CAM & SHAP) to provide accurate predictions with transparent explanations, supporting medical professionals in critical decision-making. The technologies used include SVM for imaging pattern analysis, XGBoost for structured clinical data classification, as well as Grad-CAM and SHAP for model interpretability. These advances benefit society by enabling early disease detection, reducing healthcare costs, supporting overburdened healthcare systems, improving accessibility in low-resource settings, and fostering trust in AI-driven healthcare."}, {"id": "DS-044", "title": "Intelligent Traffic Monitoring and Obstruction Detection for Emergency Vehicle Path Optimization Using OpenCV and Deep Learning", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH Problem Statements, SIMENS Industrial R&D Problem Statements, NVIDIA Graphics Hardware Grant Problem Statement 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Sahul Goyal", "sitting_place": "34-203-CH21", "description": "Urban traffic congestion has become a major challenge for emergency vehicles such as ambulances, fire trucks, and police vans, often delaying their timely arrival at destinations. One of the primary causes of this delay is the failure of other vehicles to give way during emergencies. Our project, \"Smart Traffic Monitoring and Obstruction Detection for Emergency Vehicle Path Management\" aims to create an intelligent, real-time surveillance system that can automatically detect vehicles obstructing the path of emergency vehicles and record the violations efficiently. The system uses OpenCV for image processing and motion detection, analyzing live video feeds from roadside or traffic signal cameras. When a vehicle is identified as blocking an emergency route, the system automatically captures the frame and extracts the license plate number using Optical Character Recognition (OCR). This information is then stored in a centralized database, which can be accessed through a web-based interface. The platform allows authorities to view violation records, check vehicle ownership details, and take necessary actions. The interface is designed to be simple, responsive, and informative, ensuring easy use for law enforcement personnel. Technically, the project integrates Python and OpenCV for detection, Tesseract OCR for plate recognition, MySQL or MongoDB for data storage, and Flask or Django for backend connectivity. A ReactJS or HTML/CSS/JavaScript frontend is used to display the processed data on a clean and intuitive dashboard. The system ensures reliable performance in different lighting and weather conditions, with a focus on low-cost implementation for smart city applications. By combining computer vision, web development, and automated data handling, this project demonstrates how technology can enhance emergency response systems. The outcome is a scalable and efficient solution that supports faster emergency movement, promotes responsible driving behavior, and strengthens urban traffic management through intelligent automation."}, {"id": "DS-045", "title": "IoT-Based Medical Emergencies Device", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Application", "source": "Research Papers", "supervisor": "Pardeep Kumar", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH3", "description": "This project aims to develop an IoT-enabled device capable of detecting and responding to medical emergencies in real time. It uses health sensors to monitor vital signs such as heart rate, temperature, and oxygen levels. When abnormal readings are detected, alerts are automatically sent to caregivers, hospitals, or emergency contacts via the internet, helping to ensure timely medical assistance."}, {"id": "DS-046", "title": "Learning App for Deaf and Mute Sign Language", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Komal Arora", "sitting_place": "27-205-CH6", "description": "The learning app for deaf and mute sign language is an educational application designed to facilitate communication and learning for individuals with hearing and speech impairments. The system leverages multimedia content, artificial intelligence, and gesture recognition technologies to enable effective sign language learning and real-time translation between sign language and spoken/written text. The project integrates machine learning models for sign recognition, computer vision algorithms for gesture detection, and a database-driven content management system for storing educational modules and sign animations. It aims to provide both self-learning resources for users and communication tools for interaction between hearing and non-hearing individuals. System objectives: -To develop an interactive application for learning and practicing sign language. -To implement a gesture recognition system using computer vision techniques to identify and evaluate sign gestures -To enable real-time translation of text or voice input into sign language animations. -To design a user-friendly and accessible interface tailored to the needs of deaf and mute users -To integrate offline functionality for accessibility in low connectivity environments."}, {"id": "DS-047", "title": "Leveraging Fine-Tuned LLMs for Forecasting Respiratory Health Risks from Air Quality Data", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "Integration for AI/GenAI Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Pardeep Kumar", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH3", "description": "This project focuses on developing an AI-driven predictive model to assess respiratory health risks based on air quality trends. By leveraging fine-tuned Large Language Models (LLMs), the system will analyze historical air pollution data alongside health records to forecast potential respiratory issues. The model aims to support policymakers, healthcare providers, and environmental bodies in taking proactive measures to reduce health risks. This solution eliminates the need for real-time sensors by utilizing existing datasets, making it cost-effective and scalable."}, {"id": "DS-048", "title": "lmage based Animal Type Classification for cattle and buffaloes", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025 (Problem Statement number: SIH25005)", "supervisor": "Anchal Kaundal", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH8", "description": "In dairy farming, evaluating the body structure of animals is vital to predict their longevity, productivity, and reproductive efficiency. Traditionally, Animal Type Classification (ATC) which involves scoring animals for physical traits is conducted by trained personnel through visual inspection and manual measurement of specific body parts. However, this manual method is prone to human error and subjectivity, even with trained professionals, resulting in inconsistent and potentially unreliable data. With advances in Artificial Intelligence (AI) and image processing technologies, there is an opportunity to automate this process. Automated scoring based on images can ensure standardization, minimize observer bias, and improve the reliability of data captured for scientific and breeding purposes."}, {"id": "DS-049", "title": "lmage based breed recognition for cattle and buffaloes of India.", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Priyanka Kumari", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH11", "description": "Image-based breed recognition for cattle and buffaloes of India uses artificial intelligence and computer vision to identify breeds automatically from images. India has a wide variety of indigenous breeds with distinct physical traits like coat color, horn shape and body structure. Traditional identification methods are manual and error-prone, while AI-based systems offer fast and accurate results. By analyzing visual features using deep learning, the system can distinguish between breeds efficiently. This technology supports livestock management, breed conservation and productivity improvement, contributing significantly to the modernization and digital transformation of India's agricultural and dairy sectors."}, {"id": "DS-050", "title": "Low-Cost IoT-Enabled Waste Management System with Community Feedback for Slum & Semi-Urban Areas", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH : Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Maneet Kaur", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH18", "description": "Motivated the students regarding the registration for project expo."}, {"id": "DS-051", "title": "Multimodal Fusion of Chest X-Ray Images and Clinical Text Reports for Pneumonia Detection Using Vision-Language Deep Learning", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Big Data", "nature": "Research", "source": "Research Analysis", "supervisor": "Anoop Kumar", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH16", "description": "Pneumonia is one of the leading causes of mortality worldwide, particularly among children under five and elderly populations. Early and accurate diagnosis is critical for effective treatment, yet it remains heavily dependent on the availability of experienced radiologists, which is limited in resource. Chest X-ray imaging is the most widely used and cost-effective diagnostic tool for pneumonia detection, but manual interpretation is time-consuming, error-prone, and subject to inter-observer variability."}, {"id": "DS-052", "title": "Online Chatbot based ticketing system of Museum using Natural Language Processing", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Komal Arora", "sitting_place": "27-205-CH6", "description": "The proposed project aims to develop an online chatbot-based ticketing system for a museum that allows visitors to interact with an intelligent virtual assistant for booking tickets, exploring exhibits, and obtaining museum-related information through Natural Language Processing (NLP). The chatbot will serve as a digital guide, enabling users to communicate in simple natural language rather than navigating complex web pages or forms. The system will be integrated with the museum's existing online ticketing portal to handle key operations such as ticket booking, cancellation, timing inquiries, price details, exhibit information, and event updates. Using NLP techniques such as intent recognition, named entity extraction, and context understanding, the chatbot will accurately interpret user queries and respond in a conversational manner."}, {"id": "DS-053", "title": "Optimizing NGO Engagement and Donations through a ReactJS-Powered Web Solution", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH: Smart Indian Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Jaffar Amin Chacket", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH8", "description": "Students are Currently working on developing a ReactJS-based web platform aimed at enhancing NGO engagement and donation management. The platform focuses on simplifying donation processing, improving volunteer interaction, and ensuring mobile responsiveness through a unified, user-friendly interface. It integrates secure payment gateways like Razor pay and UPI, provides a dedicated volunteer and admin portal, and leverages modern web technologies to create a scalable, efficient, and accessible solution for NGOs struggling with outdated systems."}, {"id": "DS-054", "title": "Public Transport monitoring and optimization for small cities in Punjab", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH 2024", "supervisor": "Parminder Singh", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH11", "description": "Design and deploy a data-centric platform for real-time tracking, prediction, and optimization of public transport in small cities of Punjab. The system will leverage machine learning to forecast bus arrivals, suggest optimized routes, and provide a visual dashboard for government use, enhancing urban mobility and operational efficiency."}, {"id": "DS-055", "title": "Real-Time Fire Detection in Surveillance Systems Using YOLO-Based Transfer Learning with a Tkinter Monitoring Interface.", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Big Data", "nature": "Research", "source": "YOLO-based fire detection research", "supervisor": "Dr. Gargi Sharma", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH6", "description": "This project proposes a YOLOv8-based fire detection model using transfer learning to identify fire patterns in image datasets. The system analyzes live video streams from surveillance cameras, performs frame-based detection, and displays results through a Tkinter-based interface. Visual alerts are generated upon fire detection, and the system's effectiveness is evaluated for early fire detection and safety monitoring."}, {"id": "DS-056", "title": "Real-Time Public Transport Tracking for Small Cities", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Application", "source": "Topic taken from SIH", "supervisor": "Kavita Devi", "sitting_place": "34-202-CH24", "description": "This project, inspired by SIH, aims to develop a Real-Time Public Transport Tracking System tailored for small cities, where public transport is often unorganized and unreliable. Commuters and visitors face daily challenges such as uncertain bus or auto timings, delays, and lack of clarity about routes and fares. To overcome these issues, the system will be designed as a mobile and web-based application powered by a cloud backend and mapping APIs. It will enable live vehicle tracking through a driver's smartphone, provide accurate Estimated Time of Arrival (ETA) at stops or pick-up points, and display interactive maps with available routes. In addition, the application will include fare estimation, schedule information, and an offline access feature to support low-connectivity areas common in smaller towns"}, {"id": "DS-057", "title": "Reinforcement Learning-Based Task Offloading Decision Framework in 5G-Enabled Mobile Cloud Networks for IoT Devices", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "ITU AI/ML in 5G Challenge", "supervisor": "Dr. Robin Prakash Mathur", "sitting_place": "28-203-C1", "description": "The work will develops a reinforcement learning-based framework for optimal task offloading in 5G-enabled mobile cloud networks. It addresses the challenge of efficiently managing computation tasks from IoT devices by dynamically deciding whether to process locally or offload to the cloud. The framework aims to minimize latency and energy consumption enhancing IoT device performance and resource utilization in next-generation networks."}, {"id": "DS-058", "title": "Reverse mood methodologies: ethical algorithmic interventions to prevent emotional collapse in youngsters", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Mandeep Kaur", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH7", "description": "In digital environments, recommendation algorithms reinforce depressive content loop among emotionally vulnerable youth. This research introduces \"reverse mood methodologies\", a conceptual framework embedded within platform algorithms that ethically detects emotional collapse signals and redirects users toward uplifting and confidence-building content. Grounded in emotional design, trauma-informed computing, and culturally adaptive strategies, it calls for a moral evolution in algorithmic priorities-from engagement to emotional recovery."}, {"id": "DS-059", "title": "S.A.F.E. India : Smart, Adaptive & Forensic Evaluation of Driver Behaviour for National Road Safety.", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Jaffar Amin Chacket", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH8", "description": "Project S.A.F.E. India is a pioneering Behaviour Governance System designed to drastically improve road safety across India by shifting the enforcement paradigm from reactive to proactive and adaptive. At its core, the system utilizes a network of integrated multi-modal sensors (CCTV, dashcams, and mobile devices) running edge-based AI models to perform real-time, highly accurate detection of key human violations (helmet non-use, speeding, ANPR) and infrastructure hazards (potholes, obstacles). This real-time data is streamed via a secure ingestion layer (Kafka/Kinesis) to a cloud-based analytics engine. The system's central innovation is the Citizen Safety Score (CSS), a dynamic metric calculated for every licensed driver. The CSS acts as an immutable, continuous record---it increases with compliant behaviour and decreases with every violation or accident. This score serves as the policy trigger: authorities can mandate remedial action (like retraining or re-testing) when the score drops below a pre-defined threshold, or incentivize good behaviour with benefits (insurance discounts, etc.)."}, {"id": "DS-060", "title": "Sentiment Analysis of Comments from E-Consultation Module", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Vikas Mangotra", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH9", "description": "eConsultation module is an online platform wherein proposed amendments/draft legislations are posted on MCA's website for external users to submit their comments and suggestions pertaining to the same through the MCA21 portal. The comments are captured in a structured format for due consideration with respect to amending the draft legislation, based on the suggestions or observations received."}, {"id": "DS-061", "title": "Sentiment Analysis of Comments Received through E-Consultation Module.", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Business Model", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Aashima", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH5", "description": "This project aims to develop an automated and sophisticated system for analysing the public sentiment, from their received comments via the government's e-consultation module. In this digital age, governments are actively relying on online platforms to solicit public feedback on the proposed policies, initiatives and services they provide. As this generates numerous amounts of data, manually examining through those thousands of comments to gauge the public opinion which is a subjective & often an inefficient process.Proposed solution leverages the Natural Language Processing (NLP) Machine Learning Solutions to address this challenge. The core idea behind this project involves building a multi-class classification model which is much capable of accurately categorizing each comment as positive, negative or neutral. This is far better than any simple positive/negative binary classification, where it may be the case that the significant portion of the feedback is suggestive or neutral in tone. The process begins with the rigorous preprocessing pipeline to clean, removing noise like stop words & irrelevant characters, then preparing the data for analysis.After this, the project will dive into different machine learning models, including deep learning architectures like BERT, which is particularly effective at understanding the complex context & semanntics of human language. The project's main aim is to identify and fine-tune a model which achieves high accuracy.The final output will be the interactive dashboard, which will serve as a powerful tool for policymakers, allowing them to visualize the sentimental trends over the time, leveraging them to compare public reactions to different policy topics & to drill down into specific areas of concerns. This will help them shift from manual review to automated, and the visual analysis will provide government bodies with rapid and actionable insights, enabling them to be more responsive & transparent in their decision making"}, {"id": "DS-062", "title": "Smart Attendance: Automated Attendance System for Rural Schools", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Gaurav Sharma", "sitting_place": "27-203-CH8", "description": "The project \"Smart Attendance: Automated Attendance System for Rural Schools\" aims to modernise and simplify the attendance process in rural educational institutions through affordable technology. In many rural schools, attendance is still recorded manually, which is time-consuming, prone to errors, and difficult to manage. This project proposes an automated solution using facial recognition or RFID-based identification to mark attendance efficiently and accurately. The system automatically identifies students as they enter the classroom and records their attendance in a digital database. It helps teachers save time, ensures data accuracy, and allows school administrators to access attendance reports instantly. For areas with limited internet connectivity, the system supports offline data storage and synchronizes attendance records once the network becomes available. Designed with low-cost hardware such as Raspberry Pi, RFID readers, or camera modules, the project focuses on affordability and scalability to suit rural schools with limited resources. The accompanying software provides a simple dashboard for teachers and administrators to view attendance records, generate reports, and monitor absenteeism patterns. Parents can also receive notifications for consistent absences, encouraging regular student participation. By reducing manual effort, improving transparency, and promoting regular attendance, this project supports the goals of Digital India and strengthens smart education initiatives in rural areas. It offers an efficient, reliable, and sustainable solution that can significantly enhance the management of school operations and contribute to improved learning outcomes."}, {"id": "DS-063", "title": "Smart Community Health Monitoring and Early Warning System for Diseases", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Application", "source": "https://www.sih.gov.in/sih2025PS (Organization: Ministry of Development of Northeastern Region (MoDoNER), Category: Software, Problem statement Number: SIH25001)", "supervisor": "Dr. Fayaz Ahmad Khan", "sitting_place": "26-205-CH19", "description": "The Smart Health Surveillance and Early Warning System aims to harness the power of data science, artificial intelligence (AI), and andMachine Learning (ML) to predict and help prevent disease outbreaks across communities. The system will collect and integrate real-time data from multiple sources such as clinics, hospitals, community health workers, IoT-based environmental sensors, and citizen reports via mobile apps. Using advanced data science techniques, the platform will clean, analyze, and visualize this data to identify trends, detect anomalies, and generate early warnings of potential disease outbreaks. The solution will include predictive modeling, automated alert systems, and interactive dashboards for public health departments to visualize hotspots, monitor interventions, and make informed decisions. Additionally, the system will support multilingual community interfaces to enable local reporting, awareness generation, and preventive healthcare education. This project demonstrates how data-driven intelligence can strengthen public health surveillance, reduce response time, and enhance resilience against infectious and communicable diseases globally."}, {"id": "DS-064", "title": "Smart Disaster Preparedness and Response System for Educational Institutions", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Sadaf Qureshi", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH13", "description": "Smart Disaster Preparedness and Response System for Educational Institutions Our project aims to create a smart system that helps schools and colleges stay prepared for disasters like fires, floods, or earthquakes. The system will give early alerts, safety tips, and training activities for students and teachers to handle emergencies better. We also made a Google Sheet to study different research papers on disaster management, which helped us understand the problems and plan better solutions for our project."}, {"id": "DS-065", "title": "Smart Farm Advisory System", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025: SIH25010", "supervisor": "Dr. Karan Bajaj( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "Small and marginal farmers often struggle to make informed agricultural decisions due to limited access to expert advice, real-time weather information, and soil health data. Existing advisory services are either generalized or not easily accessible to rural communities. This leads to poor crop selection, inefficient use of resources, and low productivity."}, {"id": "DS-066", "title": "Smart Mushroom Disease Detection and Classification for Real-Time Decision Support", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "Real world problem", "supervisor": "Manpreet Singh", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "Mushroom farming plays a crucial role in providing food and income, yet it faces significant threats from infections like green mold, dry bubble, and bacterial blotch. These diseases can drastically diminish both the quantity and quality of mushrooms harvested, which in turn affects profitability. Relying on traditional methods of human inspection for disease detection can be quite tedious, labor-intensive, and often subjective. Fortunately, advancements in machine learning are paving the way for real-time detection of mushroom diseases, allowing for the differentiation between various types and timely alerts. This innovative approach not only enhances diagnostic accuracy but also aids in disease management strategies, ultimately promoting sustainable mushroom production by reducing losses and boosting economic returns for farmers. Gaps 1.There is a shortage of AI approaches specifically designed for mushroom disease detection, limiting effectiveness for the unique characteristics of mushroom pathogens. 2.Few high-quality, annotated mushroom disease image datasets are publicly available, restricting the training and evaluation of robust machine learning models. 3.Most current studies focus only on disease identification without providing actionable guidance or preventive measures for farmers. 4.There is limited research on classifying multiple mushroom disease types, even though accurate categorisation is essential for targeted interventions."}, {"id": "DS-067", "title": "Smart Tourist Safety Monitoring & Incident Response System using AI, Geo-Fencing, and Blockchain-based Digital ID", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Zeenat Zahra", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH7", "description": "Tourism is one of the fastest-growing industries, but ensuring the safety and security of travelers remains a serious challenge. Tourists often visit unfamiliar places where they may face risks such as accidents, theft, medical emergencies, or even getting lost. Traditional safety measures like manual monitoring, emergency helplines, or local guides are often slow to respond and lack real-time accuracy. With the rise of smart technologies, there is an urgent need for an intelligent system that can actively monitor tourist safety, detect unusual incidents, and provide immediate assistance. Many existing solutions either focus only on navigation or on general information, but they do not integrate real-time monitoring, automatic alerts, and secure digital identity verification. This gap highlights the necessity for a Smart Tourist Safety Monitoring & Incident Response System that leverages AI for threat detection, geo-fencing for location-based alerts, and blockchain for secure digital identity management. Such a system would not only enhance the safety of tourists but also build trust in the tourism sector, encouraging more people to travel with confidence."}, {"id": "DS-068", "title": "SmartBreed: AI-Based Identification of Indian Cattle", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Anchal Kaundal", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH8", "description": "Misidentification of cattle and buffalo breeds in the Bharat Pashudhan App impacts data validity and decision-making in breeding, health, and nutrition schemes. An AI-driven image identification system can identify and classify breeds automatically from images, minimizing human errors, providing reliable data, and assisting field staff with real-time breed authentication upon animal registration. Machine learning models trained on diverse image datasets can adapt to varying field conditions and animal appearances. This system can also support genetic improvement programs by ensuring correct breed tagging during artificial insemination drives. Ultimately, it contributes to improving productivity, disease control, and resource allocation. Additionally, real-time breed verification can help detect crossbreeding trends and preserve indigenous genetic resources."}, {"id": "DS-069", "title": "Soft Computing-Based Hybrid Frameworks for Threat Classification and Analysis", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Research", "source": "Google Scholar", "supervisor": "Dr. Mrinalini Rana", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH3", "description": "In the era of big data, effective threat detection and prevention are critical across domains such as finance, healthcare, and network security. Traditional detection systems often struggle to cope with high-dimensional data, evolving threat vectors, and complex behavioral patterns. This will explores the integration of feature engineering with soft computing-based hybrid frameworks to enhance the accuracy and efficiency of cyber threat classification and analysis. The proposed approach aims to accelerate threat detection while reducing false positives and computational overhead, thereby improving overall system performance in dynamic and data-intensive environments."}, {"id": "DS-070", "title": "Tea Leaves Disease Detection Using A Deep Learning Approach", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science & Big Data", "nature": "Research", "source": "Research", "supervisor": "Dr. Virrat Devaser", "sitting_place": "26-202-C1", "description": "Tea is one of the most widely consumed beverages in the world, and the quality and yield of tea crops are highly affected by leaf diseases such as blister blight, red rust, and grey blight. Traditional disease identification relies on manual inspection by experts, which is time-consuming, subjective, and difficult to scale for large plantations."}, {"id": "DS-071", "title": "Women Safety Analytics -- Smart Safe-Zone Predictor", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart india hackathon , problem statement id 1605", "supervisor": "Sandeep", "sitting_place": "33-205-CH18", "description": "The Women Safety Analytics -- Smart Safe-Zone Predictor is an AI-powered platform that aims to increase women's safety in cities by forecasting and mapping the safety of various city zones. The initiative proposes a real-time Women Safety Index (WSI) that dynamically updates with geospatial information, past crime data, social media trends, and live user comments. Applying machine learning algorithms like XGBoost and ConvLSTM, the system makes spatio-temporal predictions to predict the risk level of each zone based on parameters such as time of day, crowd intensity, and past incidents. The WSI values are subsequently used in graph-based pathfinding algorithms (Dijkstra or A\\*), and the system can suggest low-risk routes of travel rather than just shortest routes. A mobile-optimized dashboard displays this data as interactive heatmaps, risk trend charts, and safe-zone recommendations. The dashboard also allows users to make live safety reports, reinforcing community engagement and enhancing model performance. The evaluation metrics of the project are prediction accuracy (AUC, F1-score), routing efficiency (risk reduction vs. shortest path), and user satisfaction through pilot evaluation"}, {"id": "AI-060", "title": "The HerbAI - An AI-Herbal Identification and Disease Recommendation", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH1555:Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Vaibhav Nanda", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH5", "description": "Conventional herbal medicine, though rich in knowledge, faces several challenges: 1. Manual Identification: Herb recognition depends on experts and is prone to misidentification, leading to possible misuse. 2. Lack of Centralized Knowledge: Herbal data is scattered across books and databases, making research and reference difficult. 3. Absence of AI Integration: No existing platform integrates image-based recognition with NLP-driven medicinal mapping. 4. Public Inaccessibility: Common users lack tools to identify herbs and access reliable information. Hence, there is a strong need for an intelligent, automated system capable of identifying herbs via photos and mapping them to their health benefits and safe applications. B. Objective of the Invention The invention aims to build an AI-assisted framework that can: 1. Automatically detect medicinal herbs through computer vision-based image identification. 2. Build a comprehensive knowledge base linking herbs, active compounds, and associated diseases. 3. Provide AI-driven herbal therapy recommendations using NLP. 4. Offer findings via an accessible mobile and web platform. 5. Bridge traditional herbal knowledge and modern AI technology for scalability and education."}, {"id": "AI-061", "title": "AI-based framework for Online real-time survey and monitoring of water bodies.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2024, Problem Statement (ID 1619)", "supervisor": "Amer Amin", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH33", "description": "Water bodies in Delhi, such as lakes, ponds, and drains, play a crucial role in maintaining the city's ecological balance and groundwater recharge. However, over the past few decades, these natural assets have been severely affected by rapid urbanization, industrial discharge, untreated sewage inflows, and encroachments. The absence of a centralized and continuous monitoring system has further aggravated the situation, leading to a decline in both water quality and quantity. There is, therefore, an urgent need to develop a comprehensive technological solution capable of monitoring and assessing the real-time condition of water bodies across Delhi. The proposed project aims to design and implement an IoT (Internet of Things) and Artificial Intelligence (AI) based model that can continuously collect, process, and analyze water-related data from various sites across the city. The system will be equipped with smart sensors to measure critical water quality parameters such as pH, turbidity, temperature, dissolved oxygen (DO), biochemical oxygen demand (BOD), and levels of harmful chemicals or heavy metals. The sensors will transmit real-time data to a central cloud-based platform, where the information will be processed and stored for further analysis. Using AI algorithms and predictive analytics, the system will interpret the incoming data to identify pollution sources, detect anomalies, and forecast potential contamination or depletion trends. This will help authorities take preventive actions before conditions worsen. Additionally, machine learning techniques will be used to improve the model's accuracy over time by learning from historical patterns and seasonal variations. The model can also integrate meteorological and geographical data to assess the impact of rainfall, temperature, and urban expansion on water body conditions."}, {"id": "AI-062", "title": "Al-Based Cloud Detection from Satellite Images", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "SIH1563 - Automatic Change Detection in Synthetic Aperture Radar Satellite Images", "supervisor": "Siya Thakur", "sitting_place": "26-205-CH18", "description": "This project focuses on the application of artificial intelligence, particularly deep learning techniques, for the automatic detection and classification of clouds in satellite imagery. Traditional cloud detection methods often struggle with variations in cloud types and complex atmospheric conditions, leading to reduced accuracy. By employing convolutional neural networks (CNNs), this project aims to enhance the precision and efficiency of cloud segmentation. The proposed approach assists meteorologists and climate researchers by providing reliable data for weather prediction, climate monitoring, and environmental analysis. Overall, the project demonstrates how Al can significantly improve the processing and interpretation of satellite data for scientific and practical applications."}, {"id": "AI-063", "title": "Echo - The AI-Powered Desk Assistant", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "AICTE1082", "supervisor": "Dr. Subhita", "sitting_place": "26-205-C1", "description": "The primary objective of the 'Echo' project is to create a physical, AI-powered desk assistant that makes daily work and study tasks easier and more efficient. In today's world, many people struggle to manage physical documents like notes and receipts, stay focused, and remain motivated. While digital assistants exist, they often pull our attention back to a screen, causing distractions. 'Echo' aims to solve this problem by being a helpful companion that sits on the desk and interacts through simple voice commands and visual cues. Beyond just handling tasks, the project aims to foster a more productive and positive work environment. Echo will act as a personal motivator, offering timely encouragement and reminders to take breaks. The ultimate objective is to develop an affordable, user-friendly, and tangible tool that bridges the gap between our physical and digital workspaces, helping users stay organized and focused."}, {"id": "AI-064", "title": "Explainable AI for Breast Cancer Detection", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Himanshu", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH15", "description": "Breast cancer is one of the most common cancers affecting women worldwide, and early detection is essential for improving survival rates and treatment outcomes. Medical imaging techniques such as mammography and histopathology imaging are widely used for detecting breast cancer. Recently, deep learning models, especially Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), have shown high accuracy in identifying cancerous patterns from these medical images."}, {"id": "AI-065", "title": "SignBridge: A Bidirectional Sign Language Translation Mobile Application with Real time Recognition and 3D Animation", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SMART INDIA HACKATHO 2024", "supervisor": "Dr. Vidhi Sood", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH6", "description": "The primary challenges addressed by this project are: 1. Communication Barrier: Lack of effective real-time translation between sign language and spoken/written English 2. Limited Accessibility: Existing solutions are not optimized for mobile devices or real-world usage scenarios 3. Unidirectional Systems: Most current systems only translate in one direction (sign-to-text or text-to-sign) 4. Poor User Experience: Lack of intuitive interfaces and visual feedback for both learning and communication purposes 5. Technical Limitations: Insufficient accuracy in real-time hand pose recognition and gesture classification Solution SignBridge proposes a comprehensive mobile application built using Ionic React that provides: 1 Bidirectional Translation System • Mode 1- Sign to Text: Real-time camera-based sign language recognition using MediaPipe hand pose detection, converting gestures to English text • Mode 2- Text to Sign: Input English text and display corresponding sign language through realistic 3D avatar animations 2 Advanced Machine Learning Architecture The system employs a novel approach adapted from 2D landmark-based handwriting recognition: • Hand landmark extraction (21 points × 3D coordinates) • Rich feature engineering including velocity, acceleration, curvature, and geometric features • BiLSTM + Multi-head Attention architecture for sequence modeling • CTC (Connectionist Temporal Classification) loss for alignment-free learning 3 Cross-Platform Mobile Application • Native-like performance on both iOS and Android platforms • Real-time processing with on-device inference • Intuitive user interface with accessibility features • Offline capability for core translation functions 5 Objectives Primary Objectives 1. Develop a real-time sign language recognition system with ¿90% accuracy for common gestures 2. Create a bidirectional translation interface supporting both sign-to-text and text to-sign conversion 3. Build a cross-platform mobile application using Ionic React framework 4. Implement 3D avatar-based sign language animation for visual learning and communication Secondary Objectives 1. Optimize the system for real-time performance on mobile devices 2. Create an extensible architecture that can support multiple sign languages 3. Develop a user-friendly interface accessible to both deaf and hearing users 4. Establish a foundation for future enhancements including gesture learning and personalization"}, {"id": "AI-066", "title": "SMART TOURIST SAFETY MONITORING & INCIDENT RESPONSE SYSTEM USING AI, GEO-FENCING, AND BLOCKCHAIN-BASED DIGITAL ID", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart india hackathon", "supervisor": "Rashika Gupta", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "To improve visitor safety, the Smart Tourist Safety Monitoring and Incident Response System combines blockchain, AI, and geofencing. Blockchain guarantees safe identity verification, AI forecasts hazards, and geofencing sends out real-time alerts for danger areas. In order to lower incidents and boost visitor confidence through smart, tech-driven safety management, the system provides proactive monitoring, quick emergency response, and privacy protection"}, {"id": "AI-067", "title": "A Comparative Study and Development of an Efficient Machine Learning-Based Framework for Heart Disease Prediction", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Research studies", "supervisor": "Dr. Uzma Saghir", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH20", "description": "This research focuses on developing an efficient machine learning-based framework for heart disease prediction. It involves a comprehensive study and analysis of existing predictive methods to understand their strengths and limitations. Based on these insights, an interactive and optimized framework is proposed to enhance prediction accuracy and usability. The effectiveness of the proposed approach is then evaluated through a comparative analysis against existing models, highlighting improvements in performance and efficiency."}, {"id": "AI-068", "title": ":Explainable Neurosymbolic Deep Learning Framework for Driver Drowsiness Detection.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Identified from recent research on road safety, driver monitoring systems, and emerging work on neurosymbolic and explainable AI in intelligent transportation.", "supervisor": "Dr. Neeta Rana", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH5", "description": "The proposed project is a software only, explainable neurosymbolic deep learning architecture of driver drowsiness detection based on publicly available video data. A deep model derives the visual fatigue indicators, like eye closure, blink rate, yawning, and head pose. A symbolic reasoning layer is then used to impose explicit rules on these indicators to categorize the level of driver alertness and come up with human understandable explanations to enhance reliability and interpretability compared to black-box deep models."}, {"id": "AI-069", "title": "\" AI/ML-Based GNSS Satellite Clock and Orbit Error Prediction System \"", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon (SIH) 2025", "supervisor": "Raghu Raja Sharma", "sitting_place": "34-202-CH8", "description": "The accuracy of Global Navigation Satellite Systems (GNSS) is fundamentally limited by errors in satellite clock biases and ephemeris (satellite orbit) predictions. These errors, if not accurately modeled and predicted, can lead to significant deviations in positioning and timing solutions. This challenge tasks participants with developing and applying generative Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) methods to model and predict the differences between uploaded (broadcast) and ICD based modelled values. The goal is to produce highly accurate error predictions for future time intervals, enhancing the reliability and precision of GNSS applications. Participants will be provided with a seven-day dataset containing recorded clock and ephemeris errors between uploaded and modeled values from GNSS satellites in both GEO/GSO and MEO. The models must be capable of predicting these errors at 15-minute intervals for an eighth day that is not included in the training data. Evaluation will focus on the accuracy of these predictions over various validity periods: 15 minutes, 30 minutes, 1 hour, 2 hours, and up to 24 hours into the future from the last known data point. Competitors are encouraged to explore a wide range of generative AI/ML techniques, including but not limited to: • Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs), such as Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) and Gated Recurrent Units (GRUs), for time-series forecasting. • Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for synthesizing realistic error patterns. • Transformers for capturing long-range dependencies in the data. • Gaussian Processes for probabilistic modeling of errors. This project also emphasizes inclusivity and usability. Many farmers may not be technically skilled, so the interface will be designed with simplicity. The advisory will be aligned with government agricultural guidelines to ensure authenticity and trust. By providing a low-cost, accessible, and scalable system, the proposed solution will not only empower farmers to make better decisions but also contribute to food security, rural income stability, and sustainable farming practices."}, {"id": "AI-070", "title": "\"AI-Based Crop Recommendation for Farmers\"", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon (SIH) 2025", "supervisor": "Raghu Raja Sharma", "sitting_place": "34-202-CH8", "description": "One of the major challenges faced by farmers is crop disease, which often goes unnoticed until it spreads widely, leading to reduced yield and economic losses. Traditionally, farmers depend on their own experience or local experts to identify crop diseases --- methods that are often inaccurate, time-consuming, and inaccessible in remote areas. In addition, many young and upcoming farmers lack sufficient knowledge about the ideal crop-laying seasons and suitable crops for their specific regions and soil types. This often results in poor crop selection, reduced productivity, and financial loss. Therefore, there is a strong need for a technologically supported system that can guide farmers in both disease identification and crop planning to achieve maximum yield and sustainability. The AI-Based Crop Recommendation System aims to address these challenges by integrating Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Cloud Computing into a smart, farmer-friendly platform. Farmers can upload images of their crop leaves through a simple web or mobile application. The system will analyze the image to detect if the crop is diseased. If a disease is found, the model will identify the type of disease (e.g., bacterial blight, powdery mildew, rust, etc.) and provide treatment and preventive advisory in simple, regional languages. Additionally, the system will recommend the most suitable crops for each season based on soil, climate, and regional data --- helping farmers, especially beginners, make informed planting decisions and improve productivity. The solution will consist of three main components: 1. Farmer-Facing Application: A web/mobile interface for farmers to upload crop images, receive disease reports, and get advisory in their local language. 2. Expert Dashboard: A dedicated portal for agricultural officers and experts to review cases, validate AI predictions, and offer manual feedback. 3. Cloud-Based Backend: Cloud infrastructure (e.g., AWS S3 & SageMaker or Google Cloud Run & GCS) for storing data, deploying AI models, and managing notifications efficiently. 4. Organic Farming Advisory Page: A dedicated section to promote organic and sustainable farming practices, helping farmers reduce dependency on chemical fertilizers and pesticides. Cloud platforms like AWS (S3, SageMaker) or Google Cloud (GCS, Cloud Run) will be used for scalable model deployment, while a database will maintain farmer records, disease history, and advisory logs. This project also emphasizes inclusivity and usability. Many farmers may not be technically skilled, so the interface will be designed with simplicity. The advisory will be aligned with government agricultural guidelines to ensure authenticity and trust. By providing a low-cost, accessible, and scalable system, the proposed solution will not only empower farmers to make better decisions but also contribute to food security, rural income stability, and sustainable farming practices. Key Features: ? AI-based disease detection from crop leaf images. ? Multilingual advisory (regional languages) for accessibility. ? Crop recommendation based on season, soil, and weather. ? Integration with cloud storage and analytics for scalability. ? Expert review mechanism for improved model accuracy and trust. ? Dedicated organic farming knowledge base for sustainable agriculture."}, {"id": "AI-071", "title": "\"AI-Based Disaster Alert & Resource Dashboard for One District (Flood Detection & Response)\"", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Vidhi Sood", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH6", "description": "The project aims to develop an AI-based flood alert and resource dashboard for a selected district using open satellite APIs (ISRO/NASA) and social media feeds. It will detect flood-prone areas through ML on satellite imagery, generate real-time alerts, and recommend rescue and resource allocation using a web dashboard connected via Firebase backend."}, {"id": "AI-072", "title": "A Comprehensive Evaluation of Multimodal Large Language Models Using Open-Source Datasets", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Dr.Varsha", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "we will evaluate open-source multimodal Large Language Models (LLMs) using publicly available datasets across various tasks such as image captioning, visual question answering, and document understanding. We will assess their performance in both zero-shot and fine-tuned settings, leveraging free computational resources for reproducibility. Our methodology includes dataset preprocessing, model selection, experimental design, and rigorous evaluation using standardized metrics. The goal is to establish a transparent and accessible benchmarking framework for multimodal LLMs."}, {"id": "AI-073", "title": "A Continual Learning Framework for Personalized Intent Modeling via Confidence-Adaptive Interaction and Memory Decay in Conversational AI Systems", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH25173", "supervisor": "Parminder Singh", "sitting_place": "27-203-CH6", "description": "Conversational AI systems have become integral to modern human--computer interaction, powering applications such as virtual assistants, customer support bots, and recommendation systems. Despite significant advancements, most existing systems rely on static intent models and lack the ability to continuously adapt to individual user behavior. This limitation often leads to misinterpretation of user intent, reduced personalization, and inconsistent response reliability. This research proposes a continual learning framework for conversational AI that integrates three key components: personalized intent modeling, confidence-adaptive interaction, and a memory decay (forgetting) mechanism. The system is designed to dynamically learn from user interactions over time, refining its understanding of user-specific intent patterns while maintaining robustness and adaptability. A central feature of the proposed approach is the use of confidence-aware decision-making, where the system evaluates the reliability of its predictions and adjusts its response strategy accordingly---either providing direct answers, requesting clarification, or confirming inferred intent. This mechanism aims to reduce ambiguity and improve user trust. To prevent overfitting and outdated personalization, the framework incorporates a memory decay mechanism, which gradually reduces the influence of older interactions. This ensures that the system remains responsive to evolving user preferences and avoids reliance on stale behavioral patterns. Overall, the proposed system seeks to bridge the gap between static conversational models and adaptive, human-like learning systems, enabling more accurate, reliable, and personalized interactions in real-world AI applications."}, {"id": "AI-074", "title": "A Deep Learning-Based Framework for Automated Backtesting and Strategy Optimization", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Anurag Tewari", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH14", "description": "The project titled, \"A Deep Learning-Based Framework for Automated Backtesting and Strategy Optimization,\" will attempt to disrupt the way traders could evaluate and improve their trading strategies. Professional traders will take a number of weeks or months to conduct manual backtesting using historical data, both of which are laborious and infused with human tendency to mitigate. We will use the power of deep learning, vectorized simulations, and optimization algorithms to automate the backtesting process and offer automated backtesting responses in near real-time. This toolkit will include realistic modeling of transaction cost, slippage, risk-adjusted performance metrics, and walk-forward validation. Additionally, this toolkit will have multi-objective optimization to maximize returns, minimize drawdown and reduce risk ratios, making it useful for a number of different trading styles. With the real-time processing turnaround, the framework could empower traders with rapid insecurities, enhance better judgment, and lessen systemic risk in the financial markets reducing both time and effort while increasing parametric prudence and realism. Finally, we bridge research level innovation and utility with an engaging, scalable, efficient, and trustworthy toolkit to trade."}, {"id": "AI-075", "title": "A Deep Retinex Network-Based Approach for Illumination Correction and Structure Preservation in Low-Light Lunar Images", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "This work is inspired by vision systems used in planetary exploration, where illumination-robust perception is critical for safe navigation and surface analysis.", "supervisor": "Dr. Ruby Singh", "sitting_place": "25-202-CH29", "description": "This work focuses on the development of a Deep Retinex-based framework for illumination correction of low-light lunar images. The work addresses challenges specific to extraterrestrial imaging, including extreme shadow regions, abrupt lighting transitions, low reflectance surfaces, and noise amplification under poor illumination. The study encompasses image decomposition into reflectance and illumination components, structure-preserving relighting, and quantitative evaluation using perceptual and statistical quality metrics. The framework is validated using curated lunar imagery under controlled experimental conditions. The scope is limited to software-based enhancement and does not include hardware-level sensor design or onboard deployment. The methodology is designed toward real mission datasets and space vision applications."}, {"id": "AI-076", "title": "A Federated Artificial Intelligence-Driven Intrusion Detection Framework for Secure Autonomous Vehicles", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Web of Science", "supervisor": "Dr. Komal Singh Gill", "sitting_place": "27-203-CH7", "description": "This research proposes a federated artificial intelligence--driven intrusion detection framework designed to enhance the security and resilience of autonomous vehicle networks. The framework leverages federated learning to enable collaborative model training across distributed vehicles while preserving data privacy. It aims to detect cyber threats such as spoofing, Byzantine, and CAN bus attacks in real time, improving robustness, scalability, and trust in connected autonomous vehicle ecosystems."}, {"id": "AI-077", "title": "A Holistic AI-Powered Virtual Fitness Coach for Real-time Form Correction and Adaptive Diet Planning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "AI-driven health and wellness solutions featured in Smart India Hackathon (SIH) 2024", "supervisor": "Dr. Ankita Wadhawan", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH16", "description": "The project titled \"A Holistic AI-Powered Virtual Fitness Coach for Real-time Form Correction and Adaptive Diet Planning\" focuses on creating an intelligent fitness and nutrition companion using artificial intelligence. Today, most fitness apps track only basic data like steps or calories but fail to guide users on correct workout form or provide personalized, adaptive meal plans. This leads to ineffective workouts, risk of injuries, and poor long-term results. The proposed system acts as a virtual personal trainer and nutritionist by integrating computer vision, deep learning, and data analytics. Using a webcam or smartphone camera, the AI model performs pose estimation to track body movements, detect incorrect exercise postures, and provide instant corrective feedback through visual or voice prompts. This ensures safer and more effective training sessions."}, {"id": "AI-078", "title": "A Light Gradient Boosting Model for Identification of Coronary Artery Disease", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Dr. Kewal Krishan", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH19", "description": "Coronary Artery Disease (CAD) is a major cause of death worldwide, caused by the narrowing of coronary arteries due to plaque buildup. Early detection is vital to prevent heart attacks and improve survival rates. Traditional diagnostic methods are often invasive, expensive, and time-consuming. With advancements in artificial intelligence, machine learning techniques like Light Gradient Boosting Machine (LightGBM) offer efficient and accurate alternatives for disease prediction. LightGBM is known for its speed, scalability, and ability to handle complex clinical data. This study aims to develop a LightGBM-based model that predicts CAD using patient attributes such as age, cholesterol, blood pressure, diabetes, and smoking status. The goal is to support healthcare professionals in early diagnosis and risk management of coronary artery disease."}, {"id": "AI-079", "title": "a machine learning- approach for crops", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "INTERNET", "supervisor": "Chetan Singh", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH32", "description": "Agriculture plays a critical role to Indian global economy and contributes a major part to GDP. With the expansion of the human population, it is necessary to maintain food security, it is achieved and controlled by the agricultural yield produced by the nation. The yield of a crop is mainly determined by the climatic conditions like temperature, rainfall, soil conditions, and fertilizers. Due to these variable factors, the production gets affected and remains a huge problem for the agricultural sector to strengthen the need for exactness for proper analyzing the crop production in variable climatic conditions. Recently, the machine learning algorithms are used by the researchers to predict the yield of a crop before its actual cultivation. This research study has proposed a machine learning algorithm: AdaBoost to predict the yield of crops based on the parameters like state, district, area, seasons, rainfall, temperature, and area. To enhance the yield, this research study also suggests a fertilizer based on the soil conditions like NPK values, soil type, soil PH, humidity, and moisture. Fertilizer recommendation is primarily done by using the Random Forest \\[RF\\] algorithm. The foundation of a developing nation like India is agriculture. The majority of the people rely on agriculture for income. Agriculture practises are being modernised today for the benefit of the farmers. An emerging area of informatics called machine learning can be used to great effect in the agriculture sector. For agricultural stakeholders, fertilizer recommendations and crop output forecasting are crucial. The weather, environmental changes, rainfall (which can be unpredictable at times), water management, and fertilizer use all have a significant impact on crop yield or production. These changeable factors have a negative impact on productivity, which makes it even more important to be precise when properly analyzing crop yield under changing climatic conditions. As a result, growers are unable to produce the crop's predicted yield. Today, a variety of researchers apply data mining, machine learning, and deep learning techniques to boost and improve crop productivity and quality. The proposed approach builds a collaborative system for predicting crop yield and recommending fertilizer. In this project, a system is created that uses agricultural datasets, where the Extra Trees Regressor algorithm is used to recommend the right production yield, and additionally, our suggested system employs fertilizer datasets, where the Gaussian NB algorithm is used to suggest the right fertilizer. Utilizing our proposed system for crop yield prediction and fertilizer recommendations would undoubtedly boost agricultural output. This approach supports decisions on fertilization that are beneficial to farmers. The accuracy of this system is around 99% for Crop yield prediction and 100% for fertilizer recommendation"}, {"id": "AI-080", "title": "A Novel Approach for Medical Image Encryption and Decryption Using Hybrid Deep Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "self", "supervisor": "Dr. Vikas Verma", "sitting_place": "26-201 A-WW1", "description": "To develop a hybrid deep-learning framework that integrates a privacy-aware medical image encryption/decryption pipeline with a DP-CRNN (Differential-Privacy Convolutional Recurrent Neural Network) model to perform intelligent online pre-diagnosis and department/medicine recommendation from patient queries. The system targets improved accuracy, privacy, and scalability for telemedicine applications."}, {"id": "AI-081", "title": "A novel approach for Skin Cancer Detection Using Deep Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Journals", "supervisor": "Dipen Saini", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "Skin cancer is one of the most prevalent and potentially life-threatening forms of cancer. Early detection plays a crucial role in improving survival rates. Traditional diagnostic methods rely on visual examination and biopsies, which can be time-consuming and prone to human error. This research aims to develop an automated deep learning-based approach for the early and accurate detection of skin cancer. By leveraging convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and other deep learning architectures, the study intends to detect and classify different types of skin lesions with high precision, thereby assisting dermatologists in making accurate diagnoses."}, {"id": "AI-082", "title": "A Sequential Pattern Learning Framework for Animal-Centric Surveillance and Motion Analysis", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH 2025 Problem statement number SIH25167", "supervisor": "Dr. Madhu Bala", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH9", "description": "Road accidents involving animals have become a significant concern, especially in rural and highway environments, leading to loss of animal life and posing risks to human safety. Existing surveillance and motion detection systems are primarily designed for human-centric applications and often fail to accurately detect and interpret animal movements in real-world conditions. Challenges such as low-light environments, occlusions, and varying backgrounds further reduce the effectiveness of traditional systems.Recent advancements in motion analysis have introduced hybrid approaches that combine techniques such as deep learning, optical flow, and object detection frameworks. Although these methods improve activity recognition, they often suffer from high computational complexity, limited real-time applicability, and poor generalization across diverse environments, particularly for animal motion scenarios. To overcome these limitations, this research proposes a hybrid spatio-temporal motion analysis framework that integrates spatial and temporal feature learning with motion feature extraction techniques. The proposed system aims to provide efficient, real-time detection and improved accuracy, thereby enhancing early detection of animal movement on roads and contributing to safer transportation environments."}, {"id": "AI-083", "title": "A Smart and Sustainable Framework for Millet Crop Monitoring Equipped with Disease Detection Using Enhanced Predictive Intelligence", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Review", "source": "Smart crop advisory system for small and marginal farmers, Government of Punjab", "supervisor": "Dr. Tanima Thakur", "sitting_place": "27-205-CH10", "description": "This project develops a software based intelligent system of millet disease detection using image analysis. The application uses machine learning algorithms to process the images of the leaves to detect diseases such as blast and rust in real-time using a lightweight predictive model. It adds visual explanations of affected areas for helping users understand and make decisions. The system does not require cloud infrastructure for efficient operation, and mechanisms to operate effectively and quickly, and to be accessible. By facilitating identification in the early stages, it facilitates the decrease in the use of pesticides and aims at the decrease of losses in agricultural crops, encouraging sustainable agricultural practices."}, {"id": "AI-084", "title": "A Smart Crop Advisory System for Small and Marginal Farmers", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Tushar Kasana", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH36", "description": "SCAS is an IoT + ML advisory system for small-scale Indian farmers. ESP32 sensors monitor soil moisture, temperature, and humidity, feeding data to a cloud pipeline where Random Forest, LSTM, and CNN models generate crop, irrigation, weather, and disease advisories. Delivered via a multilingual app or SMS, the system achieved 92.8% crop-recommendation accuracy and 91.7% disease detection accuracy, with 6.1s average response time."}, {"id": "AI-085", "title": "A smart crop selection system using Machine Learning models", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2025 (SIH25010)", "supervisor": "Dr. Avnish Thakur", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH10", "description": "The proposed project aims to develop a Smart Crop Selection System that leverages Machine Learning (ML) techniques to recommend the most suitable crops for a region. In the first phase, relevant agricultural datasets will be identified and analyzed to determine the most significant features influencing crop suitability. The second phase focuses on training and testing various machine learning algorithms to identify the model that delivers the highest prediction accuracy and generalization capability. The methodology, model evaluation, and findings will be presented in the form of a research paper."}, {"id": "AI-086", "title": "A Unified Deep Learning Framework for Segmentation-Aware Classification Using ROI-Based Feature Extraction", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Online research surveys", "supervisor": "Dr. Karandeep Kaur", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH12", "description": "To develop and evaluate a unified deep learning framework that leverages a fine-tuned segmentation model for precise image segmentation, with the aim of improving the performance of subsequent classification or prediction tasks in real-time domain-specific applications. The proposed framework will incorporate a segmentation-aware classification pipeline in which segmentation model-generated masks are utilized to isolate the Region of Interest (ROI), thereby reducing background noise. The extracted ROI-based features will then be fed into advanced deep learning classifiers to enhance overall classification accuracy and robustness."}, {"id": "AI-087", "title": "Adaptive Multiscale CNN for Smart Traffic Management", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "Real-Time Public Transport Tracking for Small Cities, SIH25013", "supervisor": "Deepali Kumari( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This project aims to develop an AI-driven smart traffic surveillance system using an Adaptive Multiscale CNN. The model processes live traffic feeds to detect vehicles, congestion, and anomalies in real-time. Integrated with a cloud dashboard, it provides traffic analytics, density heatmaps, and alerts, assisting authorities in efficient traffic control and urban mobility planning."}, {"id": "AI-088", "title": "Adaptive Streaming-Aware Spatio-Temporal Graph Attention Network (AS-STGAT) for Real-Time Traffic Flow Prediction", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH25050 : Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Yatika Hasija", "sitting_place": "26-205-CH11", "description": "This project proposes AS-STGAT, a streaming-aware spatio-temporal graph neural network for real-time traffic flow prediction. It dynamically updates graph structure using live sensor correlations, detects concept drift using Page-Hinkley, and adapts via Elastic Weight Consolidation. The system integrates with Kafka-Flink pipelines to achieve low-latency (\\<100 ms) predictions in streaming environments."}, {"id": "AI-089", "title": "Adaptive Video Question Answering: A Hybrid RAG Approach Using Vector Embeddings and Knowledge Graphs", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Dr. Ravindra Singh Yadav", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH12", "description": "Adaptive Video Question Answering using a hybrid RAG approach combines vector embeddings and knowledge graphs to improve how systems understand and answer questions from video content. In this approach, videos are first processed by extracting audio, text (via speech-to-text), and visual information such as frames or captions. This extracted data is then transformed into vector embeddings using models like BERT or CLIP, which enable semantic search by finding content that is contextually similar to a user's query. At the same time, a knowledge graph is constructed by identifying entities, concepts, and relationships present in the video data. This structured representation helps the system understand connections and perform logical reasoning. When a user asks a question, the hybrid RAG framework retrieves relevant information from both the vector database (for semantic similarity) and the knowledge graph (for relational context). This combined information is then provided to a language model such as GPT to generate accurate, context-aware answers. By integrating both unstructured and structured retrieval methods, this approach enhances answer accuracy, improves explainability, and enables deeper understanding of complex video content, making it suitable for applications like education, video search, and intelligent analytics."}, {"id": "AI-090", "title": "AgriAid: AI-Powered Crop Health Assistant Using Voice and Image Analysis", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Abhinav Singh", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH11", "description": "AgriAid: AI-Powered Crop Health Assistant Using Voice and Image Analysis\" is an intelligent agricultural support system designed to help farmers monitor and manage crop health efficiently. The system allows users to describe crop symptoms through voice input or capture images of affected plants for real-time disease detection and diagnosis. Using deep learning for image analysis and natural language processing (NLP) for voice interaction, AgriAid identifies crop diseases and suggests suitable treatments such as fertilizers, pesticides, or organic remedies. Featuring a user-friendly, multilingual interface, the system ensures accessibility for farmers of varying literacy levels. Powered by AI models trained on extensive agricultural datasets, it delivers accurate, reliable results and can be integrated with cloud services for continuous model updates. By combining AI, voice recognition, and image processing, AgriAid enables timely disease management, improves crop yields, and promotes sustainable farming practices, making advanced agricultural assistance more accessible to all."}, {"id": "AI-091", "title": "AgriMindX 2025: AI-Driven Intelligent Crop Recommendation & Climate-Resilient Farming System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "1.Smart India Hackathon (SIH) 2025 -- Agriculture & Sustainability Track. 2 Government of India's Digital Agriculture Mission 2025 and IndiaAI Mission 2025. 3 United Nations Sustainable Development Goals (SDG-2 & SDG-13) emphasizing zero hunger and climate action.4. Emerging need in 2025 for AI-powered, market-integrated agri-tech solutions that solve food security and farmer livelihood challenges.", "supervisor": "Isha", "sitting_place": "26-205-CH6", "description": "AgriMindX 2025 is an AI-powered crop recommendation and climate-resilient farming system that integrates soil analytics, IoT sensors, satellite weather data, and market intelligence to suggest the most profitable and sustainable crops. Unlike existing models, it personalize recommendations for each farmer, enabling climate-smart decisions, improving yields, and fostering eco-friendly agriculture fit for 2025 and beyond."}, {"id": "AI-092", "title": "AgriMind-X: AI-based crop recommendation and farming decision system", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Ha kathin 2025 (SIH25030)", "supervisor": "Ravi Kant Sahu", "sitting_place": "27-205-CH8", "description": "AgriMind-X is an AI-based system designed to help farmers make better decisions for crop selection and farming practices. The system uses machine learning algorithms to recommend suitable crops based on soil parameters such as nitrogen (N), phosphorus (P), potassium (K), pH, and environmental factors like temperature, humidity, and rainfall. The project also includes additional modules like seasonal analysis, fertilizer recommendation, irrigation planning, and climate risk prediction to provide complete farming guidance. A location-based dataset is used to improve the accuracy of recommendations for specific regions. The system is further enhanced with an AI-based assistant that allows users to interact in a simple way and get explanations for the recommendations."}, {"id": "AI-093", "title": "AgriPredict: ML-Driven Irrigation, Fertilizer & Sowing Recommendations", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH25044", "supervisor": "Ishika", "sitting_place": "27-207-CH17", "description": "Generate actionable recommendations for optimal resource utilization, including irrigation schedules, fertilizer application, and sowing times, to enhance productivity while minimizing environmental impact. Develop a voice-to-text system that allows farmers to interact with the prediction tool in their regional languages, removing literacy barriers and making AI insights directly usable in the field."}, {"id": "AI-094", "title": "AgriVision -- Integrated Smart Farming Support Platform", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart Crop Advisory System for Small and Marginal Farmers (Theme Agriculture, FoodTech & Rural Development)", "supervisor": "Deepali Kumari( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "Agriculture remains the backbone of India, yet many farmers still struggle with limited access to reliable information and modern decision-support tools. Challenges such as unpredictable weather, lack of crop health awareness, ineffective soil nutrient management, difficulty identifying plant diseases, and uncertainty in market pricing directly affect productivity and profit. Due to this, most farmers rely on assumptions, middlemen guidance, and conventional methods, which may not always lead to optimal outcomes. AgriVision is an AI-integrated web platform designed to support farmers throughout the farming lifecycle by offering smart, data-driven recommendations in a simple and accessible way. The platform is built to work efficiently on smartphones and in local languages, making it suitable for small and marginal farmers. The Weather Status module provides real-time and forecasted weather insights to help farmers plan irrigation, fertilizer application, and harvest timing. The Crop Explorer and Plant Finder tools help farmers identify suitable crop varieties based on region, season, and soil type. Through the Soil Diagnostics and Soil Insights modules, farmers can input basic soil information such as pH value and NPK levels. The system analyzes this data and recommends accurate fertilizer doses and watering schedules to maintain soil health and reduce unnecessary resource usage. The Fertilizer Finder additionally suggests cost-effective and locally available fertilizer options. Disease Detection enables farmers to upload images of affected leaves or plants directly from their mobile camera. The AI model detects symptoms and suggests treatment solutions, including organic and chemical control methods. This helps prevent crop loss and reduces excessive pesticide use. The Crop Advisor component provides personalized cultivation guidance, covering sowing time, spacing, irrigation intervals, and pest prevention tips for specific crops. The Crop Road Map guides farmers step-by-step from sowing to harvesting. To improve earning potential, Price Forecast and Market Trends help farmers stay informed about market demand and price fluctuations. Farmers can decide the best time and location to sell their produce, reducing dependency on middlemen and improving income stability. Additionally, the platform includes a Voice-to-Search feature that allows easy navigation and usage for farmers who are not comfortable typing or reading extensively. By integrating AI with practical field knowledge, AgriVision empowers farmers to make informed decisions that improve crop yield, reduce losses, optimize input usage, and enhance profitability. The platform promotes sustainable, smart, and accessible agriculture for all."}, {"id": "AI-095", "title": "AgroSoil AI: Predictive Soil Analysis for Sustainable Crop Planning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Investigative research about grievance filing and management", "supervisor": "Dr. Neeta Rana", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH5", "description": "This project develops an AI-based crop recommendation system that suggests the most suitable crops for farmers using soil nutrients, weather conditions, pH, rainfall, soil color, and acidity or alkalinity. The model analyzes field data and predicts the best crop option to improve yield, reduce input cost, and support sustainable farming decisions through data-driven recommendations."}, {"id": "AI-096", "title": "AI Based crop Recommendation for farmers", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "SIH 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Suchi Jain", "sitting_place": "36-307-CH17", "description": "India's agricultural landscape is defined by diversity in soil profiles, climate conditions, and crop markets, yet millions of farmers remain dependent on generic advice that fails to capture the unique complexities of their fields. This lack of personalized guidance contributes to poor yields, unsustainable resource use, and economic uncertainty, particularly among small and marginal farmers. Our capstone project, \"AI-Based Crop Recommendation for Farmers,\" formulates the core problem as designing a scalable, data-driven solution that transforms how crop decisions are made. The project centres on developing a web-based platform that harnesses machine learning to generate customized crop recommendations. Users input essential field parameters---soil pH, nutrient content, moisture---while the system also ingests local weather forecasts and real-time market information. By training and benchmarking algorithms like Random Forests and Decision Trees on curated crop datasets, we ensure our predictions are both accurate and interpretable for practical use. A defining feature of our approach is its dual focus: alongside maximizing crop yield and profitability, each recommendation is scored for sustainability in alignment with key United Nations Sustainable Development Goals. This integration encourages farmers to make choices that are not only economically rewarding but also environmentally responsible. To maximize accessibility and impact, the application offers a multilingual, responsive interface that works on any device. The \"API-first\" architecture ensures future scalability to mobile platforms. Through iterative development and real-world testing, we deliver a solution that empowers Indian farmers with scientific, actionable insight---paving the way for resilient, sustainable agriculture."}, {"id": "AI-097", "title": "AI BASED CROP RECOMMENDATION FOR FARMERS", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Mehvish Firdous", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH19", "description": "The AI-based crop recommendation system is designed to assist farmers in making informed decisions regarding crop selection. By analyzing soil nutrient levels, weather conditions, and historical yield data, the system can suggest the most suitable crops for cultivation in a particular region. The platform aims to be farmer-friendly, providing recommendations in multiple languages and integrating real-time APIs for weather and market prices."}, {"id": "AI-098", "title": "AI based Lung Cancer Detection using Deep Learning on Medical Imaging Data", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon - theme MedTech / BioTech / HealthTech", "supervisor": "Gunseerat Kaur", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH29", "description": "This project aims to develop an AI based system for lung cancer detection using deep learning techniques on CT scan images. The system will incorporate explainability methods to provide insights into model predictions, improving interpretability and reliability. The objective is to achieve accurate classification while enhancing trust in automated medical diagnosis."}, {"id": "AI-099", "title": "AI Based Mental Health Monitoring System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Dr. Janpreet Singh", "sitting_place": "28-202-C3", "description": "The AI Mental Health Monitoring System leverages AI-driven multimodal analysis to detect mental health conditions such as stress, anxiety, and depression in individuals. It collects data from live video, audio, facial expressions, and behavioral patterns during working hours. Using machine learning models, the system analyzes these inputs to assess activity levels, vocal tone, and facial cues. It generates real-time emotional scores, stress alerts, and personalized wellness feedback, along with dashboard insights that track mental health trends over time."}, {"id": "CLD-004", "title": "AI Based pipeline for Automated Error Detection in Cloud Computing Servers", "category": "Cloud Computing", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "Google Scholar", "supervisor": "Isha", "sitting_place": "28-204-CH9", "description": "The proposed research on \\*\\*AI-Based Pipeline for Automated Error Detection in Cloud Computing Servers\\*\\* focuses on designing an intelligent, scalable, and efficient system that enhances the reliability and performance of modern cloud infrastructures. With the rapid growth of cloud services, managing server errors in real time has become a critical challenge. Traditional monitoring approaches are often reactive, manual, and inefficient when dealing with large-scale distributed systems. This research aims to address these limitations by integrating artificial intelligence into automated monitoring and error detection processes. The first objective is to \\*\\*develop an intelligent error detection model\\*\\* capable of identifying anomalies and failures in cloud servers proactively. This model leverages machine learning and deep learning techniques to analyze system logs, performance metrics, and network activity patterns. By learning from historical data, the model can detect unusual behaviors such as sudden spikes in CPU usage, memory leaks, or abnormal request patterns. Unlike rule-based systems, the AI model adapts over time, improving its accuracy and reducing false positives. This ensures early detection of potential issues before they escalate into critical failures. The second objective is to \\*\\*build a scalable and automated monitoring pipeline\\*\\* that integrates seamlessly with cloud environments. The pipeline is designed to collect, process, and analyze large volumes of real-time data generated by distributed servers. Technologies such as stream processing, microservices architecture, and containerization can be utilized to ensure scalability and flexibility. Automation plays a key role in reducing human intervention by enabling continuous monitoring, automated alert generation, and intelligent decision-making. This pipeline ensures that the system can handle increasing workloads efficiently without compromising performance. The third objective is to \\*\\*improve system reliability and response time\\*\\*, which are crucial factors in cloud computing. By detecting errors early and automating responses, the system minimizes downtime and enhances service availability. Faster response times are achieved through real-time analysis and automated remediation strategies, such as restarting services or reallocating resources. This not only improves user experience but also reduces operational costs associated with manual troubleshooting and system failures. Overall, this research contributes to the advancement of intelligent cloud management systems by combining AI with automation and scalable architecture. The proposed solution aligns strongly with SDG 9: Industry, Innovation and Infrastructure by promoting innovation in digital infrastructure, and also supports SDG 7: Affordable and Clean Energy and SDG 13: Climate Action by optimizing resource utilization and reducing energy consumption in data centers. The outcome of this work is expected to provide a robust, adaptive, and efficient framework for automated error detection and management in cloud computing environments."}, {"id": "AI-100", "title": "AI Driven Public Health Chatbot for Disease Awareness", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "https://www.sih.gov.in/sih2025PS (PS ID -- SIH25049)", "supervisor": "Harshpreet Kaur", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH19", "description": "This AI-powered chatbot aims to enhance disease awareness among the public by delivering accurate health information, prevention guidelines, early symptom detection support, and disease knowledge dissemination. The chatbot utilizes NLP and AI models to interact with users, understand their symptoms or queries, and provide relevant public health guidance. It helps reduce misinformation, improves public health knowledge, and assists communities in understanding disease risks and preventive measures."}, {"id": "AI-101", "title": "AI- DRIVEN PUBLIC HEALTH CHATBOT FOR DISEASE AWARENESS", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Isha Bhatia", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH7", "description": "This project aims to develop a lightweight, offline-first mobile application to empower ASHA workers and PHC staff in rural India. The app will securely store patient data offline, support voice-based inputs with NLP, provide AI-powered health risk predictions, generate intelligent vaccination and antenatal care reminders, and sync automatically when internet connectivity is available. It will feature multilingual support, a chatbot assistant for ASHA workers, and role-based dashboards for efficient healthcare delivery."}, {"id": "AI-102", "title": "AI enabled Smart Application to Boost Fitness Activities and Assist in Keeping Fit.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Bharat Sharma", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH33", "description": "This project is a student innovation idea that can boost fitness activities and assist in keeping fit. The solution will be in the form of a comprehensive fitness application that leverages AI and smart data analytics to encourage daily workouts, track progress, and enhance user motivation through goal-based recommendations and gamified rewards. To design a data-driven system workflow that ensures smooth fitness tracking which will take input as User profile, daily activity, and health data and give output as Tailored fitness/diet plans, performance analytics, and motivational insights. This workflow promotes intelligent automation and continuous user engagement. This will integrate Artificial Intelligence (AI) that analyze user activity patterns, health metrics, and preferences to provide personalized workout plans, adaptive diet suggestions, and real-time feedback for performance improvement. Additionally, an AI chatbot or virtual fitness coach will guide users through exercises, answer fitness-related queries, and keep them motivated."}, {"id": "AI-103", "title": "AI Interviewer - Online AI-based Mock Interview Platform", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr.Varun Dogra", "sitting_place": "55-302-C3", "description": "In the current recruitment landscape, interview preparation remains one of the most critical yet underserved aspects of student placement and professional development. Traditional mock interviews are often manual, time-consuming, and inconsistent, relying heavily on human evaluators who may have biases or limited availability. While there are numerous online learning and test preparation tools, there is a significant gap in intelligent, AI-driven mock interview platforms that can provide a realistic, adaptive, and data-based interview experience. Existing tools usually assess only textual answers or resume content - they fail to simulate a real interview environment where a candidate's facial expressions, tone, confidence, and body language play a key role. Moreover, institutions struggle to offer individualized feedback to large batches of students during placement drives. Hence, there is a clear need for an AI-powered virtual interviewer that combines automation, personalization, and analytics to enhance interview readiness."}, {"id": "AI-104", "title": "AI powered conversational agents for enhanced customer support", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "google scholar", "supervisor": "Rakshit Bansal( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "AI-powered conversational agents, such as chatbots and virtual assistants, are transforming customer support by providing fast and automated responses to user queries. These systems use technologies like Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Machine Learning (ML) to understand and respond to human language in a natural way."}, {"id": "AI-105", "title": "AI Powered Personalized Learning Path Generator", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25199", "supervisor": "Abdul Malik Ansari", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH18", "description": "integrated issue from both emotional cognitive and decision making confusion in students. It combines Edge AI, IoT monitoring, mulitmodal sensing and skill gap mapping."}, {"id": "AI-106", "title": "AI Smart Crop Advisory System for Small and Marginal Farm", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2025 ( Problem Statement ID: 25070)", "supervisor": "Mallepalli Gautham( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This project aims to develop an AI-powered integrated advisory system that supports small and marginal farmers in making smarter, data-driven farming decisions. The system combines image processing, speech recognition, and predictive analytics to deliver precise, personalized crop management recommendations. Firstly, the system includes a dual-input disease detection model that accepts both image and speech inputs from farmers. A farmer can either upload a picture of a diseased crop leaf or describe symptoms verbally (e.g., \"leaves turning yellow\"). The AI model uses a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) for image analysis and a speech-to-text NLP model for symptom interpretation. Together, these enable accurate disease identification and provide treatment suggestions in real time, making it accessible even to farmers with limited literacy or technical skills. Secondly, an AI-based fertilizer advisory module is designed to recommend safe and effective fertilizer combinations. It analyzes soil pH, nutrient levels, and crop requirements to prevent the use of harmful or incompatible fertilizers while ensuring balanced nutrient supply. The system generates optimized fertilizer dosages and highlights eco-friendly alternatives, reducing input costs and environmental damage. Finally, the system integrates an AI-driven crop spacing and nutrient optimization model. By analyzing soil characteristics, moisture content, and crop type, the model recommends the ideal planting distance and nutrient dosage for each field. It helps farmers achieve maximum yield, better nutrient absorption, and improved soil health by minimizing overcrowding and nutrient competition among plants. Together, these modules create a comprehensive AI Smart Crop Advisory System that empowers farmers with precise disease diagnosis, safe fertilizer planning, and intelligent crop spacing recommendations. The project enhances productivity, reduces waste, and promotes sustainable farming --- all through an easy-to-use interface compatible with mobile or web applications in local languages."}, {"id": "AI-107", "title": "AI SmartCattle: Classification System-Based Animal Type Recognition", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH 25004 : Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Arshiya", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH6", "description": "India is home to a rich diversity of cattle and buffalo breeds, each with unique genetic, physical, and economic traits. These breeds differ in milk production, growth rate, disease resistance, adaptability, and other characteristics, which directly influence livestock management, breeding programs, insurance claims, and policy planning. Accurate identification of breeds is therefore critical for farmers, veterinarians, and government authorities to make informed decisions about breeding, health management, and resource allocation. Traditionally, breed identification relies on manual observation, requiring trained experts to analyze physical features such as coat color, body size, horn shape, and other morphological traits. While this method can be effective, it is time-consuming, prone to human error, and often inaccessible in remote areas where expert knowledge may be limited. Furthermore, in the modern era, there is an increasing demand for digital solutions that enable automated, real-time, and scalable livestock monitoring. The SIH25004 problem statement addresses these challenges by proposing the development of an AI-powered image recognition system capable of automatically identifying the breed of cattle and buffaloes from images or videos. This system would leverage computer vision and deep learning techniques, particularly Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), to analyze visual features, classify breeds, and provide accurate results under varying conditions such as different lighting, angles, and partial visibility. This project is interdisciplinary, bridging the domains of Artificial Intelligence, Computer Vision, Agriculture, Animal Husbandry, Agricultural Economics, and Extension Services. Technologically, it involves image preprocessing, feature extraction, model training, and deployment through web or mobile applications. Agriculturally, it supports farmers and policymakers by enabling breed-specific management, improving productivity, and facilitating insurance and subsidy schemes."}, {"id": "AI-108", "title": "AI/ML-Driven Outbreak Prediction for Water-Borne Diseases", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH 2025 PS 25001: Ministry of Development of Northeastern Region (MoDoNER)", "supervisor": "Bhanu Talwar", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH14", "description": "Develop an AI/ML system to forecast water-borne disease outbreaks (like Cholera/Typhoid) 1-3 weeks in advance. It integrates time-series health data with environmental features (rainfall, water quality, temperature) using advanced models (LSTMs/XGBoost). The goal is a highly accurate, deployable early warning model and an interactive geospatial dashboard for proactive public health intervention."}, {"id": "AI-109", "title": "AI-BASED CROP & PROFITABILITY ADVISORY SYSTEM", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Al-Based Crop Recommendation for Farmers ( PS No- SIH25030 )", "supervisor": "Dr. Mohit Arora", "sitting_place": "28-202-C1", "description": "The AI-Based Crop & Profitability Advisory System is a full-stack web platform that helps farmers make data-driven decisions. By combining soil inputs, weather data, and machine learning models, it predicts crop yield, estimates profitability, and recommends fertilizers. The system delivers results through an intuitive dashboard designed for easy farmer use."}, {"id": "AI-110", "title": "AI-Based Crop Recommendation & Farmer Advisory Platform", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Enjula Uchoi", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH9", "description": "This project outlines the development of a comprehensive mobile and web application designed to empower farmers with data-driven insights for enhanced agricultural productivity and sustainability. The platform, \"Agri Advisory AI,\" will act as a digital agronomist, providing personalized crop recommendations and real-time advisory services to help farmers make informed decisions and optimize their farming practices. The primary objective is to bridge the knowledge gap often faced by small and medium scale farmers, leading to increased crop yields, reduced resource waste, and improved livelihoods. At the heart of the application lies a sophisticated machine learning model that serves as the crop recommendation engine. This model will be trained on a vast dataset comprising key agricultural parameters, including soil nutrient levels (Nitrogen, Phosphorus, Potassium), pH balance, geographical location, and historical crop performance data. By allowing farmers to input their specific soil and land information, the system will analyze these variables against a database of viable crops. It will then generate a prioritized list of crops that are most likely to thrive in their unique conditions, thereby minimizing the risk of crop failure and maximizing potential profitability."}, {"id": "AI-111", "title": "AI-Based Crop Recommendation for Farmers", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "HACKATHON", "supervisor": "Lalit Verma", "sitting_place": "27-207-CH15", "description": "This project uses Artificial Intelligence and IoT to recommend the most suitable crops for farmers based on soil type, pH, rainfall, temperature, and climatic conditions. Machine Learning models like Decision Tree and Random Forest are trained on FAO and ICAR datasets, while IoT sensors provide real-time soil and weather data. The system delivers accurate, data-driven crop recommendations through an easy-to-use web application, improving productivity and sustainability."}, {"id": "AI-112", "title": "AI-Based Crop Yield Forecasting Using Climate and Environmental Data", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "IEEE", "supervisor": "Sakshi", "sitting_place": "27-203-CH5", "description": "This project proposes the development of an AI based system for predicting crop yield using climate, soil, and remote sensing data. The system will use historical crop yield records together with climate variables such as temperature, rainfall, humidity, and solar radiation obtained from publicly available sources. Additional datasets such as soil properties and satellite derived vegetation indices (e.g., NDVI) will also be integrated. The collected datasets will be preprocessed, cleaned, and aligned spatially and temporally. Feature engineering will be performed to compute climate indices such as growing degree days and drought indicators. A deep learning model (such as an LSTM, CNN, or multimodal neural network) will then be trained using these inputs to learn the relationship between environmental conditions and crop productivity. The model will be validated using historical data to measure prediction accuracy, and once trained, the system will generate yield predictions for upcoming seasons based on current climate conditions. The system may also provide early warnings when predicted yield falls below expected thresholds. A simple web interface will be developed to visualize predicted yields and climate trends and to support decision making. The overall objective is to support farmers, researchers, and policymakers in planning agricultural activities and improving food security. The project will rely primarily on publicly available datasets to ensure reproducibility. Climate aware modelling improves prediction accuracy by explicitly incorporating weather variability and long term climate patterns into yield forecasting."}, {"id": "AI-113", "title": "AI-Based Early Detection and Classification of Lung Cancer from Chest CT/X-Ray Using Deep Learning and Self-Supervised Models", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2024 (Adapted from SIH1547 -- Angiography Imaging: Medical Imaging Diagnosis)", "supervisor": "Dr. Bhupinder Singh", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH8", "description": "This project aims to design an AI-driven diagnostic system capable of early detection and classification of lung cancer using chest CT and X-ray images. Leveraging deep learning architectures such as CNNs and Vision Transformers, the model will identify and categorize pulmonary nodules as benign or malignant. Self-supervised learning and ensemble techniques will be explored to enhance performance under limited labeled data scenarios, enabling reliable early screening support for clinicians."}, {"id": "AI-114", "title": "AI-Based Personalized Diet Recommendation System using Machine Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Healthcare + Technology Trend Based", "supervisor": "Atul Kumar Kaithal", "sitting_place": "27-204-CH8", "description": "This project develops a machine learning-based system that analyzes parameters like age, BMI, glucose, cholesterol, lifestyle, and food cuisine preferences to generate personalized diet plans. Unlike traditional systems, it offers dynamic, data-driven recommendations through a real-time, user-friendly application, making diet planning more practical and tailored to individual needs."}, {"id": "AI-115", "title": "AI-Based Public Health Guidance System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH25049", "supervisor": "Ishika", "sitting_place": "27-207-CH17", "description": "Understands user queries in simple language or regional languages. Provides information on symptoms, preventive measures, treatment options, and vaccination schedules. Allows users to ask questions conversationally and receive real-time responses. Supports multiple languages for wider accessibility, reducing literacy barriers. Tracks most asked questions, common concerns, and user engagement trends."}, {"id": "AI-116", "title": "AI-Based Smart Traffic Optimization for Urban Mobility", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Karan Kumar( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "Smart Traffic Optimization for Urban Mobility (STOUM) is an AI-driven solution designed to optimize traffic flow, reduce congestion, and enhance urban mobility using real-time data analysis and predictive modeling. The system leverages machine learning algorithms, sensor and API data, and an interactive dashboard to monitor, analyze, and control traffic conditions dynamically. Modern cities face increasing congestion due to the rapid rise in vehicles, poor traffic coordination, and static signal systems that do not adapt to real-time conditions. Traditional systems often rely on fixed timers and manual intervention, leading to inefficiencies during peak hours, emergencies, or special events. The Smart Traffic Management System overcomes these challenges by integrating IoT, AI, and data analytics to create an intelligent ecosystem that can: Predict congestion levels before they occur. Dynamically control traffic signals. Prioritize emergency and public transport. Provide actionable insights to city authorities. Through its web-based interface, traffic administrators can monitor live traffic conditions, identify bottlenecks, and take automated or manual actions based on AI recommendations."}, {"id": "AI-117", "title": "AI-based soil composition analysis system for the nutrient availability", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon (SIH) 2025", "supervisor": "Raghu Raja Sharma", "sitting_place": "34-202-CH8", "description": "Soil nutrient imbalance is a major challenge faced by farmers across India. Traditional soil testing methods are time-consuming, expensive, and require technical expertise, which makes them inaccessible for many small and medium-scale farmers. This leads to incorrect fertilizer use, poor crop yield, and long-term soil degradation. The AI-based Soil Composition Analysis System aims to revolutionize soil testing by using artificial intelligence and data analytics to automatically analyse soil composition and evaluate nutrient availability. The system will use soil sensor data or uploaded lab test reports to determine the levels of essential nutrients such as Nitrogen (N), Phosphorus (P), and Potassium (K), along with micro-nutrients like Sulphur, Zinc, and Iron. Based on the analysed data, it will generate crop-specific fertilizer and treatment recommendations, helping farmers optimize yield and minimize wastage. The solution will consist of three major components: 1. Farmer-facing mobile/web application for uploading soil data, images, or test results, and receiving instant fertilizer recommendations. 2. AI-powered analytical engine that interprets soil data and predicts deficiencies using machine learning models trained on agricultural datasets. 3. Cloud-based backend system for scalable deployment, storage of soil records, and continuous model improvement through feedback. Additionally, the interface will support regional languages and provide simple graphical visualizations to ensure usability for all farmers. Integration with weather APIs and government agricultural databases will make recommendations more accurate and localized. This system promotes smart farming practices, reduces environmental pollution caused by over-fertilization, and ensures sustainable agricultural productivity"}, {"id": "AI-118", "title": "AI-based system for plant disease detection, severity analysis, and intelligent pesticide recommendation using deep learning and computer vision.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Ajay Kumar Badhan", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH31", "description": "Farmers lack efficient tools to detect plant diseases early and do not receive severity-based treatment guidance Plant diseases significantly reduce crop yield, and farmers often rely on manual inspection, which is slow and inaccurate. Existing AI systems detect diseases but do not provide severity analysis or actionable treatment recommendations, leading to improper pesticide usage and reduced productivity."}, {"id": "AI-119", "title": "AI-Based Underwater Image Enhancement System for Increased Maritime Security.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH25243", "supervisor": "Mohit Dewangan", "sitting_place": "27-209-CH12", "description": "Underwater environments pose significant challenges for image quality because of light absorption that depends on wavelength, where red light is rapidly absorbed, leading to a dominance of bluish-green tones. Additional deterioration arises from particle scattering and water currents, greatly impacting vital maritime security tasks such as immediate coastal monitoring, border protection, and anomaly detection (e.g., detecting submarines, mines, drones, or divers). Traditional methods like histogram equalization or basic filtering often struggle to address the complex degradations encountered underwater, such as haze, low contrast, and color distortion, frequently creating artifacts that reduce their reliability for defense applications. The objective is to develop an AI-driven system that manages unprocessed underwater images or videos to boost clarity, enhance features, and aid in later applications like threat identification, while operating in constrained environments, like edge devices on AUVs or ROVs. The system needs to improve visibility, contrast, and clarity to guarantee reliable performance in various underwater conditions, encompassing different water salinities, turbidity levels (ranging from clear to very turbid), and illumination situations (natural light, dim light, or artificial sources). It needs to function in almost real-time to assist with live monitoring and reconnaissance, allowing defense staff to make quick, informed choices. The solution should assist in applications like object detection and classification, guaranteeing that enhanced images increase the precision of recognizing threats such as submarines or mines etc. Resilience is crucial for handling diverse oceanic situations without being adapted to particular settings, and the system needs to offer understandable results, like confidence scores or visual clarifications, to enhance operator trust. By tackling these issues, the solution will enhance the effectiveness of maritime security operations, aiding India's defense strategy and autonomy in essential technologies."}, {"id": "AI-120", "title": "AI-Driven Approaches for Milk Adulteration Detection: A Comprehensive Review", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Review", "source": "Reserch Papers", "supervisor": "Dr. Gurbinder Singh Brar", "sitting_place": "34-203-C3", "description": "Milk adulteration is a critical issue affecting public health, necessitating the development of accurate and efficient detection techniques. This study presents a detailed review and comparative analysis of recent advancements in deep learning and machine learning approaches for detecting milk adulteration. The research examines algorithms such as CNNs, LSTM, Artificial Neural Networks, Gated Recurrent Units (GRUs), and Hybrid Blended Deep Learning Models (HyBDL) which integrate CNN, CNN-LSTM, and CNN-GRU. Furthermore, machine learning models such as XGBoost, RandomForestAlgorithm(RF), K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN), and CatBoost are analyzed in conjunction with hyperspectral imaging, PCAM-ResNet50, and MALDI-MS-based methods. The comparative study highlights that CNN and hybrid deep learning architectures achieve high accuracy in image-based adulteration detection, while machine learning models effectively analyze tabular data derived from spectroscopy and sensor-based techniques. Raman spectroscopy, although not AI-based, is essential for detecting microplastics in dairy products. The findings indicate that combining techniques in deep learning and machine learning. can enhance adulteration detection accuracy, offering a scalable and robust solution for ensuring dairy quality and consumer safety. Future research should focus on integrating AI with portable sensor-based solutions for real-time monitoring of milk adulteration."}, {"id": "AI-121", "title": "AI-Driven Cultural Artifact Recognition App", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Dr. Premananda Sahu", "sitting_place": "28-206-C1", "description": "The preservation and understanding of cultural heritage have become increasingly important in today's digital age. Many ancient artifacts, monuments, and artworks remain unknown or under-documented to the general public due to limited accessibility and lack of awareness. The proposed AI-Driven Cultural Artifact Recognition App aims to bridge this gap by using Artificial Intelligence and Deep Learning to identify and describe cultural artifacts from simple images uploaded by users. The primary goal of this system is to make cultural knowledge more accessible and interactive. When a user uploads an image of an artifact---such as a sculpture, coin, pottery, or monument---the app analyzes the image using advanced computer vision and transfer learning techniques to extract key features. These features are then compared with the system's knowledge base to recognize and identify the artifact. If the artifact is recognized, the app displays its name, origin, and a detailed historical description to the user. In cases where the artifact is not recognized within the existing knowledge base, the system employs an intelligent fallback mechanism. It integrates Google Cloud Vision API, Wikipedia search, and AI-powered language models (LLMs) to generate a detailed and accurate description of the object. This ensures that even new or rare cultural artifacts can be analyzed and understood without requiring prior manual labeling. One of the distinguishing features of this application is its self-learning capability. Whenever an unknown artifact is identified using online resources, the newly obtained information is stored within the system. This allows the app to gradually expand its knowledge base over time. As more users interact with the application and upload images, the system continuously improves its accuracy, efficiency, and cultural coverage. Essentially, the app becomes smarter and more comprehensive with every interaction. From a societal perspective, this project has significant potential in education, tourism, and cultural preservation. It empowers tourists and travelers to instantly learn about the historical significance of the objects they encounter. It also serves as an educational tool for students and researchers, helping them explore cultural heritage through visual learning. Furthermore, by digitally documenting and categorizing artifacts, the system contributes to the broader goal of safeguarding and promoting cultural heritage in a digital format. In summary, the AI-Driven Cultural Artifact Recognition App represents an innovative step toward merging artificial intelligence with cultural preservation. It not only democratizes access to historical knowledge but also creates a dynamic, evolving platform where technology and heritage coexist. Through intelligent automation, user interaction, and continuous learning, this system supports the long-term vision of global cultural awareness and digital heritage conservation."}, {"id": "AI-122", "title": "AI-Driven Maize Yield Prediction & Farm Optimization Platform", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2025 ( Problem Statement ID: 25044)", "supervisor": "Mallepalli Gautham( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This project focuses on developing an AI-driven platform that helps farmers predict maize yield and manage their farms more efficiently. Farmers often face difficulties in estimating crop yield because of unpredictable weather, poor soil health, and pest attacks. Traditional methods of yield prediction are outdated and do not provide accurate or timely information, which leads to poor planning and financial losses. The proposed system uses artificial intelligence and machine learning to predict maize yield based on past agricultural data, current weather conditions, and soil health metrics. Real-time data from IoT-based soil sensors and weather APIs like OpenWeather or IMD will be integrated into the platform. This data will be processed using machine learning algorithms such as regression and deep learning models to generate accurate yield predictions. The platform will also offer smart recommendations for irrigation, fertilizer use, and pest management. These suggestions will help farmers use their resources wisely and increase productivity. The front end of the platform will be developed using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to create a simple and user-friendly interface. The back end will be built with Python using frameworks like Flask or FastAPI, while the data will be stored in PostgreSQL or MySQL databases. An analytics dashboard will be created using Power BI or Tableau to visualize yield forecasts, soil health trends, and farm optimization strategies. These visual insights will help both farmers and agricultural policymakers make better decisions. By using this AI-based system, farmers can increase maize productivity by around 10 percent, reduce unnecessary expenses, and improve overall farm sustainability. The project aims to combine modern technology with traditional farming to create a smart, reliable, and data-driven solution for the agricultural community."}, {"id": "AI-123", "title": "AI-Driven Prediction System for Early Detection of Kidney Disease", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH and Global Medical Datasets", "supervisor": "Dr. Ankita Wadhawan", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH16", "description": "Chronic Kidney Disease (CKD) is a progressive condition that often goes undetected until advanced stages, leading to severe health complications or renal failure. This project aims to build a machine learning--based predictive model that analyzes patient health parameters (such as blood pressure, blood sugar, serum creatinine, hemoglobin, etc.) to accurately predict the likelihood of kidney disease at an early stage. The solution will help doctors and healthcare professionals in early intervention, thereby reducing the risk of complications and mortality."}, {"id": "AI-124", "title": "AI-Driven Privacy Masking: A context Aware Hybrid Model for Multilingual and Unstructured Documents", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Review", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2024 Ministry of Electronics and Information Technology (MeitY)", "supervisor": "Dr. Tanima Thakur", "sitting_place": "27-205-CH10", "description": "The proposed system is an AI-powered privacy protection platform that automatically detects and masks Personally Identifiable Information (PII) in digital documents such as PDFs, scanned forms, and emails. Using BERT-based Named Entity Recognition combined with rule-based detection, the system identifies sensitive identifiers like Aadhaar, PAN, phone numbers, and addresses. It then automatically redacts or masks this information, preventing accidental data leaks and ensuring compliance with privacy regulations such as the DPDP Act and GDPR."}, {"id": "AI-125", "title": "AI-Driven Public Health Chatbot", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Makul Mahajan", "sitting_place": "34-209-C1", "description": "This project focuses on developing a sophisticated AI-Driven Public Health Chatbot to provide accessible, 24/7 health information, symptom triage, and resource navigation, transcending the limitations of basic chatbots. It will uniquely integrate hyper-localized disease surveillance with public health data (like air quality and local outbreaks) to offer real-time, neighbourhood-specific risk assessments and personalized advice. Furthermore, it will be engineered for multilingual and cultural adaptability, moving beyond simple translation to understand regional dialects and culturally sensitive health beliefs. The system will also feature optional secure integration with patient wearables to track biometrics and deliver proactive, personalized coaching for chronic conditions, all while utilizing an advanced \"empathy model\" for a more supportive and less transactional user experience."}, {"id": "AI-126", "title": "AI-Driven Public Health Chatbot for Disease Awareness", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Tushar Kasana", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH36", "description": "Develop a multilingual AI chatbot to educate rural and semi-urban populations about preventive healthcare, disease symptoms, and vaccination schedules. The chatbot integrates with government health databases, provides real-time alerts for disease outbreaks, and offers interactive guidance via WhatsApp or SMS"}, {"id": "AI-127", "title": "AI-Driven Public Health chatbot for Disease Awareness", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Review", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Mahipal Singh Papola", "sitting_place": "36-307-CH12", "description": "This project aims to develop an AI-powered public health chatbot that provides accurate and easy-to-understand disease awareness to the general public. It helps users learn about common illnesses, their symptoms, and preventive measures through natural, conversational interaction. The chatbot supports multilingual communication to assist rural and semi-urban populations. It also offers basic risk assessment based on user inputs and suggests appropriate next steps. This solution enhances public health literacy and promotes early awareness before medical emergencies arise."}, {"id": "AI-128", "title": "AI-Driven Public Health Chatbot for Disease Awareness and Early Disease Prediction", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2025 Problem Statmenet no 25049", "supervisor": "Dr. Dhiraj Kapila", "sitting_place": "27-205-C2", "description": "This capstone project develops an AI-powered multilingual chatbot to educate rural and semi-urban populations about preventive healthcare, disease symptoms, and vaccination schedules. The system will be enhanced with an integrated Multiple Disease Prediction Module that leverages machine learning models to predict the likelihood of diseases such as diabetes, heart disease, and Parkinson's disease based on user-input symptoms and health parameters. The chatbot will use Natural Language Processing (NLP) to understand user queries in regional languages and provide responses in an easy-to-understand format. It will also integrate with government health databases and public health APIs to offer real-time alerts for disease outbreaks and vaccination drives. By combining awareness, prediction, and accessibility, the system aims to improve healthcare outreach and enable early diagnosis in underserved communities."}, {"id": "AI-129", "title": "AI-Driven Real-Time Intelligent Object Detection and Tracking System Using YOLOv8 and Centroid-Based Multi-Object Tracking", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "https://www.sih.gov.in/sih2025PS", "supervisor": "Lalita", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH11", "description": "The topic is inspired from the domain of Computer Vision and Artificial Intelligence, specifically focusing on real-time object detection systems used in: Smart surveillance systems Autonomous vehicles Traffic monitoring Industrial automation It is based on: Recent advancements in YOLO (You Only Look Once) models (especially YOLOv8 by Ultralytics) Research papers and implementations in deep learning-based object detection and tracking."}, {"id": "AI-130", "title": "AI-Driven Real-Time Wildlife Surveillance and Anti-Poaching System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Dr. Premananda Sahu", "sitting_place": "28-206-C1", "description": "Wildlife conservation is one of the most crucial challenges of our time. Illegal poaching, deforestation, and wildfires continue to endanger countless species and disturb the natural ecosystem. Traditional surveillance methods such as manual patrolling or static camera monitoring are often inefficient, time-consuming, and limited in real-time responsiveness. To overcome these limitations, our capstone project, \"AI-Driven Real-Time Wildlife Surveillance and Anti-Poaching System\", integrates the power of Artificial Intelligence (AI), Deep Learning, and IoT-based edge technologies to monitor wildlife zones effectively and prevent illegal activities in real-time. The proposed system leverages computer vision models and AI-based analytics to detect animals, identify potential poaching activities, and recognize early signs of wildfire. Using drones or fixed surveillance cameras, real-time video feeds are captured and processed using AI algorithms. The system then performs automatic detection and classification, sending instant alerts to forest authorities if any unusual or harmful activity is identified. The architecture is built using YOLO-based object detection models and LSTM/CNN-based activity recognition networks to analyze frame-by-frame patterns. The models are trained on diverse datasets including wildlife species, human activities in restricted zones, and environmental cues related to fire or smoke. All detections are processed locally or on cloud servers depending on available computational resources, ensuring flexibility and scalability. Furthermore, the system includes a Streamlit-based dashboard for visualization where authorities can monitor live camera feeds, get detection logs, and analyze statistical reports of wildlife movement and security alerts. By integrating IoT sensors (such as temperature, motion, and smoke sensors), the project enhances detection accuracy and provides a multi-modal surveillance approach."}, {"id": "AI-131", "title": "AI-Driven Trading System for Optimizing Financial Markets with Predictive Models and Sentiment Analysis", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "sih", "supervisor": "Madhuri", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH4", "description": "The project introduces an AI-based trading system that maximizes choice at the international financial markets. It provides high accuracy trade signals in real-time that suit breakout-trading patterns, scalping, and swing trade strategies. Combined into one seamless experience with TradingView, the system employs four advanced models: the Predictive Trend Learning Model (PTLM), a price forecasting model, Sentiment Fusion Engine (SFE), which can analyze large volumes of financial news and social sentiment using large language models, QuantScore Signal Engine (QSE) which can score trade set-ups based on statistical measures, and ChartVision AI, which can be used to detect technical pattern definitions with high levels of precision. the system will diminish the need to manually analyze the market and will assist novice and professional traders. It allows its users to instill comprehension, conviction, and promptness in making trading choices without extensive market knowledge or having to spend much time in front of a computer screen. Through automation of the important trading mechanisms, this solution democratizes access to institutional level trading instruments, improves profitability, and reduces the emotional mistakes made in turbulent, volatile markets."}, {"id": "AI-132", "title": "AI-Enhanced Career Guidance System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Dr. Premananda Sahu", "sitting_place": "28-206-C1", "description": "The AI-Enhanced Career Guidance System is an intelligent recommendation platform designed to provide personalized career guidance through advanced machine learning techniques. The system integrates a user's educational background, technical skills, and personal interests to suggest optimal professional pathways across diverse domains. By leveraging data-driven insights, it bridges the gap between individual capabilities and evolving career opportunities in a rapidly changing job market. System Architecture and Implementation The architecture of the system is structured into three main layers: data processing, predictive modeling, and user interface, each performing distinct yet interconnected roles to ensure accurate and efficient career recommendations. The foundation of the system relies on a curated dataset (AI-based Career Recommendation System.csv) containing comprehensive information about various career profiles, including their corresponding educational qualifications, technical skills, and interest categories. This dataset undergoes extensive preprocessing within the Model.ipynb notebook. During preprocessing, categorical attributes are encoded, and numerical values are normalized to maintain uniformity and enhance model performance. The encoding modules---edu_enc.joblib, skill_enc.joblib, and int_enc.joblib---convert qualitative data into numerical representations, while scaler.joblib standardizes numerical inputs such as age to ensure consistent feature scaling. Following data preparation, a machine learning model is trained to identify relationships between user attributes and suitable career outcomes. The trained model, stored as model.joblib, encapsulates these learned patterns for predictive inference. The save_model.py script manages the serialization and persistence of the model and encoders, ensuring reproducibility and easy deployment. The backend layer, implemented in backend.py, is developed using the Flask framework with Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) enabled for secure API communication. It loads the pre-trained model artifacts at startup and provides a RESTful API endpoint that accepts candidate data in JSON format. Upon receiving input, the backend performs a series of transformations, including educational encoding, skill vectorization, interest encoding, and numerical normalization, before passing the processed data to the predictive model. The resulting career prediction is then converted into a user-friendly output and returned as the final recommendation. The frontend interface, designed with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, offers an intuitive and visually appealing user experience. The interface allows users to input their educational qualifications, skills, and interests through structured form fields. The script.js file manages asynchronous communication with the backend API, displaying progress indicators and dynamic feedback for enhanced user engagement. Technical Capabilities and Applications This system exemplifies a robust end-to-end machine learning pipeline, encompassing data preparation, model training, artifact management, and deployment. Its modular architecture ensures maintainability, while the RESTful integration enables smooth communication between components. The system's user-friendly design promotes accessibility and responsiveness, catering to diverse users. This AI-driven career guidance solution holds practical applications across educational institutions, career counseling centers, and HR departments, offering data-backed career recommendations. Future extensions may include confidence scoring, alternative career pathways, and personalized skill development roadmaps. With minor scalability and security enhancements, this project serves as a comprehensive model for intelligent, adaptive, and personalized career recommendation systems."}, {"id": "AI-133", "title": "AI-Integrated Free Food Redistribution Website Connecting Event Donors and NGOs", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25126 - Student Innovation: Swadeshi for Atmanirbhar Bharat - Agriculture, FoodTech & Rural Development", "supervisor": "Dr. Mohit Arora", "sitting_place": "28-202-C1", "description": "The project develops an AI-powered web platform that connects event hosts who have surplus food with nearby NGOs in real time. The system analyzes food availability, location, NGO capacity, and urgency to recommend the best match and schedule pickups. AI prediction and automation reduce manual coordination, prevent food waste, and ensure that safe, edible food reaches people in need efficiently."}, {"id": "AI-134", "title": "AI-Optimized Biohybrid Photovoltaic Leaves: Integrating Natural Photosystems with Adaptive Energy Conversion Architectures", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "https://www.sih.gov.in/sih2025PS", "supervisor": "Lalita", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH11", "description": "AI-Optimized Biohybrid Photovoltaic Leaves is an advanced energy project that combines natural photosynthesis with artificial solar technology to create highly efficient, adaptive energy systems. In this concept, biological components such as photosystems from plants, algae, or cyanobacteria are integrated with synthetic photovoltaic materials. These natural photosystems are extremely efficient at capturing sunlight and converting it into chemical energy."}, {"id": "AI-135", "title": "AI-Powered Administration Platform for Educational Institutions", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "SIH 2025 (https://www.sih.gov.in/sih2025PS) Topic 11 (Smart Curriculum Activity & Attendance App)", "supervisor": "Blossom", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH15", "description": "This proposed platform provides AI-assisted tools for managing campus activities, including digital attendance, performance tracking, scheduling, and automated student support. It helps reduce manual tasks for faculty and administrators while offering students organized academic guidance and easy access to essential information, enabling more efficient and transparent campus management."}, {"id": "AI-136", "title": "AI-Powered Breed Recognition System for Indian Cattle and Buffaloes", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25004", "supervisor": "Dr. Harwinder Singh Sohal", "sitting_place": "26-205-CH10", "description": "Developing an AI-powered web application to accurately classify indigenous breeds of Indian cattle and buffaloes. The system uses a deep learning (CNN) model. A user can upload an image and instantly receive a breed prediction. This tool aims to assist farmers in breeding and sales, aid conservation efforts, and support livestock insurance verification by providing an accessible and reliable identification method."}, {"id": "AI-137", "title": "AI-Powered Crop Disease Detection and Yield Prediction System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr Dhanpratap Singh", "sitting_place": "26-203-C2", "description": "Agriculture remains the backbone of India's economy, yet millions of farmers face significant losses due to unrecognized crop diseases and unpredictable yields. Traditional methods of disease diagnosis are time-consuming and often inaccurate, leading to delayed interventions. To address this, an AI-powered crop disease detection and yield prediction system can revolutionize modern farming by leveraging machine learning (ML) and computer vision technologies. This system uses a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) model trained on thousands of images of healthy and diseased crops. Farmers can capture leaf or plant images using a mobile application, which instantly analyzes them to detect diseases such as blight, rust, or mildew. The model identifies the disease type, estimates severity, and recommends appropriate pesticide or nutrient treatments. Additionally, the system integrates environmental and soil data (temperature, rainfall, pH, and moisture levels) to forecast crop yield using regression-based ML algorithms like Random Forest Regressor or XGBoost. The fusion of image-based and environmental data ensures both disease prevention and optimized production forecasting. A cloud-based dashboard stores data securely and allows government agencies or agricultural departments to monitor regional disease outbreaks. This enables proactive policymaking and ensures that resources such as fertilizers or irrigation are distributed efficiently. By combining machine learning, IoT sensors, and edge computing, the proposed solution empowers farmers with real-time insights, reduces dependency on manual inspections, and enhances productivity and sustainability in agriculture. It aligns perfectly with SIH's vision of using AI for smart agriculture and rural development."}, {"id": "AI-138", "title": "AI-Powered Crop Yield Prediction and Optimization", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon (SIH) 2025", "supervisor": "Siya Thakur", "sitting_place": "26-205-CH18", "description": "The AI-Powered Crop Yield Prediction and Optimization system represents a comprehensive agricultural technology solution that transforms traditional farming through intelligent data analysis and machine learning. At its core, the platform integrates diverse data sources---real-time weather patterns, soil health metrics (pH levels, nutrient content, moisture), historical farm performance records, and high-resolution satellite imagery---to generate highly accurate crop yield predictions exceeding 90% accuracy rates\\[1\\]. The system architecture employs an ensemble of advanced machine learning algorithms including Random Forest Regressor for handling non-linear agricultural relationships, LightGBM for rapid processing of large-scale datasets, Decision Trees for interpretable predictions, and Convolutional Neural Networks for analyzing visual crop health data from satellites and drones\\[1\\]\\[2\\]. These algorithms work synergistically to process complex, multi-dimensional agricultural datasets and extract meaningful patterns that inform farming decisions. Beyond prediction, the platform delivers actionable, farmer-centric recommendations covering the entire crop lifecycle. It suggests optimal sowing windows based on weather forecasts and soil readiness, generates precision irrigation schedules considering soil moisture sensors and crop water requirements at different growth stages, recommends site-specific fertilizer application rates using Variable Rate Technology, and provides early warnings for pest infestations and disease outbreaks with targeted intervention strategies\\[3\\]\\[4\\]. The platform's user interface is designed for accessibility, featuring vernacular language support, intuitive dashboards with visual representations of predictions, and mobile-responsive design enabling farmers to access critical information in the field. It promotes climate-resilient farming by helping farmers adapt to changing weather patterns, reduces environmental impact through optimized resource utilization, and enhances farmer income stability through better crop planning, reduced input costs, and informed market timing decisions\\[3\\]\\[4\\]. The system represents a scalable, technology-driven approach to modernizing Indian agriculture while addressing sustainability and profitability challenges."}, {"id": "AI-139", "title": "AI-Powered Crop Yield Production & Advisory System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH: Smart Indian Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Anzah Bashir", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH17", "description": "The AI-Powered Crop Yield Production Advisory System represents an innovative leap in modern agricultural technology, uniquely merging artificial intelligence, satellite remote sensing, and user-friendly interfaces to address critical farming challenges. At its core, the platform automates crop health assessment using computer vision models that analyze photos submitted by farmers, classifying fields as healthy or stressed in real time. This feature empowers farmers to swiftly address crop threats before they escalate. Further, the system utilizes advanced time-series analysis with Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) algorithms to provide early pest risk forecasts, integrating satellite and meteorological data for timely recommendations. A robust geospatial mapping module allows precise field boundary determination, ensuring that all predictions and advice are tailored to specific farm locations. The advisory services are democratized through a multilingual, voice-enabled chatbot, which responds in local languages---including Hindi, Marathi, and English---delivering expert guidance at any hour. On the backend, the system orchestrates powerful machine learning models (CNNs, LSTMs) with seamless data management, intuitive dashboard visualizations, and continuous performance validation. Sustainability metrics like water management savings and carbon credit estimates are tracked, encouraging climate-resilient and resource-efficient agricultural decisions. Collectively, these integrated features enable this platform to help farmers optimize crop yield, minimize risks, and embrace sustainable best practices, paving the way for wide-scale adoption of smart farming across diverse regions and scales."}, {"id": "AI-140", "title": "AI-Powered Electricity Demand Forecasting for Delhi", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Dr. Nikita", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH11", "description": "This project addresses the challenge of forecasting Delhi's uniquely volatile electricity demand. The city's power consumption is marked by extreme seasonal swings, two distinct daily peaks, and the \"duck curve\" effect from solar power, making simple forecasts unreliable. Our solution is an advanced AI model trained on a rich dataset that combines standard load and weather data with crucial real-world context. We integrated public holidays, major policy events like COVID-19 lockdowns and GRAP pollution alerts, and socio-economic trends such as population growth, economic output (GSDP), and the increasing adoption of electric vehicles to build a more intelligent and accurate predictive tool."}, {"id": "AI-141", "title": "AI-Powered Food Nutrition Analyzer for LPU Campus", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25126", "supervisor": "Sandeep", "sitting_place": "33-205-CH18", "description": "This project aims to develop an AI-based mobile and web application that automatically calculates the nutritional value of food items served within LPU campus. Using computer vision and machine learning models, the system will identify food items from images or menus and estimate calories, macronutrients, and other dietary parameters. The solution promotes healthy eating habits, smart meal choices, and campus wellness awareness."}, {"id": "AI-142", "title": "AI-powered monitoring of crop health, soil condition, and pest risks using multispectral/hyperspectral imaging and sensor data.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2025(-SIH25099)", "supervisor": "Dr. Dhiraj Kapila", "sitting_place": "27-205-C2", "description": "This capstone project is an AI-powered platform built using the Hyperspectral Imaging Library and deep learning models that ingests and aligns multispectral/hyperspectral image sequences with historical datasets, extracts vegetation and soil indices, and applies models like LSTM and CNN to detect trends and predict vegetation stress or disease risk. Environmental sensor data, such as soil moisture, air temperature, humidity, and leaf wetness, is integrated to contextualize spectral anomalies, improve the accuracy of stress and pest predictions, and trigger zone-specific alerts."}, {"id": "AI-143", "title": "AI-Powered Neural Disorder Detection Tool", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Dr. Janpreet Singh", "sitting_place": "28-202-C3", "description": "The project aims to develop an intelligent machine learning (ML)-based tool to accurately detect Parkinson's disease. In Step 1, we will collect online health data of Parkinson's patients and use standard ML models to establish a baseline accuracy. Step 2 focuses on training advanced, recently developed ML models to identify subtle patterns and improve prediction accuracy compared to the baseline. In Step 3, we will create an AI-based Detection System that allows users to input their data, which the trained model will analyze to predict the likelihood of Parkinson's disease quickly and accurately, aiding early diagnosis and awareness."}, {"id": "AI-144", "title": "AI-Powered Rockfall Detection & Risk Mapping in Open-Pit Mines", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2025 ( Problem Statement ID: 25071)", "supervisor": "Mallepalli Gautham( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "The primary objective of this project is to develop an AI-based rockfall detection system for open-pit mines, complemented by a dynamic risk map to enhance miner safety. The system leverages advanced deep learning models to deliver highly accurate and dependable results. Rockfall detection is achieved using two robust yet distinct approaches. The first utilizes LiDAR data, which offers valuable insights into terrain characteristics such as elevation, slope, and surface length. These features are processed and used to train a neural network capable of identifying potential rockfall zones. The second approach relies on seismic data, where waveform analysis enables the detection of ground vibrations associated with rockfall events. Together, these methods provide a flexible and reliable detection framework adaptable to various mining conditions. The model's outputs are integrated into a live risk map, offering miners and planners real-time visual insights into safety levels across different site areas. Additionally, the accompanying application delivers instant alerts based on live risk data and includes an AI assistant designed to guide miners with context-specific safety recommendations."}, {"id": "AI-145", "title": "AI-Powered Smart Medical Report and Doctor Recommendation System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "NA", "supervisor": "Dr.Varun Dogra", "sitting_place": "55-302-C3", "description": "The AI-Powered Smart Medical Report and Doctor Recommendation System is an intelligent web-based healthcare platform designed to help patients quickly understand their health conditions and connect with qualified doctors nearby. By leveraging artificial intelligence and machine learning, the system analyzes medical images (such as skin lesions, infections, or affected body areas) uploaded by users. It then generates an automated medical report that includes the detected condition, confidence level, a short description, precautionary measures, and recommended next steps. Using geolocation and external APIs (Google Maps), the system further recommends verified doctors in the user's locality, sorted by specialization, rating, and proximity. This solution significantly improves accessibility and efficiency in healthcare by reducing the time between symptom detection and professional consultation."}, {"id": "AI-146", "title": "AI-powered Stress and Emotion Detection using Facial and Voice Analysis", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "self problem identification", "supervisor": "Puneet", "sitting_place": "27-204-CH4", "description": "In today's fast-paced world, rising stress levels and emotional fatigue often go unnoticed until they affect health and productivity. This project proposes an AI-based system that detects stress and emotions in real time by analyzing facial expressions and voice tone. Using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for facial analysis and MFCC-based audio processing, the system identifies emotions such as happiness, anger, sadness, and stress. By combining both visual and vocal cues, it achieves higher accuracy and reliability. The solution can be implemented in workplaces to detect early signs of burnout or mental pressure, enabling timely preventive action and employee support. It also holds potential in driver safety, healthcare, and mental wellness applications to promote emotional well-being and safer environments."}, {"id": "AI-147", "title": "AI-Powered Student Performance Prediction System Using Machine Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Abhinav Singh", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH11", "description": "This project aims to design and implement an AI-powered Student Performance Prediction System that utilizes machine learning algorithms to predict academic outcomes based on various student parameters such as attendance, assignment marks, internal assessments, and participation records. The model will be trained on real or synthetic datasets and tested for accuracy using algorithms such as Random Forest, Decision Tree, and Support Vector Machine. The system will feature a user-friendly web interface for teachers to upload student data and view predictions, along with visual analytics like charts and progress graphs. This tool can help institutions identify struggling students early, enabling timely intervention and improved academic success rates."}, {"id": "AI-148", "title": "AI-powered symptom checker optimized for low-bandwidth areas.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH25018-Telemedicine Access for Rural Healthcare in Nabha", "supervisor": "Dr. Bhupinder Singh", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH8", "description": "This project develops a research-based simulation framework to model and evaluate AI-assisted symptom triage strategies in rural India, where limited connectivity, scarce specialist access, and high burdens of undiagnosed neurological conditions---such as stroke, epilepsy, Meningitis and Encephalitis---pose critical public health challenges. Rather than deploying a mobile application, the work focuses on computational simulation to rigorously test the feasibility, accuracy, and equity of lightweight AI diagnostic logic under real-world constraints. The simulation integrates epidemiological data from national surveys (NFHS, ICMR, and district health reports) to construct synthetic rural populations reflective of age, literacy, disease prevalence, and healthcare access patterns. Within this environment, simplified AI classifiers---trained on validated clinical datasets that include regionally relevant neurological symptom presentations---are embedded into a discrete-event model of the rural care cascade. The model simulates patient journeys from symptom onset through community health worker interaction, potential teleconsultation, and referral, all under bandwidth limitations typical of remote areas (\\<50 kbps, intermittent connectivity). A core research objective is to quantify how early AI-informed triage impacts detection rates and time-to-care for brain diseases. For example, the simulation evaluates whether rule-based or pruned machine learning models can reliably flag stroke-like symptoms (e.g., sudden weakness, slurred speech) or progressive cognitive changes using only minimal, verbally reported inputs---mirroring interactions with ASHA workers or voice-based interfaces. The framework also tests system-level trade-offs: How does model size affect inference latency on low-end devices? What level of symptom noise or missing data degrades performance? Can caching or offline updates maintain diagnostic reliability? By varying these parameters, the research generates evidence-based design principles for future AI health tools deployable across India's diverse rural landscapes."}, {"id": "AI-149", "title": "AI-powered system to minimize accidents and improve driving behavior through predictive analytics and real-time monitoring.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "self problem identification", "supervisor": "Puneet", "sitting_place": "27-204-CH4", "description": "Road accidents in India are increasing due to overspeeding, unsafe lane changes, distracted driving, and lack of road awareness. To address this, the proposed system uses AI-based video analytics to monitor driving behavior in real-time and provide smart safety alerts. The system takes input from dashcam or roadside CCTV footage and applies Computer Vision and Machine Learning models to detect vehicles, lanes, pedestrians, and driving patterns. Based on this, it predicts potential accident risks such as tailgating, sudden braking, lane departure, overspeeding, and near-collision situations. It then sends instant alerts to the driver for corrective action."}, {"id": "AI-150", "title": "Al-Based Crop Recommendation for Farmers", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025 (Problem Statement ID 25030)", "supervisor": "Danish Meiraj", "sitting_place": "28-204-CH18", "description": "Background Farmers often face challenges in accessing timely, personalized, and accurate agricultural support. Language barriers, lack of technical knowledge, and limited reach of conventional advisory services reduce the effectiveness of existing solutions. Emerging generative AI technologies present an opportunity to deliver hyper-localized guidance in natural language, paired with visual understanding to assist with field-level problems like crop disease detection. Detailed Description The objective is to create an AI-driven decision support system that determines real-time soil properties (pH, moisture, nutrient content) based on satellite data (e.g., Soil Grids, Bhuvan APIs) or IoT sensors. The system must also account for localized weather forecasts, past crop rotation data to preserve soil fertility, and existing market demand and price trends obtained through APIs or scraping agri-market websites. A machine learning model will provide the most appropriate crops for specified conditions, forecasting yield, profit margins, and sustainability scores. The solution should comprise a mobile application with a simple multilingual interface where farmers can enter or retrieve relevant data, see recommendations, and operate offline in low-connectivity regions. Expected Solution A mobile-based prototype offering farmers customized, science-guided crop advice, increasing income, making resources more efficient, and facilitating sustainable agriculture. The solution should deliver an AI-powered platform that integrates text and image-based interactions tailored for agricultural use. It must support voice and chat interfaces in local languages, enabling farmers to ask questions and receive actionable responses."}, {"id": "AI-151", "title": "Al-Based Internship Recommendation Engine for PM Internship Scheme", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25034", "supervisor": "Dr. Harwinder Singh Sohal", "sitting_place": "26-205-CH10", "description": "The AI-Based Internship Recommendation Engine for the Prime Minister's Internship Scheme is a research-oriented system designed to automate, streamline, and enhance the internship allocation process through the integration of Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) methodologies. The project's core objective is to develop a data-driven, intelligent recommendation framework that aligns students' profiles with the most suitable internship opportunities, thereby promoting digital empowerment and employability across educational institutions. The proposed system utilizes a hybrid AI architecture that combines content-based and machine learning-based recommendation techniques. The model analyses student data attributes such as academic background, domain expertise, technical and soft skills, research interests, and historical performance records. Simultaneously, it processes internship descriptions, including role requirements, skill expectations, and domain keywords. To interpret and extract semantic meaning from these textual data sources, the system employs advanced Natural Language Processing (NLP) algorithms such as Term Frequency--Inverse Document Frequency (TF-IDF), Word2Vec, and Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers (BERT) embeddings. These models convert unstructured text into contextualized numerical representations, enabling accurate similarity computation between student and internship profiles. The recommendation engine leverages supervised machine learning models, including Decision Trees, Random Forest Classifiers, and Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs), to predict the most compatible internship matches. The prediction models are trained using historical internship data, where successful student placements serve as labeled examples. Additionally, similarity-based algorithms such as Cosine Similarity and Semantic Search are implemented to compute match scores, generating a ranked list of internship recommendations personalized for each student. A web-based user interface is developed using Flask or Django frameworks to facilitate real-time interaction between students, institutions, and internship providers. The interface supports functionalities such as dynamic profile updates, internship browsing, preference filtering, and feedback collection. The backend infrastructure integrates a relational database (MySQL/PostgreSQL) for structured data storage and a RESTful API layer to manage communication between the AI model and the web application. The system architecture emphasizes scalability, modularity, and interoperability to accommodate growing datasets and institutional expansion. The implementation of this AI-driven recommendation framework significantly enhances efficiency, transparency, and fairness in internship allocation. By automating candidate-internship mapping, it minimizes manual intervention, reduces administrative workload, and mitigates human bias in selection decisions. Moreover, the use of interpretable ML models ensures explainability and trustworthiness in recommendations, aligning with emerging ethical AI standards. Beyond its technical capabilities, the project contributes to national digital transformation initiatives and supports multiple United Nations Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs), particularly SDG 4 (Quality Education), SDG 8 (Decent Work and Economic Growth), SDG 9 (Industry, Innovation, and Infrastructure), and SDG 10 (Reduced Inequalities). By intelligently bridging the gap between academia and industry, the AI-Based Internship Recommendation Engine fosters a data-centric ecosystem for employability, empowering students with equitable access to relevant internship opportunities and enabling institutions to make informed, data-driven placement decisions."}, {"id": "AI-152", "title": "Al-Driven Crop Disease Prediction and Management System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Pritam Sunil Mahajan( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "Agriculture productivity can be severely affected by crop diseases. A machine learning model using regression, decision trees, or ensemble methods can analyze historical weather data, soil conditions, and crop health images to predict potential outbreaks and recommend appropriate actions. This system can help farmers take preventive measures and reduce losses."}, {"id": "AI-153", "title": "Al-Driven Public Health Chatbot for Disease Awareness", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH ID : 25049", "supervisor": "Dr. Bhupinder Singh", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH8", "description": "The Transformer-Based Public Health Agent for Syndromic Triage and Awareness represents a sophisticated fusion of advanced artificial intelligence and public health infrastructure. This system is engineered to function as a scalable first line of defense in community health, leveraging a state-of-the-art neural architecture to process and understand complex user queries in natural language. Its core capability lies in performing real-time syndromic surveillance and preliminary triage, interacting with users to assess reported symptoms, exposure history, and risk factors against a continuously updated medical knowledge graph. Technically, the platform is built upon a microservices architecture, ensuring robustness, scalability, and seamless integration with existing public health databases and electronic health records (EHRs) under strict HIPAA/GDPR compliance. The intelligence layer utilizes a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) framework, augmenting a large language model (LLM) with verified, up-to-date information from sources like the CDC and WHO. This prevents hallucination and ensures all disseminated guidance is evidence-based and current, crucial for combating misinformation. Key functionalities include dynamic risk stratification, where the agent categorizes cases based on urgency, providing tailored recommendations from self-care to immediate emergency referral. It supports multi-modal interactions, offering educational videos and infographics, and can deliver proactive alerts on local outbreak trends. By anonymizing and aggregating interaction data, the system provides public health officials with invaluable insights into emerging community health threats and knowledge gaps. This AI-driven agent is not intended to replace clinicians but to augment public health capacity, offering 24/7 accessible, accurate, and personalized guidance, thereby reducing the burden on healthcare systems and empowering individuals with reliable health intelligence."}, {"id": "AI-154", "title": "Al-Powered Crop Yield Prediction and Optimization", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH25044", "supervisor": "Mohit Dewangan", "sitting_place": "27-209-CH12", "description": "Develop an AI-based platform to predict crop yields using historical agricultural data, weather patterns, and soil health metrics. The system should provide actionable recommendations for farmers to optimize irrigation, fertilization, and pest control, tailored to specific crops and regional conditions."}, {"id": "AI-155", "title": "Al-Powered Crop Yield Prediction and Optimization using Machine Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH 2025 -- Problem No. SIH44: Al-Powered Crop Yield Prediction and Optimization", "supervisor": "Navjot Kaur", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH27", "description": "This project develops an AI-powered system to predict crop yields using weather, soil, and crop parameters. It integrates real-time weather APIs to improve accuracy and recommends the most suitable crops for given conditions. The system provides an interactive dashboard for yield forecasts, crop suggestions, and trend analysis, helping farmers and policymakers make data-driven decisions to improve productivity and sustainability. In addition, it supports precision farming by analyzing fertilizer, irrigation, and resource needs. The solution ultimately aims to enhance food security, reduce crop loss, and promote sustainable agricultural practices."}, {"id": "AI-156", "title": "An AI-Driven Agricultural Decision Support System Fusing Heterogeneous Telemetry Feeds for Hyper-Localized Crop Optimization", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH25030-Al-Based Crop Recommendation for Farmers", "supervisor": "Dr. Bhupinder Singh", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH8", "description": "This research proposes a comprehensive machine learning framework for agricultural decision support, integrating heterogeneous data streams through a structured analytical pipeline. The system employs a multi-branch neural architecture that processes satellite-derived soil parameters, IoT sensor telemetry, meteorological forecasts, and market data through separate feature extraction layers before fusion in a unified latent space. The core recommendation engine utilizes an ensemble of Gradient Boosting machines for yield prediction and a constrained optimization module that balances economic returns with sustainability metrics derived from soil health indices and water efficiency calculations. A specialized computer vision pipeline addresses the critical challenge of rare disease identification through a dual-phase approach. Initial feature extraction leverages pre-trained vision transformers (ViT-Base) fine-tuned on an augmented dataset of uncommon pathologies including Bakanae disease, Phyllody, and Purple Blotch. To overcome data scarcity for these rare conditions, the framework incorporates a generative adversarial network (GAN) for synthetic sample generation and employs progressive learning techniques. The diagnostic module implements Bayesian uncertainty quantification to flag low-confidence predictions, triggering a secondary analysis using a graph neural network that incorporates spatial disease patterns and environmental correlations. The entire framework is designed for edge deployment through model distillation techniques, converting the ensemble architectures into lightweight TensorFlow Lite models capable of offline operation. This enables real-time inference directly on mobile devices, providing farmers with immediate access to both strategic crop recommendations and tactical disease management protocols. The integration of rare pathogen diagnostics within a comprehensive agronomic decision support system represents a significant advancement in precision agriculture, offering protection against niche biological threats while optimizing broader cultivation strategies."}, {"id": "AI-157", "title": "An Edge-Computing Prototype for Autonomous Household Waste Classification using Deep Learning and IoT", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH25046-Smart Waste Segregation and Recycling System", "supervisor": "Dr. Bhupinder Singh", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH8", "description": "The Smart Waste Segregation and Recycling System is an innovative, end-to-end solution designed to revolutionize household waste management. By leveraging the power of the Internet of Things (IoT) and advanced Machine Learning (ML), the system automatically classifies disposed waste at the source into three primary categories: organic, recyclable, and hazardous. The core of the system is a smart bin prototype equipped with a suite of affordable sensors. A camera module captures images of the waste item, which are then analyzed in real-time by a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) trained on thousands of waste images. This visual data is fused with inputs from complementary sensors, such as weight and gas detectors, to achieve a classification accuracy exceeding 90%. Upon identification, servo mechanisms automatically direct the waste into the correct internal compartment, ensuring precise segregation."}, {"id": "AI-158", "title": "An Efficient Deep Learning-Based Diagnostic Approach for the Classification and Segmentation of Gastrointestinal Diseases", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH 2024: Student Innovation(MedTech / BioTech / HealthTech), Problem Statement ID:1597", "supervisor": "Salil Batra", "sitting_place": "34-207-CH13", "description": "Gastrointestinal diseases, including polyps and other abnormalities, are a significant concern in global healthcare due to their potential to develop into more severe conditions such as colorectal cancer. Early detection plays a crucial role in improving patient outcomes and preventing complications. With the advancement of medical imaging technologies, the ability to diagnose these conditions has greatly improved, but the challenge remains in automating the process for faster and more accurate diagnoses. Deep learning has emerged as a powerful tool for automating the analysis of medical images, offering the potential to improve classification and segmentation accuracy. This research work leverages deep learning models to automate the classification and segmentation of gastrointestinal images, specifically focusing on polyps. By using advanced models for image classification and segmentation, this work aims to enhance the ability of healthcare professionals to detect and diagnose gastrointestinal issues early and accurately."}, {"id": "AI-159", "title": "An Explainable AI-Driven Multimodal Fusion Approach for Breast Cancer Diagnosis", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Digital Health and AI-driven Early Detection of Non-Communicable Diseases (NCDs)", "supervisor": "Arun Singh", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH21", "description": "Breast cancer is one of the leading causes of death among women worldwide, where early and accurate detection plays a crucial role in improving survival rates. However, traditional diagnostic approaches often face challenges such as variability in interpretation, delayed detection, and limited integration of patient-specific information. This project proposes the development of an Explainable Multimodal Artificial Intelligence (AI) framework for efficient and reliable breast cancer detection. The proposed system will integrate multiple data sources, including medical imaging (mammograms, ultrasound, and histopathology images) and structured clinical data such as patient history and risk factors. By leveraging multimodal learning, the framework can capture complementary insights from different data types, leading to improved diagnostic accuracy compared to single-modality systems. Advanced deep learning models, including Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and transformer-based architectures, will be utilized for feature extraction and classification. Additionally, ensemble strategies may be incorporated to enhance model robustness. A key highlight of this research is the integration of Explainable AI (XAI) techniques such as Grad-CAM, SHAP, and LIME, which provide visual and feature-based explanations for model predictions. This ensures transparency and helps clinicians understand and trust AI-driven decisions."}, {"id": "AI-160", "title": "An Intelligent Predictive Framework for Bank Loan Approval Using Advanced Machine Learning and Data-Driven Risk Assessment Techniques", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Review", "source": "Google Scholar and Springer Book Series", "supervisor": "Tiyas Sarkar", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH24", "description": "The core output would be a working system that automates the loan approval decision-making process. This framework would take applicant data as input and provide an output of either \"Approved,\" \"Rejected,\" or \"Refer for manual review\". Highly accurate machine learning models: The students would train and evaluate several machine learning models, such as Logistic Regression, Random Forest, Gradient Boosting, or Support Vector Machines, to identify which provides the most accurate and reliable predictions for loan approval. The final framework would likely use the highest-performing model. Data preprocessing and feature engineering pipeline: The project would develop a systematic process for cleaning, transforming, and selecting the most relevant features from raw historical loan data. This pipeline ensures the ML model can learn effectively and produce reliable results. Comparative analysis of algorithms: Students would provide a report detailing the performance of different ML algorithms using standard evaluation metrics like accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score, and ROC AUC. This analysis would justify the choice of the final model. Model explainability module: To address transparency concerns in AI-driven decisions, the project may include an Explainable AI (XAI) component. This module would provide insight into the factors that most influenced a particular loan decision, building trust with both bank staff and applicants"}, {"id": "AI-161", "title": "An ML model that detects heart diseases and brain tumer by images of scanning of heart and brain", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Aarti Shar", "sitting_place": "34-202-CH7", "description": "This project focuses on developing a machine learning model to detect heart diseases and brain tumors using medical imaging scans such as MRI, CT, or ultrasound images. The primary goal is to assist healthcare professionals by providing an automated, accurate, and fast diagnostic tool. The model uses deep learning techniques, particularly convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which excel at image recognition and classification tasks. The project begins by collecting a large dataset of labeled heart and brain scans, including both healthy and diseased cases. The images are preprocessed to improve quality and normalize data, ensuring consistent input to the model. The CNN architecture is then trained to identify patterns and abnormalities indicative of heart conditions like cardiomegaly or myocardial infarction, as well as brain tumors of various types. Once trained, the model can analyze new scans and classify them as normal or diseased, highlighting regions of concern. This can significantly reduce diagnostic errors and speed up the detection process, ultimately improving patient outcomes. The system can be integrated into clinical workflows, serving as a decision support tool for radiologists and cardiologists. Overall, this project combines medical imaging and AI to advance early disease detection and personalized healthcare."}, {"id": "AI-162", "title": "Angika -- Bridging Communication, Empowering Inclusion", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "RELATED TO SOCIETY PROBLEM \"A system that translates sign language into speech and text, enabling seamless communication for people with speech and hearing impairments.\"", "supervisor": "Rithik Dubey", "sitting_place": "27-203-CH10", "description": "The project Angika is a mobile application developed to advance inclusive education for hearing- and speech-impaired students, with a specific focus on Indian Sign Language (ISL). The application integrates artificial intelligence (AI)-based sign language recognition with a robust cloud infrastructure to deliver an innovative, user-centric solution. Key features include: • Real-time translation between ISL and text/speech to bridge communication gaps. • Curriculum-aligned educational modules covering alphabets, numbers, vocabulary, and mathematics. • An intuitive, accessible user interface designed for diverse age groups and varying levels of digital literacy. • Adaptive and personalized learning experiences, powered by analytics and progress tracking. By addressing limitations of existing sign language applications---such as limited vocabulary, low recognition accuracy, and lack of structured educational integration---Angika aims to transform the learning environment for deaf and mute students. The system not only enhances academic outcomes but also fosters social inclusion by enabling effective communication among students, educators, and parents. Through its scalable design and strong educational orientation, Angika represents a step toward building a more inclusive and equitable digital learning ecosystem."}, {"id": "AI-163", "title": "Apex Vitality: An AI Health and Fitness Assistant", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Dr. Neeta Rana", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH5", "description": "Apex Vitality is an innovative AI-based health and fitness assistant developed to promote healthier living through technology-driven guidance. The project integrates an interactive landing page and an AI-powered chatbot that helps users manage their health by offering personalized suggestions on fitness routines, nutrition, sleep improvement, and stress management. The platform aims to make preventive healthcare accessible and engaging by providing instant, reliable, and customized health insights. Users can interact with the chatbot to receive feedback on their habits, enabling them to make informed decisions for a balanced lifestyle. The web interface is designed to be intuitive and visually appealing, allowing users to explore sections such as About Us, Health Insights, and AI Assistant Introduction. By merging artificial intelligence with user-centered web design, Apex Vitality demonstrates how technology can be effectively used to enhance physical and mental well-being. It serves as a foundation for future expansion into advanced health management systems---such as integration with wearable devices, nutrition planners, and mental health tools. The project ultimately aspires to create a comprehensive digital ecosystem that supports individuals in maintaining their long-term wellness."}, {"id": "AI-164", "title": "AquaVerse --- A world of water intelligence", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Munish Katoch", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH7", "description": "AquaVerse is an AI-powered mobile app that provides real-time beach safety and recreational suitability insights using INCOIS API data. It integrates geospatial visualization, machine learning predictions, and an interactive chatbot, AquaVerse.ai, to assess risk levels and offer personalized alerts. Built with Flutter, it promotes safe and sustainable coastal tourism through real-time analysis, notifications, and intelligent recommendations."}, {"id": "AI-165", "title": "Artificial Inteligence Based Plant/Crop Disease Detection and Prevention System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Business Model", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Lalit Verma", "sitting_place": "27-207-CH15", "description": "This project focuses on developing an AI-powered system that detects and prevents plant or crop diseases at an early stage using image processing and machine learning techniques. By capturing images of plant leaves through a camera or mobile device, the system analyzes visual features such as color, texture, and shape to identify symptoms of common diseases. Once a disease is detected, the system provides preventive measures and treatment suggestions to the farmer. The project helps in minimizing crop loss, improving yield quality, and promoting smart farming practices through real-time, data-driven decision-making."}, {"id": "AI-166", "title": "Augmenting the INGRES Virtual Assistant with Causal Inference Networks: A Data-Driven Reasoning using LLM Architecture for Evidence-Based Water Policy Simulation and Recommendation", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Bhupinder Singh", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH16", "description": "An AI-powered chatbot integrated with the INGRES system that uses causal inference and LLM based reasoning to provide intelligent, data-driven responses about groundwater resources. It enables users to query, analyze, and simulate water policies through natural language, making groundwater data access simple, interactive, and evidence-based."}, {"id": "AI-167", "title": "Automated Attendance System for Rural Schools.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Vinay Bhardwaj", "sitting_place": "34-202-CH39", "description": "The Automated Attendance System for Rural Schools is designed to simplify and digitize student attendance using low-cost technologies like RFID, biometrics, or mobile apps. It reduces manual effort, prevents errors, ensures accurate record-keeping, and provides real-time reports for teachers and administrators, helping improve efficiency, transparency, and educational outcomes in rural communities."}, {"id": "AI-168", "title": "Automated Detection of Misleading News Content Using Machine Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Heena( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "The widespread circulation of misleading information across digital platforms has created an urgent need for automated detection methods. This project applies machine learning techniques to classify news articles as real or fake based on linguistic patterns and textual features. A labeled dataset undergoes preprocessing steps such as text cleaning, tokenization, and feature extraction using TF IDF. Multiple models, including Logistic Regression, Naive Bayes, and SVM, are trained and evaluated using accuracy and F1-score metrics. The results demonstrate that machine learning provides an effective and reliable approach for identifying misleading news content and supporting misinformation prevention efforts."}, {"id": "AI-169", "title": "Automated Morphological Processing on Low Resource language Using Deep Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Abhinav Singh", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH11", "description": "This project aims to design and implement an automated morphological analyzer for Kokborok, a low-resource Tibeto-Burman language with minimal annotated data. The system leverages a parallel English--Kokborok corpus (Bible translations), where Part-of-Speech tags and lemmas are automatically transferred from English to Kokborok. Additionally, an unsupervised segmentation model (Morfessor) is trained to decompose Kokborok words into prefixes, roots, and suffixes, generating BIO-style segmentation labels. The annotated corpus is used to train a BiLSTM+CRF model that jointly predicts POS tags, lemmas, and morphological segmentation. The resulting analyzer demonstrates how weak supervision and unsupervised techniques can bootstrap NLP tools for under-resourced languages, creating both a dataset and a working model."}, {"id": "AI-170", "title": "Automated Student Attendance Monitoring and Analytics System Using Face Recognition", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Automated Student Attendance Monitoring and Analytics System for Colleges ( PS No - SIH25016 )", "supervisor": "Dr. Mohit Arora", "sitting_place": "28-202-C1", "description": "This project develops an automated, cloud-based student attendance system using face recognition. It captures real-time images, identifies students through AI/ML models, and records attendance in Firebase. The system removes proxy attendance, provides real-time analytics, supports multiple classrooms, and streamlines academic management."}, {"id": "AI-171", "title": "Automated Trash Classification using Machine Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Dr. Tanima Thakur", "sitting_place": "27-205-CH10", "description": "Due to the rapid growth of urbanization, our recycling bins should no longer be considered optional but mandatory through automated waste classification systems. Traditional manual sorting is inefficient and error-prone, much like trying to organize a hoarder's garage blindfolded. Keeping this in mind, our system enables automatic trash classification into distinct categories such as paper, plastic and many more. Using various feature engineering and machine learning models, we will categorize trash into further meaningful categories"}, {"id": "AI-172", "title": "Automatic classification of Guava fruit diseases using a deep neural network model", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Research Paper from google scholar", "supervisor": "Ajay Kumar Badhan", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH31", "description": "Fruit diseases reduce crop quality and cause economic loss. Manual disease identification is slow and error-prone. Existing models vary in performance and efficiency. This research compares multiple deep learning algorithms and proposes an optimized model for accurate fruit disease classification using public datasets."}, {"id": "AI-173", "title": "Autonomous Drone-Based System for Controlled and Sustainable Pesticide Spraying in Agriculture", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Indu Bala", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH10", "description": "This project aims to design and develop an autonomous drone system that can intelligently spray pesticides on agricultural fields in a controlled, efficient, and environmentally sustainable manner. Using AI, computer vision, and IoT-based sensors, the drone will identify crop areas affected by pests and determine the optimal quantity and spray pattern required. The system minimizes human exposure to harmful chemicals, reduces pesticide wastage, and ensures uniform coverage across the fields. Additionally, it helps in monitoring crop health and contributes to precision agriculture, improving both productivity and sustainability in farming practices."}, {"id": "AI-174", "title": "AyuSense: An AI-Driven Symptom Checker for Panchakarma and Telemedicine", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH : Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Ishita Malhotra", "sitting_place": "26-205-CH12", "description": "This project, \"ML-based Symptom Checker for Panchakarma and Telemedicine,\" uses Artificial Intelligence to analyze patient symptoms and predict possible conditions. By applying NLP for text understanding and Machine Learning for disease prediction and therapy recommendation, the system supports automated triage and suggests suitable Ayurvedic or Panchakarma treatments, improving accessibility and efficiency in telemedicine services."}, {"id": "AI-175", "title": "Bias detection in pre-trained models", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH2024", "supervisor": "Dr. Archana Chhabra", "sitting_place": "34-207-CH16", "description": "the goal of bias detection is to make it eligible for mitigation and useful for the improvement of other AIs. This is why, not only is it required to work with the technical front, but also working with a disciplined approach is required. By analyzing important documents like \"Data statements\", ensuring the validity of our measures, and getting lessons from psychometric sectors, we can move towards justice."}, {"id": "AI-176", "title": "Blockchain-Based Security Framework with NLP Integration for Unstructured Clinical Data Management", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Research based", "supervisor": "Richa Sharma", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH21", "description": "To address the challenges of securing unstructured clinical data while ensuring scalability, this problem statement combines blockchain technology, NLP, and Layer 2 solutions. Blockchain provides tamper-proof data integrity and secure sharing, while NLP processes unstructured medical records like physician notes or imaging reports. However, high transaction volumes in clinical systems risk blockchain congestion, necessitating Layer 2 protocols (e.g., Lightning Network) to offload data processing and maintain scalability. The research focuses on designing a hybrid framework where NLP-extracted insights are securely stored on a Layer 2-optimized blockchain, enabling efficient, auditable, and privacy-preserving healthcare data management."}, {"id": "AI-177", "title": "Brain Tumor Detection and Classification from MRI Scans using Deep Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "SIH 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Nikita", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH11", "description": "Brain tumor detection involves analyzing MRI (Magnetic Resonance Imaging) scans to automatically identify whether a brain tumor is present, and if so, classify its type (e.g. glioma, meningioma, pituitary) or characterize its features. The project will use supervised deep learning methods (CNNs, transfer learning) on publicly available MRI datasets. It may include segmentation (marking tumor region) and/or classification (which tumor type). The end goal is a tool where a user (doctor or technician) can upload an MRI image and receive a prediction +, if possible, the tumor region highlighted, with explainability components (e.g. heatmaps) to support trust and interpretability. Novelty: 1. Segmentation + Classification Cascade with Explainability:Instead of only classification, include segmentation (tumor boundary) to pinpoint region + use explainability (Grad-CAM or similar) so the model can show why it's making its prediction. Some papers do this with Mask-RCNN + classification. 2. Comparison of Detection & Segmentation Algorithms: Not just building one model, but comparing object detection networks (like YOLO, Faster R-CNN, SSD) + segmentation networks (U-Net, Mask RCNN) to see trade-offs in accuracy vs inference speed vs model size. 3. Using Augmented Data / Synthetic Data: Augmenting data using advanced augmentation techniques, or perhaps generating synthetic MRI images to balance classes / simulate rare tumor types."}, {"id": "AI-178", "title": "Breed Recognition for Indian Cattle and Buffaloes", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH: Smart Indian Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Khalid Hafiz Mir", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH16", "description": "DESCRIPTION OF THE INVENTION: It is an intelligent system integrating hardware with AI for breed identification of Indian buffaloes and cattle. It functions through six primary steps. First, clear photographs of animals under normal farming conditions are taken by drones or cameras. Then, noise removal, brightness adjustments, and normalization of them for proper AI decoding are carried out on these photographs. Then, photographs are transferred to an AI/ML unit where deep learning architecture such as CNNs and Vision Transformers examine important features such as hump, horns, face, and body form to arrive at the breed. To make it operable in rural locations where there is no availability of the internet, an edge device such as Raspberry Pi, Jetson Nano, or TPU executes the AI model on the local machine. Once determined, the breed is shown to the farmer through a mobile application or a small display screen with a pile of confidence to express the system's confidence. Finally, records of the data could be stored locally or in the cloud for records of the animals as well as for sharing with the agency of the governments for a census of livestock or wider surveillance."}, {"id": "AI-179", "title": "Browser-Based Face Liveness Detection to Prevent Spoofing Attacks", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Abhinav Singh", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH11", "description": "This project focuses on developing a browser-based face liveness detection system designed to prevent spoofing attacks during online identity verification. The system uses a compact machine learning model that runs directly within web browsers through frameworks like TensorFlow.js or ONNX.js, removing the need for server-side processing and ensuring data privacy. The proposed model can detect whether the face presented to the camera is real or fake by analyzing subtle cues such as movement, depth, and texture. Optimized for performance, the model size remains under 5 MB, and detection completes in under 500 milliseconds, making it suitable for low-bandwidth environments. This solution can be integrated into digital identity systems like Aadhaar authentication, enhancing both security and user experience. The final prototype demonstrates real-time face spoofing prevention with measurable accuracy and efficiency, contributing to safer, more reliable web-based biometric authentication."}, {"id": "AI-180", "title": "Causal and Explainable Machine Learning for Bias Reduction in Decision-Making Systems", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Self-identified based on recent research trends in Explainable AI and Causal Inference and research platform like ScienceDirect.", "supervisor": "Dr. Ravishanker", "sitting_place": "28-204-CH5", "description": "This research aims to enhance the reliability of machine learning systems by integrating explainable AI and causal inference. A predictive model will be developed and interpreted using SHAP to understand feature influence. Causal analysis using Do Why will identify cause-effect relationships and detect bias. The proposed system will improve transparency, fairness, and trust in decision-making processes."}, {"id": "AI-181", "title": "CNN-Based Tuberculosis Detection System with Data Augmentation and Regularization", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "(WHO)", "supervisor": "Konne Madhavi", "sitting_place": "26-205-CH7", "description": "This invention develops a CNN-based system for automated TB detection from chest X-rays, achieving 99.32% accuracy. It addresses manual diagnosis limitations, overfitting in deep learning, and generalization issues in existing AI models through data augmentation (rotation, flipping, scaling) and dropout regularization. The system includes preprocessing, CNN architecture with three dropout layers, SVM benchmarking, and explainability via Grad-CAM. It offers scalable deployment for resource-limited settings, outperforming MEGB (96.42%) and SVM (93%)."}, {"id": "AI-182", "title": "Comparative Analysis of Machine Learning Models for Diabetes Prediction and Risk Stratification", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Diabetes Prediction and Risk Stratification", "supervisor": "Dr.Varsha", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "Diabetes mellitus is one of the fastest-growing global health concerns, requiring effective predictive systems to support early detection and timely intervention. This research investigates the application of multiple machine learning techniques for diabetes prediction and risk stratification using patient health records. The study employs both supervised and unsupervised learning approaches, including Linear Regression, Logistic Regression, and K-Means clustering, to explore different dimensions of predictive modeling. Logistic Regression is applied to classify patients as diabetic or non-diabetic based on clinical indicators such as glucose level, BMI, age, and family history, while Linear Regression is used to predict continuous risk scores. In parallel, K-Means clustering is utilized to group patients into distinct risk categories, offering an unsupervised perspective on hidden patterns within the dataset. The models are evaluated using accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score, and clustering metrics to assess their performance. The findings are expected to highlight trade-offs between interpretability and predictive power, demonstrating how machine learning can aid in early detection, personalized risk assessment, and preventive healthcare strategies for diabetes management."}, {"id": "AI-183", "title": "Comparative Effectiveness of AI/ML Methods for Stock Market Forecasting: Focused on Regional Context ,Robustness and Practical Utility", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Research", "supervisor": "Kamalpreet Kaur Bagral", "sitting_place": "34-205-CH9", "description": "This project evaluates the comparative effectiveness of AI and machine-learning methods for stock market forecasting, emphasizing regional market characteristics, model robustness, and real-world applicability. It assesses accuracy, stability under volatility, and practical utility for informed financial decision-making."}, {"id": "AI-184", "title": "Conjunctiva Image-Based Anemia Detection Using a Hybrid VGG16 and Random Forest", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Business Model", "source": "Inspired by research papers on medical image-based anemia detection (IEEE, Kaggle).", "supervisor": "Akshay Kumar", "sitting_place": "28-204-CH13", "description": "This project focuses on detecting anemia using conjunctiva (inner eyelid) images with the help of deep learning and machine learning techniques. The VGG16 model is used for feature extraction from conjunctiva images, and the Random Forest algorithm is used for final classification of anemic and non-anemic cases. This hybrid approach improves accuracy and provides a non-invasive, fast, and cost-effective method for early anemia detection without requiring blood tests."}, {"id": "AI-185", "title": "Context-Aware Explainable Intelligent System for Story Point Prediction in Scrum Projects using Hybrid Machine Learning Models", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Faculty Proposed Research Topic based on recent advancements in Explainable Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning for Agile Software Effort Estimation", "supervisor": "Dr. Mohit Arora", "sitting_place": "28-202-C1", "description": "This project aims to develop a context-aware intelligent system to predict story points in Scrum-based Agile software projects using hybrid machine learning models. The system will analyze user story text and contextual project attributes to estimate effort. Explainable AI techniques will be incorporated to interpret predictions and support Scrum teams in improving estimation accuracy and sprint planning."}, {"id": "AI-186", "title": "Continuous Healthcare Monitoring: IoT meets CNN in real-time medical imaging", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart Community Health Monitoring and Early Warning System for Water-Borne Diseases in Rural Northeast India , SIH25001", "supervisor": "Deepali Kumari( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This project integrates IoT-based continuous patient monitoring with CNN-driven real-time medical imaging analysis. IoT sensors collect physiological data, while CNN models process imaging data to detect anomalies instantly. The system provides early warnings and cloud-based dashboards for doctors and caregivers, enabling preventive healthcare and remote patient monitoring under the SIH 2025 HealthTech theme."}, {"id": "AI-187", "title": "Crime Prediction and Detection using Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning: A Systematic Literature Review", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Review", "source": "IEEE Xplore, ScienceDirect, Book Chapter and Elsevier", "supervisor": "Tiyas Sarkar", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH24", "description": "Prediction and detection of crime using artificial intelligence and machine learning is an extensive field of study that helps us to improve public safety law enforcement and efficiency this study reviews deep learning techniques data mining techniques that are applied for crime analytics The hybrid and deep learning models achieve higher accuracy compared to traditional approaches particularly in special tempo- ral crime prediction tasks resulting in analysing and predicting data that changes across both geographic spaces and time it identifies patterns such as impact of crime and occurrence of crime by modelling how nearby data points and trend line influence current of solution"}, {"id": "AI-188", "title": "Crisis Map: Real-Time Distress Detection from Social Media", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "real-world humanitarian needs", "supervisor": "Jaspreet Kaur", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH17", "description": "This project focuses on Content Lifecycle Management (CLM) using a Microservices Architecture to efficiently manage the processes of content creation, storage, distribution, and archiving. The system is designed for scalability, flexibility, and fault tolerance by dividing the architecture into independent, well-defined microservices. The architecture consists of services like Content Creation, Version Control, Storage Management, User Authentication, and Analytics. Each service functions independently and communicates through RESTful APIs or message queues, ensuring loose coupling and easy maintenance. The Content Creation Service supports real-time collaboration, while the Version Control Service maintains complete version histories. The Storage Management Service manages file storage, metadata, and retrieval to ensure data integrity and consistency across distributed systems. Using Docker and Kubernetes, services are containerized for easy deployment, scalability, and fault recovery. The system uses asynchronous communication through APIs and message brokers to enhance reliability and performance. Security is implemented through JWT-based authentication and Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) to ensure secure and authorized data access. For performance monitoring, tools like Prometheus and Grafana are integrated to track system health and uptime. This project demonstrates the advantages of shifting from a monolithic to a microservices-based architecture by improving modularity, scalability, and collaboration. Overall, it delivers a robust, efficient, and secure solution for modern enterprise-level content management."}, {"id": "AI-189", "title": "Crop Damage Estimation and Recovery Planning Post-Disaster using Machine Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Abrar Ahmed Raza", "sitting_place": "27-209-CH10", "description": "The goal of this research is to create an AI-powered system that can calculate crop damage after natural disasters like droughts or floods. The system evaluates pre- and post-disaster data using satellite images and machine learning algorithms to precisely estimate crop loss, pinpoint impacted areas, and offer data-supported recovery and replanting suggestions. Reducing evaluation delays and facilitating quicker compensation processing are the goals of the solution."}, {"id": "AI-190", "title": "Crop Recommendation & Fertilizer Advisor (CropOra)", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India hackathon", "supervisor": "Yuvraj Singh", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH26", "description": "Agriculture is crucial to India, yet many farmers rely on traditional or non-scientific methods when choosing crops and fertilizers, leading to low yield and soil degradation. This project provides a data-driven solution using Machine Learning to recommend the most suitable crop and the correct fertilizer based on soil nutrients (N, P, K, pH), climate factors (temperature, humidity, rainfall), and regional data. Supervised ML models such as Random Forest or SVM are trained on agricultural datasets to learn which crop grows best under specific soil-weather conditions. Users can input real-time soil data through a web or mobile interface, and the system predicts the ideal crop. A second model suggests appropriate fertilizer ratios to maintain soil health and improve productivity. The system includes a multilingual AI chatbot for farmer-friendly guidance and supports offline usage for rural areas with low connectivity. It is developed using Python (Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-learn) and deployed via Flask/Django with visualization dashboards. This solution promotes precision farming, reduces fertilizer misuse, increases crop yield, and aligns with Sustainable Agriculture and Smart India Hackathon (SIH) objectives---empowering farmers with simple, scientific, and scalable decision support."}, {"id": "AI-191", "title": "Crop Yield Prediction using Machine Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "AI powered crop yield prediction and optimization. (SIH25044)", "supervisor": "Dr. Harpreet Singh", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH9", "description": "This project focuses on developing a machine learning-based system for predicting crop yield using historical and real-time agricultural data such as soil quality, rainfall, temperature, humidity, and fertilizer usage. By applying algorithms like linear regression, decision trees, and random forests, the system identifies patterns between environmental factors and crop productivity to generate accurate yield predictions. It features a user-friendly interface where farmers and stakeholders can input relevant data and receive predictions along with recommendations for improving output. The system can also integrate external sources such as weather data and satellite information to enhance accuracy and reliability. A robust back-end processes the data and executes predictive models, while a secure database stores past records for continuous learning and performance improvement. This solution enables farmers to make informed decisions regarding crop selection, irrigation, and resource management, reducing risks and increasing efficiency. Additionally, it supports agricultural planners and policymakers in optimizing food production strategies. Overall, the project promotes data-driven and sustainable farming practices, improves productivity, and contributes to better resource utilization in the agriculture sector."}, {"id": "AI-192", "title": "Croptreat - AI based integration system for plant leaf disease detection & weed classification", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH25099", "supervisor": "Aman Rao", "sitting_place": "34-202-CH30", "description": "\"CropTreat is an intelligent, AI-based integrated system developed to revolutionize modern agriculture by enabling precise plant leaf disease detection and weed classification. The system uses advanced computer vision and deep learning algorithms to analyze crop images captured through smartphones, drones, or cameras, identifying early signs of disease and distinguishing between healthy plants and harmful weeds. By processing these images, CropTreat detects visual symptoms such as color changes, spots, or texture variations on leaves, accurately classifies the type of disease, and provides actionable insights to farmers for timely intervention. The weed classification feature helps in recognizing various weed species that compete with crops for nutrients and sunlight, allowing for selective removal or controlled herbicide application. This not only reduces the cost of pesticide use but also minimizes environmental damage caused by excessive chemical spraying. CropTreat's AI model continuously learns from new datasets, improving its accuracy and adaptability across different crops, climates, and soil conditions. With a user-friendly mobile and web interface, it empowers farmers to monitor crop health in real time, receive instant recommendations, and maintain digital records of their fields. By integrating technology and agriculture, CropTreat promotes sustainable farming practices, enhances productivity, reduces manual labor, and supports farmers in making data-driven decisions for healthier crops and higher yields, marking a major step toward the future of smart agriculture. \""}, {"id": "AI-193", "title": "Crowdsourced Civic lssue Reporting and Resolution System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Vinay Bhardwaj", "sitting_place": "34-202-CH39", "description": "Municipalities struggle to discover, prioritize, and resolve local infrastructure and public-service problems (potholes, broken streetlights, illegal dumping, water leaks, etc.) in a timely, transparent, and resource-efficient way. Crowdsourced reporting from citizens can increase coverage and speed, but raises challenges in quality, prioritization, privacy, engagement, and integration with municipal workflows."}, {"id": "AI-194", "title": "Crowdsourced Civic lssue Reporting and Resolution System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH: Smart Indian Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Anzah Bashir", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH17", "description": "The Crowdsourced Civic Issue Reporting and Resolution System is a web-based platform designed to bridge the gap between citizens and local authorities by enabling real-time reporting and resolution of civic issues such as potholes, garbage accumulation, streetlight failures, and water leakage. The system empowers citizens to report problems by submitting detailed descriptions, images, and location data, which are then directed to the appropriate government departments for prompt action. It ensures transparency, accountability, and efficient communication between the public and officials. The backend is developed using Node.js and Express.js, while MongoDB serves as the database for storing user and issue details. The frontend, built with React.js, provides an intuitive and user-friendly interface for both citizens and administrators. Citizens can track the status of their submitted issues, while administrators can manage reports, update resolutions, and monitor progress through an interactive dashboard."}, {"id": "AI-195", "title": "Cyberattack Prediction using TabTransformer", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Anurag Tewari", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH14", "description": "This project aims to develop a robust cyberattack prediction system using deep learning, specifically the TabTransformer model, on a heterogeneous cybersecurity dataset containing 40,000 records and 25 network-related features. The objective is to accurately classify and predict potential cyberattacks by learning complex relationships between numerical and categorical features such as IP address, protocol, severity level, and traffic type. The TabTransformer architecture leverages attention mechanisms to capture dependencies between categorical embeddings, providing superior performance over traditional machine learning models like Random Forest or XGBoost. The system not only enhances real-time detection capability but also enables the creation of a deployable web application for network administrators to monitor, predict, and mitigate cyber threats efficiently. By integrating deep learning with cybersecurity, the project contributes to strengthening digital resilience and proactive defense against evolving cyberattacks."}, {"id": "AI-196", "title": "Deep Learning Approaches for Brain Tumor Detection", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Self", "supervisor": "Dr. Gursharan Singh", "sitting_place": "28-202-C2", "description": "This paper presents a systematic review of deep learning techniques for brain tumor detection using MRI, highlighting the evolution from traditional machine learning methods with handcrafted features to advanced deep learning models such as CNNs, U-Net architectures, and transformer-based hybrids. It emphasizes that deep learning provides superior performance in tumor segmentation and classification due to its ability to learn complex features automatically, but also identifies key challenges including limited generalization across datasets, high computational requirements, lack of interpretability, and insufficient clinical validation. The paper further explores hybrid models and Explainable AI approaches to improve both accuracy and trust in predictions, and concludes by suggesting future directions such as lightweight model design, multi-institutional data usage, and better integration of explainable AI for real-world clinical deployment."}, {"id": "AI-197", "title": "Deep Learning Based Automated Detection of Diabetic Retinopathy Using Retinal Fundus Image Analysis", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Recent research trends in Artificial Intelligence in Healthcare and Medical Image Analysis, inspired by publicly available retinal image datasets and advancements in deep learning for disease detection.", "supervisor": "Dr. Richa Jain", "sitting_place": "27-209-C1", "description": "This project aims to develop a deep learning-based system for the automated detection of Diabetic Retinopathy using retinal fundus images. The proposed model will analyze medical images of the retina to identify early signs of the disease. Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) will be used to classify retinal images into different stages of diabetic retinopathy to assist early diagnosis."}, {"id": "AI-198", "title": "Deep Learning based early disease detection in Legume crops", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Kaggle and SIH 2025", "supervisor": "Apoorv Dubey", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH23", "description": "The primary objective is to evaluate how effectively deep learning models can detect diseases at an early stage compared to traditional observation methods. Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), along with selected lightweight or transfer learning architectures, will be explored for feature extraction and classification, particularly under conditions where symptoms are not visually prominent."}, {"id": "AI-199", "title": "Deep Learning Based Network Intrusion Detection Systems: Innovations in Architectures, Performance Optimization and Adversarial Robustness", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Maneet Kaur", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH18", "description": "This research focuses on analysing deep learning-based Network Intrusion Detection Systems (NIDS) by comparing multiple architectures including CNN, LSTM, Transformer, GAN, and Graph Neural Networks. The study evaluates performance across benchmark datasets and analyses robustness against adversarial attacks such as FGSM and PGD. The objective is to identify optimal architectures that balance detection accuracy, computational efficiency, and security robustness for real-world deployment."}, {"id": "AI-200", "title": "Deep Learning for Skin Cancer Detection: A Convolutional Neural Network Apporach", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SDG", "supervisor": "Arvind Kumar Bhatia", "sitting_place": "27-204-CH6", "description": "Deep Learning for Skin Cancer Detection: A Convolutional Neural Network Approach. This study explores the application of deep learning for skin cancer detection using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Three models were developed and trained on a dataset of 2,239 training images and 118 test images across nine skin lesion classes. Initial models faced challenges due to class imbalance and overfitting. To address these issues, data augmentation techniques and dropout layers were implemented, significantly improving performance. Further enhancement was achieved by balancing the dataset using Augmentor, resulting in 9,000 augmented images. The final model achieved a training accuracy of \\~95% and validation accuracy of \\~90%. This iterative approach highlights the importance of addressing class imbalance and leveraging data augmentation in medical imaging tasks, demonstrating the potential of CNNs for accurate and robust skin cancer classification."}, {"id": "AI-201", "title": "Deep Learning-Based Approaches for Pulmonary Embolism Detection and Risk Assessment", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "AI Applications in healthcare", "supervisor": "Dr. Ankita Wadhawan", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH16", "description": "Pulmonary embolism (PE) is a severe and potentially fatal cardiovascular condition caused by the blockage of pulmonary arteries due to blood clots. Early diagnosis is crucial for preventing complications, but traditional diagnostic methods, such as CT pulmonary angiography (CTPA) and D-dimer tests, often have limitations in accuracy, accessibility, and time efficiency. This research aims to develop a machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL)-based framework for the automated detection and risk assessment of pulmonary embolism using clinical and imaging data. The proposed methodology will integrate multiple data sources, including patient demographics, vital signs, laboratory test results, and radiological images, to improve prediction accuracy. Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) will be employed for analyzing medical images, such as CTPA scans, to detect embolic blockages with high precision. Additionally, ensemble ML techniques, including Random Forest and XGBoost, will be utilized to classify PE severity based on patient-specific risk factors. A key component of this research is the incorporation of Explainable AI (XAI) techniques to enhance model interpretability, ensuring that the AI-driven predictions align with clinical decision-making standards. The study will also compare the performance of traditional diagnostic approaches with AI-based models to highlight potential improvements in sensitivity, specificity, and overall efficiency. The expected outcome of this research is an AI-powered decision-support system that can assist healthcare professionals in early PE detection, risk stratification, and personalized treatment planning. This project has the potential to improve patient outcomes by reducing diagnostic delays, minimizing false positives, and optimizing resource allocation in emergency care settings."}, {"id": "AI-202", "title": "Deep Learning-Based Facial Emotion Recognition System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Jimmy Singla", "sitting_place": "28-204-C2", "description": "The project aims to develop a system capable of automatically recognizing human emotions from facial expressions using deep learning techniques. By analyzing facial features such as eyes, mouth, and eyebrows, the system can classify emotions like happiness, sadness, anger, surprise, fear, and disgust. The model leverages convolutional neural networks (CNNs) or other deep learning architectures to achieve high accuracy in emotion detection. This technology has applications in human-computer interaction, mental health monitoring, driver safety systems, and social robotics."}, {"id": "AI-203", "title": "Deep Learning-Based Facial Expression Recognition and Emotion-Aware Music Recommendation System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "SIH2025", "supervisor": "Upinder Kaur", "sitting_place": "27-209-CH6", "description": "This project aims to develop an AI-powered, NextGenAI-based emotion-aware music recommendation system that interprets real-time facial, vocal, and contextual emotional data with high accuracy. It leverages cutting-edge deep learning techniques such as Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Vision Transformers (ViTs) to detect micro-expressions and subtle emotional cues. Through a fusion of multimodal emotion analysis, the system dynamically adapts playlists in real time, ensuring an emotionally synchronized and personalized music experience."}, {"id": "AI-204", "title": "Deep Learning-Based Image Classification Framework for Distinguishing Cattle and Buffaloes in Livestock Management", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH2025(25005)", "supervisor": "Nitish Kumar", "sitting_place": "27-207-CH11", "description": "This project aims to develop a deep learning-based image classification framework to accurately distinguish between cattle and buffaloes. Using convolutional neural networks and transfer learning, the system will analyze livestock images and automate species identification. The model will support smart livestock management, enhancing productivity, monitoring, and data-driven decision-making in the agriculture sector."}, {"id": "AI-205", "title": "Deep Learning-Based Integrated System for Crop Disease Detection and Yield Prediction", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Anurag Tewari", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH14", "description": "This paper proposes an AI-based intrusion detection and threat intelligence framework using CNN, BiLSTM, and Attention mechanisms to detect modern cyberattacks in complex network environments. It integrates deep learning with threat intelligence correlation to improve anomaly detection, reduce false positives, and prioritize alerts for analysts. Evaluated on CICIDS2017 and CIC-IoT2023 datasets, the model achieved 98.7% accuracy, outperforming traditional IDS approaches and adapting effectively to evolving threats."}, {"id": "AI-206", "title": "Deep Learning-Based Smart Home Intrusion Detection System Using IoT Network Traffic Analysis", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH2026", "supervisor": "Aman Deep", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH32", "description": "This project focuses on developing a Deep Learning-Based Smart Home Intrusion Detection System using IoT network traffic data, addressing the growing need for improved security in smart home environments where traditional systems struggle to detect complex and unknown cyberattacks. Existing solutions, such as the supervised machine learning approach proposed in the base paper , show high accuracy but lack scalability, real-time capability, and effectiveness against evolving threats. The objective of this research is to design and implement a more robust intrusion detection system that enhances detection accuracy and identifies both known and unknown attacks in real time. To achieve this, the project will utilize deep learning techniques such as Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) and/or Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) models applied to publicly available IoT datasets (e.g., IoT-23 or TON-IoT), along with preprocessing and feature extraction methods for network traffic analysis. The expected outcome is a high-performance, scalable, and efficient intrusion detection system that outperforms traditional machine learning models in terms of accuracy, detection rate, and adaptability, making it suitable for practical smart home security applications."}, {"id": "AI-207", "title": "Deep Learning-Based Traffic Prediction System Using YOLO", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Abhinav Singh", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH11", "description": "Deep Learning-Based Traffic Prediction System Using YOLO focuses on developing an intelligent system that uses YOLO (You Only Look Once) object detection to identify and count vehicles from real-time video streams. The detected data is then analyzed using deep learning techniques to predict traffic flow and congestion patterns. This approach enables accurate, fast, and automated traffic monitoring, helping in better decision-making for traffic management and smart city planning."}, {"id": "AI-208", "title": "Deepfake-Resistant Biometric Access Control System and Method", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "(Smart India Hackathon )", "supervisor": "Rakesh Gagneja", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH23", "description": "It proposes an AI/ML-based privacy-preserving deepfake detection system, using federated learning with CNN architecture for the real-time detection of face-swap videos. It looks for facial inconsistencies, temporal artifacts, and identity-spoofing patterns in distributed datasets without aggregating sensitive data. It is aimed at biometric controls for access, facial recognition systems, enterprise security, and banking authentications to ensure strong verification and no unauthorized access."}, {"id": "AI-209", "title": "DermaXAI: CBAM-Driven Multi-Model Ensemble for Fine-Grained and Explainable Dermatological Analysis", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "CICPS 2026", "supervisor": "Danish Meiraj", "sitting_place": "28-204-CH18", "description": "DermaXAI is an AI-driven dermatological analysis system that integrates CBAM-enhanced deep learning models with a multi-model ensemble to enable fine-grained classification of skin conditions from images. The system incorporates explainable AI techniques to provide transparent, interpretable predictions, supporting early diagnosis, improved clinical decision-making, and accessible smart health monitoring."}, {"id": "AI-210", "title": "Design an AI-Driven Framework for Automated Research Paper Generation and Validation", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25231", "supervisor": "Dr. Ankita Wadhawan", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH16", "description": "The proposed topic focuses on leveraging artificial intelligence to automate and enhance the research paper generation process. With the rapid advancement of natural language processing (NLP) and large language models (LLMs), AI systems can assist in literature review, idea generation, structuring, drafting, and even citation management. This research aims to design an intelligent framework that integrates machine learning and NLP techniques to generate coherent, context-aware, and academically structured research papers."}, {"id": "AI-211", "title": "Design and Development of a Novel Machine Learning-based System for Medical Diagnosis", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:2024", "supervisor": "Dr. Jimmy Singla", "sitting_place": "28-204-C2", "description": "The Research work, \"Design and Development of a Machine Learning-based System for Medical Diagnosis,\" focuses on leveraging artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) techniques to enhance medical diagnosis processes. This system is aimed at supporting healthcare professionals in diagnosing medical conditions with greater accuracy and efficiency. It can be particularly beneficial in areas such as disease prediction, early detection, personalized treatment planning, and decision support. The core objective of the project is to develop a machine learning model that can analyze datasets---such as patient medical records, imaging data (like X-rays, MRIs, and CT scans), and lab results to provide insights that assist doctors in diagnosing a variety of health conditions. The system uses historical data to learn patterns and make predictions about the likelihood of a patient having a particular disease or medical condition."}, {"id": "AI-212", "title": "Design and Implementation of a Real-Time AI/ML-Based Framework for Phishing Detection and Prevention", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH2025", "supervisor": "Nitish Kumar", "sitting_place": "27-207-CH11", "description": "This project develops a real-time AI/ML-based framework for detecting and preventing phishing attacks across emails and websites. By leveraging machine learning algorithms to analyze URLs, content patterns, and user behavior, the system identifies malicious activities instantly. The framework enhances cybersecurity by providing adaptive, automated defense against evolving phishing threats."}, {"id": "AI-213", "title": "Design and Implementation of an AI-Based Real-Time Network Intrusion Detection and Monitoring System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/10934308", "supervisor": "Dr. Pushpender", "sitting_place": "36-307-C2", "description": "The proposed research project, titled \"Design and Implementation of an AI-Based Real-Time Network Intrusion Detection and Monitoring System,\" focuses on developing an intelligent cybersecurity framework capable of detecting and monitoring malicious network activities in real time. With the rapid expansion of digital infrastructure, cloud computing, IoT devices, and enterprise networks, cyber threats such as Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) attacks, malware infections, phishing attempts, and unauthorized access have become increasingly sophisticated. Traditional rule-based intrusion detection systems (IDS) often struggle to identify novel or evolving attack patterns. Therefore, integrating Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) techniques into network security systems has become essential for enhancing detection capabilities. The primary objective of this project is to design and implement a robust AI-driven intrusion detection system that can analyze network traffic data dynamically and accurately classify activities as normal or malicious. The system will leverage supervised and/or unsupervised machine learning algorithms such as Decision Trees, Random Forest, Support Vector Machines (SVM), K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN), and Deep Learning models like Artificial Neural Networks (ANN) or Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks. These algorithms will be trained to recognize patterns in network traffic and detect anomalies that may indicate cyberattacks. The proposed system architecture will consist of multiple modules, including data collection, data preprocessing, feature extraction, model training, real-time monitoring, and alert generation. Network traffic data will be captured using appropriate tools and converted into structured datasets. Data preprocessing techniques such as data cleaning, normalization, feature selection, and dimensionality reduction will be applied to enhance model efficiency and reduce computational complexity. Feature engineering will play a critical role in identifying significant attributes such as packet size, protocol type, connection duration, and traffic flow statistics. To evaluate the effectiveness of the proposed system, standard benchmark datasets such as NSL-KDD, CIC-IDS2017, or UNSW-NB15 will be used for training and testing. The performance of the implemented models will be assessed using widely accepted evaluation metrics including accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score, and Receiver Operating Characteristic (ROC) curve analysis. Special emphasis will be placed on minimizing false positives and false negatives to ensure reliable and practical deployment in real-world environments. In addition to offline testing, the system will be implemented in a simulated or controlled real-time network environment to monitor live traffic and generate alerts upon detection of suspicious activities. The monitoring dashboard will provide visual insights into traffic behavior, attack types, and system performance, enabling administrators to take immediate preventive actions."}, {"id": "AI-214", "title": "Design and Simulation of a Privacy-Preserving Social Media Platform using Federated Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon and Research Papers", "supervisor": "Ajay Kumar Badhan", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH31", "description": "Problem Statement: Social media platforms generate vast amounts of user data that are valuable for sentiment analysis and trend detection. However, centralized collection of this data raises significant privacy and security concerns. Federated Learning offers a decentralized alternative where models are trained across multiple devices without exposing raw user data, enabling privacy-preserving analytics. Problem Description: The project aims to design and simulate a federated learning framework for social media analytics. Multiple simulated clients collaboratively train sentiment analysis models without sharing raw posts. The system ensures user privacy while enabling real-time insights. Comparative analysis across ML models and FL algorithms will be conducted to evaluate trade-offs between accuracy, efficiency, and privacy."}, {"id": "AI-215", "title": "Detection of Malicious URL-Based Activities from IP Data Using Machine Learning Techniques", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH2025", "supervisor": "Nitish Kumar", "sitting_place": "27-207-CH11", "description": "This project aims to develop a machine learning-based system to detect and classify URL-based cyberattacks by analyzing IP traffic data. The model will identify malicious patterns, unusual request behaviors, and potential threats, contributing to enhanced network security, early intrusion detection, and improved resilience against evolving cyberattacks."}, {"id": "AI-216", "title": "Detection of Phishing with the Use of Machine Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Literature Review and Academic Research on Phishing Detection using Machine Learning", "supervisor": "Amandeep Kaur", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH23", "description": "This project focuses on detecting phishing websites using machine learning techniques. It analyzes features such as URL structure, domain information, and webpage content to identify malicious sites. Various models like SVM, Random Forest, and Naïve Bayes are studied and compared. The system aims to achieve high accuracy and improve cybersecurity by detecting evolving phishing attacks."}, {"id": "AI-217", "title": "Develop AI-Based Farmer Query Support and Advisory System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Shivani Sharma", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH15", "description": "This project proposes an AI-powered advisory system for farmers integrating emotional support, scenario-based simulations, waste-to-income mapping, crop insurance claim assistance, and a self-learning FAQ builder. The system provides personalized guidance, stress-aware responses, and data-driven decision support. It aims to enhance farmer well-being, improve productivity, reduce risks, and connect them with local markets, insurance, and expert networks using a scalable business model."}, {"id": "AI-218", "title": "Developement of Deepfake detection Model", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "NA", "supervisor": "Dr. Shivali Chopra", "sitting_place": "34-207-CH12", "description": "Deepfake detection focuses on identifying AI-generated media that manipulate videos, images, or audio to create realistic yet fake content. It employs deep learning, computer vision, and forensic analysis to detect inconsistencies in facial expressions, lip-syncing, or artifacts. Research aims to enhance detection accuracy, improve model robustness against adversarial attacks, and develop real-time, explainable, and efficient solutions for combating misinformation and digital fraud."}, {"id": "AI-219", "title": "Development of a Digital Mental Health and Psychological Support System for Students in Higher Education", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH 25092", "supervisor": "Dr. Bhupinder Singh", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH8", "description": "This project proposes the development and research implementation of an integrated framework to address two prevalent and co-occurring mental health challenges in higher education students: Adjustment Disorder with Mixed Anxiety and Depressed Mood, and Circadian Rhythm Sleep-Wake Disorders. The framework is designed to tackle the cyclical relationship where the stress of transitioning to university life triggers emotional distress, which in turn disrupts sleep patterns, creating a feedback loop that further impairs academic and social functioning. This initiative moves beyond generic support to offer a targeted, evidence-based approach. The core of this research implementation is a multi-component support framework that synergizes evidence-based psychological strategies for adjustment challenges with structured sleep health interventions. It integrates standardized assessment protocols, psychoeducational resources tailored for academic contexts, and clear pathways to existing counseling services. The framework is designed for seamless integration into existing student welfare ecosystems, providing a structured methodology for identifying at-risk students and delivering timely, context-specific support without the need for a standalone platform."}, {"id": "AI-220", "title": "Development of a Smart Digital Platform to Promote Eco & Cultural Tourism in Jharkhand", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2025 , Problem Statement ID: 25032", "supervisor": "Anzar Hussain Lone", "sitting_place": "33-205-CH8", "description": "Design and develop an AI-powered digital tourism platform (mobile app and/or website) for Jharkhand that offers: AI-based personalized itinerary planning and multilingual chatbot assistance for tourists. Blockchain-enabled secure transactions, guide verification, and digital certification for local service providers. Interactive maps and AR/VR previews of major tourist and cultural sites. Real-time transport and location info using geo-location. Integrated local marketplace for tribal handicrafts, events, homestays, and ecotourism. AI-driven feedback and sentiment analysis for continuous improvement. Analytics dashboard for tourism officials to monitor trends and impact."}, {"id": "AI-221", "title": "Development of AI/ML Based Solution for Detection of Face-Swap Based Deep Fake Videos", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart india hackathon (National Technical Research Organisation)", "supervisor": "Sandeep", "sitting_place": "33-205-CH18", "description": "This project aims to develop an AI/ML-based forensic solution for detecting face-swap deep fake videos. Using datasets like FaceForensics++, Celeb-DF, and DFDC-P, the system will analyze visual, audio, and temporal inconsistencies through CNN, RNN, LSTM, and hybrid models. The model will output authenticity reports highlighting abnormalities and deep fake characteristics to support digital media verification."}, {"id": "AI-222", "title": "Development of Map-Matching Algorithm using AI-ML Techniques to Distinguish Vehicular Movement on Highway and Service Road.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2024, Problem Statement (ID 1740)", "supervisor": "Raman Goyal", "sitting_place": "26-205-CH15", "description": "In modern urban environments, highways and adjacent service roads often run parallel, causing ambiguity in determining the exact route of a moving vehicle using standard GPS data. GPS inaccuracies, signal noise, and overlapping road networks make it challenging for conventional navigation systems to precisely identify whether a vehicle is traveling on a highway or the nearby service road. This leads to inefficiencies in traffic management, inaccurate toll calculations, route planning errors, and incorrect data for intelligent transportation systems (ITS). This project proposes to design and develop an Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) based map-matching algorithm capable of distinguishing vehicular movement on highways and service roads with high accuracy. The model will integrate spatial, temporal, and contextual data such as vehicle speed, heading direction, acceleration, lane geometry, and road topology. By employing advanced AI-ML techniques like neural networks and probabilistic modelling, the algorithm will correct GPS deviations, learn from historical movement patterns, and dynamically adapt to various driving environments. The solution aims to support traffic authorities, navigation systems, and autonomous vehicle platforms in achieving precise route classification and real-time decision-making."}, {"id": "AI-223", "title": "Diabetic foot Ulcers Detection using Deep learning Techniques", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Diabetic Foot Ulcer Grand Challenge 2024", "supervisor": "Dr. Ruby Singh", "sitting_place": "25-202-CH29", "description": "Image Processing is an essential field of computer vision that allows for the analysis, interpretation, and improvement of visual information gathered by digital images and video. It is central to many applications, such as medical imaging, autonomous vehicles, industrial automation, and satellite remote sensing. Classic image processing methods, like edge detection, histogram equalization, and morphological operations, relied on hand-designed features extraction. Though successful in controlled settings, these methods tended to falter when used with complicated and high- dimensional data, resulting in inconsistent performance. The development of an efficient and accurate deep learning model for Diabetic Foot Ulcer (DFU) detection requires a well-defined research methodology. This methodology broadly encompasses two major phases: data preprocessing and model building. Each phase is crucial for ensuring that the final model not only performs well on training data but also generalizes effectively to unseen clinical scenarios."}, {"id": "AI-224", "title": "Diabetic Retinopathy Detection using Deep Learning (ResNet50) and Flask Web Application", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon, WHO Diabetes Reports", "supervisor": "Divya Mahajan", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH20", "description": "This project focuses on early detection of diabetic retinopathy using Deep Learning techniques. A pre-trained ResNet50 model with transfer learning is applied on retinal images to classify disease stages. A Flask-based web application integrates the trained model, enabling users to upload retinal images and receive instant predictions. SQLite is used for database management. The system aims to assist doctors in diagnosis and improve healthcare accessibility."}, {"id": "AI-225", "title": "Digital Mental Health Support for College Students", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025: SIH25092", "supervisor": "Dr. Karan Bajaj( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "College life brings stress, anxiety, and pressure. Many students don't seek help because counselling is limited, hard to access, or feels stigmatizing. A digital system can give them safe, timely, and personalized support."}, {"id": "AI-226", "title": "Digital Psychological Intervention System for College Students", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Madhuri", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH4", "description": "The Digital Psychological Intervention System for College Students is a MERN-based web app offering AI-driven mental health support through chat assistance, counselor booking, and awareness resources. It ensures privacy, accessibility, and real-time help. Built using MongoDB, Express.js, React.js, and Node.js, it includes JWT authentication, Socket.io for live chat, and analytics dashboards to track well-being trends, deployed on platforms like AWS or Vercel for scalability and reliability"}, {"id": "AI-227", "title": "Digital Twin-Based AI System for Mental Health Monitoring in Academic Environments", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH: Smart Indian Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Khalid Hafiz Mir", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH16", "description": "The project \"Digital Twin-Based AI System for Mental Health Monitoring in Academic Environments\" develops an AI-driven platform to detect, monitor, and support student mental well-being. It provides personalized psychological first-aid, confidential counselling access, and peer support while offering institutions real-time analytics for early intervention and policy planning. The system ensures cultural relevance, privacy, and scalability across diverse academic settings."}, {"id": "AI-228", "title": "DocuChatAI -- Multi-Modal RAG Chatbot", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH 25231", "supervisor": "Vishal Khanna", "sitting_place": "26-205-CH16", "description": "The DocuChatAI -- Multi-Modal RAG Chatbot is an advanced conversational AI system designed to retrieve, analyze, and respond to user queries using both text and visual data. Built on the Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) architecture, the system intelligently combines large language models with document retrieval mechanisms to deliver accurate, context-aware answers. Unlike traditional chatbots limited to text inputs, DocuChatAI supports multi-modal interaction, enabling users to upload and query diverse data types such as PDFs, images, and documents. The chatbot processes this information through natural language understanding and multimodal embeddings, ensuring precise and explainable responses. This project aims to enhance information accessibility, automate document comprehension, and streamline knowledge discovery across various domains such as education, business, healthcare, and research."}, {"id": "AI-229", "title": "Early Prediction of Student Retention Based on Academic Performance", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Jimmy Singla", "sitting_place": "28-204-C2", "description": "This project work will focus on the early prediction of student retention using academic performance indicators. By analyzing data such as grades, attendance, and assessment scores, the model identifies students who are at risk of dropping out or discontinuing their studies. Early prediction enables educational institutions to implement timely interventions, provide academic support, and improve overall student success rates. Machine learning techniques, such as logistic regression, decision trees, or random forests, are often employed to build predictive models that help in monitoring and enhancing student retention effectively."}, {"id": "AI-230", "title": "Early Sepsis Prediction in ICU Patients Using Machine Learning Techniques", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:2026", "supervisor": "Dr. Jimmy Singla", "sitting_place": "28-204-C2", "description": "Sepsis is a critical and life-threatening condition that requires early detection to improve patient survival rates, especially in Intensive Care Units (ICUs). This research aims to develop a machine learning-based predictive model to identify the early onset of sepsis using patient data such as vital signs, laboratory test results, and clinical records. The study will involve preprocessing and analyzing ICU datasets, followed by the application of various machine learning algorithms such as Logistic Regression, Random Forest, Support Vector Machine, and Gradient Boosting. The performance of these models will be evaluated using metrics like accuracy, precision, recall, and AUC-ROC to identify the most effective approach. The proposed system is expected to assist healthcare professionals by providing early warnings of sepsis, enabling timely medical intervention. This can significantly reduce mortality rates, improve patient outcomes, and enhance decision-making in critical care environments."}, {"id": "AI-231", "title": "Early Warning System for Glacial Lake Outburst Floods", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Indu Bala", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH10", "description": "A system that detects early signs of Glacial Lake Outburst Floods using sensors and automated alerts. It continuously monitors water levels, temperature, and pressure around glacial lakes to warn nearby areas in advance. The project helps reduce loss of life and damage by improving disaster preparedness in mountain regions."}, {"id": "AI-232", "title": "EcoVision: AI-Powered Smart Waste Segregation and Monitoring System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25128", "supervisor": "Rakshit Bansal( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This project aims to design an AI and IoT-enabled waste management system that automatically detects, classifies, and sorts waste materials across the LPU campus. Using computer vision and smart sensors, the system will identify recyclable and non-recyclable items, optimize collection routes, and provide real-time monitoring through a dashboard. The goal is to promote eco-friendly practices and campus cleanliness automation."}, {"id": "AI-233", "title": "Edge-AI-based healthcare monitoring system", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Anurag Tewari", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH14", "description": "This project aims to develop an Edge-AI-based healthcare monitoring system capable of detecting health anomalies in real time without relying on cloud servers. Conventional healthcare monitoring solutions depend heavily on cloud-based processing, which often leads to issues such as high latency, data privacy risks, and unreliable connectivity in rural or remote areas. To overcome these challenges, this project focuses on integrating lightweight deep learning models optimized for on-device processing. These models analyze biomedical signals such as ECG and EEG to identify anomalies like arrhythmia, stress patterns, or epileptic activity with high accuracy. Techniques such as model compression, pruning, and quantization are applied to reduce computational complexity while maintaining performance. The system includes an intuitive dashboard interface that displays real-time health metrics and generates instant alerts for medical professionals when irregularities are detected. By enabling secure, fast, and continuous monitoring directly at the data source, this Edge-AI solution enhances accessibility to quality healthcare, particularly in underserved regions, and represents a significant step toward decentralized, intelligent medical diagnostics."}, {"id": "AI-234", "title": "Edge-Enabled Multimodal Deep Learning Framework for Real-Time Prediction of Airborne Fungal Diseases in Wheat", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH25268", "supervisor": "Dr. Ankita Wadhawan", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH16", "description": "This project aims to develop an edge-compatible multimodal AI system for real-time prediction of airborne fungal diseases in wheat across diverse agro-climatic zones. It begins with a comparative analysis of existing image-based, environmental, and multimodal approaches to identify gaps in accuracy, generalization, and deployability. An efficient image preprocessing and segmentation pipeline will be designed to extract relevant leaf and lesion regions from field images. A multimodal framework will then be developed by integrating visual features from CNN models with environmental parameters such as temperature and humidity, using suitable fusion strategies. The model will be trained, tested, and validated on cross-region datasets, optimized using techniques like quantization and pruning, and deployed on edge devices to ensure low-latency, real-time inference, with performance evaluated using standard metrics such as accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score, and inference time."}, {"id": "AI-235", "title": "Edge-Optimized Deep Learning for Real-Time Waste Detection and Classification in Smart Waste Management Systems: A Review", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH and Top Research papers", "supervisor": "Dr. Abhishek Bhattacherjee( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This review paper examines the use of deep learning and edge computing for real-time waste detection and classification in smart waste management systems. It analyzes over 150 research studies (2023--2025), covering object detection models such as YOLO, classification architectures such as EfficientNet, and optimization techniques including quantization, pruning, and knowledge distillation. The study highlights that although deep learning models achieve high accuracy, most are not optimized for resource-constrained edge devices. It identifies key research gaps, including the lack of integrated detection--classification pipelines, limited evaluation on edge hardware, and insufficient real-world datasets. The paper emphasizes the need for efficient, scalable, and deployable AI systems capable of real-time operation on edge devices to support sustainable and automated waste management solutions."}, {"id": "AI-236", "title": "EDU TRACK- A SMART LEARNING SUITE", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "https://www.sih.gov.in/sih2025PS", "supervisor": "Lalita", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH11", "description": "Indoor air pollution has emerged as a critical environmental and public health challenge due to rapid urbanizatigon and increased indoor exposure. The pollutants that are very dangerous in terms of human health include particulate matter (PM 2.5, PM 10), carbon monoxide (CO), nitrogen dioxide (NO 2 ), sulfur dioxide (SO 2 ), ozone (O 3 ) and ammonia (NH 3 ). Traditional air purification systems have a work based on the use of static control and are not adaptable to dynamic environmental changes, which leads to inefficient work and energy consumption."}, {"id": "AI-237", "title": "EduConnect: AI-Based Student Community Learning and Knowledge Sharing Platform", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Abhinav Singh", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH11", "description": "EduConnect is a full-stack web application designed to foster personalized peer-to-peer knowledge exchange among university students. It addresses the lack of personalized interaction and structured knowledge sharing in current online learning environments. The platform is built around five core AI/NLP components---including a Hybrid Content Recommender, an AI Discussion Summarizer, and a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) Mentor Chatbot---to make learning collaborative, personalized, and efficient. The project will demonstrate strong proficiency in Full-Stack Development, System Architecture, and the practical application of advanced Machine Learning for social good."}, {"id": "AI-238", "title": "Emotion-Aware Speech-to-Sign Language Converter with Cultural Gesture Adaptation", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH2020", "supervisor": "Dr. Harwinder Singh Sohal", "sitting_place": "26-205-CH10", "description": "A web-based application that translates live spoken language into Indian Sign Language (ISL) using a 3D avatar. The system detects nuanced emotions in speech and adapts signs accordingly for natural, real-time communication. It uses advanced speech recognition, natural language processing (NLP), and 3D animation for accessibility and inclusiveness. The system is culturally adapted for ISL and demonstrates a blend of AI, human-computer interaction, and linguistics"}, {"id": "AI-239", "title": "Enhancing Fight Detection in CCTV Videos Using Motion Analysis and Human Pose Estimation", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Self", "supervisor": "Dr. Chirag Sharma", "sitting_place": "27-207-C1", "description": "This research focuses on improving the detection of fights in CCTV footage by combining motion analysis with human pose estimation. By tracking body movements and identifying aggressive actions through pose dynamics and motion patterns, the system aims to accurately and efficiently detect violent behavior in real-time, enhancing surveillance capabilities for public safety."}, {"id": "AI-240", "title": "Enhancing Intrusion Detection Systems Using Generative AI Techniques.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Self discovered", "supervisor": "Pritam Sunil Mahajan( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This project aims to develop a robust Intrusion Detection System (IDS) by leveraging Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) to address the challenge of imbalanced datasets in network security. By generating high-fidelity synthetic malicious traffic, the system will enhance the training of traditional supervised learning classifiers. The objective is to improve the detection of 'Zero-Day' attacks and rare anomalies in known network environments while significantly reducing the False Discovery Rate (FDR) compared to standard ML approaches."}, {"id": "AI-241", "title": "Enhancing Web Application Security in the Era of AIdriven Cyber Threats", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Research topic", "supervisor": "Anzar Hussain Lone", "sitting_place": "33-205-CH8", "description": "The rapid expansion of internet technologies has significantly increased the reliance on web applications for communication, business transactions, education, and online services. While web Applications provide convenience and e?ciency, they also create new opportunities for cyber attackers to exploit vulnerabilities. Traditional security mechanisms such as firewalls and signature-based intrusion detection systems often struggle to detect sophisticated and evolving cyber threats. In recent years, crackers have begun using artificial intelligence (AI) techniques to automate cyber attacks, generate advanced phishing campaigns, and develop intelligent malware capable of bypassing conventional security measures. As a result, there is a growing need for more intelligent and adaptive security solutions to protect web applications from these emerging threats. This research paper focuses on enhancing web applications on security by integrating artificial intelligence techniques into cybersecurity frameworks. The main objective of the study is to explore how AI-driven approaches can improve the detection, prevention, and response to cyber attacks targeting web applications. By analyzing current security challenges and existing protection mechanisms, the study highlights the limitations of traditional systems and proposes a more advanced approach that utilises machine learning algorithms and data-driven analysis. The proposed framework aims to monitor web application on tra?c, analyze user behavior patterns, and detect anomalies that may indicate malicious activity. Machine learning models are capable of processing large volumes of data, identifying hidden patterns, and recognizing abnormal behaviors that may not be easily detected through rule-based systems. By combining AI-based analysis with existing security tools such as web application firewalls and intrusion detection systems, the framework provides a multi-layered defence mechanism that improves the overall protection of web platforms"}, {"id": "AI-242", "title": "e-Swasthya JalRakshak:Intelligent Health Monitoring System for Predicting Water-Borne Disease Outbreaks", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart Community Health Monitoring and Early Warning System for Water-Borne Diseases in Rural Northeast India", "supervisor": "Dr. Baljinder Kaur", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH6", "description": "Water-borne diseases continue to be a significant public health concern, particularly in regions with inadequate sanitation and contaminated drinking water. Conventional surveillance is usually characterized by delays and incomplete reporting. The purpose of this project is to design a data-based health monitoring and warning system for forecasting water-borne disease epidemics. The system will merge historical data--- such as weather, water quality, and health records --- to detect patterns and predict risks through machine learning models such as regression and classification analysis. It will provide risk scores and alerts to health authorities. The system will make use of one integrated dataset to analyze patterns, enhance readiness, and assist in minimizing the impact of water-borne disease outbreaks."}, {"id": "AI-243", "title": "Explainable Artificial Intelligence for Battery Health Monitoring in Electric Vehicles", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Literature Survey from IEEE, Scopus Indexed Research Papers", "supervisor": "Harshpreet Kaur", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH19", "description": "This paper analyzes the role of Explainable Artificial Intelligence (XAI) in battery health monitoring for electric vehicles. It examines existing machine learning and deep learning techniques used for predicting battery state of health and remaining useful life. The study focuses on improving model transparency and interpretability to enhance reliability, safety, and trust in EV battery management systems."}, {"id": "AI-244", "title": "Explainable Deep Learning Approach for Semantic Plagiarism Detection", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India", "supervisor": "Dr. Tanima Thakur", "sitting_place": "27-205-CH10", "description": "With the rapid growth of digital content, plagiarism detection has become a critical concern in academia and industry. Traditional plagiarism detection techniques primarily rely on surface-level matching, such as keyword overlap and string similarity, which are ineffective in identifying semantic and paraphrased plagiarism. Recent advancements in Natural Language Processing and deep learning have enabled machines to understand contextual and semantic relationships between texts. Models such as BERT have significantly improved performance in text similarity tasks. However, many existing systems still treat plagiarism detection as a simple binary classification problem, lacking the ability to capture deeper semantic variations and provide interpretability. Inspired by similarity learning approaches such as the Siamese Neural Network, this research proposes an advanced framework for semantic plagiarism detection. Unlike traditional methods, Siamese architectures learn meaningful representations by comparing pairs of inputs, making them highly effective for detecting paraphrased content."}, {"id": "AI-245", "title": "Explainable Generative AI-Augmented Multimodal Machine Learning for Early Detection of Depression", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Literature Review and Research Papers", "supervisor": "Pardeep Kumar", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH3", "description": "This project focuses on early detection of depression using advanced Artificial Intelligence techniques, particularly Generative AI and multimodal machine learning. Traditional diagnostic methods rely on subjective and time-consuming assessments, creating a need for scalable, automated solutions. The proposed framework analyzes multiple data modalities, including text, speech, visual, and behavioral data, to identify patterns linked to depressive symptoms. Natural Language Processing and transformer models are used for text analysis, while speech and visual features capture emotional and facial cues. Behavioral data adds contextual insights. Generative AI enhances performance through data augmentation and improved feature learning, addressing data limitations. Additionally, Explainable AI techniques are integrated to ensure transparency and trust in predictions. The methodology includes data collection, preprocessing, feature extraction, multimodal fusion, and predictive modeling. The system is evaluated using standard metrics, aiming to provide an accurate, scalable, and interpretable solution for early depression detection."}, {"id": "AI-246", "title": "Exploring Vision Transformer (ViT) for Multi-Class Classification in Skin Disease Detection", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s41870-023-01647-3", "supervisor": "Anzar Hussain Lone", "sitting_place": "33-205-CH8", "description": "Skin diseases are among the most common health concerns worldwide, affecting millions of individuals. Accurate and early detection is crucial for effective treatment. Deep learning models, especially Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), have shown remarkable success in skin disease classification. However, Vision Transformers (ViTs), a relatively new approach, have demonstrated superior performance in image classification tasks by capturing long-range dependencies more effectively. This study explores the application of ViT for multi-class skin disease classification, comparing its performance with CNN-based models to determine its suitability for dermatological diagnostics. Traditional skin disease detection methods rely on manual diagnosis by dermatologists, which can be subjective and time-consuming. While CNNs have improved classification accuracy, they have limitations in capturing global dependencies and often require large labeled datasets for generalization. This research aims to evaluate whether ViT can outperform CNNs in classifying multiple skin diseases, leveraging its self-attention mechanism for more effective feature extraction."}, {"id": "AI-247", "title": "Fake Currency Detector Application", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Based on real-world issues from Smart India Hackathon (SIH) and RBI counterfeiting initiatives.", "supervisor": "Dr. Ravindra Singh Yadav", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH12", "description": "Fake Currency Detector Application is a machine learning-based system designed to identify counterfeit banknotes with high accuracy. Using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN), the model analyzes key visual features such as texture, color, and patterns to distinguish fake notes from genuine ones. Integrated into a user-friendly mobile and desktop app, it enables real-time verification for use in banks, ATMs, and retail sectors, enhancing financial security and trust."}, {"id": "AI-248", "title": "Fake News Detection on Social Media Using NLP", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Business Model", "source": "Inspired by NLP-based fake news detection research (IEEE, arXiv, Kaggle).", "supervisor": "Akshay Kumar", "sitting_place": "28-204-CH13", "description": "Fake news spreads quickly on social media, leading to misinformation, panic, and a decline in public confidence in digital platforms. At scale, manual verification is ineffective. In order to automatically identify whether news content is authentic or fraudulent, this project suggests a machine learning-based fake news detection system that uses NLP techniques."}, {"id": "AI-249", "title": "Fake Social Media Accounts Detection", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Dr. Premananda Sahu", "sitting_place": "28-206-C1", "description": "In the modern digital era, social media has become an integral part of human life, serving as a powerful platform for communication, business promotion, news sharing, and social interaction. However, the rapid expansion of these platforms has also led to the proliferation of fake accounts---profiles created to mislead users, spread misinformation, conduct fraudulent activities, or manipulate public opinion. These accounts pose significant threats to online security, user privacy, and the credibility of social networks. Hence, the need for an efficient fake account detection system has become more crucial than ever. The main objective of this project, \"Social Media Fake Account Detection\", is to design and develop a machine learning-based model that can automatically identify fake or suspicious accounts on social media platforms. The project utilizes data mining and predictive analytics techniques to detect unusual behavior patterns that distinguish genuine users from fake ones. The system analyzes various parameters such as profile completeness, number of followers and following, posting frequency, content originality, and engagement behavior. The project follows a systematic workflow that includes data collection, data preprocessing, feature extraction, model training, and performance evaluation. Publicly available datasets containing real and fake user profiles are used to train and validate the model. The preprocessing step involves cleaning the data, handling missing values, and normalizing numerical features to ensure model accuracy. Feature extraction focuses on identifying meaningful attributes like account activity ratio, average post length, frequency of likes and comments, and use of hashtags or URLs, which often differ significantly between genuine and fake users. Several machine learning algorithms are tested and compared in this project, including Logistic Regression, Random Forest, Decision Tree, and Support Vector Machine (SVM). Each algorithm is evaluated based on accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score to determine the most effective model for fake account detection. Among these, ensemble learning methods like Random Forest and XGBoost often provide better performance due to their ability to handle large feature sets and reduce overfitting. The implementation is carried out using Python, leveraging libraries such as Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-learn, and Matplotlib for data analysis, model building, and visualization. The project also includes an interactive dashboard that visualizes the detection results, making it easier to understand which accounts are genuine or fake based on computed metrics."}, {"id": "AI-250", "title": "FRIDAY: Evolutionary Multi-Agent Reinforcement Learning for Regime-Adaptive Algorithmic Trading", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "NA", "supervisor": "Amandeep Kaur", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH23", "description": "FRIDAY is an adaptive AI-based trading assistant that supports smarter market decision-making by combining reinforcement learning, market-regime awareness, and large language model assistance. The project is designed to analyze changing market conditions, generate data-driven trading insights, and present them in a clear, user-friendly interface for faster and more informed decisions."}, {"id": "AI-251", "title": "Gamified Learning Platform for Rural Education", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Gargi Sharma", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH6", "description": "Gamifi ed learning platforms are digital environments that integrate game design elements and principles into educational content to enhance student engagement, motivation, and learning outcomes. While a staple in modern educational technology (EdTech), their application in rural education presents a unique and compelling opportunity. Rural communities, particularly in developing countries, often face signifi cant educational challenges, including a lack of qualifi ed teachers, inadequate infrastructure, limited resources, and low student retention rates. Traditional teaching methods in these areas can be monotonous, failing to capture students' interest and leading to a passive learning experience. A gamifi ed approach, which uses elements like points, badges, leaderboards, missions, and interactive storytelling, can transform this paradigm. By making learning fun and rewarding, it can increase student participation, improve attendance, and make complex subjects more accessible. This topic explores the design, development, and implementation of a specialized gamifi ed learning platform tailored to the specifi c context of rural education, aiming to address its inherent challenges and create a more equitable and eff ective learning environment."}, {"id": "AI-252", "title": "GetItDone: Unified Freelancing and Everyday Services Platform", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SMART INDIA HACKATHO 2024", "supervisor": "Dr. Vidhi Sood", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH6", "description": "Problem Statement Current freelancing platforms such as Freelancer, Upwork, and Fiverr primarily cater to professional and online-based services like software development, graphic design, content writing, and digital marketing. However, these platforms do not adequately support everyday workers (e.g., electricians, carpenters, cleaners, delivery helpers, or other offline task providers) who also seek visibility and opportunities through digital platforms. This limitation creates a significant access gap between customers who require offline, local services and the workforce available to fulfill them. Gap Analysis Limited Workforce Coverage: Existing platforms emphasize only professional freelancers, excluding a large segment of skilled everyday workers. Online-Only Restriction: Most current systems are optimized for online work delivery, but offline, location-based services (home repairs, manual labor, etc.) remain underserved. Accessibility Challenge: Everyday workers often lack access to digital marketplaces where they can showcase skills, build trust, and connect with potential customers. Customer Limitation: Customers must rely on informal sources (word-of-mouth, local contacts) to find offline workers, which is often unreliable and inefficient compared to verified, platform-based hiring. Proposed Solution We propose developing a comprehensive work marketplace platform -- GetItDone -- that integrates both professional freelancing services and everyday offline tasks, making it a hybrid solution for users. Key Features: Dual Categories: Professional Services (online/offline, based on client needs and service provider acceptance): Software development, design, tutoring, consulting. Everyday Services (mostly offline): Electricians, plumbers, household helpers, drivers. Mode of Work: Online work assignments for digital freelancers. Offline, location-based bookings for everyday workers. User Verification & Trust: Profile-based verification, customer reviews, and ratings. Search & Filter System: Allows customers to find both online professionals and local offline workers. Tech Stack: Backend: Java, Spring Boot Frontend: React, JavaScript, HTML, CSS Database: MySQL / PL/SQL This solution bridges the gap between professionals and everyday workers by bringing both segments onto a single digital platform, empowering workers with more opportunities and giving customers a reliable, trusted source for services."}, {"id": "AI-253", "title": "GrievEase -- AI-Powered Grievance Management System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Investigative research about grievance filing and management", "supervisor": "Dr. Neeta Rana", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH5", "description": "GrievEase is an AI-integrated grievance management system that not only classifies complaints but also predicts resolution time, assigns priority automatically, and identifies recurring issues through pattern analysis. It features emotion-based complaint detection, smart routing to relevant departments, and a feedback-based improvement module. Built with Next.js, MongoDB, and JWT, it ensures transparency, automation, and secure communication between users and authorities."}, {"id": "AI-254", "title": "HAAWWW: AI-POWERED NEWS AUTHENTICITY CLASSIFIER AND DEEP RESEARCH PLATFORM", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Business Model", "source": "Self-inspired project based on AI and NLP research (IEEE, arXiv, Kaggle).", "supervisor": "Akshay Kumar", "sitting_place": "28-204-CH13", "description": "The aim of the project is to develop a web-based platform that classifies news content and generates an explainable analysis of source credibility, linguistic quality, and factual suspicion, while also supporting deeper AI-powered research for comprehensive verification."}, {"id": "AI-255", "title": "HealthMate: Personalized Nutrition, Workout, and Body Tracking System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Abhishek", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH13", "description": "HealthMate is an AI-driven health and fitness application that provides personalized nutrition plans, workout routines, and real-time body tracking. By analyzing uploaded body images using computer vision models, it detects fat/muscle distribution and suggests tailored diet & exercise plans for weight loss, gain, or maintenance. Integrated with Stripe API for premium services and geolocation APIs, it also helps users locate the nearest hospitals or clinics during health emergencies."}, {"id": "AI-256", "title": "Heart Disease Utilising Hybrid Models", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH 2024", "supervisor": "Akshat Srivastava( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "The Project focuses on predicting Heart Disease risk using Hybrid Machine Learning models that combine ensemble and deep learning techinques it analyzes patient health parameters such as age, cholesterol, blood pressure, and heart rate to achieve higher prediction accuracy and support early diagnosis for preventive healthcare."}, {"id": "AI-257", "title": "Hybrid Convolutional Neural Network Architecture for Early Diagnosis of Retinal Pathologies Using Fundus Imaging", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH 2024", "supervisor": "Vikas Sharma", "sitting_place": "26-205-CH22", "description": "The Research proposes a hybrid convolutional neural network architecture that automatically analyzes retinal fundus images to identify pathological features at an early stage. The hybrid model improves feature extraction and classification accuracy by combining multiple deep learning components. The system can assist healthcare professionals in faster and more reliable diagnosis. The solution aligns with healthcare innovation initiatives promoted through programs like Smart India Hackathon and supports digital health goals encouraged by organizations such as Ministry of Health and Family Welfare and Ministry of Electronics and Information Technology. It can help improve large-scale screening, support telemedicine services, and increase access to eye care in underserved regions."}, {"id": "AI-258", "title": "Hybrid Deep Learning Methods for Faster and Improved Face Recognition", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Bharat Sharma", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH33", "description": "This research focuses on developing a hybrid face recognition framework that combines the high feature-learning capability of deep learning models with the computational efficiency of classical machine learning techniques. While deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) such as FaceNet or VGGFace achieve high accuracy, they often require significant computational resources, making them less suitable for real-time or edge-based applications. The proposed hybrid approach integrates deep learning for feature extraction and classical algorithms for dimensionality reduction and classification. For instance, a CNN can generate deep facial embeddings, which are then optimized using PCA or LDA to reduce redundancy and improve separability. The final classification can be performed using lightweight classifiers such as SVM or k-Nearest Neighbors (k-NN). This combination enhances recognition accuracy while significantly reducing computational load and memory usage."}, {"id": "AI-259", "title": "Hybrid Pet Breed Classification System using CNN and SVM", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH 2025", "supervisor": "Aman Deep", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH32", "description": "Current breed classification systems mostly rely only on CNNs. While they achieve high accuracy on large datasets, their performance drops when data is limited or the images contain noise, poor lighting, or similar-looking breeds. The motivation is to develop a hybrid model that extracts robust features using CNN and classifies breeds more accurately using SVM. Solving this problem can make breed identification more reliable, especially in real-world scenarios (mobile pictures, adoption centers, or vet records)."}, {"id": "AI-260", "title": "Hybrid Rule-Based and Fuzzy Matching Framework for Classifying Patient Complaints in Healthcare NLP Systems", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Self-Initiated / Internship Project", "supervisor": "Rashika Gupta", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This project focuses on developing an AI-based system to normalize and classify unstructured medical chief complaints into predefined categories. It uses NLP techniques such as abbreviation expansion, spell correction, negation handling, and machine learning models for multi-label classification. The system improves healthcare data quality and supports clinical decision-making."}, {"id": "AI-261", "title": "Hyper-Local Air Quality Forecasting and Explainable Health Mapping Using AI-Driven Predictive Intelligence", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2025 (Ministry of Mines Problem Statement)", "supervisor": "Rishul Verma", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH13", "description": "Urban residents are increasingly exposed to dangerous micro-level pollution hotspots that remain undetected by traditional city-wide air quality forecasting systems. This project proposes AeroSense, a hyper-local, explainable AI framework for air quality forecasting and health risk visualization at the neighborhood and street scale. By integrating advanced machine learning algorithms with explainable modeling and a dynamic visualization interface, the system enables data-driven decision-making for both citizens and policymakers. The predictive engine employs XGBoost and LightGBM models trained on high-quality historical air quality datasets (e.g., UCI, Kaggle) enriched with temporal and geospatial features such as time-lagged pollutant trends, meteorological parameters, and proximity to emission sources (e.g., highways, industrial zones). This hybrid feature engineering approach ensures enhanced spatial resolution and reduced root mean square error (RMSE) in PM2.5 concentration forecasting. A novel integration of SHAP (SHapley Additive exPlanations) provides model interpretability within the FastAPI backend, allowing users to understand the contribution of specific environmental factors (e.g., wind speed, traffic density) influencing air quality predictions. The front-end React dashboard renders an interactive health-risk heat map, enabling real-time visualization of pollution hotspots and forecasting their short-term evolution. By delivering transparent, accurate, and actionable environmental intelligence, AeroSense empowers citizens, researchers, and policymakers to take localized, evidence-based interventions. The framework establishes a strong foundation for AI-augmented environmental monitoring, urban planning, and public health analytics in next-generation smart cities."}, {"id": "AI-262", "title": "Identification of Bone Tumor Using Machine Learning Algorithms", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Shambhu Bhardwaj", "sitting_place": "34-202-CH34", "description": "This project focuses on the automated identification of bone tumors from X-ray images using a hybrid approach that combines machine learning and deep learning techniques. It leverages ResNet50 for feature extraction, SegFormer for semantic segmentation, and ensemble learning using Random Forest (RF) and Multi-Layer Perceptron (MLP) for classification.A Streamlit-based web application was developed to provide a real-time interface where users can upload medical images and receive tumor detection results with visualization (e.g., Grad-CAM heatmaps and performance metrics).The system aims to assist radiologists by enhancing diagnostic accuracy, reducing human error, and enabling faster clinical decisions."}, {"id": "AI-263", "title": "IEEE(ElderConnect: An AI-Powered Platform to Empower Seniors Against Cyberthreats)", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Ajay Sharma", "sitting_place": "27-209-CH16", "description": "ElderGuard is a digital security platform designed to protect users from online threats and promote safe internet use. It combines a community-driven scam reporting system, an AI voice assistant for disabled users, and a real-time fake link scanner to alert users about scams, guide them safely online, and prevent fraud before it happens. The project empowers users and fosters a secure, inclusive digital environment."}, {"id": "AI-264", "title": "Image based Breed Recognition for Cattle and Buffaloes of India", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Jaspreet Kaur", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH17", "description": "An AI-driven image recognition solution to accurately identify indigenous and crossbreed cattle and buffalo breeds in India. The system minimises manual breed identification errors using computer vision and machine learning. It supports diverse environments, maintains a breed database, and provides a user-friendly interface for field workers."}, {"id": "AI-265", "title": "Image-based Animal Type Classification for Cattle and Buffaloes", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Dr. Chetna Vaid Kwatra", "sitting_place": "34-207-CH15", "description": "Accurate identification of cattle and buffaloes is essential for livestock management, disease control, breeding, and monitoring. Farmers often face challenges in manually distinguishing between cattle and buffaloes, especially when animals are of similar color or size. A manual process is time-consuming, error-prone, and requires expert knowledge. There is a need for an automated, image-based classification system that can differentiate between cattle and buffaloes efficiently and accurately."}, {"id": "AI-266", "title": "Image-Based Animal Type Classification for Cattle and Buffaloes", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon (SIH) 2024", "supervisor": "Anjum Rouf( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This project aims to develop an AI-powered image classification system capable of distinguishing between cattle and buffaloes using deep learning and computer vision techniques. By analyzing physical features such as body structure, color, and horn shape, the model will automate animal type classification, reducing human error and improving accuracy in dairy management and livestock monitoring."}, {"id": "AI-267", "title": "Image-based Animal Type Classification for Cattle and Buffaloes", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Cherry Khosla", "sitting_place": "34-205-CH10", "description": "To develop an AI-driven Animal Type Classification System capable of automatically evaluating images of cattle and buffaloes to determine their physical traits and assign standardized classification scores. The tech Stack that we will be using through out this project will be Machine Learning (ML), Computer Vision, Web Development, Data Analysis, UI/UX Design, and DevOps"}, {"id": "AI-268", "title": "Image-Based Animal Type Classification for Cattle and Buffaloes Using Deep Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Arshiya", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH6", "description": "The project focuses on the development of an image-based animal classification system to accurately distinguish between cattle and buffaloes using advanced deep learning techniques. In traditional livestock management, identification and monitoring of animals are performed manually, which is time-consuming, error-prone, and inefficient, especially in large-scale farming environments. This project aims to automate this process by leveraging computer vision and machine learning approaches. The proposed system will utilize Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) to extract visual features from animal images and classify them into predefined categories. A dataset consisting of labeled images of cattle and buffaloes will be collected, preprocessed, and augmented to improve model robustness and accuracy. Various deep learning architectures such as MobileNet, ResNet, or YOLO may be explored to achieve optimal performance in terms of accuracy and inference speed. The system is designed to work in real-time scenarios, where images captured through cameras or mobile devices can be processed instantly to identify the type of animal. This real-time capability is particularly useful in smart farming applications, where continuous monitoring and automated decision-making are required. Additionally, the project may incorporate edge computing techniques to enable deployment on low-resource devices, making the solution practical for rural and remote areas. The implementation process includes dataset preparation, model training, validation, and performance evaluation using standard metrics such as accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score. The system will also be tested under varying environmental conditions such as lighting, background noise, and occlusion to ensure reliability and robustness. The expected outcome of this project is a scalable and efficient classification model that can assist farmers, dairy industries, and agricultural stakeholders in improving livestock management. By reducing manual effort and increasing accuracy, the system contributes to better productivity, resource optimization, and decision-making. Furthermore, this project aligns with the concept of smart agriculture and supports the integration of artificial intelligence in the agricultural domain."}, {"id": "AI-269", "title": "Image-Based Breed Recognition of Buffaloes and Cattles of India", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Gautam Kumar", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH25", "description": "This project focuses on developing an image-based breed recognition model that automatically identifies and classifies Indian cattle and buffalo breeds using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) and YOLO (You Only Look Once) object detection algorithms. The system aims to support the Bharat Pashudhan App (BPA) initiative by the Government of India, which promotes systematic data recording of livestock. The model will recognize major Indian breeds such as Gir, Sahiwal, Tharparkar, Hariana, Kankrej, Murrah, Mehsana, and Surti, among others. The current phase of the project focuses solely on model development, including dataset creation, training, and evaluation. In the future, this model can be extended into a web or mobile application to assist Field Level Workers (FLWs), farmers, and veterinary officers in automated livestock breed identification."}, {"id": "AI-270", "title": "Image-Based Early Detection and Classification of Major Tomato Leaf Diseases", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Research topic", "supervisor": "Anzar Hussain Lone", "sitting_place": "33-205-CH8", "description": "This project will investigate and implement advanced computer vision and machine learning (or deep learning) techniques for the automated classification of diseases affecting the Solanum lycopersicum (tomato) plant. The reliance on manual, visual inspection by farmers or agricultural experts is often time-consuming, subjective, and prone to error, leading to delayed or incorrect treatment and significant crop loss. This research aims to develop an efficient, accurate, and scalable system capable of rapidly classifying the type of disease present (e.g., Bacterial Spot, Early Blight, Late Blight, Tomato Yellow Leaf Curl Virus, etc.) from images of the plant's leaves. The methodology will involve: Data Acquisition and Preprocessing: Utilizing a comprehensive dataset of labeled tomato plant leaf images, including healthy and various diseased states. Model Development: Designing and training a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) or similar deep learning model to learn and extract subtle, distinguishing visual features associated with each disease. Performance Evaluation: Rigorously testing the model's performance metrics, such as accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score, against state-of-the-art methods."}, {"id": "AI-271", "title": "Image-Based Identification of Indian Cattle and Buffalo Breed Using Deep Learning Techniques.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Tushar Kasana", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH36", "description": "This research presents an automated deep learning system for identifying Indian cattle and buffalo breeds. Using CNN architectures like Xception, DenseNet, and MobileNetV2, the model extracts features such as horn shape and body structure from images to classify breeds. Xception achieved the highest accuracy at 72%. The project aims to replace subjective manual identification, supporting precision agriculture, dairy productivity, and genetic conservation."}, {"id": "AI-272", "title": "Imbalanced Learning Techniques for Reliable Disease Prediction in Healthcare Data", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH25131", "supervisor": "Dr. Harpreet Singh", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH9", "description": "In healthcare datasets, the number of patients with a particular disease is often significantly lower than those without it, leading to a class imbalance problem. Traditional machine learning models tend to be biased toward the majority class, resulting in poor detection of minority cases---often the critical ones (e.g., rare diseases or early-stage conditions). This research focuses on applying and evaluating various imbalanced learning techniques, such as oversampling (e.g., SMOTE), undersampling, cost-sensitive learning, and ensemble methods, to improve the predictive performance of models on minority classes. The goal is to build a reliable disease prediction system that not only achieves high overall accuracy but also improves sensitivity and recall for underrepresented disease cases, thereby supporting better clinical decision-making."}, {"id": "AI-273", "title": "IndiBreed-ML: Automated Breed Detection for Indian Livestock", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Manish Kumar Sharma", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH7", "description": "This project develops an intelligent system to automatically identify the breed of cattle from images using artificial intelligence. A deep learning model is trained on a dataset containing multiple cattle breeds. The model learns to recognize distinctive features such as body structure. It provides fast and accurate predictions for uploaded images. The system is designed to be user-friendly and easy to operate. It helps farmers, livestock experts, and researchers quickly identify cattle breeds. The tool supports breed management, breeding programs, and genetic studies. It eliminates the need for manual identification, saving time and effort. The project demonstrates the practical application of AI in livestock monitoring. Overall, it provides a scalable and efficient solution for cattle breed identification."}, {"id": "AI-274", "title": "IN-GRES GPT: AI Groundwater Intelligence Companion", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "https://www.india.gov.in/spotlight/smart-cities-mission-step-towards-smart-india (Falls under Smart City and Urban Development initiatives.)", "supervisor": "Savleen Kaur", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH9", "description": "Theme: Agriculture & Rural Development (SIH 2024 Theme) Objective: Predict the yield of a crop based on soil, weather, and fertilizer data, and recommend suitable crops for a given region. Available Dataset: Indian Crop Production Dataset (1950--2020) -- https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/abhinand05/crop-production-in-india Data: https://punjab.data.gov.in/catalogs?sector=Agriculture"}, {"id": "AI-275", "title": "IN-GRES GPT: AI Groundwater Intelligence Companion", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "https://www.india.gov.in/spotlight/smart-cities-mission-step-towards-smart-india (Falls under Smart City and Urban Development initiatives.)", "supervisor": "Amanpal Singh Rayat", "sitting_place": "36-209-A-CH9", "description": "Theme: Agriculture & Rural Development (SIH 2024 Theme) Objective: Predict the yield of a crop based on soil, weather, and fertilizer data, and recommend suitable crops for a given region. Available Dataset: Indian Crop Production Dataset (1950--2020) -- https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/abhinand05/crop-production-in-india Data: https://punjab.data.gov.in/catalogs?sector=Agriculture"}, {"id": "AI-276", "title": "Intelligent Disaster Relief Tracking System using AI and Blockchain", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH: Smart Indian Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Anzah Bashir", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH17", "description": "During natural disasters like floods and earthquakes, timely and transparent distribution of relief supplies is a critical challenge. Often, aid reaches affected areas late or fails to reach altogether due to poor demand forecasting, logistical inefficiencies, and diversion of resources. This project proposes the development of an Intelligent Disaster Relief Tracking System that leverages Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Blockchain to address these issues. The AI module will utilize real-time weather reports, satellite imagery, and historical disaster data to predict which regions are most vulnerable and in urgent need of relief. By identifying hotspots and estimating supply requirements in advance, this system ensures faster decision-making and prioritization of resources. The Blockchain module will provide a transparent and tamper-proof record of every relief package, from dispatch to delivery. Each supply unit will be logged on a decentralized ledger, preventing corruption, diversion, and duplication of aid. This ensures accountability among all stakeholders, including government agencies, NGOs, and local authorities. The system will include a user-friendly dashboard to visualize high-risk areas, track package movement in real-time, and generate automated alerts for delayed or missing deliveries. By combining predictive analytics with secure supply chain tracking, the project aims to create a reliable, transparent, and efficient disaster management ecosystem. Overall, the solution will not only reduce delays and losses in relief distribution but also restore trust in disaster management processes, making humanitarian aid more impactful."}, {"id": "AI-277", "title": "Intelligent Document Management System: An AI-Driven Approach for Automated Document Processing, Classification, and Knowledge Retrieval", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SMART INDIA HACKATHO 2024", "supervisor": "Dr. Vidhi Sood", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH6", "description": "The era of digital transformation has transformed the way the organizations manage, store, analyze and access information. This paper introduces an Intelligent Document Management System (IDMS) which is a composite of artificial intelligence (AI), natural language processing (NLP), retrieval-augmented generation (RAG), and automated classification to enhance document perception and efficiency of operations. The suggested system addresses major lapses in existing document management techniques because it provides semantic insight, automated rerouting, multilingualization and adherence checks. According to the experimental results the system reduces the time spent processing documents more than 90 percent and maintains OCR and NLP accuracy rates at greater than 90 percent. The system manages to achieve department routing accuracy of 82-90 percent and context-relevant question-answering of RAG-based retrieval. This study enjoys a representation of a theoretical model, as well as a practical implementation of next generation document intelligence systems, which can be adapted in government institutions and large corporations."}, {"id": "AI-278", "title": "Intelligent Medical Text Classification from Discharge Summaries Using Deep Learning-Based NLP Techniques", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Research Papers", "supervisor": "Komal Arora", "sitting_place": "27-205-CH6", "description": "This research focuses on building an intelligent system for medical text classification, particularly from hospital discharge summaries, using advanced deep learning-based NLP techniques. Discharge summaries are rich in clinical insights but are often unstructured and filled with domain-specific jargon. The proposed work aims to design a robust and scalable classification framework that can accurately categorize such summaries into predefined medical classes or ICD codes. Using transformer-based language models pre-trained on biomedical corpora, the study adapts these models to understand and process complex medical language. This approach not only enhances accuracy but also ensures relevance in real-world hospital environments. The research contributes toward improved clinical decision support systems, medical coding automation, and efficient healthcare data management."}, {"id": "AI-279", "title": "Intelligent Pesticide Sprinkling System Determined by the Infection Level of a Plant", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Apoorv Dubey", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH23", "description": "The Intelligent Pesticide Sprinkling System is an automated and smart agriculture solution designed to optimize pesticide usage based on the actual infection level of plants. The system employs image processing and machine learning techniques to detect and analyze plant leaf conditions in real-time. By identifying the type and severity of infection, it determines the precise amount of pesticide required and activates a targeted sprinkling mechanism. This minimizes chemical waste, reduces environmental pollution, and lowers farming costs while ensuring effective pest control. The system can be integrated with IoT sensors and a mobile interface for remote monitoring and control, promoting sustainable and precision agriculture practices."}, {"id": "AI-280", "title": "Intelligent Spatiotemporal Compliance Assessment for Emergency Vehicle Priority", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH, NITI Aayog Problem Statements, Nvidia research grant under edge-AI & Autonomous Vehicles", "supervisor": "Rishul Verma", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH13", "description": "Emergency response effectiveness is critically dependent on minimizing delays caused by traffic congestion and non-compliance with right-of-way regulations. This project proposes SmartEV-Priority, an intelligent, real-time spatiotemporal compliance assessment system that autonomously detects emergency vehicles and evaluates the yielding behavior of surrounding traffic. Leveraging advancements in computer vision, deep learning, and multi-object tracking, the proposed framework aims to enhance urban traffic management, reduce emergency response time, and support automated rule enforcement. The system processes live video feeds from roadway or CCTV cameras using real-time object detection models such as YOLOv8 or Faster R-CNN, augmented through transfer learning to accurately identify emergency vehicle classes (ambulances, fire trucks, and police vehicles). A DeepSORT-based tracking mechanism ensures robust identity persistence across frames, enabling trajectory reconstruction for both emergency and non-emergency vehicles in dense urban scenarios. A rule-based compliance engine then analyzes spatiotemporal parameters, including inter-vehicle distance, velocity, lane occupancy, and yielding latency, to determine whether surrounding vehicles grant appropriate right-of-way. Detected violations are logged with timestamped video evidence, metadata, and vehicle trajectories to facilitate auditing, analytics, and potential integration with adaptive traffic signal systems for dynamic green-wave generation. Developed using Python, OpenCV, TensorFlow/Keras or YOLO and integrated through a lightweight Flask/Django web interface, the system is designed for scalability, modularity, and deployment in smart city infrastructures. Expected outcomes include high-accuracy real-time emergency vehicle detection, automated compliance reporting, and quantifiable improvements in emergency response times, contributing to safer, smarter, and more responsive urban transportation ecosystems."}, {"id": "AI-281", "title": "IntelliMatch: AI-Driven Internship Recommendation Engine for PM Internship Scheme", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "SIH25034 https://www.sih.gov.in/sih2025PS", "supervisor": "Deepali Kumari( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This project develops an AI-powered recommendation system for the PM Internship Portal to help students, especially from rural areas, find suitable internships. Based on inputs like education, skills, and interests, the model recommends the top 3--5 matching internships. The system is built using Python (scikit-learn) for AI modeling, MySQL as the database server, and Flask for backend integration. The frontend uses HTML, CSS, and JS, with deployment on a cloud-based server for real-time access and scalability."}, {"id": "AI-282", "title": "IT system Log Analyzer", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Indu Bala", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH10", "description": "The project aims to design an AI-based system that analyzes and classifies large-scale IT system logs in real time. By using Machine Learning and Natural Language Processing, the system detects errors, anomalies, and security threats automatically. It reduces manual log analysis efforts, enables faster troubleshooting, and enhances the overall reliability and performance of IT infrastructure"}, {"id": "AI-283", "title": "Jigyasa: Explore, Discover, Shine!", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "SIH 2025 (https://www.sih.gov.in/sih2025PS): Topic 48 (Gamified Learning Platform for Rural Education)", "supervisor": "Blossom", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH15", "description": "This proposed solution is an AI-driven, gamified learning platform designed to make education engaging for children. It adapts to a learner's ability through dynamic content recommendations, offers module-based lessons with interactive activities, and provides parents with meaningful progress insights. With intelligent feedback and rewarding progression, it motivates students to learn at their own pace."}, {"id": "AI-284", "title": "Joint Detection of Diabetic Retinopathy and Glaucoma Using Hybrid ViT-CNN Architecture with Lesion-Aware Explainable AI (XAI)", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon (SIH) 2025 problem themes in Healthcare AI and Intelligent Diagnostics • WHO Vision 2030 initiative to reduce preventable blindness through early AI-based screening", "supervisor": "Isha", "sitting_place": "26-205-CH6", "description": "Diabetic Retinopathy (DR) and Glaucoma are two of the leading causes of blindness worldwide. Many diabetic patients suffer from both diseases simultaneously, making diagnosis very difficult because both share similar symptoms in the eye (like optic disc changes and hemorrhages).Current AI systems either detect DR or Glaucoma separately. There is no systematic review that studies Hybrid ViT-CNN models, which combine the strengths of both Vision Transformers (good at understanding the whole image) and Convolutional Neural Networks (good at finding small lesions) for detecting both diseases together.So study will aims to systematically review and analyze existing research on disease detection using medical imaging, classify different methodological approaches based on their design and integration strategies, assess whether analytical outputs align with clinically relevant features used in diagnosis, and develop a standardized evaluation framework to measure the reliability, consistency, and practical applicability of such methods for future research."}, {"id": "AI-285", "title": "KisanMitra - CNN Based Crowdsourced Crop Disease Detection", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Akanksha Pandey", "sitting_place": "28-204-CH14", "description": "Kisan-Mitra, hybrid cloud-based mobile application empowering farmers through crowdsourced crop disease identification powered by CNN models for identification. Processing images via distributed ML workers, detects disease outbreaks using geospatial clustering, and disseminates mass alerts to farmers within affected regions, while integrating inventory management, weather forecasting, and AI-driven crop recommendations for comprehensive precision agriculture."}, {"id": "AI-286", "title": "Lightweight Convolutional Neural Network with Residual Attention for Efficient Image Classification.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart Traffic Management Systern for Urban Congestion,SIH25050", "supervisor": "Deepali Kumari( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This project proposes LightCNN-Att, a lightweight convolutional neural network enhanced with residual and dual-attention mechanisms for efficient image classification. It focuses on achieving high accuracy with minimal parameters, making it suitable for real-time and edge devices. The model improves feature extraction by combining spatial and channel attention, reducing computational cost while maintaining strong performance on datasets like STL-10."}, {"id": "AI-287", "title": "lmage based breed recognition for cattle and buffaloes of India", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2025 (Problem Statement ID 25004)", "supervisor": "Danish Meiraj", "sitting_place": "28-204-CH18", "description": "Background The Government of India is implementing the Bharat Pashudhan App (BPA) for systematic data recording of breeding, health, and nutrition of dairy animals. Field Level Workers (FLWs) are responsible for capturing animal data on the ground. However, despite multiple training programs, a recurring issue is the incorrect identification and registration of animal breeds of cattle and buffaloes. This misclassification significantly affects the integrity and usability of the data for research, policy planning, and targeted interventions. Description Breed identification errors in BPA often arise due to manual judgment and lack of breed-specific awareness among FLWs. India, being home to a diverse array of indigenous and crossbred cattle and buffalo breeds, presents a complex challenge for accurate breed identification. Incorrect entries compromise the value of collected data and, in turn, impact the effectiveness of genetic improvement, nutrition planning, disease control, and overall program outcomes. To address this, an AI-driven solution that can identify the breed of an animal using its image can prove extremely valuable. By using image recognition and machine learning techniques, the software can standardize breed identification and minimize manual errors. If successfully developed and validated, such a system can be integrated with the BPA to act as a decision-support tool for FLWs during registration. Expected Solution • Uses Artificial Intelligence (AI) and image analysis to recognize and classify the breed of cattle and buffaloes based on images. • Can handle diverse environmental backgrounds, lighting conditions, and varying animal poses. • Maintains a breed database (for the most common Indian cattle and buffalo breeds and their crosses). • Provides breed suggestions or confirmations at the time of registration in BPA. • Can be seamlessly integrated with the BPA platform to support real-time validation or correction of breed entries. • Includes a user-friendly interface for FLWs with minimal technical training requirements."}, {"id": "AI-288", "title": "lmage based breed recognition for cattle and buffaloes of India", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25004", "supervisor": "Dr. Gurbinder Singh Brar", "sitting_place": "34-203-C3", "description": "The present invention introduces an innovative and advanced system for image-based breed recognition of cattle and buffaloes through a data driven, intelligent approach. This system harnesses state of the art technologies, including artificial intelligence, machine learning, the Internet of Things, and big data analytics, to deliver precise, real-time, and actionable insights into livestock identification and management. By integrating diverse datasets encompassing phenotypic attributes, high-resolution visual data, and ancillary farm metadata the system facilitates accurate breed identification, classification, and traceability for Indian bovines, transforming livestock informatics"}, {"id": "AI-289", "title": "Machine learning and deep learning in traumatic brain injury", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Vidhi Sood", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH6", "description": "Traumatic brain injury (TBI) is a significant world-wide critical scenario impacting around 50 million people every year with enormous death and prolonged inability costs which have exhibited little positive results and changes in decades of profound investigation. The nonhomogeneous characteristics of TBI: heterogeneous injury patterns, physiological responses, and recovery trajectories require shifting to an alternative paradigm of population-averaged, guideline-based treatment methods to individual, precision medicine models. This single-title narrative review is an integration of existing applications of artificial intelligence (AI) in seven complementary TBI management areas, including emergency mortality using large language models and support vector machines, prognostic classification using electroencephalography through hybrid machine learning software, integrative neuroinformatics to find precision, prognostic, and automated analysis of radiological images by convolutional neural networks, biological discovery of biomarkers via neuroproteomics, multimodal physiological monitoring based on machine learning, and computed tomography to detect and estimate volumes of a hematoma. All of the methodological procedures present a different biological dimension: molecular signals are present by proteomics, real-time physiological by continuous monitoring, structural by state-of-the-art imaging, and temporal by electro-encephalography. The combination of the modalities is a transformative opportunity in prediction of patient-specific outcomes and optimizing the therapeutic. But, there remain substantial gaps: little external validation, little multi-modal integration, restrictive population demographics in available datasets, no longitudinal designs, no explainability despite years of effort, and no experimental clinical findings of part of better patient outcomes. It is the review that provides a coherent framework of how individual AI innovations can be integrated to create truly personalized TBI care, but also specifies various critical infrastructure, validation and regulatory needs that must be accomplished before translating the research can be translated into clinical practice. The way to do it is through multi-institutional collaboration, the standard of data collection procedures and the continued funding of longitudinal cohort studies to facilitate the transformative capability of precision neuroinformatics in the management of traumatic changes of the brain."}, {"id": "AI-290", "title": "Machine Learning based animal type classification for cattle and buffaloes", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Business Model", "source": "Image based animal Type classification for cattle and buffaloes. (SIH25005)", "supervisor": "Dr. Harpreet Singh", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH9", "description": "This project focuses on developing a machine learning-based system for animal type classification, specifically distinguishing between cattle and buffaloes using image processing and classification techniques. The system utilizes datasets of animal images and applies algorithms to automatically extract features like shape, texture, color patterns, and horn structure for accurate identification. A user-friendly interface allows farmers, dairy managers, or veterinary staff to upload images and receive instant classification results. The model is trained and validated on labeled datasets to ensure high accuracy and robustness under varying environmental conditions such as lighting, background, and pose variations. The back-end processes the images and runs the trained model, while a secure database maintains records for further analysis and improvement. This solution helps in efficient livestock management, breed monitoring, and automation of manual identification processes, reducing human effort and errors. It can also support applications in dairy production, veterinary services, and agricultural research by providing reliable animal classification data. Overall, the project enhances productivity, improves decision-making in livestock management, and demonstrates the practical application of machine learning in the agriculture and dairy sector."}, {"id": "AI-291", "title": "Machine learning based Crop management system", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Self", "supervisor": "Abdul Malik Ansari", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH18", "description": "A Machine Learning--based Crop Management System is a smart agriculture solution that uses data, sensors, and AI models to help farmers monitor crops, predict problems early, and improve productivity with fewer resources. It supports precision farming, where decisions are made based on real-time field conditions instead of guesswork"}, {"id": "AI-292", "title": "Machine learning based fake news detection system", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2025 (SIH25161)", "supervisor": "Dr. Avnish Thakur", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH10", "description": "The proposed project aims to design and develop a Machine Learning--based Fake News Detection System capable of identifying misleading or false information circulating across digital media platforms. The first phase of the project involves data acquisition and feature identification. In the second phase, various machine learning and deep learning models will be trained using labeled datasets. The third phase focuses on testing, validation, and performance evaluation. Additionally, a research paper will be prepared to document the methodology and experimental results."}, {"id": "AI-293", "title": "Machine Learning based smart crop advisory system", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2025 (SIH25010)", "supervisor": "Dr. Avnish Thakur", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH10", "description": "The proposed project aims to develop a Machine Learning--based Smart Crop Advisory System that recommends the most suitable crops for cultivation on the basis of weather and soil parameters. The first phase focuses on identifying relevant datasets and extracting significant features influencing crop suitability using statistical and feature selection techniques. In the next phase, various machine learning models such as Random Forest, Support Vector Machine, and Neural Networks will be trained and tested to determine the most effective model based on performance metrics like accuracy and F1-score. The final phase involves real-time system implementation using APIs."}, {"id": "AI-294", "title": "Machine Learning for Early Health Risk Prediction using Activity, Sleep, and Behavioural Pattern Changes", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Kaggle Competition: Child Mind Institute -- Detect Sleep States", "supervisor": "Sangeeta Rai( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This research focuses on developing a machine learning-based framework for early health risk prediction using activity, sleep, and behavioral pattern changes obtained from wearable sensors and lifestyle datasets. The study aims to analyze temporal and behavioral features such as sleep irregularity, sedentary duration, movement intensity, activity transitions, stress indicators, circadian rhythm shifts, and daily lifestyle variations. These features will be used to identify subtle abnormal deviations that may act as early signs of fatigue, stress, cardiovascular issues, metabolic disorders, or poor sleep health. Multiple machine learning and deep learning models will be designed, trained, and compared for accurate risk classification and prediction. In addition, explainable AI techniques will be integrated to identify the most influential behavioral factors contributing to the predicted risk, improving interpretability, reliability, and healthcare-oriented decision support."}, {"id": "AI-295", "title": "Machine Learning Model for Early Prediction of Water-Borne Disease Outbreaks Using Environmental and Public Health Data", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Dr. Premananda Sahu", "sitting_place": "28-206-C1", "description": "A Machine Learning Model for Early Prediction of Water-Borne Disease Outbreaks Using Environmental and Public Health Data is an intelligent system designed to forecast outbreaks of diseases such as cholera, typhoid, and dysentery before they spread widely. The main goal of such a model is to support public health authorities in taking timely preventive measures, thereby reducing morbidity and mortality. The model relies on the integration of environmental data and public health data. Environmental data typically includes factors like temperature, rainfall, humidity, water quality indicators (pH, turbidity, contamination levels), and seasonal variations. These factors significantly influence the growth and transmission of pathogens in water sources. Public health data, on the other hand, includes hospital records, reported disease cases, population density, sanitation conditions, and access to clean drinking water. Combining these heterogeneous data sources enables a more comprehensive understanding of outbreak patterns. The development of such a model begins with data collection and preprocessing. Data is gathered from multiple sources such as meteorological departments, water quality monitoring agencies, and healthcare institutions. Preprocessing steps include handling missing values, removing noise, normalizing features, and encoding categorical variables. Feature engineering is then performed to extract meaningful attributes, such as moving averages of rainfall or infection rates over time. Next, suitable machine learning algorithms are applied. Common approaches include supervised learning techniques such as Logistic Regression, Decision Trees, Random Forest, Support Vector Machines, and Gradient Boosting models like XGBoost. Deep learning methods such as Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) or Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks can also be used to capture temporal dependencies in time-series data. The dataset is typically split into training, validation, and testing sets to ensure proper model evaluation and avoid overfitting. The model learns patterns that correlate environmental conditions and historical disease data with outbreak occurrences. For example, heavy rainfall combined with poor sanitation may lead to increased contamination of water sources, thereby raising the risk of disease outbreaks. The trained model can then predict the probability or risk level of an outbreak in a specific region over a given time period. Evaluation metrics such as accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score, and ROC-AUC are used to assess model performance. In public health applications, recall (sensitivity) is particularly important, as missing an outbreak prediction can have severe consequences. Once validated, the model can be deployed as part of a real-time monitoring system. It can continuously analyze incoming data and generate early warnings for high-risk areas. These predictions can be visualized using dashboards or geographic information systems (GIS), enabling authorities to take actions such as issuing public advisories, improving water treatment, or allocating medical resources. In conclusion, a machine learning-based early prediction system for water-borne diseases is a powerful tool that leverages data-driven insights to enhance public health preparedness. By integrating environmental and health data, such models enable proactive decision-making, ultimately contributing to disease prevention and improved community well-being."}, {"id": "AI-296", "title": "Machine Learning-Based Detection of Fake Social Media Profiles", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH: 1775", "supervisor": "Sonia Jassi", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH29", "description": "The increasing prevalence of fake social media profiles poses risks such as identity theft, phishing, misinformation, spamming, and manipulation of public opinion. Traditional detection methods are ineffective against sophisticated fake profiles. The project aims to design an intelligent detection system using machine learning techniques to distinguish genuine users from deceptive profiles by analyzing behavioral, structural, and content-based features."}, {"id": "AI-297", "title": "Machine Learning-Based Indian Sign Language (ISL) Generator from Audio and Video Inputs", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "AICTE Social Impact Project & Inspired from Smart India Hackathon (SIH) Accessibility Theme.", "supervisor": "Dr. Sandeep Sharma", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH30", "description": "The project focuses on converting audio and visual speech inputs into Indian Sign Language (ISL) gestures using Machine Learning. It aims to assist hearing and speech-impaired individuals by providing real-time ISL translation. The system enhances communication between ISL users and non-sign language speakers through an intelligent multi-modal translation model."}, {"id": "AI-298", "title": "Machine Learning-Based Intelligent System for Automated Detection of Potholes and Road Surface Cracks", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "This topic was selected based on literature and industry trends in the field of infrastructure monitoring and smart city technologies", "supervisor": "Dr. Syed Abdul Basit Andrabi", "sitting_place": "34-202-CH11", "description": "The research aims to use machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) methods to find road surface problems like potholes and cracks. These issues pose significant risks to road safety and vehicle maintenance, making their timely identification crucial. Traditional methods of road inspection are time-consuming, labor-intensive, and often ineffective. By using smartphone sensors, cameras, and advanced ML/DL models, this project aims to provide a cost-effective, scalable, and accurate solution for road surface monitoring"}, {"id": "AI-299", "title": "Machine Learning-Based Modeling and Prediction of Time-Varying Error Build-Up Between Uploaded and Modeled Satellite Clock and Ephemeris Parameters in Navigation Satellites", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH2025(25175)", "supervisor": "Nitish Kumar", "sitting_place": "27-207-CH11", "description": "This project aims to develop machine learning-based models to analyze and predict the time-varying error build-up between uploaded and modeled satellite clock and ephemeris parameters in navigation satellites. The study focuses on identifying dynamic error patterns, improving predictive accuracy, and enhancing satellite navigation system reliability and positioning precision through data-driven modeling approaches."}, {"id": "AI-300", "title": "Mango Fruit Disease Detection using Machine Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Kaggle", "supervisor": "Gaurav Sharma", "sitting_place": "27-203-CH8", "description": "This project aims to develop an intelligent system that can automatically detect diseases in mango fruits using image data. Using the MangoFruitDDS dataset, which contains 1,700 images of healthy and diseased mangoes (Alternaria, Anthracnose, Black Mould Rot, and Stem and Rot), a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) model is trained to classify the images accurately. The system can help farmers and agricultural experts quickly identify mango diseases, enabling timely treatment and reducing crop losses. The project leverages machine learning and image processing techniques, with potential for deployment as a mobile or web application for real-time disease detection."}, {"id": "AI-301", "title": "Maximizing Section Throughput Using AI-Powered Precise Train Traffic Control", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Manish Kumar Sharma", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH7", "description": "The proposed study addresses the critical problem of railway congestion and suboptimal section throughput caused by static, rule-based traffic control systems. The project suggests developing an AI-powered, real-time train traffic control system that maximizes throughput defined as the number of trains handled per hour on a route section without compromising safety.? The system design involves several core modules: Real-time data ingestion and digital twin creation, integrating sensor and GPS data for continuous system monitoring.? Predictive analytics, using machine learning algorithms to forecast congestion points, delays, and disruptions.?? Dynamic optimization, which applies DRL to adjust schedules, train speeds, and routing dynamically for maximum efficiency.? Automated disruption management, ensuring resilient recovery from disturbances with minimal human intervention. The goal is to achieve automated, adaptive train traffic management that increases capacity, punctuality, and network reliability through AI-based precision control."}, {"id": "AI-302", "title": "Microplastic Pollution: A Review of Sources, Formation, Toxicity, Remediation, and Detection Approaches", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Development for Detection Of Microplastics(SIH-2025), Statement ID-25036", "supervisor": "Ajay Kumar Badhan", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH31", "description": "Problem Description: Microplastic pollution has emerged as a global environmental challenge due to the widespread fragmentation of plastics into microscopic particles that persist in ecosystems. These particles originate from multiple sources, undergo complex formation processes, and accumulate in soil, water, and air, where they pose potential risks to both ecological and human health. Despite growing concern, current research remains fragmented---studies often examine only isolated aspects such as sources, toxicity, or detection, without offering an integrated understanding. Furthermore, existing detection methods are costly and time-consuming, remediation technologies are limited in scalability, and the long-term toxicological impacts remain insufficiently explored. This lack of a comprehensive framework hampers the development of effective monitoring, policy interventions, and sustainable solutions."}, {"id": "AI-303", "title": "MindSpace: A Privacy-Centric, GPU-Accelerated Digital Psychological Intervention System Support System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Development of a Digital Mental Health and Psychological Support System for Students in Higher Education ( PS No- SIH25092 )", "supervisor": "Dr. Mohit Arora", "sitting_place": "28-202-C1", "description": "MindSpace is a privacy-first AI counseling system designed for universities, running entirely on local infrastructure using optimized Small Language Models. It provides real-time, empathetic mental health support without sending data to the cloud. The platform ensures confidentiality, fast responses, and safe guidance while connecting students to campus resources."}, {"id": "AI-304", "title": "ML-Based Personalized Learning Recommendations for Students Organization: Government of Punjab", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Hardarshan Kaur", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH12", "description": "Rural schools in Nabha have limited digital resources. Students struggle to learn at their own pace, and teachers cannot easily identify which lessons each student needs most. Objective Develop a Machine Learning module that provides personalized lesson recommendations based on individual student performance and learning pace. Proposed ML Module • Input: Student quiz scores, lesson completion data, engagement metrics. • Output: Recommended next lessons or exercises tailored to the student's learning needs. • Method: o Use supervised learning to predict student performance trends. o Cluster students with similar learning patterns to suggest appropriate lessons. o Continuously update recommendations as students complete lessons and quizzes."}, {"id": "AI-305", "title": "Multi-Agent Collaborative Reasoning Framework for Hallucination-Free Fact-Checking in High-Stakes Domains", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon (SIH) 2025", "supervisor": "Raghu Raja Sharma", "sitting_place": "34-202-CH8", "description": "A single Large Language Model (LLM) architecture frequently fails at tasks requiring deep, multi-step logical reasoning and domain expertise to verify complex claims. In safety-critical applications, absolute factual accuracy is non-negotiable, yet standard LLMs remain prone to hallucination. This research proposes the design and implementation of an advanced framework where multiple specialized LLM agents (e.g., retriever, verifier, and generator agents) debate and cross-check each other to arrive at a verified, hallucination-free consensus. By utilizing atomic claim decomposition, these specialized agents will systematically break down and verify complex inputs against a pipeline designed for real-time data integration. This agentic workflow ensures the foundational knowledge remains strictly factual and up-to-date. The proposed architecture will specifically target high-stakes real-world applications, such as automated legal contract auditing and preliminary patient symptom triage, where robust factual grounding is paramount."}, {"id": "AI-306", "title": "Multimodal NLP for Conversational AI: Enhancing Human-Machine Interactions", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Inspired by advancements in Natural Language Processing (NLP), Computer Vision, and Speech Processing in AI-driven communication systems.", "supervisor": "Zeenat Zahra", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH7", "description": "Traditional conversational AI models rely primarily on text, limiting their ability to understand human interactions holistically. Multimodal NLP integrates text, speech, and visual data, enabling AI to process and respond more naturally. This research explores multimodal datasets (AVSD, MELD, MMDialog), transformer-based models (CLIP, BLIP, multimodal BERT), and fusion strategies to enhance chatbot performance and user engagement."}, {"id": "AI-307", "title": "Non Invasive Voice Based Parkinson's Disease risk prediction system", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Dev-post technical blogs", "supervisor": "Priyanka Kumari", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH11", "description": "This project is a artificial intelligence--based early risk screening system for Parkinson's Disease (PD) using voice signal biomarkers. Parkinson's affects motor control, and subtle changes in speech often appear years before severe physical symptoms, making voice a powerful non-invasive diagnostic signal. The system analyzes acoustic features extracted from sustained phonations and speech recordings to predict whether a subject is at risk of Parkinson's Disease."}, {"id": "AI-308", "title": "NOVA -- Neural Operated Versatile Autobin", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025(Problem Statement ID: 25046)", "supervisor": "Salil Batra", "sitting_place": "34-207-CH13", "description": "The project focuses on developing a smart AI-powered dustbin capable of automatically identifying and segregating waste into categories such as biodegradable, recyclable, non-recyclable, and others. The system is equipped with a camera module integrated with AI-based image recognition, which captures images of the waste and classifies them using a trained dataset. Based on the classification results, the waste is then automatically directed to its respective compartment, ensuring accurate segregation, improved recycling rates, and efficient waste management. Once implemented, the project will result in efficient and automated waste segregation, leading to faster, more precise, and eco-friendly processing with minimal human intervention. It will also enhance user convenience by offering a smart and intuitive disposal process that eliminates the need for manual sorting, making waste disposal easier and more accessible in public and private spaces. Furthermore, the system will incorporate smart waste monitoring capabilities through IoT integration, enabling real-time tracking of bin status, timely waste collection, and prevention of overflow, thereby contributing to cleaner and better-managed environments."}, {"id": "AI-309", "title": "Offline Multimodal Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) System Using Large Language Models", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Robin Kumar", "sitting_place": "27-209-CH8", "description": "The project aims to develop an offline multimodal RAG system capable of ingesting and indexing heterogeneous data formats like PDFs, DOCs, images, and audio. Using local LLMs and vector databases, it enables semantic search and context-aware answer generation with transparent citations. The system supports text, image, and speech-based queries in a unified offline interface ensuring data security and accessibility."}, {"id": "AI-310", "title": "One-Stop Personalized Career & Education Advisor", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH: Smart Indian Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Khalid Hafiz Mir", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH16", "description": "It has always been very difficult for students and for employees also to decide what the right career or educational path is, and still, this process is the most critical one. At the present time, numerous separated and fragmented platforms provide information, thus making it very hard for users to get direct, customized guidance. This concept revolves around building an intelligent, AI-powered advisory platform that can offer tailored career and education advice to a single person based on the factors of the profile of that person, namely the interests, the educational history, the skills, and the current job market trends. The system will aggregate the data from reliable sources such as educational institutions, e-learning platforms, and labor market statistics to recommend apt careers, courses, and certifications of skills. Besides, the users will be introduced to their current levels of advancement, the skills that they do not possess and may be missing, and the discoveries of new job roles happening at the moment."}, {"id": "AI-311", "title": "OralShield-AI System for Real-Time Oral Cancer detection", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon (SIH) 2025-Student Innovation: Swadeshi for Atmanirbhar Bharat - MedTech / BioTech / HealthTech", "supervisor": "Isha", "sitting_place": "26-205-CH6", "description": "Oral cancer is a major global health concern, with high mortality rates often linked to late-stage diagnosis. Early detection is critical for improving patient outcomes. This project focuses on the development of an AI-powered mobile system capable of screening oral images to distinguish between cancerous and non-cancerous conditions. The system provides interpretable diagnostic outputs, including a classification, a confidence score, and a visual heatmap highlighting areas of concern. Additionally, the project documents the methodology, dataset preparation, and model development, contributing to research on AI-assisted oral cancer detection and aiding clinicians in informed decision-making"}, {"id": "AI-312", "title": "Personalized Resume Optimization using Artificial Intelligence", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Ankita Wadhawan", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH16", "description": "In today's competitive job market, creating a professional and tailored resume is a crucial step toward employability. However, most job seekers, especially students and fresh graduates, face challenges in drafting resumes that effectively highlight their skills, match job requirements, and pass through automated Applicant Tracking Systems (ATS). The project \"Intelligent Resume Building using AI\" aims to address these challenges by developing an advanced, AI-powered system capable of generating personalized and optimized resumes based on user input and job descriptions. The proposed system leverages Artificial Intelligence, Natural Language Processing (NLP), and Machine Learning (ML) techniques to automate the resume creation and optimization process. Users will provide their basic details such as education, skills, experience, and career interests through a user-friendly interface. The AI model will then analyze this data to generate a structured, grammatically correct, and professional resume tailored to specific job profiles. By utilizing NLP-based keyword extraction and similarity matching, the system ensures that the resume aligns with industry standards and job-specific requirements."}, {"id": "AI-313", "title": "Plant Disease Detection Using Deep Learning: A Review of Methods, Challenges, and Real-World Implementation", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Self developed", "supervisor": "Hardarshan Kaur", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH12", "description": "The application of deep learning to plant disease detection has seen explosive growth over the past decade. Numerous studies report remarkable classification accuracies, frequently exceeding 99%, on standardized, controlled laboratory datasets such as PlantVillage. However, a critical bottleneck has emerged in translating these academic successes into practical agricultural tools. When deployed in real-world farming environments, models trained exclusively on single-leaf, uniform-background images often suffer a catastrophic drop in performance, sometimes falling below 50% accuracy. This project proposes a comprehensive systematic review to critically analyze the current landscape of deep learning methodologies for plant pathology, with a primary focus on understanding this lab-to-field deployment gap and evaluating strategies for real-world implementation."}, {"id": "AI-314", "title": "PRAVAH: An AI-Driven Hyper-Local Early Warning System for Urban Flash Floods using Multi-Modal Data Fusion.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Gautam Kumar", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH25", "description": "Project PRAVAH is an AI-powered system designed to provide hyper-local, street-level flash flood predictions. It works by intelligently fusing diverse data sources---live weather, city topography, and real-time social media posts---to create a dynamic and accurate early warning system for urban areas. Technology Stack ? Backend: Python, Node.js, express.js, Geospatial data API ? AI / Machine Learning: Python with libraries like TensorFlow or PyTorch, GeoPandas for geospatial analysis ? Database/Dataset: MongoDB, Kaggle, UCI ? Frontend (Dashboard): Vue.js, React.js, a modern JavaScript library for building interactive user interfaces, with a mapping library like Mapbox."}, {"id": "CLD-005", "title": "Praxium AI : A Cloud-Native, AI-Driven Platform to Remediate Systemic Deficiencies in Indian Engineering Education", "category": "Cloud Computing", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Anurag Tewari", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH14", "description": "Indian higher education, especially in engineering (B-Tech), faces a major challenge marked by the contradiction of producing large numbers of graduates with very low employability. This crisis stems from outdated curricula, limited teaching innovation, faculty shortages, and inadequate infrastructure. To address these issues, the paper introduces Praxium AI, a cloud-native, AI-driven educational technology platform designed to transform engineering education at scale. The platform is built on a microservices-based, offline-first architecture, ensuring accessibility and robustness across diverse digital conditions in India. Praxium AI incorporates three key AI-powered pedagogical modules. The first is a hybrid recommendation engine that creates personalized learning pathways for students. The second is an intelligent tutoring system capable of answering domain-specific technical questions, thereby supporting deeper conceptual understanding. The third is an automated assessment engine equipped with advanced features, including the ability to evaluate handwritten submissions. Alongside technical design, the paper outlines a strategic framework for effective deployment and faculty empowerment. A comprehensive mixed-methods evaluation plan is also proposed to assess the platform's educational outcomes and system performance. Overall, Praxium AI is positioned as a holistic, scalable, and equitable solution to bridge the skills gap, enhance employability, and reshape the future of engineering education in India."}, {"id": "AI-315", "title": "Precision Insurance Premium Forecasting Using Adaptive Machine Learning Model Framework", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Review", "source": "Google Scholar and Springer Book Series", "supervisor": "Tiyas Sarkar", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH24", "description": "An adaptive machine learning (ML) framework for insurance premium forecasting can provide insurers with three detailed outcomes: superior predictive accuracy, dynamic and explainable pricing, and enhanced business agility. By using ensemble models and Explainable AI (XAI) techniques, the framework can move beyond traditional actuarial methods to produce more precise, transparent, and responsive forecasts"}, {"id": "AI-316", "title": "predicting road accident severity with ensemble machine learning models", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "sih", "supervisor": "Dr. Ravindra Singh Yadav", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH12", "description": "Road accidents remain a critical public safety issue worldwide, leading to severe injuries, fatalities, and economic loss. Accurate prediction of accident severity can play a significant role in preventing accidents, optimizing emergency responses, and supporting evidence-based policymaking. This project aims to develop an intelligent, data-driven system for predicting the severity of road accidents using advanced ensemble machine learning techniques. The proposed system leverages historical accident datasets containing variables such as weather conditions, time of occurrence, road type, vehicle type, driver behavior, and location-specific factors. Data preprocessing will include handling missing values, feature encoding, outlier detection, and data normalization. Feature selection methods will be applied to identify the most influential factors affecting accident severity, ensuring model efficiency and interpretability. The core of this research involves implementing and evaluating multiple ensemble learning algorithms such as Random Forest, XGBoost, LightGBM, and stacking ensemble models. These methods will be compared against traditional machine learning models like logistic regression and decision trees to highlight performance improvements. Ensemble models are expected to offer better generalization, reduced variance, and higher predictive accuracy compared to single classifiers. Performance evaluation will be carried out using standard metrics such as accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score, AUC-ROC curve, and confusion matrix. Cross-validation techniques will ensure the robustness of the models and prevent overfitting. Additionally, explainable AI (XAI) techniques like SHAP or LIME will be integrated to provide interpretability and explain the contribution of each feature to accident severity prediction. The outcomes of this project can assist traffic management authorities in identifying high-risk zones and times, optimizing resource allocation for emergency services, and designing preventive measures. It can also support smart transportation systems and contribute to road safety policies. Furthermore, the research demonstrates how ensemble machine learning can be effectively applied to real-world safety-critical domains. Overall, this project blends machine learning, data analytics, and intelligent transportation concepts to address a pressing societal challenge. The expected deliverables include a trained and validated prediction model, a user-friendly dashboard for visualization of accident severity trends, and a research report detailing methodology, analysis, and conclusions."}, {"id": "AI-317", "title": "Predictive Analysis of Medicines & Doctors Availability", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Dr. Premananda Sahu", "sitting_place": "28-206-C1", "description": "Efficient healthcare delivery in government hospitals is often challenged by the unpredictable availability of medicines and medical staff. Shortages of essential drugs or unavailability of doctors, especially in rural and semi-urban regions, lead to delayed treatments, overcrowding, and reduced patient satisfaction. To address this recurring issue, this project focuses on building a Predictive Analysis System that utilizes Machine Learning (ML) to forecast the availability of medicines and doctors based on historical and real-time data. The system aims to analyze trends in medicine consumption, patient inflow, procurement cycles, and staff schedules to anticipate future demand and availability levels. By leveraging time-series forecasting and regression models, the project seeks to predict shortages before they occur, enabling timely interventions such as restocking or staff redistribution. The model will be trained using hospital datasets containing information like medicine usage records, doctor attendance, patient admission rates, seasonal disease patterns, and procurement logs. Data preprocessing techniques, such as missing value handling and normalization, will ensure data quality. Feature engineering will be used to identify influential variables --- for example, disease outbreak patterns, supply timelines, and local health events --- that directly impact availability. Once trained, the predictive model will provide real-time insights through a dashboard interface designed for hospital administrators. This interface will display predicted medicine stock levels, upcoming shortage alerts, and doctor availability forecasts for the next few weeks or months. By visualizing these trends, decision-makers can schedule timely procurement, manage workforce allocation, and ensure critical resources are never understocked. The system will also integrate with hospital management databases to automatically update forecasts as new data arrives, creating a self-learning ecosystem that improves accuracy over time. Techniques like ARIMA, LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory networks), and Linear Regression can be explored to evaluate and select the most accurate forecasting model for both medicines and staff availability. In addition to improving operational efficiency, this project will support evidence-based policymaking for healthcare administrators. Predictive insights can help identify recurring bottlenecks, optimize supply chain management, and ensure equitable distribution of resources across multiple hospital units. Moreover, it can reduce manual tracking dependency and mitigate emergency shortages during peak medical demand periods, such as monsoon-related disease outbreaks or pandemic situations. Ultimately, the Predictive Analysis of Medicines & Doctors Availability system aims to transform healthcare resource planning into a proactive, data-driven process. By anticipating needs rather than reacting to crises, government hospitals can improve patient care quality, reduce operational stress, and enhance trust in public healthcare services."}, {"id": "AI-318", "title": "Privacy-Aware Forensic DNA Matching System Using Encrypted STR Comparison and Synthetic DNA Generation", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "The topic originates from Smart India Hackathon (SIH) 2024, which encourages innovative tech solutions for national challenges. It focuses on developing a secure and privacy-preserving DNA matching system using encryption and synthetic DNA techniques for forensic applications.", "supervisor": "Dr. Isha Bhatia", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH7", "description": "The project aims to build a Privacy-Aware Forensic DNA Matching System using encrypted STR comparison and synthetic DNA generation. It ensures secure, accurate, and privacy-preserving DNA identification for forensic use. By applying encryption and synthetic data, it protects sensitive genetic information while maintaining matching accuracy. This SIH 2024 project promotes ethical and secure digital forensic practices."}, {"id": "AI-319", "title": "Privacy-Aware Forensic DNA Matching System Using Encrypted STR Comparison and Synthetic DNA Generation", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "The topic originates from Smart India Hackathon (SIH) 2024, which encourages innovative tech solutions for national challenges. It focuses on developing a secure and privacy-preserving DNA matching system using encryption and synthetic DNA techniques for forensic applications.", "supervisor": "Dr. Karandeep Kaur", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH12", "description": "The project aims to build a Privacy-Aware Forensic DNA Matching System using encrypted STR comparison and synthetic DNA generation. It ensures secure, accurate, and privacy-preserving DNA identification for forensic use. By applying encryption and synthetic data, it protects sensitive genetic information while maintaining matching accuracy. This SIH 2024 project promotes ethical and secure digital forensic practices."}, {"id": "AI-320", "title": "Proactive India: AI- Powered Platform for Transparent and Accountable Governance", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "SIH 2025 (https://www.sih.gov.in/sih2025PS) Topic 31 (Crowdsourced Civic lssue Reporting and Resolution System)", "supervisor": "Blossom", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH15", "description": "This proposed work introduces Proactive India, a civic-tech platform designed to enhance transparency and accountability in public infrastructure projects by enabling real-time tracking, AI-assisted issue reporting, and structured communication between citizens, government bodies, and contractors. It empowers citizens to report problems with geotagged evidence, provides authorities with analytics dashboards for decision-making, and enables contractors to maintain transparent project updates, collectively strengthening participatory governance."}, {"id": "AI-321", "title": "Public Health Chatbot for Disease Awareness and Early Risk Detection using Full-Stack Architecture", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "AI driven Public Health Chatbot for Disease Awareness. (SIH25049)", "supervisor": "Dr. Harpreet Singh", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH9", "description": "This project proposes the development of an AI-driven public health chatbot for disease awareness and early risk detection using a full-stack architecture. The system leverages natural language processing (NLP) to understand user queries and extract symptoms, enabling a hybrid model (rule-based and machine learning) to provide preliminary risk assessment for common diseases such as flu, dengue, diabetes, and respiratory conditions. Designed as a first-level support tool, the chatbot delivers instant responses, preventive guidance, and recommendations for seeking medical consultation when necessary, without replacing professional healthcare services. The application is built with a scalable full-stack framework, where the front-end (using React or Angular) ensures a responsive and user-friendly interface, and the back-end (using Node.js or Django) handles request processing, chatbot logic, and API integrations. A secure database like MongoDB or MySQL is used to store interactions while maintaining data privacy through encryption and anonymization. Additional features include multilingual support, real-time public health updates, and analytics for monitoring user trends and health concerns. Overall, the system offers a cost-effective, accessible, and scalable solution to improve public health awareness, encourage preventive care, and assist in early identification of potential health risks."}, {"id": "AI-322", "title": "RAG -- Language Agnostic Ai Query resolver", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH 2025", "supervisor": "Sandeep kaur", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH39", "description": "A production-ready Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) chatbot designed to understand and respond across multiple languages without being tied to any single language model or locale. The system ingests official policies, process documents, and FAQs; indexes them in a vector database; and answers user queries with grounded citations. It supports department/tenant segmentation, secure user login, and optional integrations with internal portals (via connectors) to fetch user-specific records where permitted. The initial release focuses on a web-based user interface and an admin console---no public or partner APIs are exposed. This project is novel because it delivers one end-to-end Q&A platform that keeps each department's knowledge separated yet consistently managed, securely connects to internal systems for personalized, permission-aware answers, and automatically handles document upload, deduplication, versioning, and re-indexing closing the current gap where teams lack a simple, multilingual, always-up-to-date, feedback-driven way to get trustworthy answers at scale."}, {"id": "AI-323", "title": "RAG-Augmented Personalized Heart Rate Forecasting with Explainable Physiological Insights.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "rricc22/heart-rate-prediction-lstm((SUB3_V2)", "supervisor": "Bhanu Talwar", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH14", "description": "This project predicts individual heart rate trends using LSTM-based time-series modeling and explains variations through a RAG framework. By integrating wearable data with retrieved physiological knowledge, it generates clear explanations of influencing factors like stress, sleep, and activity. It enables proactive health monitoring and provides actionable insights for improved clinical and personal decision-making."}, {"id": "AI-324", "title": "Real Time AI/ML Based Phishing and Prevention System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Anjum Rouf( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This project develops a real-time AI/ML-based system to detect and prevent phishing attacks. It analyzes URLs, emails, and website features to identify malicious activities and alert users instantly. Using machine learning, it improves accuracy over time, helping protect users from data theft and enhancing online security and trust."}, {"id": "AI-325", "title": "Real time Multimodel Monitoring system and Analytics System//TRACE: Time & Recognition Automated Check-in Engine", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Karanbir Singh", "sitting_place": "27-203-CH9", "description": "TRACE: Time & Recognition Automated Check-in Engine. This system provides Automated Attendance and Real-time Analytical Tracking. It uses a bi-modal recognition approach based on Gait and Facial features. It leverages an advanced Fusion LLM (e.g., Context-Aware/Adaptive Fusion with attention) to dynamically weigh the two modalities, achieving Complex Covariate Invariance (e.g., masks, coats). The analytics module provides occupancy monitoring and precise hour-stay duration within the premises. FaceNet (E_face) and a 3D CNN/GaitSet (E_gait-seq) extract feature embeddings for the final bi-modal network fusion."}, {"id": "AI-326", "title": "Real Time Object Detection Using YOLO-Based Deep Learning Models", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "google scholar", "supervisor": "Rakshit Bansal( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "Real-time object detection has become a critical component in various applications such as autonomous driving, surveillance systems, and smart city infrastructure. This research focuses on the design and implementation of an efficient object detection system using the YOLO deep learning framework."}, {"id": "AI-327", "title": "Real-Time Crop Disease Diagnosis System Using CNNs and Transfer Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Dr.Max Bhatia", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-C1", "description": "Crop diseases are one of the leading causes of reduced agricultural productivity and economic loss for farmers. Identifying these diseases early is often difficult without expert help, and traditional diagnosis methods are time-consuming and prone to errors. To address this, the Real-time Crop Disease Diagnosis System provides an innovative and accessible solution for farmers to detect crop diseases quickly and accurately using their smartphones. The system employs Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and transfer learning models such as MobileNet or ResNet to analyze images of crop leaves, stems, or fruits. It classifies the image as healthy or diseased, identifies the type of disease, and offers actionable treatment suggestions. The platform includes a mobile and web interface for easy image uploads, real-time analysis, and crop health tracking over time through visual analytics. To enhance user engagement, the system can be integrated with voice-enabled guidance feature that can overlay infected areas on the live camera feed. This interactive feature make the solution not only technologically advanced but also farmer-friendly and accessible to all, including those with limited literacy."}, {"id": "AI-328", "title": "Real-Time Multi-Class Object Detection for Automated Waste Stream Sorting and Actuation", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Business Model", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Gunseerat Kaur", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH29", "description": "This project will develop a high-speed, automated waste sorting mechanism using a Deep Learning Object Detection model (e.g., YOLOv8). We will capture a live video stream from a simulated conveyor belt and use the model to accurately identify the type (Plastic, Metal, Paper, etc.) and the precise pixel coordinates of each waste item. The core task is translating this detection data into a simulated actuation command (a signal for a robotic arm or air-jet) to accurately divert the item into its designated bin."}, {"id": "AI-329", "title": "Real-Time Multilingual Simplified Captioning System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Develop a real-time closed captioning solution with simplified captions in multiple Indian languages for accessibility and inclusivity of Deaf and hard-of-hearing individuals. ( PS No - SIH25246 )", "supervisor": "Dr. Mohit Arora", "sitting_place": "28-202-C1", "description": "This project develops a real-time multilingual captioning system for India's diverse linguistic environment. It transcribes speech across Hindi, English, and regional languages, detects code-switching, converts scripts, translates content, and simplifies text for Deaf and Hard-of-Hearing users. With low latency and enhanced readability, it enables accessible communication in classrooms, meetings, and public events."}, {"id": "AI-330", "title": "Real-Time Public Transport Tracking for Small Cities", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Vidhi Sood", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH6", "description": "In small cities and tier-2 towns, public transport systems lack real-time tracking, causing inconvenience to commuters who face unpredictable bus schedules. This leads to overcrowding, wasted time, and reduced reliance on public transport. The problem is acute in cities with growing populations but limited digital infrastructure for transport management. Impact / Why this problem needs to be solved Over 60% of commuters in small cities face delays due to lack of real-time information, reducing public transport usage and increasing private vehicle dependency, which worsens traffic and pollution. A solution would enhance commuter experience and promote sustainable transport."}, {"id": "AI-331", "title": "Real-Time Smart Pest Detection System for Crop Protection and Precision Farming", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "https://www.sih.gov.in/sih2025PS", "supervisor": "Palvi Soni", "sitting_place": "27-207-CH7", "description": "Smart Pest Detection for Farmers refers to the use of advanced technologies like computer vision, artificial intelligence (AI), and IoT sensors to automatically detect, identify, and monitor pests in agricultural fields. Traditional pest management relies on manual inspection, which is time-consuming, error-prone, and often leads to delayed intervention. A smart pest detection system, however, captures images of crops or pest activity and uses machine learning algorithms to accurately identify the type of pest and assess the severity of infestation."}, {"id": "AI-332", "title": "Reducing hallucination in large language models using retrieval-augmented generation with confidence scoring", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "\"FloatChat: AI-Powered Conversational Interface for Data\"", "supervisor": "Deepali Kumari( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This project proposes a robust AI system to reduce hallucinations in Large Language Models by integrating Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) with a confidence scoring mechanism. The system retrieves relevant, verified data from trusted sources and generates responses grounded in factual information. A confidence score is assigned to each output based on relevance and supporting evidence, ensuring reliability and transparency. The solution enhances trust in AI systems and is applicable across domains such as education, healthcare, and governance."}, {"id": "AI-333", "title": "Remote learning ecosystem for rural higher education", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Monika Sharma( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "Rural colleges in India face significant challenges that directly affect the quality of education and student success. One of the major issues is the shortage of qualified faculty, especially in specialized subjects, which limits students' ability to gain a comprehensive understanding of core concepts and stay updated with evolving academic and industry standards. Additionally, the lack of exposure to practical, career-oriented learning and modern teaching methods reduces students' employability and confidence in the job market. Another critical concern is the unstable or low-bandwidth internet connectivity prevalent in rural areas, which makes most existing online learning platforms impractical for students and educators. Moreover, the dominance of a few major languages on these platforms further excludes students who prefer to learn in their native or regional languages, creating a linguistic barrier to effective learning. These combined issues have resulted in a widening digital and educational divide between rural and urban learners. Therefore, there is an urgent need for an affordable, inclusive, and connectivity-friendly remote learning ecosystem designed specifically for rural higher education. Such a system should incorporate adaptive technology, multilingual support, and interactive learning tools to ensure equal access to quality education for every student, regardless of location."}, {"id": "AI-334", "title": "Revolutionizing Education Through Smart and Innovative Technologies", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Dr. Sangeeta", "sitting_place": "34-202-CH23", "description": "In today's fast-paced digital world, the education sector is evolving rapidly to keep up with technological advancements. The Smart Education App, developed using Android Studio with Kotlin, is an innovative solution designed to make learning more accessible, interactive, and personalized for students. The application aims to transform traditional education into a digital, data-driven, and student-centric experience by integrating Artificial Intelligence (AI), Firebase, and cloud-based learning features. The Smart Education App serves as a comprehensive learning management platform where students can attend video lectures, take interactive quizzes, access study materials, track their learning progress, and collaborate with peers and mentors. The app is developed using Kotlin, the official programming language for Android development, ensuring a modern, efficient, and type-safe codebase. Its architecture follows MVVM (Model-View-ViewModel) principles, making the app more scalable, maintainable, and efficient. The app is connected to Firebase Authentication for secure login and user management, allowing users to sign up using email or Google accounts. All user data, including profiles, quiz results, and learning progress, are stored in Firebase Firestore, a real-time cloud database. This ensures seamless data synchronization across devices and allows instant updates for any changes made by the users. The use of Firebase Storage also enables uploading and streaming of educational videos, ensuring smooth video playback experiences within the app. One of the key features of Smart Education is its AI-integrated personalized learning system. The AI module analyzes a learner's quiz performance, time spent on topics, and engagement levels to provide personalized recommendations. For instance, if a student struggles with mathematics quizzes, the system suggests targeted video tutorials and practice questions to improve their understanding. This AI-driven adaptive learning helps bridge knowledge gaps and enhances retention. The quiz and leaderboard module adds a gamified learning experience. Students can attempt topic-wise quizzes, and their scores are updated in real-time on a leaderboard. The leaderboard displays usernames instead of IDs for privacy and creates a sense of healthy competition among learners. Additionally, educators can add, edit, or manage quiz content using Firestore, ensuring flexibility in updating course materials. The app's user interface is built using Jetpack Compose, Google's modern UI toolkit for Kotlin. Compose allows developers to design sleek, dynamic, and responsive interfaces with minimal boilerplate code. The clean layout, intuitive navigation, and visually appealing design enhance user engagement and ensure a delightful learning experience. In future enhancements, the app can integrate voice-based AI assistants, AR/VR-based learning simulations, and predictive analytics dashboards for teachers to monitor student performance trends. The Smart Education App embodies the vision of transforming traditional classrooms into intelligent digital learning environments, aligning with the government's vision of Digital India and Smart Learning"}, {"id": "AI-335", "title": "Rockfall Prediction with Quantum Machine Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Inspired from SIH'25 : Problem ID 25071", "supervisor": "Kawal Preet Kaur( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "Rockfalls in open-pit mines pose serious risks to human lives, equipment, and operations, causing injuries, delays, and financial losses. Existing monitoring methods rely on manual inspections or costly proprietary systems that are slow or lack predictive power. With the rise of AI and digital monitoring, there is a need for predictive, real-time, and cost-effective solutions. Quantum Machine Learning (QML) can help process large multi-source geological datasets more efficiently than classical ML. Description This project proposes a hybrid Quantum-Classical ML system to predict rockfall incidents by fusing: • Digital Elevation Models (DEM) • Drone imagery • Geotechnical sensors (strain, displacement, pore pressure, vibrations) • Environmental data (rainfall, temperature) Key components: • Preprocessing & data fusion (classical pipelines) • Dimensionality reduction with Quantum PCA (QPCA) • Predictive models using Quantum Neural Networks (QNN) / Quantum SVM (QSVM) in a hybrid setup • Optimization (QAOA) for alert thresholds and evacuation prioritization • Dashboard: real-time risk maps, probability forecasts, SMS/email alerts"}, {"id": "AI-336", "title": "SafeDrive AI: Driver Alertness System using Machine Learning Techniques", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH25002", "supervisor": "Priyanka Gupta", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH20", "description": "A system that uses AI to prevent road accidents, by leveraging the phone's front camera and a real-time facial landmark detection model, it monitors the driver for drowsiness (eye closure, yawning) and distraction (head turned away). If dangerous behavior is detected, it triggers immediate audio alerts, acting as a smart co-pilot to enhance driver safety without needing any special hardware."}, {"id": "AI-337", "title": "Safeguard: A Web-Based Parental Control Extension for Filtering Age-Appropriate YouTube Content", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Dr. Kewal Krishan", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH19", "description": "It focuses on developing a browser-based application that allows parents to regulate the type of content accessible to their children on YouTube. The extension analyzes video ratings and categories to filter out content containing strong language, adult themes, or inappropriate visuals. Parents can customize viewing preferences or give voice/text commands to block or allow specific genres such as stand-up comedy, vlogs, or cartoons. By doing so, Safeguard ensures a safer and more controlled digital environment for children. It empowers modern parents to maintain healthy and age-appropriate screen time for their kids."}, {"id": "AI-338", "title": "sahayak- AI powered one stop career and education guidance platform", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Monika Sharma( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "sahayak is an A- driven full stack development web platform that bridges the gap between students and career guidance in goverment colleges. it uses AI/ML , NLP and a hybrid recommender system to provide personalized course and career suggestions. key features include visual career mapping nearby college listings, admission/scholarship alerts, and a resource hub for data- driven academic and career decisions."}, {"id": "AI-339", "title": "Sentiment Analysis and Classification of Tourist Place Reviews Using Machine Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "\"Inspired by real-world problem statements from Smart India Hackathon (SIH) 2024 and advancements in AI-driven sentiment analysis for tourism.\"", "supervisor": "Dr. Baljinder Kaur", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH6", "description": "This research focuses on analysing and classifying the sentiments expressed in tourist place reviews to understand visitor experiences better. By examining feedback from travellers, the study aims to provide valuable insights for tourism stakeholders. The findings can help improve destination management, enhance tourist satisfaction, and promote travel destinations more effectively. This research contributes to the growing field of sentiment analysis by addressing the unique challenges of multilingual and culturally diverse tourist reviews."}, {"id": "AI-340", "title": "Sentiment Analysis of Comments", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Aryan Maan", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH17", "description": "The project focuses on developing an AI-driven system to analyze large volumes of public comments and feedback submitted on draft policies, legislations, or proposals. When significant numbers of comments are received, manual review becomes time-consuming and risks overlooking important inputs. The system will apply natural language processing techniques to perform sentiment analysis, generate concise summaries of submissions, and create words highlighting frequently used terms. This ensures that every comment is systematically considered, enabling policymakers and organizations to gain clear insights into stakeholder perspectives and prioritize feedback effectively."}, {"id": "AI-341", "title": "Sentiment analysis of comments received through E-consultation module", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH25035", "supervisor": "Mohit Dewangan", "sitting_place": "27-209-CH12", "description": "The draft document soliciting comments is made available for a specified period, during which any stakeholder may submit their observations either on the overall amendment or on specific provisions of the draft legislation. In instances where a substantial volume of comments is received on draft legislation, there exists a risk of certain observations being inadvertently overlooked or inadequately analysed. In order to review each individual submission, leveraging AI-assisted tools will help ensure that all remarks are duly considered and systematically analysed. Requirement is the development of an AI model aimed at predicting the sentiments of the suggestions provided by stakeholders in the eConsultation module. It should also generate a visual representation in the form of a word cloud, highlighting the keywords utilised by the stakeholders within their suggestions."}, {"id": "AI-342", "title": "Sentiment analysis of comments received through E-consultation module", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025 (Problem Statement ID 25035)", "supervisor": "Danish Meiraj", "sitting_place": "28-204-CH18", "description": "Background eConsultation module is an online platform wherein proposed amendments/draft legislations are posted on MCA's website for external users to submit their comments and suggestions pertaining to the same through the MCA21 portal. The comments are captured in a structured format for due consideration with respect to amending the draft legislation, based on the suggestions or observations received. Problem Statement The draft document soliciting comments is made available for a specified period, during which any stakeholder may submit their observations either on the overall amendment or on specific provisions of the draft legislation. In instances where a substantial volume of comments is received on draft legislation, there exists a risk of certain observations being inadvertently overlooked or inadequately analysed. In order to review each individual submission, leveraging AI-assisted tools will help ensure that all remarks are duly considered and systematically analysed. Requirement is the development of an AI model aimed at predicting the sentiments of the suggestions provided by stakeholders in the eConsultation module. It should also generate a visual representation in the form of a word cloud, highlighting the keywords utilised by the stakeholders within their suggestions. Expected Outcome The intention is to discern the feedback received from the stakeholders through the following: • Sentiment analysis • Summary generation • Word cloud The solution should considerably reduce the effort of the end user in analysing a high volume of comments. It should be able to clearly identify the sentiments of comments individually as well as broadly overall. The summary generation should be accurate and convey the meaning of the comment properly, in a precise manner. The word cloud feature should showcase the density of the words used by all users."}, {"id": "AI-343", "title": "Smart City Noise Pollution Prediction", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "https://www.india.gov.in/spotlight/smart-cities-mission-step-towards-smart-india (Falls under Smart City and Urban Development initiatives.)", "supervisor": "Amanpal Singh Rayat", "sitting_place": "36-209-A-CH9", "description": "Theme: Smart Cities / Environment Objective: Build ML models to predict noise levels in urba areas using time-series or regression methods. Available Dataset: UrbanSound8K Dataset (Environmental Sound Classification): https://urbansounddataset.weebly.com/urbansound8k.html Noise Pollution Data for Indian Cities (Open Government Data): https://data.gov.in/catalog/noise-pollution-levels Research paper scope: Compare ML (Random Forest, Gradient Boost) vs DL (CNN, RNN) for noise classification. Map and visualize noise levels using GIS and Python Dash. Predict future noise hotspots based on traffic patterns. SIH relevance: Falls under Smart City and Urban Development initiatives."}, {"id": "AI-344", "title": "Smart Crop Advisory System for Small and Marginal Farmers", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Shilpa Sharma", "sitting_place": "25-301-C2", "description": "A majority of small and marginal farmers in India rely on traditional knowledge, local shopkeepers, or guesswork for crop selection, pest control, and fertilizer use. They lack access to personalized, real-time advisory services that account for soil type, weather conditions, and crop history. This often leads to poor yield, excessive input costs, and environmental degradation due to overuse of chemicals. Language barriers, low digital literacy, and absence of localized tools further limit their access to modern agri-tech resources."}, {"id": "AI-345", "title": "Smart Crop Advisory System for Small and Marginal Farmers", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH2025", "supervisor": "Abdul Malik Ansari", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH18", "description": "A majority of small and marginal farmers in India rely on traditional knowledge, local shopkeepers, or guesswork for crop selection, pest control, and fertilizer use. They lack access to personalized, real-time advisory services that consider soil type, weather conditions, and crop history. This often results in: Poor crop yield High input costs Environmental degradation due to excessive chemical use Additionally, language barriers, low digital literacy, and absence of localized tools further limit farmers' access to modern agri-tech resources."}, {"id": "AI-346", "title": "Smart Crop Advisory System for Small and Marginal Farmers", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Priyanka Gupta", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH20", "description": "An AI-powered system that provides personalized crop recommendations, detects plant diseases from leaf images using CNNs, and integrates real-time weather data to help small and marginal farmers make informed farming decisions, optimize yield, and reduce costs."}, {"id": "AI-347", "title": "Smart Crop Advisory System for Small and Marginal Farmers", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025 (Problem Statement ID 25010)", "supervisor": "Danish Meiraj", "sitting_place": "28-204-CH18", "description": "Problem Description A majority of small and marginal farmers in India rely on traditional knowledge, local shopkeepers, or guesswork for crop selection, pest control, and fertilizer use. They lack access to personalized, real-time advisory services that account for soil type, weather conditions, and crop history. This often leads to poor yield, excessive input costs, and environmental degradation due to overuse of chemicals. Language barriers, low digital literacy, and absence of localized tools further limit their access to modern agri-tech resources. Impact / Why this problem needs to be solved Helping small farmers make informed decisions can significantly increase productivity, reduce costs, and improve livelihoods. It also contributes to sustainable farming practices, food security, and environmental conservation. A smart advisory solution can empower farmers with scientific insights in their native language and reduce dependency on unreliable third-party advice. Expected Outcomes • A multilingual, AI-based mobile app or chatbot that provides real-time, location-specific crop advisory. • Soil health recommendations and fertilizer guidance. • Weather-based alerts and predictive insights. • Pest/disease detection via image uploads. • Market price tracking. • Voice support for low-literate users. • Feedback and usage data collection for continuous improvement. Relevant Stakeholders / Beneficiaries • Small and marginal farmers • Agricultural extension officers • Government agriculture departments • NGOs and cooperatives • Agri-tech startups Supporting Data • 86% of Indian farmers are small or marginal (NABARD Report, 2022). • Studies show ICT-based advisories can increase crop yield by 20--30%."}, {"id": "AI-348", "title": "Smart Crop Advisory System for Small and Marginal Farmers using LLM and RAG", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Sandeep Sharma", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH30", "description": "The Smart Crop Advisory System leverages Large Language Models (LLMs) with Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) to provide personalized, real-time, and context-aware agricultural guidance to small and marginal farmers. By integrating local weather, soil, and crop data with curated agricultural knowledge, the system delivers accurate crop recommendations, pest/disease alerts, and best practices, helping farmers improve yield, reduce risks, and make informed decisions."}, {"id": "AI-349", "title": "Smart Curriculum Activity & Attendance Application", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25011", "supervisor": "Abdul Malik Ansari", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH18", "description": "Many educational institutions still rely on manual attendance systems, which are time-consuming and prone to errors. Teachers spend a large portion of class time marking attendance, reducing valuable instructional hours. Meanwhile, students often spend free periods unproductively due to a lack of structured guidance, leading to poor time management and reduced alignment with long-term academic or career goals. There is also a gap in personalized learning support during idle classroom hours. Currently, institutions lack tools that integrate daily schedules with individual student planning and automated tracking"}, {"id": "AI-350", "title": "Smart Curriculum Activity & Attendance Monitor App", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon (SIH) 2025", "supervisor": "Raghu Raja Sharma", "sitting_place": "34-202-CH8", "description": "Managing curriculum activities and attendance in educational institutions often involves multiple manual processes---ranging from recording attendance, tracking student participation, to maintaining academic and extracurricular records. This leads to inefficiency, data inaccuracy, and limited insights into student engagement and performance. The Smart Curriculum Activity & Attendance App aims to digitize and automate these key academic management tasks through a unified, intelligent platform. The system will help institutions, teachers, and students streamline daily operations by integrating attendance tracking, activity management, notifications, and analytics into one platform. The proposed system will consist of three main components: 1. Student & Faculty App (web/mobile): • Enables real-time attendance marking using QR codes, face recognition, or NFC. • Provides access to academic schedules, activity updates, and attendance records. 2. Admin Dashboard: • Allows administrators to monitor attendance reports, manage events, upload activity data, and generate analytical insights on student participation and performance. 3. Cloud-Enabled Backend: • Ensures secure data storage, seamless synchronization, and role-based access. • Employs AI-based analytics to identify attendance trends, student engagement patterns, and suggest improvements in academic planning. By integrating all curriculum activities and attendance under a single digital platform, the solution reduces administrative workload, enhances transparency, and promotes a more data-driven approach to academic management. It also empowers students by giving them better visibility into their own academic participation and performance."}, {"id": "AI-351", "title": "Smart Curriculum Activity & Attendance App", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Richa Nigam( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "The Smart Curriculum Activity and Attendance System (SCAAS) is a state-of-the-art deep learning and data-driven platform that essentially intends to transform the management and the personalization aspects of the academic sector. The implementation uses a blend of computer vision, natural language processing (NLP), and machine learning techniques in such a way that not only the attendance tracking is automated, but the academic performance can also be predicted, and the personalized learning paths can be provided. By means of facial recognition and liveness detection methods, the system's first feature, Smart Attendance Automation, is the one which actually performs real-time student attendance in a very accurate way with the help of TensorFlow and OpenCV. The Personalized Learning Recommendation, the third and the most innovative component of the system, uses transformer-based NLP models like BERT and Sentence-BERT for understanding student feedback, study patterns, and learning preferences. The truth is the system suggests the learners the materials and the methods that meet each student's needs based on these data, hence, it is them who have the freedom to determine the pace of their learning and simultaneously they see their grades improving."}, {"id": "AI-352", "title": "Smart Home Energy & Water Consumption Dashboard", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Cherry Khosla", "sitting_place": "34-205-CH10", "description": "The Smart Home Energy & Water Consumption Dashboard is a web-based application developed using the MERN stack (MongoDB, Express.js, React.js, Node.js) designed to promote sustainability and smart resource management in households. The system enables users to monitor, analyze, and optimize their home appliances' energy and water consumption (e.g., refrigerator, washing machine, air conditioner, desert cooler). It provides real-time usage data, personalized recommendations, and AI-based predictions to help reduce wastage and improve efficiency. By integrating IoT data or sensor APIs (simulated or real), the platform gives users a complete view of their daily, weekly, and monthly energy and water consumption. Through insightful graphs and alerts, users can understand their usage patterns and take action to minimize resource consumption---contributing directly to a sustainable and eco-friendly lifestyle."}, {"id": "AI-353", "title": "Smart System for Detection and Recommendation of Crop Disease", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Agriculture and Rural Development Sector Problem Statements", "supervisor": "Dr. Isha Bhatia", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH7", "description": "This project aims to develop an automated system that detects crop diseases from leaf images and recommends suitable management strategies. Using image processing and machine learning techniques, the system identifies affected areas and suggests remedies to help farmers take timely action, reduce crop loss, and improve productivity through a simple and user-friendly interface."}, {"id": "AI-354", "title": "Smart System for Early Detection of Diseases from Reported Symptoms\"", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Healthcare and Wellness Problem Statements", "supervisor": "Dr. Isha Bhatia", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH7", "description": "This project is inspired by healthcare innovation challenges from Smart India Hackathon 2024. It aims to create an AI-based system that predicts possible diseases early by analyzing user-reported symptoms. The system helps users understand potential health risks and seek timely medical advice. It promotes digital health awareness, early diagnosis, and preventive care through smart technology and intelligent health monitoring."}, {"id": "AI-355", "title": "Smart Traffic Signal Prediction and Control System using Deep Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2024 -- Smart Mobility & Traffic Management Theme", "supervisor": "Dr. Ankita Wadhawan", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH16", "description": "This project develops a web-based intelligent traffic signal prediction system using deep learning models such as LSTM and CNN. The system analyzes real-time traffic data from cameras or sensors to predict signal changes and optimize control, reducing congestion, wait time, and fuel consumption in urban intersections."}, {"id": "AI-356", "title": "Smart Voice Assistant for Professionals", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "Self-proposed", "supervisor": "Shridhar Pandey", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH16", "description": "AI-powered Smart Voice Assistant for Professionals that records and transcribes meetings in real time, identifies speakers, extracts action items, dates, and assignees, and generates editable summaries. Built with React, Node.js, and Python, it reduces manual note-taking and helps professionals turn conversations into tasks, calendar events, and follow-ups more efficiently."}, {"id": "AI-357", "title": "Soil data analytics with AIOT based system for smart agro-pastoral advisory.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "SIH25030", "supervisor": "Aman Rao", "sitting_place": "34-202-CH30", "description": "It uses Internet of Things (IoT) sensors, drones, and satellites to gather real-time and historical data on soil moisture, nutrient levels, pH, temperature, and environmental factors like weather.AI-powered analysis: Machine learning algorithms and predictive analytics process and interpret this vast and complex dataset. This provides actionable insights that human analysis alone cannot achieve, such as forecasting soil degradation trends and predicting optimal crop yields. Precision and customization: The analysis helps create detailed soil health maps of a field, allowing for \"precision agriculture\" where resources are applied only where needed. For example, AI can recommend the precise amount of water or fertilizer for specific zones, reducing waste and environmental impact. Advisory services: The output is delivered to farmers and pastoralists via user-friendly interfaces, often mobile applications or chatbots. These services offer actionable recommendations for crop selection, irrigation scheduling, livestock grazing patterns, and pest control. Advisory services: The output is delivered to farmers and pastoralists via user-friendly interfaces, often mobile applications or chatbots. These services offer actionable recommendations for crop selection, irrigation scheduling, livestock grazing patterns, and pest control."}, {"id": "AI-358", "title": "SoilSense Horizon: AI-Powered Multimodal Advisory with Sustainability & Profitability Analytics for Farmers", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Anjum Rouf( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "The project develops an AI-based crop recommendation and advisory system that analyzes soil, weather, and market data to guide farmers in selecting suitable crops. It integrates weather-resilient dynamic suggestions that adjust to climatic changes and a community interaction module for farmer-to-farmer learning. The multilingual mobile app supports offline access, promoting sustainable and profitable agriculture."}, {"id": "AI-359", "title": "Super Market Analysis and Prediction", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "The topic comes from \\*\\*industry/retail company problem statements provided in SmartHackathon 2024 for real-world sales and demand prediction.", "supervisor": "Dr. Isha Bhatia", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH7", "description": "\\*\\*Super Market Analysis and Prediction\\*\\* (in SmartHackathon 2024) focuses on analyzing retail sales data to understand customer behavior and using machine learning to predict future product demand and sales."}, {"id": "AI-360", "title": "Sustainable Robotic System for Smart Waste Collection and Classification", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "SIH25014", "supervisor": "Aman Rao", "sitting_place": "34-202-CH30", "description": "The Smart Waste Segregation Robot is an innovative hardware-based project designed to automate the process of waste collection and segregation for cleaner and smarter cities. The robot, built on a mobile car-like structure, can be remotely controlled using a mobile application or wireless remote. It navigates through roads or designated areas to collect waste efficiently. Using a combination of sensors, cameras, and AI-based detection systems, the robot identifies and segregates waste into different categories such as dry, wet, biodegradable, and e-waste. This ensures proper disposal and enhances recycling efficiency. The system integrates IoT technology to enable real-time monitoring and control, allowing users to track collection data or robot status remotely. By reducing human intervention in waste handling, this project promotes hygiene, safety, and environmental sustainability. The Smart Waste Segregation Robot aims to support Swachh Bharat and Smart City initiatives by providing an intelligent, eco-friendly solution for waste management."}, {"id": "AI-361", "title": "SwachhAI: AI-Powered Garbage Monitoring and Collection System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Inspired by Swachh Bharat Mission & Smart India Hackathon problem statements", "supervisor": "Dr. Manik", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "SwachhAI is an AI-powered application designed to monitor waste bins, detect garbage overflow using computer vision, and optimize collection routes with machine learning. The system integrates IoT-enabled sensors and GPS tracking to ensure timely waste collection, reduce manual monitoring, and promote cleaner cities. It aligns with Smart City and Swachh Bharat initiatives."}, {"id": "AI-362", "title": "Syscon: AI driven performance advisory", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Derived from real-world computer optimization challenges and research inspiration", "supervisor": "Dr. Neeta Rana", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH5", "description": "SysCon is an intelligent PC management system that monitors system health using AI-based analytics. It detects performance bottlenecks, predicts issues, and provides user-friendly recommendations. With adaptive learning and feedback loops, it enhances optimization accuracy and suggests hardware upgrades tailored to user needs such as gaming or productivity."}, {"id": "AI-363", "title": "System and Method for Adaptive Multi-Layer Phishing Detection Using Dynamic Risk Recalibration and Behavioral Intelligence", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Nirmaljeet Kaur", "sitting_place": "55-302-CH7", "description": "The Adaptive Multi-Layered Phishing Detection System (AMPDS) aims at mitigating phishing through various digital platforms through behavioral intelligence and risk-based assessments. This system uses machine learning to conduct analysis on user behaviors and contents of URLs. AMPDS continuously updates itself to adapt to changes brought about by phishing attacks. The system comprises layers that monitor behavior, URL, email, content, and traffic. Integrating machine learning with continuous real-time risk scores, the system changes thresholds to adapt to new tactics being used by phishers. Our ultimate goal is to drastically reduce phishing incidents in all enterprises, websites, and other end users through highly accurate detections."}, {"id": "AI-364", "title": "System to predict Tsunami using Machine Learning models", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2025 (SIH25039)", "supervisor": "Dr. Avnish Thakur", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH10", "description": "This project focuses on developing a Machine Learning--based Tsunami Prediction System capable of forecasting the likelihood of tsunami occurrence using key seismic and oceanographic parameters. The study involves identifying the most relevant features influencing tsunami events, training suitable ML models such as Random Forest, SVM, and Neural Networks, and evaluating their performance through testing and validation. The goal is to design a data-driven, predictive model that can enhance the accuracy and reliability of tsunami forecasting systems."}, {"id": "AI-365", "title": "Tracking & Nowcasting of severe convective storms using Deep Learning/Machine Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "IIST", "supervisor": "Smriti Gautam", "sitting_place": "34-202-CH29", "description": "This research is working to make those warnings smarter and faster. By using advanced artificial intelligence and machine learning, the project aims to \"see\" dangerous storms using data from satellites, radar, and lightning detectors, and then predict as early as possible where and when severe weather will strike. The goal is to turn complex weather data into clear, reliable alerts that reach people in time to help them stay safe, save property, and reduce the impact of disasters. Ultimately, this technology could give communities more time to take shelter, reroute travel, and protect homes and livelihoods---transforming severe weather warnings into practical, lifesaving information that really makes a difference for everyone at risk."}, {"id": "AI-366", "title": "Transparent Recursive Vocabulary Attention Transformer", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "Self", "supervisor": "Amanpreet", "sitting_place": "36-307-CH11", "description": "This RVAT (Recursive Vocabulary Attention Transformer) project addresses the critical \"black box\" problem in AI by developing a transformer-based text classification architecture that makes explainability a core feature rather than an afterthought. The innovation lies in computing vocabulary-level attention at every layer of the transformer alongside standard multi-head self-attention between input tokens, my model computes parallel \"vocabulary attention\" that reveals which words from the entire vocabulary dictionary most influenced each internal representation, creating interpretable connections between predictions and known vocabulary. The \"recursive\" aspect refers to my two-level explanation mechanism: primary attention identifies top vocabulary words influencing decisions, semantic decomposition breaks these into related semantic groups, and my XAI modules analyze how these vocabulary attention patterns evolved across 26 training epochs to understand which training phases shaped the model's behavior. Implemented on the AG News dataset with 120,000 samples across 4 categories (World, Sports, Business, Science/Tech), my architecture consists of 4 transformer layers each with 5 parallel vocabulary attention modules tracking queries, keys, values, attention outputs, and feed-forward outputs, coupled with specialized XAI components (VocabAttentionPatternLearner and OutputExplanationGenerator) that classify attention patterns into meaningful types (Stable, Focused, Broad, Features, Semantic) and generate confidence-scored explanations. The result is a production-ready system where every text classification prediction comes with vocabulary-backed explanations, semantic breakdowns, attention visualizations, and confidence scores making it ideal for high-stakes applications like legal document analysis, medical text processing, financial compliance, or any regulatory domain where auditable, transparent, and human-verifiable AI decisions are essential."}, {"id": "AI-367", "title": "TRUTH IN PIXELS: ADVANCING DEEP LEARNING MODELS FOR RELIABLE DEEPFAKE DETECTION", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2024 as Problem Statement SIH1683 -- Development of AI/ML based solution for detection of face-swap based deep fake videos.", "supervisor": "Harjit Kaur", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH24", "description": "Deepfake videos are becoming more common and pose serious risks by spreading false information, threatening security, and damaging trust in media. Existing detection methods often fall short, especially when dealing with different types of fake content or when speed and accuracy are both required. This project aims to create a stronger and more practical solution that can reliably detect deepfakes and be useful in real-world situations."}, {"id": "AI-368", "title": "Unified Multi-Modal Authenticity Scoring System Detection of Phishing & Deepfake Attacks", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Nirmaljeet Kaur", "sitting_place": "55-302-CH7", "description": "A Unified Multi-Modal Authenticity Scoring System is an AI-driven approach that detects phishing and deepfake attacks by analyzing multiple data types such as text, images, audio, and video. It combines machine learning and deep learning models to identify suspicious patterns and assign a credibility score. By integrating results from different modalities, the system improves accuracy, enhances cybersecurity, and helps users identify manipulated or fraudulent content in real time."}, {"id": "AI-369", "title": "uniGPT: Retrieval-Augmented Generation Chatbot for University Knowledge", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "SIH 2024", "supervisor": "Akshat Srivastava( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "A university information assistant using advanced Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG), combining document embeddings and a chatbot interface. It answers queries on courses, events, and policies by retrieving up-to-date data from internal sources, providing fast, accurate support for students and staff."}, {"id": "AI-370", "title": "Unveiling AI in Glaucoma: A Roadmap from Neural Networks to Clinical Adoption", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Dr. Chetna Vaid Kwatra", "sitting_place": "34-207-CH15", "description": "The research will comprise of comprehensive survey of deep learning models used for glaucoma detection, encompassing CNN-based architectures, transfer learning methods, and multimodal data fusion techniques. It identifies key research gaps such as dataset limitations, lack of standardization, and the opaque nature of AI decision-making, thereby highlighting opportunities for future investigation. A model will be suggested and will be implemented on benchmark dataset. Eventually it will be evaluated on the basis of performance metrics."}, {"id": "AI-371", "title": "Vehicle Health Monitoring and Alerting with Multi-dimensional Data", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Indian Army", "supervisor": "Dr. Rahul Saha", "sitting_place": "38-207-C3", "description": "The project motivation/idea comes from the direct communication with the Indian Army through some collaborative source. In the second stage, the application will monitor army vehicles, while the first stage will only involve monitoring normal vehicles. It will then trigger various alerts based on threshold and priority models."}, {"id": "AI-372", "title": "Vision based road damage detection system using YOLO model", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Hardarshan Kaur", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH12", "description": "This project aims to develop an intelligent system for automatically detecting and classifying road surface damages such as potholes, cracks, and patches using computer vision and deep learning techniques. The system employs the YOLO (You Only Look Once) object detection model, which enables real-time identification of road defects from captured images or video streams. By training the YOLO model on a labeled dataset of road surface images, the system can accurately locate and categorize different types of road damages. The project enhances efficiency and safety by reducing the need for manual road inspections and enabling authorities to prioritize maintenance work."}, {"id": "AI-373", "title": "Vision-Based Pothole Detection with Adaptive Cruise Control for Intelligent Vehicles", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Dr. Manik", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This project proposes a real-time intelligent vehicle assistance system that detects potholes using YOLOv8-based computer vision techniques and automatically adjusts vehicle speed through adaptive cruise control. The system uses a front-facing camera to capture road images, identifies potholes under various lighting and weather conditions, estimates pothole severity and distance, and performs smooth speed adaptation to improve passenger safety and driving comfort. The project combines deep learning, object detection, and intelligent transportation concepts for safer and smarter driving systems."}, {"id": "AI-374", "title": "Vitanex: Intelligent Emergency Health Alert System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "self", "supervisor": "Gagandeep Kaur", "sitting_place": "34-204-CH8", "description": "n critical medical emergencies, timely communication and response are vital for saving lives.Vitanex is an intelligent emergency alert system designed to automatically detect accidents or sudden health crises and instantly notify nearby medical services, emergency contacts, and rescue authorities. The system integrates sensors (such as accelerometers, GPS, and biometric monitors) to identify abnormal events like collisions or drastic health parameter changes. Once triggered, it transmits the user's location, health data, and incident details through cloud-based communication channels. Machine learning algorithms enhance detection accuracy by analyzing real-time physiological and motion patterns. This project aims to reduce response time, ensure immediate medical intervention, and create a reliable safety network for individuals in both urban and remote environments. is an intelligent emergency alert system designed to automatically detect accidents or sudden health crises and instantly notify nearby medical services, emergency contacts, and rescue authorities. The system integrates sensors (such as accelerometers, GPS, and biometric monitors) to identify abnormal events like collisions or drastic health parameter changes. Once triggered, it transmits the user's location, health data, and incident details through cloud-based communication channels. Machine learning algorithms enhance detection accuracy by analyzing real-time physiological and motion patterns. This project aims to reduce response time, ensure immediate medical intervention, and create a reliable safety network for individuals in both urban and remote environments."}, {"id": "AI-375", "title": "Voice-Based Emotional Insights for Telehealth Mental Wellness Monitoring", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Voice-Based Emotional Insights for Telehealth Mental Wellness Monitoring", "supervisor": "Dr. Isha Bhatia", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH7", "description": "This project develops an AI-based telehealth system that analyzes voice to detect emotions such as stress, anxiety, or sadness. By extracting vocal features like pitch and tone, it provides real-time emotional insights to support mental wellness monitoring. The system helps doctors and users track emotional changes remotely, enabling early detection of mental health issues and promoting well-being through smart, non-invasive technology."}, {"id": "AI-376", "title": "Women Safety Analytics -- Protecting Women from Safety Threats", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH 2025", "supervisor": "Minu Choudhary", "sitting_place": "27-209-CH9", "description": "Women Safety Analytics is a system designed to protect women from potential safety threats by analyzing data from crime reports, social media, and IoT devices. Using AI and predictive analytics, it identifies high-risk areas, detects suspicious activities, and provides real-time alerts, enhancing personal safety and enabling timely preventive actions.\""}, {"id": "AI-377", "title": "XAI-based Breed Recognition for Indian Cattle", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH 2025 (https://www.sih.gov.in/sih2025PS) - Topic 4 (lmage based breed recognition for cattle and buffaloes of India)", "supervisor": "Blossom", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH15", "description": "This proposed work aims to develop an explainable deep-learning system for automatic recognition of Indian cattle breeds. The approach will employ advanced feature-learning methods to achieve robust performance on real-world images, while XAI techniques will provide visual explanations to ensure transparency and user trust. A user-friendly interface will allow image upload, breed prediction, and explanation viewing, with potential deployment on edge devices for rural use."}, {"id": "AI-378", "title": "X-FL: An Explainable Multi-Modal Federated Framework for Privacy-Preserving Breast Cancer Detection", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH 2025 Healthcare", "supervisor": "Sheetal Chauhan", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH22", "description": "This project proposes the development of a privacy-preserving AI-driven breast cancer detection system using Federated Learning (FL) integrated with multi-modal deep learning architectures. Traditional centralized AI models require sharing sensitive patient data across institutions, raising serious privacy and regulatory concerns. Federated Learning addresses this limitation by enabling collaborative model training across multiple hospitals without transferring raw data. The proposed system, DeepFusion-FL, will utilize Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Vision Transformers (ViTs) to analyze multi-modal medical imaging data, including mammography, ultrasound, and MRI, Clinical data. A hybrid architecture combining CNN-based local feature extraction with transformer-based global context learning will be developed to enhance tumor detection and classification performance. To simulate real-world healthcare scenarios, the dataset will be distributed across multiple federated clients (representing hospitals), where each client trains the model locally and shares only model updates with a central server using aggregation techniques such as Federated Averaging (FedAvg). To further enhance privacy, Differential Privacy (DP) mechanisms may be incorporated to prevent data leakage from model updates. The system will also integrate multi-modal data fusion techniques to combine imaging features with clinical data, improving predictive accuracy and personalized risk assessment. Additionally, Explainable AI (XAI) techniques such as SHAP or Grad-CAM will be applied to improve interpretability and clinical trust. The performance of the proposed model will be evaluated using metrics such as accuracy, sensitivity, specificity, AUC, and communication efficiency. The ultimate goal is to develop a scalable, secure, and intelligent AI-assisted decision support system that enables early breast cancer detection while preserving patient privacy and supporting real-world deployment in distributed healthcare environments."}, {"id": "AI-379", "title": "AI-Powered Online Learning Platform", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25048 (Smart Education) Gamified Learning Platform for rural education", "supervisor": "Dr. Robin Prakash Mathur", "sitting_place": "28-203-C1", "description": "The project aims to develop an intelligent online learning platform integrating video-based education, AI-generated quizzes/flashcards, real-time WebRTC study rooms, and gamified learning tools. It enhances digital education through personalized learning, automated content generation, interactive sessions, and performance analytics for students, teachers, and administrators."}, {"id": "AI-380", "title": "Early Diagnosis of Alzheimer's Disease using Deep Learning Technique in MRI Images", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "NA", "supervisor": "Dr. Jaspreet Kaur", "sitting_place": "27-209-CH15", "description": "This project focuses on Alzheimer's Disease diagnosis using Machine Learning and Deep Learning techniques such as CNN, GNN, and Vision Transformers. It involves analysis of medical imaging data like MRI, EEG, and PET, along with preprocessing methods and model comparison. The goal is to identify effective approaches for early and accurate detection of Alzheimer's Disease."}, {"id": "AI-381", "title": "Image based Animal Type Classification for cattle and buffaloes", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH25005: Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr Dhanpratap Singh", "sitting_place": "26-203-C2", "description": "This work emphasizes the creation of an intelligent system to predict cattle breeding fitness based on image analysis driven by deep learning. The aim is to help farmers and veterinarians identify the healthiest and best-suited cattle for breeding. Past research has utilized traditional image processing and machine learning techniques to evaluate livestock with low accuracy and require manual intervention. In this research, a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) is introduced that learns deep morphological features from cattle images to automatically predict total fitness and breeding ability. The proposed model attained improved accuracy and minimized false prediction compared to previous approaches. The outcome proves that our solution offers a trustworthy and scalable solution for contemporary smart farming and livestock husbandry. Future research will pay attention to the integration of real-time health monitoring sensors and multi-modal data (e.g., weight, milk production) for better prediction performance."}, {"id": "AI-382", "title": "A Vision-Language Model-based Approach for Multilingual Scene Text Extraction, Translation, and Semantic Understanding", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Research", "supervisor": "Ramanjeet Kaur Dhaliwal", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH17", "description": "At its core, the integration of Image Processing and Natural Language Processing (NLP) forms the foundation of multimodal AI systems, which aim to understand, reason, and generate insights from both visual and textual data in a unified manner. The main idea is to bridge the semantic gap between pixels (images) and language (text) so that machines can interpret the world more like humans do. This is achieved by combining computer vision models (such as CNNs or Vision Transformers) with language models (such as transformers and LLMs) into a single pipeline that can process, align, and generate multimodal information. The system typically works in stages. First, the image processing module extracts meaningful visual features from raw images or video frames. This may include object detection, scene understanding, facial analysis, or text extraction using OCR. These features are converted into dense vector representations (embeddings) that capture spatial and semantic information. Simultaneously, the NLP module processes any associated text---such as captions, questions, or documents---by converting it into contextual embeddings using transformer-based architectures."}, {"id": "AI-383", "title": "Adaptive Multi-Layer Image Encryption Using Dynamic Arnold Cat Map and Content-Driven Chaotic Diffusion", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "The research topic was identified through a systematic gap analysis in existing literature on chaos-based image encryption. The following key sources and motivations led to this topic: 3.1 Literature Gap Identified • Existing Arnold Cat Map-based schemes suffer from periodicity problems --- the map returns to its original state after a certain number of iterations, weakening security. • Most current algorithms use fixed (static) parameters, making them less unpredictable and more vulnerable to attacks. • Limited key space in standalone Arnold Cat Map implementations reduces resistance to brute-force attacks. • Standard AES and DES text-based encryption algorithms are inefficient for image data due to high pixel correlation and large data volume. 3.2 Key Reference Papers • Ibrahim & Venkatesan (2025) --- Image encryption using novel chaotic map and cellular automata dynamics • Guveneglu (2024) --- Multi-layered chaotic map encryption and security analysis • Alexan et al. (2023) --- AntEater: Ar", "supervisor": "Rahul Panola", "sitting_place": "27-205-CH16", "description": "The rapid growth of digital communication and multimedia applications has made it critically important to ensure the secure transmission of visual information across public and private networks. Images are used in numerous sensitive domains including medical imaging, military surveillance, remote sensing, and social media. However, the open nature of communication channels exposes these digital images to unauthorized access, data tampering, and sophisticated cyber-attacks. Traditional text-based encryption algorithms such as AES (Advanced Encryption Standard) and DES (Data Encryption Standard) are not well-suited for image encryption due to the large volume of data involved, the inherently high pixel correlation in images, and the significant data redundancy that exists in visual content. To address these challenges, researchers have explored chaos-based encryption methods, which leverage the properties of chaotic systems --- sensitivity to initial conditions, randomness, unpredictability, and ergodicity --- that closely mirror the properties required by strong cryptographic systems. The Arnold Cat Map (ACM) is one of the most widely studied chaotic transformations in image encryption. It is a two-dimensional discrete chaotic mapping that rearranges the spatial positions of pixels in an image, producing a highly scrambled result while"}, {"id": "AI-384", "title": "Advanced Computer Vision and Deep Learning Architectures for Real-Time Human Fall Detection: A Comprehensive Synthesis of Kinematic Modeling, Pose Estimation, and Automated Alert Systems", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "The project is inspired by Smart India Hackathon problem statements in the Healthcare and AI/ML domain, specifically related to: \"AI-based fall detection and prevention systems for elderly people.\" The proposed solution extends this concept using computer vision instead of wearable sensors.", "supervisor": "Rahul Panola", "sitting_place": "27-205-CH16", "description": "Accidental falls constitute a critical public health crisis, particularly among the global elderly demographic, leading to severe morbidity, loss of autonomy, and significant healthcare expenditures. Prompt intervention is crucial to mitigate the physiological and psychological impacts of a \"long lie.\" While traditional fall detection systems have relied heavily on wearable inertial sensors, recent advancements in artificial intelligence, deep learning, and computer vision have catalyzed a paradigm shift toward non-obtrusive, ambient monitoring. This comprehensive report analyzes the state-of-the-art in vision-based fall detection, evaluating the transition from early Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) to modern, real-time pose estimation frameworks such as YOLOv8 and MediaPipe. The analysis delves into skeletal feature extraction, kinematic mathematics, and the implementation of Finite State Machines (FSM) to distinguish actual falls from activities of daily living (ADL). Furthermore, the report synthesizes performance metrics across benchmark datasets, including UP-FALL and URFD, and explores the edge-computing architectures that enable privacy-preserving, real-time automated alerts."}, {"id": "AI-385", "title": "Age-Stratified, Cross-Dataset Evaluation for Early Cardiovascular Disease Risk Analysis", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Munish Katoch", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH7", "description": "Most existing studies rely on single, homogeneous datasets and treat all age groups uniformly, leading to dataset bias and age-related bias, resulting in limited generalization. This work addresses this gap by performing age-stratified and cross-dataset evaluation to analyze performance variation, feature influence and reliability in early CVD risk assessment and proposes improvements to enhance model generalization across diverse populations using data-driven approaches."}, {"id": "AI-386", "title": "AgriPredict: Leveraging Machine Learning for Dynamic and Location-Specific Crop Recommendation to Optimize Yield and Profitability", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Self-Ideated Academic Project", "supervisor": "Vaibhav Nanda", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH5", "description": "AgriPredict is a machine learning-based crop recommendation system designed to help farmers select the most suitable crops based on soil and weather conditions. The system analyzes soil parameters such as Nitrogen, Phosphorus, Potassium (NPK), and pH along with real-time weather data including temperature, humidity, and rainfall. It uses hybrid machine learning models including Random Forest, XGBoost, and Neural Networks to provide accurate crop recommendations. The system includes a user-friendly web interface and backend API, helping farmers improve crop yield, profitability, and promote sustainable farming practices through data-driven decisions."}, {"id": "AI-387", "title": "AI Driven Pest Detection", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Internal Research / Patent Invention --- Lovely Professional University", "supervisor": "Arun Prakash K", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH9", "description": "An AI-based system using CNN and deep learning for real-time identification of wildlife/pest species from camera trap and drone images. Achieves 90%+ accuracy using TensorFlow/PyTorch with preprocessing, transfer learning, and continuous learning capabilities. Supports biodiversity conservation, scalable field deployment, and reduces dependency on human expertise."}, {"id": "AI-388", "title": "AI Fitness Trainer - Form Correctness Detection", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH : 2025", "supervisor": "Jobanpreet Singh", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH12", "description": "AI fitness trainers use computer vision and deep learning to detect exercise form correctness in real-time, functioning as virtual personal trainers. These systems analyze body posture, count repetitions, and provide immediate feedback to help users avoid injuries and improve workout effectiveness."}, {"id": "AI-389", "title": "AI-Based Farmer Query Support and Advisory System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25076", "supervisor": "Tanwarjot Singh", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH15", "description": "The AI-Based Farmer Query Support and Advisory System aims to assist farmers by providing real-time, intelligent agricultural advice using Artificial Intelligence. The system allows farmers to ask queries related to crop selection, pest management, soil health, weather conditions, fertilizer use, and market prices, and receive accurate, data-driven responses. Using Natural Language Processing (NLP), the system can understand farmers questions in natural language (possibly regional languages) and provide relevant solutions. It can also integrate machine learning models to predict crop diseases, yield estimation, or weather risks. A chatbot interface or web app can be developed for easy farmer interaction. The system may also include a recommendation module that offers personalized suggestions based on soil type, region, and climate data. Overall, the project will empower farmers with AI-driven decision support, improving productivity, reducing risks, and promoting sustainable agricultural practices."}, {"id": "AI-390", "title": "AI-Based Network Intrusion Detection System Using Deep Learning for Real-Time Cyber Threat Detection", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Self-Proposed based on research in Cybersecurity, Network Intrusion Detection, and Machine Learning Literature", "supervisor": "Atul Kumar", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH19", "description": "This project develops an AI-based Network Intrusion Detection System that identifies cyber threats using machine learning and deep learning models. Network traffic data is analyzed to detect malicious activities such as DoS attacks, unauthorized access, and abnormal patterns. The system compares multiple models and provides real-time alerts through a monitoring dashboard to improve cybersecurity."}, {"id": "AI-391", "title": "AI-Based Waste Image Segregation System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH 2025", "supervisor": "Sheveta", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH6", "description": "Design a computer-vision model (CNN) trained on waste images to identify categories (plastic, glass, paper, organic). could be Integrate with a conveyor or robotic arm to physically sort waste."}, {"id": "AI-392", "title": "AI-Driven Learning Recommendation System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": ".", "supervisor": "Bhavna", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH14", "description": "The project aims to develop an AI-based personalized learning recommendation system that analyzes learners' profiles, interests, and performance data to suggest relevant courses, materials, and skill paths. Using Machine Learning, NLP, and Data Analytics, it enhances engagement and learning outcomes by providing adaptive and data-driven content recommendations."}, {"id": "AI-393", "title": "AI-Driven Public Health Chatbot for Disease Awareness", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25049", "supervisor": "Tanwarjot Singh", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH15", "description": "This project aims to develop a multilingual AI-powered chatbot that promotes disease awareness and public health education. Using Natural Language Processing (NLP) and machine learning, the chatbot interacts with users in their native language to provide information on preventive healthcare, disease symptoms, vaccination schedules, and verified medical guidance to improve health literacy in rural and semi-urban communities"}, {"id": "AI-394", "title": "AI-HealthConnect --- Multilingual Public Health Chatbot", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "25049", "supervisor": "Bhavna", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH14", "description": "AI-HealthConnect is a multilingual chatbot (Hindi, Odia, English + local dialect fallback) accessible via WhatsApp and SMS to educate rural & semi-urban users on preventive healthcare, symptoms, vaccination schedules and outbreak alerts. It integrates with government health databases for real-time updates, uses lightweight NLP for offline-capable responses, and supports voice-to-text for low-literacy users."}, {"id": "AI-395", "title": "AI-Powered Emotion Detection and Mental Wellness Tracker", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH 2025", "supervisor": "Sheveta", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH6", "description": "Develop an AI system that analyzes facial expressions, voice tone, and text sentiment to assess emotional well-being. Offer personalized recommendations or counselor alerts."}, {"id": "AI-396", "title": "AI-Powered Fake News Detection and Automated Verification Platform using NLP and Machine Learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Self-Initiated / Inspired by Social Media Misinformation Challenges", "supervisor": "Vaibhav Nanda", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH5", "description": "This project aims to develop an AI-powered platform that detects and verifies fake news using Natural Language Processing and Machine Learning techniques. The system analyzes textual content, identifies misinformation patterns, cross-verifies information with trusted sources, and provides a credibility score. The platform helps users identify misleading news and promotes responsible information consumption."}, {"id": "AI-397", "title": "AI-Powered Personalized Mental Health Support for Students", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "SIH 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Uzma Saghir", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH20", "description": "This project is an AI-driven web platform designed to provide personalized mental health support to university students, addressing the growing challenge of academic stress, anxiety, and emotional burnout in higher education. Unlike conventional text-based chatbots, this system uniquely integrates three complementary modalities --- voice, facial expression, and natural language processing (NLP) --- to deliver a holistic and accurate understanding of a student's emotional state."}, {"id": "AI-398", "title": "AI-Powered Student Performance Prediction & Dashboard", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:2023", "supervisor": "Sheveta", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH6", "description": "Educational institutions require data-driven insights to improve student outcomes. This project focuses on building an AI system that predicts student performance using historical academic data and visualizes insights through an interactive dashboard."}, {"id": "AI-399", "title": "An Efficient Deep Learning-Based Approach for Multiclass Classification and Lesion Segmentation of Diabetic Retinopathy", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Extensive Literature review conducted through high quality publications from reputed SCI journals and problem statement is derived.", "supervisor": "Salil Batra", "sitting_place": "34-207-CH13", "description": "Diabetic retinopathy (DR) is one of the most prevalent complications of type 1 and type 2 diabetes that damages the retinal blood vessels. It progresses through multiple stages ranging from mild non-proliferative DR to proliferative DR. It is a leading preventable cause of blindness in diabetic patients; early detection is crucial, yet manual screening remains costly, time-consuming, subjective, and heavily reliant on the availability of trained ophthalmologists. This challenge is especially severe in sub-Saharan Africa and rural regions worldwide. The emerging advancements in AI-driven screening have demonstrated promising solutions to bridge this medical gap. Advanced deep learning technologies have introduced sophisticated architectures that enable enhanced DR classification and fundus retinal image segmentation for accurate diagnosis. This study aims to underscore the need for an automated approach that unifies the capture of both local and global patterns in medical images for early detection of DR, as well as the use of lesion-level feature extraction for enhanced accuracy and interpretability. The end goal is not to replace clinicians, but to offer an automated, robust and reliable DR classification and segmentation model."}, {"id": "AI-400", "title": "An Integrated Data-Driven Approach for Precision Agriculture Monitoring and Optimization", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "research", "supervisor": "Sheveta", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH6", "description": "Precision agriculture has emerged as a data-driven approach to enhance agricultural productivity and sustainability by enabling efficient resource utilization and informed decision-making. The increasing availability of heterogeneous agricultural data, including environmental, soil, and crop-related parameters, has created opportunities for advanced monitoring and analysis. However, the lack of integrated systems capable of effectively processing and interpreting such data limits the potential benefits of these technologies. In this context, an integrated data-driven approach leveraging emerging technologies can facilitate continuous monitoring, accurate analysis, and optimization of agricultural practices. This study focuses on developing a comprehensive system that utilizes data analytics and intelligent techniques to improve agricultural monitoring and optimize crop productivity."}, {"id": "AI-401", "title": "An Intelligent Learning Framework for Predicting Prices of Agri-Horticultural Commodities", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon SIH1647", "supervisor": "Dr. Usha Mittal", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This study focuses on the development of Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) models to accurately predict the prices of agri-horticultural commodities. The unpredictable nature of agricultural markets, influenced by seasonal variations, weather conditions, supply--demand dynamics, and market policies, makes price forecasting a complex challenge. To address this, various supervised and ensemble learning techniques such as Random Forest, Support Vector Regression, Gradient Boosting, and Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks are explored. The models are trained on historical market data, including production, weather, and demand variables, to identify hidden patterns and trends. The proposed system aims to assist farmers, traders, and policymakers in making informed decisions, reducing market risks, and ensuring better price stability. Comparative analysis of model performance is conducted using standard evaluation metrics such as RMSE, MAE, and R² to identify the most effective approach for real-world deployment."}, {"id": "AI-402", "title": "An IOT POWERED SMART WASTE MANAGEMENT AND RECYCLING SYSTEM", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Sheveta", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH6", "description": "This project proposes an IoT-based Smart Waste Management and Recycling System designed to optimize waste collection, segregation, and recycling. The system employs smart sensors to monitor bin fill levels, transmits data via IoT modules to a centralized dashboard, and uses data analytics for efficient route planning and recycling decisions. The primary objectives are to reduce collection costs, prevent overflow, and promote sustainability through technology-enabled recycling."}, {"id": "AI-403", "title": "An IoT-Powered Smart Waste Management and Recycling System", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH 2024", "supervisor": "Sheveta", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH6", "description": "This project proposes an IoT-based Smart Waste Management and Recycling System designed to optimize waste collection, segregation, and recycling. The system employs smart sensors to monitor bin fill levels, transmits data via IoT modules to a centralized dashboard, and uses data analytics for efficient route planning and recycling decisions. The primary objectives are to reduce collection costs, prevent overflow, and promote sustainability through technology-enabled recycling."}, {"id": "AI-404", "title": "Analysis, Modeling, and Development of Speech Emotion Recognition Systems Using Deep Learning Approaches", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "General real-world problem", "supervisor": "Rakesh Gagneja", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH23", "description": "This dissertation focuses on the analysis, modeling, and development of Speech Emotion Recognition (SER) systems using deep learning approaches. The study will begin with analyzing existing methods and understanding how emotions can be extracted from speech signals using features like pitch, tone, and frequency. In the modeling phase, deep learning techniques such as Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN), Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN), and Transformer-based models will be explored to design an effective emotion recognition system. Finally, the development phase will involve implementing and testing the proposed model on available speech datasets to evaluate its performance. The goal of this work is to improve the accuracy and efficiency of emotion detection systems and explore their real-world applications in areas like virtual assistants, healthcare, and customer service."}, {"id": "AI-405", "title": "Assistive Navigation System for Visually Challenged People", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2020 (SIH?2020)", "supervisor": "Dr. V Devendran", "sitting_place": "26-203-C3", "description": "Create a sensor-based navigation system for visually impaired users that detects obstacles and maps the environment in real-time. Haptic or vibration feedback guides safe movement indoors and outdoors, improving mobility, independence, and accessibility without using voice instructions."}, {"id": "AI-406", "title": "Automated Bus Scheduling and Route Management System for Delhi Transport Corporation", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Research", "source": "Smart India Hackathon SIH1612", "supervisor": "Dr. Usha Mittal", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "The project aims to develop an Automated Bus Scheduling and Route Management System for the Delhi Transport Corporation (DTC) to enhance operational efficiency, reduce delays, and optimize resource utilization. The system leverages data analytics and intelligent algorithms to automate bus scheduling, route allocation, and timetable generation based on real-time passenger demand, traffic conditions, and bus availability. By integrating GPS tracking and centralized control, it ensures effective monitoring of bus movement, punctuality, and route adherence. The proposed system also facilitates dynamic rescheduling during emergencies or traffic congestion and provides a digital interface for drivers, depot managers, and passengers. It minimizes manual intervention, reduces fuel consumption, and improves service reliability. Overall, this smart transportation management system supports data-driven decision-making, leading to improved commuter satisfaction and more sustainable public transport operations across Delhi."}, {"id": "AI-407", "title": "Biological--Environmental--Economic Simulation Framework for Profitability Prediction of High-Value Crops in Indoor Aeroponic Farming Systems", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Academic Research Project (Self-Initiated)", "supervisor": "Vaibhav Nanda", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH5", "description": "The project aims to develop an integrated simulation framework for predicting biological growth performance and economic feasibility of cultivating high-value crops using indoor aeroponic farming systems. The system models plant physiological responses under controlled artificial environmental conditions and estimates biomass, yield, operational costs, and profitability metrics such as ROI and payback period for profitability-driven decision making."}, {"id": "AI-408", "title": "Blockchain technology for carbon credit management and trading in sustainable agriculture.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "research", "supervisor": "Sheveta", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH6", "description": "Sustainable agriculture is increasingly recognized as a key approach to addressing climate change through reduced emissions and enhanced carbon sequestration. Carbon credit systems provide incentives to farmers for adopting eco-friendly practices; however, traditional systems often face issues such as lack of transparency, inefficiency, and vulnerability to data manipulation. Blockchain technology, with its decentralized, immutable, and transparent nature, offers a promising solution to these challenges by enabling secure tracking, verification, and trading of carbon credits. This study focuses on exploring the application of blockchain technology to develop a reliable and efficient carbon credit management and trading system for sustainable agriculture."}, {"id": "AI-409", "title": "Brain tumor segmentation from MRI images", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH2023-HEA1281", "supervisor": "Dr. Usha Mittal", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "Brain Tumor Segmentation from MRI Images involves automatically identifying and outlining tumor regions in brain MRI scans using deep learning techniques. This helps doctors in accurate diagnosis, treatment planning, and monitoring of brain tumors. The system processes multiple MRI modalities (T1, T1c, T2, FLAIR) and segments tumor areas like the enhancing tumor, tumor core, and whole tumor. A deep learning model such as U-Net or its variants will be trained on labeled datasets like BraTS. The output will be a segmentation mask overlaid on the MRI image for easy interpretation. This AI-assisted tool aims to reduce manual effort and improve consistency in clinical workflows."}, {"id": "AI-410", "title": "Crop Recommendation System: A Simple Guide for Farmers", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25030", "supervisor": "Tanwarjot Singh", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH15", "description": "This AI tool helps farmers choose optimal crops by analyzing soil nutrients (nitrogen, phosphorus, potassium, pH) and local weather patterns. Our easy-to-use, offline capable app provides personalized crop suggestions, boosting yields and profits while saving water and fertilizer. It empowers informed planting for sustainable success."}, {"id": "AI-411", "title": "Deep Learning For Medical Imaging Advances, Benchmarks and Clinical Challenges", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH 2025", "supervisor": "Jobanpreet Singh", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH12", "description": "The approach that is most helpful to medical professionals in the process of diagnosing disorders in patients is medical imaging diagnosis, which employs a variety of imaging test modalities. In fact, the purpose of deep learning is to imitate human cognitive processes. A paradigm change is being brought about in the area of medical imaging as a result of the growing availability of data pertaining to medical imaging and the development of methodologies that revolve on deep learning."}, {"id": "AI-412", "title": "Deep Learning Models for Tomato Leaf Disease Detection Using Computer Vision", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Zeenat Zahra", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH7", "description": "This research is to develop an automated system for detecting tomato leaf diseases using deep learning and computer vision techniques. We aims to analyze and compare different deep learning architectures, including Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN), ResNet50, and MobileNet, to determine the most effective model for accurate disease classification. The research will focus on identifying common tomato leaf diseases from image inputs and evaluating the performance of different models based on metrics such as accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score. The final outcome of the research will be a working system where a tomato leaf image can be given as input, and the trained deep learning model will automatically detect and classify the disease"}, {"id": "AI-413", "title": "Deep-Learning-Based System for Automated Image Classification of Cattle and Buffaloes", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH 2025", "supervisor": "Jobanpreet Singh", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH12", "description": "deep-learning-based pipeline to automatically classify images of bovines into cattle and buffaloes. The system uses transfer learning on modern convolutional neural networks (e.g., EfficientNet / ResNet) combined with targeted data augmentation, class-imbalance handling, and explainability via Grad-CAM. We describe dataset collection and annotation best practices, training and evaluation procedures, and deployment options (ONNX / TorchScript / mobile). The method demonstrates high accuracy and interpretability while being suitable for farm-level edge deployment."}, {"id": "AI-414", "title": "DGX-Former: A Domain-Generalized Hybrid CNN--Transformer Framework for Vulnerable Object Detection in Baggage X-ray Images", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "After researching similar review papers and Public research datasets such as PIDray, SIXray, and HiXray", "supervisor": "Dr. Robin Kumar", "sitting_place": "27-209-CH8", "description": "This project proposes a hybrid CNN--Transformer model for detecting vulnerable objects in baggage X-ray images. The approach focuses on improving detection accuracy under occlusion, object overlap, and domain variations. It incorporates X-ray-specific augmentation and domain generalization techniques to enhance robustness, enabling reliable and efficient automated security screening."}, {"id": "AI-415", "title": "Domain Adaptation of Vision-Language Models for Medical Image Captioning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Self-proposed based on recent multimodal AI research", "supervisor": "Saurabh Pandey( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This project focuses on adapting pretrained vision-language models to generate accurate and clinically meaningful captions for medical images such as X-rays. It includes fine-tuning on specialized medical datasets, enhancing domain-specific understanding, and evaluating performance against general models using standard metrics. The work also involves comparative analysis, error evaluation, and development of a prototype system to demonstrate practical applicability in real-world scenarios."}, {"id": "AI-416", "title": "Early Detection of Parkinson's Disease Using Deep Learning on Gait Analysis Data: A Lightweight Model Approach", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Gaurav Sharma", "sitting_place": "27-203-CH8", "description": "Parkinson's Disease (PD) is a progressive neurodegenerative disorder affecting millions worldwide. One of the most critical challenges in PD management is the lack of early, objective, and accessible diagnostic tools. Currently, diagnosis relies heavily on clinical observation of motor symptoms, which often appear only after significant neuronal damage has already occurred.his research aims to develop a lightweight deep learning model that analyzes gait patterns to detect early-stage Parkinson's Disease. The model will be trained and evaluated on the publicly available PhysioNet Gait in Neurodegenerative Disease Database. The novelty lies in designing a computationally efficient architecture (such as a pruned LSTM or MobileNet-based model) that maintains high diagnostic accuracy while being suitable for practical deployment."}, {"id": "AI-417", "title": "Early plant disease detection using machine learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SDG", "supervisor": "Arvind Kumar Bhatia", "sitting_place": "27-204-CH6", "description": "Early plant disease detection using machine learning is an advanced approach that helps farmers identify crop diseases at an early stage. It uses image processing and algorithms to analyze leaf patterns, color changes, and texture variations. Machine learning models such as Support Vector Machines (SVM), Decision Trees, and Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) are commonly used for this purpose. These models are trained on large datasets of healthy and diseased plant images. Once trained, the system can accurately classify and predict diseases in real time. Early detection helps reduce crop loss and improves agricultural productivity. It also minimizes the excessive use of pesticides by enabling targeted treatment. The system can be integrated with mobile apps or drones for field monitoring. This technology is especially useful in precision agriculture and smart farming practices. Overall, machine learning-based plant disease detection contributes to sustainable and efficient farming."}, {"id": "AI-418", "title": "Explainable Deep Learning Framework for Brain Disease Detection using MRI", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "This topic is derived from a comprehensive literature review of recent research in medical imaging, deep learning, and Explainable AI. It addresses the need for accurate yet interpretable AI models in brain disease diagnosis.", "supervisor": "Chetan Singh", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH32", "description": "Accurate brain disease detection using MRI is vital but hindered by the black-box nature of AI. This project utilizes customized Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) and Transfer Learning architectures to classify brain tumors. By integrating XAI techniques like Grad-CAM and SHAP, the model highlights critical regions driving predictions. The overarching goal is to achieve an optimal synergy between high diagnostic accuracy and clinical interpretability, fostering physician trust."}, {"id": "AI-419", "title": "Face Detection using Deep learning", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "1\\. Research papers on FaceNet, ArcFace 2. AI/ML coursework and Real-world applications (Face ID, CCTV, attendance systems)", "supervisor": "Rahul Panola", "sitting_place": "27-205-CH16", "description": "Face recognition has become a key technology in the modern digital era, driven by rapid advancements in artificial intelligence and deep learning. It is widely used in applications such as smartphone unlocking, security surveillance, attendance systems, and identity verification. This project focuses on designing and developing a face recognition system using deep learning techniques, aiming to achieve higher accuracy and robustness compared to traditional methods. Earlier face recognition techniques relied on manual feature extraction and conventional algorithms, which often struggled under challenging conditions such as poor lighting, facial expressions, occlusions (e.g., masks or glasses), and varying angles. These limitations reduced their effectiveness in real-world scenarios. To overcome these challenges, this project leverages deep learning, which enables systems to automatically learn important features directly from large datasets without human intervention. The core of this system is based on Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), a class of deep learning models particularly well-suited for image processing tasks. CNNs are capable of capturing spatial hierarchies and patterns in images, making them highly effective for detecting and recognizing human faces. In this project, the CNN model is trained using a dataset containing multiple facial images of different individuals. The training process involves feeding labeled images into the network so that it can learn distinguishing facial features. Once trained, the model is tested on new, unseen images to evaluate its performance. The system first detects the presence of a face in an image and then identifies the person by comparing extracted features with those stored in the trained model. Experimental results demonstrate that the deep learning-based approach achieves high accuracy and performs reliably even under varying environmental conditions. This face recognition system has practical applications in areas such as automated attendance systems, security authentication, surveillance, and access control. It can also be integrated into real-time systems for enhanced usability and efficiency. In conclusion, this project highlights the effectiveness of deep learning, particularly CNNs, in improving the performance of face recognition systems. While the results are promising, it is important to address ethical considerations such as data privacy and security. Ensuring responsible use of facial data is essential for building trust and promoting the safe adoption of this technology in everyday life."}, {"id": "AI-420", "title": "Flood prone zone detection along the various riverfront using Deep Learning method.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH1587: Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Dr Dhanpratap Singh", "sitting_place": "26-203-C2", "description": "Floods are among the most frequent and destructive natural disasters, leading to extensive economic losses and human displacement worldwide. Early flood detection and monitoring are essential for mitigating their impact and improving disaster management strategies. This paper presents a deep learning--based flood detection model that classifies riverbed conditions into flooded and non-flooded categories using image data. Unlike most existing studies that rely on satellite or publicly available datasets, the dataset used in this work was self-collected through field photography of local riverbeds under varying hydrological and environmental conditions. The collected images were preprocessed and augmented to enhance model robustness. A Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) structure was utilized to execute binary classification and identify flood occurrence through visual indicators. Experimental findings show that the suggested model attains excellent classification accuracy and can successfully detect flood incid"}, {"id": "AI-421", "title": "FreshMandi -- A City-Based Farmer--Consumer Marketplace", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Technology Upgradation", "source": "SIH1596", "supervisor": "Bhavna", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH14", "description": "FreshMandi is a city-level platform connecting local farmers and consumers. Farmers can upload details and photos of their produce, manage one active mandi location at a time, and make their stock visible to nearby buyers. Consumers can browse city-wise listings and place simulated orders for pickup or delivery. The project encourages fair trade, local sourcing, and sustainable consumption."}, {"id": "AI-422", "title": "Gamified Learning Platform for Rural Education", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25048", "supervisor": "Tanwarjot Singh", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH15", "description": "A gamified education platform designed for rural areas aims to deliver engaging, interactive, and personalized learning experiences through game mechanics. It addresses barriers like limited resources and digital access, enhances motivation, and improves educational outcomes. The platform fosters inclusivity, builds digital skills, and supports Sustainable Development Goals by making quality education accessible to underserved communities."}, {"id": "AI-423", "title": "Geospatial Machine Learning Using Maps and Spatial Data for Smart Decision Systems", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "The topic idea comes from the integration of AI/ML with spatial data (GeoML) to solve real-world problems in smart systems and urban analytics.", "supervisor": "Rahul Panola", "sitting_place": "27-205-CH16", "description": "This project focuses on the development of a Geospatial Machine Learning (GeoML) system that integrates artificial intelligence with geographic data to solve real-world problems. Unlike traditional machine learning models, which assume independent data points, this project considers spatial relationships, dependencies, and geographic context to improve prediction accuracy. The system utilizes spatial data such as satellite imagery, GPS data, and geographic information system (GIS) datasets. These datasets may include raster data (images) and vector data (points, lines, and polygons). The project applies advanced machine learning and deep learning techniques, including Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for image-based analysis and Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) for modeling spatial relationships. A key component of the project is spatial feature engineering, where geographic features such as distance, neighborhood influence, and spatial autocorrelation are incorporated into the model. The system also follows a structured pipeline that includes data collection, preprocessing, feature extraction, model training, and spatial validation. The project has multiple real-world applications, such as predicting traffic congestion, monitoring environmental changes, analyzing urban growth, and supporting smart city development. It can also be extended to climate modeling, agriculture monitoring, and disaster prediction. One of the major strengths of this project is its ability to handle large-scale and dynamic spatial data. By integrating spatio-temporal modeling, the system can analyze how geographic patterns change over time. This makes it highly relevant for modern AI-driven systems. Overall, this project demonstrates how the combination of AI, machine learning, and geospatial data can enable intelligent decision-making systems. It provides practical exposure to advanced technologies and prepares students for future research and industry applications in AI, data science, and smart infrastructure development."}, {"id": "AI-424", "title": "Hand2Hear : AI-Powered Gesture Communication", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Heena( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "Hand2Hear: AI-Powered Gesture Communication is an innovative system designed to bridge the communication gap between individuals using sign language and those unfamiliar with it. The project uses advanced computer vision and artificial intelligence to accurately interpret hand gestures in real time and convert them into meaningful text. Taking accessibility a step further, the system also transforms this text into natural, human-like speech, enabling seamless interaction in everyday situations. Hand2Hear empowers people with speech or hearing impairments by giving their gestures a clear and audible voice. It eliminates the need for intermediaries and encourages independent communication across social, educational, and professional spaces. The AI model is trained to recognize a wide range of gestures with high precision, ensuring smooth and reliable performance. Its user-friendly interface and fast processing make it suitable for smartphones, desktops, and embedded devices. By combining gesture recognition with text-to-speech technology, Hand2Hear aims to create a world where everyone can be heard regardless of the language they speak with. This project showcases the power of technology in promoting inclusivity, accessibility, and meaningful human connection."}, {"id": "AI-425", "title": "Hybrid Deep Learning & Graph Neural Network Approach for Electricity Theft Detection in Smart Grids", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "NA", "supervisor": "Ashish Kumar Verma", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH31", "description": "The project proposes a hybrid Deep Learning and Graph Neural Network model for detecting electricity theft in smart grids. It analyzes time-series consumption data and grid relationships to identify anomalies and fraudulent activities. By combining temporal and spatial features, the system improves detection accuracy, reduces non-technical losses, and enhances the efficiency, reliability, and security of modern power distribution systems."}, {"id": "AI-426", "title": "Hybrid GAN Model for Vintage Image Restoration and Upscaling", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Navjot Kaur", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH27", "description": "Modern AI-based super-resolution models are predominantly trained on contemporary digital photography, optimizing for computational sharpness and perceptual clarity. When applied to cultural heritage imagery, these methods often compromise historical authenticity by introducing modern textures or erasing crucial era-specific markers. This project proposes a Hybrid GAN architecture designed to bridge the gap between generative power and historical fidelity. The model aims to restore degraded vintage media while strictly preserving the aesthetic DNA of its specific photographic era."}, {"id": "AI-427", "title": "Image Recognition of Cattle and Buffalo using AI in India", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25004", "supervisor": "Priyanka Gupta", "sitting_place": "28-202-CH20", "description": "Image recognition of cattle and buffalo is an AI-based application where cameras and computer vision identify livestock based on the image or video. The technology in Indian scenario can be used to assist farmers to differentiate cows and buffaloes, to monitor animals, early detection of disease, and enhanced farm management in dairy farms. It saves time, manual work and assists in superior decision making in rural and urban livestock sector."}, {"id": "AI-428", "title": "Intelligent Brain Tumor Diagnosis From MRI Images Via Transfer Learning And Advance Feature Optimization Techniques", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH : 2025", "supervisor": "Jobanpreet Singh", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH12", "description": "Intelligent brain tumor diagnosis from MRI images has evolved significantly through the integration of transfer learning (TL) and advanced feature optimization. These techniques address the critical challenge of limited labeled medical data by repurposing pre-trained models and refining the most diagnostic features for classification"}, {"id": "AI-429", "title": "Interactive Prompt Optimization Framework for Improving Text-to-Image Generation.", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Self-Proposed based on research in Generative AI and Prompt Engineering", "supervisor": "Atul Kumar", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH19", "description": "This project develops an interactive system that improves user text prompts for text-to-image models like Stable Diffusion. The system refines prompts using LLM suggestions and evaluates image quality using CLIP similarity and user ratings. The goal is to increase image relevance, aesthetic quality, and user satisfaction through automatic prompt optimization and feedback learning."}, {"id": "AI-430", "title": "Legal Document Summarization using NLP", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH 2025", "supervisor": "Jobanpreet Singh", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH12", "description": "Effective Summarization Techniques for Legal Document Analysis, you are tackling one of the most challenging domains in NLP. Legal text is characterized by extreme length, complex hierarchical structures, and highly specific archaic terminology"}, {"id": "AI-431", "title": "Legal Document Summarization using NLP", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH 2026", "supervisor": "Jobanpreet Singh", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH12", "description": "Effective Summarization Techniques for Legal Document Analysis, you are tackling one of the most challenging domains in NLP. Legal text is characterized by extreme length, complex hierarchical structures, and highly specific archaic terminology (legalese)."}, {"id": "AI-432", "title": "Lightweight Hybrid Deep Neural Networks for Visibility-Aware Object Detection", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Amer Amin", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH33", "description": "Lightweight Hybrid Deep Neural Networks (LH-DNNs) for visibility-aware object detection represent an advanced approach to improving detection performance in challenging real-world conditions such as fog, rain, low light, haze, and occlusion. Traditional object detection models often struggle when visibility is degraded, as important visual features become less distinguishable. LH-DNNs address this limitation by combining efficiency, adaptability, and contextual awareness into a unified framework that maintains high accuracy while reducing computational cost. At the core of this approach is the concept of \"hybridization,\" where multiple neural network paradigms are integrated to leverage their complementary strengths. Typically, convolutional neural networks (CNNs) are used for spatial feature extraction, while lightweight architectures such as MobileNet or EfficientNet variants are employed to reduce model size and computational overhead. In addition, attention mechanisms and sometimes transformer-based modules are incorporated to enhance feature representation by focusing on the most relevant regions of an image, especially under poor visibility conditions. The \"lightweight\" aspect is critical for real-time applications such as autonomous driving, surveillance systems, and mobile robotics. These systems often operate under strict constraints in terms of memory, power, and processing speed. LH-DNNs are designed using techniques such as depthwise separable convolutions, model pruning, quantization, and knowledge distillation. These optimizations significantly reduce the number of parameters and floating-point operations (FLOPs), enabling deployment on edge devices without substantial loss in detection performance. A key innovation in visibility-aware object detection is the explicit modeling of environmental conditions. LH-DNNs incorporate visibility estimation modules that assess the quality of the input image. This can be achieved through auxiliary subnetworks trained to classify or regress visibility levels (e.g., clear, foggy, rainy, or low-light). Based on this assessment, the network dynamically adjusts its feature extraction or detection strategy. For instance, in foggy conditions, the model may emphasize contrast-enhanced features or rely more on contextual cues rather than fine textures. Another important component is multi-scale feature fusion. Objects in low-visibility environments may appear blurred or partially obscured, making it difficult to detect them at a single scale. LH-DNNs use feature pyramid networks (FPNs) or similar structures to aggregate information across different resolutions. This improves the detection of both small and large objects, even when visibility varies across the scene. Data augmentation and specialized training strategies also play a crucial role. Training datasets are often enhanced with synthetic visibility degradations such as Gaussian blur, noise, haze simulation, and brightness reduction. This helps the model generalize better to diverse environmental conditions. Additionally, domain adaptation techniques may be used to bridge the gap between clean training data and real-world degraded images. Loss functions in LH-DNNs are sometimes modified to account for visibility conditions. For example, the model may assign higher weights to hard-to-detect objects in low-visibility regions, encouraging better learning in challenging scenarios. Similarly, attention-guided loss functions can help the network focus on critical areas of the image. In summary, Lightweight Hybrid Deep Neural Networks for visibility-aware object detection offer a powerful solution to the limitations of conventional detection systems. By integrating efficient architectures, adaptive mechanisms, and environmental awareness, these models achieve a balance between accuracy and computational efficiency. Their ability to operate reliably under adverse conditions makes them highly suitable for safety-critical and real-time applications, paving the way for more robust and intelligent visual systems."}, {"id": "AI-433", "title": "Livestock e-commerce platform", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Business Model", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2020 (SIH?2020) PS?ID?MK100", "supervisor": "Dr. V Devendran", "sitting_place": "26-203-C3", "description": "Develop a digital platform to connect livestock sellers and buyers, enabling farmers to list animals with details like breed, age, health status, and price. The system should support secure payments, order tracking, and basic logistics, while providing buyers with verified information and a transparent, reliable marketplace for livestock trading."}, {"id": "AI-434", "title": "Machine Learning-Based Adaptive Prediction Error Expansion for High-Capacity Image Steganography", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "Inspired by existing research in reversible data hiding and Prediction Error Expansion techniques", "supervisor": "Deepali Bhagat", "sitting_place": "34-205-CH7", "description": "With digital communication growing it's crucial to send data securely and without being noticed. Steganography, which is the art of hiding information in digital media like images seems like a good solution because it hides the fact that you're even communicating. One technique called Prediction Error Expansion (PEE) has gotten attention for letting you hide data in a way that can be reversed and doesn't distort the image much.. Old PEE methods use simple predictors, which limits how much data you can hide and how good the image looks. This project suggests an approach that uses Machine Learning (ML) with Prediction Error Expansion. The idea is to use ML models to predict pixel values accurately. This reduces the prediction error so you can hide data without making the image look bad. By making predictions more accurate hiding data gets more efficient. This means you can hide data (measured in bits per pixel) while keeping the image looking good. The proposed system also introduces a way to adapt when hiding data. Of spreading data evenly across the whole image the model will look at the images characteristics, like edges, textures and smooth areas. Usually areas with lots of detail (edges or textures) can handle hidden data without looking distorted. Smooth areas are more sensitive. Machine Learning will be used to classify these areas and decide how data to hide in each one. This ensures a balance between how much data you can hide and how well the image looks. The implementation will be done using Python with libraries like OpenCV, NumPy and TensorFlow or PyTorch. Standard image datasets will be used to test performance. The success of the method will be measured using metrics like Peak Signal-to-Noise Ratio (PSNR) Mean Squared Error (MSE) Structural Similarity Index (SSIM) and how much data can be hidden per pixel (BPP). A comparison will also be made with PEE-based methods to show improvements. The goal of this research is to create a model that combines the best of old reversible data hiding and new Machine Learning. It aims to provide a solution thats scalable and efficient for communication using images. This could be used in watermarking securing medical data and exchanging confidential information. Overall this work aims to combine steganography techniques with intelligent data-driven approaches. It offers a robust and adaptive framework, for hiding a lot of data with little distortion."}, {"id": "AI-435", "title": "Navilux:All-in-one Smart Travel Assistant", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH25082", "supervisor": "Bhavna", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH14", "description": "Navilux is an all-in-one smart travel assistant designed to solve the problem of traveler's juggling multiple disconnected apps. It provides a unified platform for real-time insights on weather, AQI, and terrain, alongside critical safety information like crime rate maps and nearby police locators. The app also helps users find essentials like EV stations, hospitals, veg/vegan food, and provides data on network strength for seamless journeys"}, {"id": "AI-436", "title": "Predictive Maintenance Using Real-Time Anomaly Detection and Automated Scheduling", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Self-Proposed based on research in Industrial IoT, Machine Learning, and Predictive Maintenance Literature", "supervisor": "Atul Kumar", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH19", "description": "This project develops a predictive maintenance system using real-time sensor data such as temperature, pressure, vibration, and humidity. Machine learning models including MLP, 1D-CNN, and Autoencoder detect anomalies and predict equipment faults. The system generates automated maintenance alerts and scheduling recommendations to reduce downtime and maintenance costs."}, {"id": "AI-437", "title": "QuantLive: Face Liveness Detection Model using AI", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "https://www.sih.gov.in/sih2024PS", "supervisor": "Dr. Fayaz Ahmad Khan", "sitting_place": "26-205-CH19", "description": "QuantLive is a next-generation face liveness detection framework designed to enhance digital security by preventing spoofing attacks in real time. Unlike traditional authentication systems that rely solely on face recognition, QuantLive integrates anti-spoofing mechanisms to verify whether the presented face belongs to a live person or is a fraudulent attempt using a photo, or mask. By leveraging lightweight machine learning (ML) models and browser-based deployment, it offers scalable, efficient, and accessible liveness verification across devices without compromising speed or accuracy. Its primary applications span secure login systems, digital attendance, online examinations, KYC verification, and fraud prevention in payment systems, making it a crucial solution for identity security in the modern digital landscape."}, {"id": "AI-438", "title": "Rehabilitation Exercise Assessment Using YOLO-Based Pose Estimation and a Graph Convolutional Network", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH186: Smart India Hackathon 2022", "supervisor": "Dr Dhanpratap Singh", "sitting_place": "26-203-C2", "description": "The growing need for remote telerehabilitation is hindered by the lack of real-time supervision, leading to poor patient adherence and incorrect exercise execution, which can delay recovery and increase the risk of injury. While traditional approaches have relied on cumbersome wearable sensors or monolithic deep learning models, these solutions often struggle to differentiate between exercise recognition and fine-grained quality assessment. To address this, we propose a lightweight, two-stage framework: first, a YOLO-based pose estimator extracts skeletal keypoints in real-time, and second, a Graph Convolutional Network (GCN) models the spatio-temporal relationships of the skeleton to classify exercise quality. Experiments on the public UI-PRMD dataset demonstrate our approach achieves 99.7% accuracy in classifying exercise correctness. This result not only surpasses traditional monolithic models like 3D-CNNs (which score approximately 89.5%) but also outperforms other contemporary spatio-temporal models, including \\*\\*LSTM-based approaches (at 98.5%) and standard \\*\\*Ensemble-based Graph Convolutional Networks (at 99.2%), highlighting our method's superior ability to capture fine-grained joint relationships. This work validates that a modular YOLO and GCN-based system is an effective and efficient solution for automated rehabilitation assessment. Future work will focus on expanding the library of exercises and incorporating 3D pose data for more robust, view-invariant analysis."}, {"id": "AI-439", "title": "SAFETY SPHERE", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Product", "source": "SDG", "supervisor": "Ramanjeet Kaur Dhaliwal", "sitting_place": "26-203-CH17", "description": "To prevent such accidents and suicides from heights, a smart safety system can be installed in buildings. All windows and terraces will have strong safety nets. If someone tries to cut these nets, an alarm will go off immediately, the doors and windows will lock automatically, and ultrasonic sensors (placed at regular intervals) will be activated. At the same time, Al cameras placed at different angles on the building will start monitoring. If the sensors detect unusual movement, a foldable hydraulic net installed on the first floor will open to catch the person safely. The system will also notify the nearest ambulance and rescue team right away. Similarly, if someone tries to cross the danger line at the terrace or balcony, pressure plates will detect their weight, and a hydraulic glass barrier will rise to block them from jumping. This way, the system can stop accidents and suicides in real time. To make it even stronger, an additional feature can be added through a mobile application. This app will connect with the system and provide SOS alerts. If a person is standing near the barrier or terrace for a long time and the Al system detects signs of sadness or anxiety, the app will send a notification to their family members. At the same time, the safety system will be activated to prevent any harmful action. The entire setup can also run on solar power, making it reliable and sustainable. With this model, we can save countless lives and provide peace of mind to families."}, {"id": "AI-440", "title": "SAHAYAK- AI POWERED OFFLINE LEARNING BASED SYSTEM", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Sheetal", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH13", "description": "Sahayak is an innovative capstone project focused on developing an offline-capable Artificial Intelligence (AI) tutoring agent designed to democratize and personalize education in resource-constrained environments. By leveraging edge computing, machine learning, and local data analytics, Sahayak operates entirely on local devices and networks to deliver adaptive instruction, real-time feedback, and individualized formative assessments without requiring continuous internet connectivity. The system integrates gamification strategies to drive and sustain student engagement, all while prioritizing data privacy and overcoming the limitations of traditional cloud-based platforms. Ultimately, Sahayak serves as a resilient, technology-driven teaching assistant that bridges the digital divide, ensuring equitable access to high-quality, personalized learning experiences for students in regions affected by technological infrastructure gaps."}, {"id": "AI-441", "title": "Sentiment Analysis for Code-Mixed Text in Low-Resource Languages using Multilingual Natural Language Processing Techniques", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Mrinalini Rana", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH3", "description": "In the current digital era, the rapid growth of online communication platforms has led to a significant increase in user-generated textual data. People frequently express their opinions, emotions, and experiences through social media, reviews, and online discussions. This has made sentiment analysis an important area of research within Natural Language Processing (NLP). However, most existing advancements in sentiment analysis are focused on resource-rich languages, while low-resource and code-mixed languages continue to receive limited attention. In multilingual environments, especially in countries like India, users commonly mix English with regional languages while communicating online. This results in code-mixed text that often includes transliteration, spelling variations, and informal expressions. Such characteristics make the task of sentiment classification more challenging. In addition, the lack of sufficient annotated datasets and linguistic resources for many regional languages further complicates the development of effective models. This study aims to explore and understand the existing approaches used for sentiment analysis in low-resource and code-mixed language settings. A set of selected research papers has been considered to examine different techniques, including traditional machine learning methods, deep learning models, and recent transformer-based approaches. The study focuses on analyzing how these methods handle multilingual data, limited resources, and real-world text variations. The purpose of this work is to build a clear and structured understanding of the current research landscape in this domain. By studying various approaches and methodologies, this report aims to identify important aspects that can guide further research work in sentiment analysis for linguistically diverse and underrepresented languages."}, {"id": "AI-442", "title": "Share&Care : A Donation Platform", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2024 (SIH?2024)", "supervisor": "Dr. V Devendran", "sitting_place": "26-203-C3", "description": "Design a digital donation platform connecting donors and receivers directly to ensure transparency, efficiency, and accountability. The system should allow donors to view verified needs, contribute securely, and track utilization, while enabling recipients to register their needs, request aid, and receive support without intermediaries, reducing delays and misuse."}, {"id": "AI-443", "title": "Smart Digital Identity and Attendance System using AI and Blockchain", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH: smart india hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Saurabh Pandey( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "A smart attendance system integrating AI-based face recognition with blockchain for secure and tamper-proof record keeping. The system uses FaceNet for identity verification and Ethereum blockchain for immutable storage, ensuring accuracy, transparency, and prevention of proxy attendance."}, {"id": "AI-444", "title": "Smart Energy Optimization System Using AI-Based Load Forecasting and Automated Appliance Scheduling", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning", "nature": "Application", "source": "Self-Proposed based on research in Generative AI and Prompt Engineering", "supervisor": "Atul Kumar", "sitting_place": "25-301-CH19", "description": "This project develops an AI-based smart energy optimization system that forecasts household energy demand using time-series machine learning models. The system schedules appliances automatically to minimize peak load, reduce electricity cost, and improve energy efficiency. IoT sensor data and real-time dashboards are used to monitor usage and evaluate performance."}, {"id": "AI-445", "title": "Smart Platform for Food Redistribution and Waste Reduction (SharePlate)", "category": "AI-ML", "area": "Cognitive Computing", "nature": "Product", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2020. (PS No. AG50)", "supervisor": "Dr. V Devendran", "sitting_place": "26-203-C3", "description": "SharePlate is an innovative digital platform designed to minimize food wastage and promote sustainable redistribution of surplus food. The system connects donors, NGOs, and volunteers through an AI-assisted web application that ensures safe and efficient collection and distribution of excess food. By using real-time tracking, data analytics, and smart notifications, SharePlate supports both environmental conservation and community welfare."}, {"id": "DS-072", "title": "AI-Based Crop Recommendation System", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Saqib Ul Sabha", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH14", "description": "Agriculture is a critical sector for food security and economic growth, yet farmers often face significant challenges in selecting the most appropriate crop for cultivation. Rapid changes in climate, variations in soil quality, and limited access to scientific knowledge or expert advice can lead to unsuitable crop choices. Such decisions frequently result in low yields, inefficient use of resources such as water and fertilizers, and financial losses for farmers. Conventional methods of crop selection rely heavily on experience or generalized recommendations, which do not account for the unique conditions of each farm. This gap highlights the need for a data-driven decision-support system that can analyze multiple environmental and soil parameters to suggest the most suitable crop. This project addresses the problem by developing an AI-based crop recommendation system that leverages soil nutrient values (Nitrogen, Phosphorus, Potassium), soil pH, and climatic factors (rainfall, humidity, temperature) to predict the most appropriate crop for a given set of conditions. By integrating machine learning with a user-friendly web application, the proposed system aims to guide farmers toward informed, evidence-based crop selection, thereby improving agricultural productivity, reducing crop failure risk, and promoting sustainable farming practices."}, {"id": "DS-073", "title": "A Robust Multi-Model Deep Learning Framework for Deepfake Image Detection Using Spatial and Frequency Domain Analysis", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Big Data", "nature": "Research", "source": "sih", "supervisor": "Dr. Saqib Ul Sabha", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH14", "description": "This project presents a robust and scalable deepfake image detection framework that leverages multiple deep learning architectures to improve detection accuracy and generalization. The system is designed to classify facial images as real or fake by integrating both spatial and frequency-domain feature analysis. A custom dataset comprising real and synthetically generated deepfake images is constructed to simulate real-world variations, including noise, compression, and blur. The proposed pipeline consists of face detection, preprocessing, feature extraction, and classification stages. Multiple state-of-the-art models, including MesoNet variants, MobileNetV2, XceptionNet, EfficientNetB4, and a custom FrequencyNet, are trained and evaluated under a unified experimental setup. Unlike traditional single-model approaches, this work performs a comprehensive comparative analysis to identify the most effective architecture in terms of accuracy, computational efficiency, and generalization capability. The integration of frequency-based analysis enables the detection of subtle manipulation artifacts that are often missed by conventional spatial models. The proposed framework aims to provide a reliable and deployable solution for real-world deepfake detection applications, contributing to the prevention of misinformation, identity fraud, and digital manipulation."}, {"id": "DS-074", "title": "A Study on the Application of Educational Data Mining and Learning Analytics Techniques for Predictive Modeling in Education", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Review", "source": "GOOGLE SCHOLAR", "supervisor": "Neha Garg( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This paper explores how Educational Data Mining and Learning Analytics techniques are applied to build predictive models in education. It highlights key algorithms, data sources, and evaluation metrics used to forecast student performance, detect at-risk learners, and support data-driven decisions. The work also discusses ethical considerations and the role of predictive analytics in improving educational outcomes"}, {"id": "DS-075", "title": "Addressing Class Imbalance in Software Fault Prediction Using Machine Learning", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Big Data", "nature": "Research", "source": "Research", "supervisor": "Dr. Ashu", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH6", "description": "Software fault prediction plays an important role in improving software quality by identifying defect-prone modules at an early stage of development. However, software fault datasets are usually imbalanced, where faulty modules are much fewer than non-faulty ones, causing conventional machine learning models to bias toward the majority class and reducing prediction effectiveness. This research focuses on addressing the class imbalance problem by proposing a hybrid machine learning-based fault prediction approach that combines imbalance handling techniques with classification models. The study aims to improve the detection of defective software modules and evaluate the proposed method using suitable performance metrics for imbalanced datasets"}, {"id": "DS-076", "title": "Advancing Clinical Intelligence: Leveraging Natural Language Processing (NLP) to Transform Unstructured Electronic Health Records (EHRs) into Actionable Data", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Saqib Ul Sabha", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH14", "description": "This project will investigate the application of advanced Natural Language Processing (NLP) and deep learning techniques to unlock the vast, yet often inaccessible, information contained within unstructured healthcare data. Approximately 80% of patient data resides in free-text clinical sources, such as physician notes, discharge summaries, pathology reports, and radiology readings. This project will focus on designing and validating robust NLP pipelines to perform key tasks, including information extraction (e.g., symptoms, dosages, procedures), computational phenotyping, and sentiment analysis of patient records. The ultimate goal is to transform narrative clinical documentation into structured, quantitative data to enhance clinical decision support, accelerate medical research, improve quality of care metrics, and support population health management."}, {"id": "DS-077", "title": "AI-based Drop-out Prediction and Counseling System", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Veerpal Kaur", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH8", "description": "By The project aims to create a unified digital dashboard that brings together student data such as attendance, test scores, and fee records, which are usually stored separately. By applying simple rule based checks along with machine learning, the system will identify students who are at risk of dropping out much earlier. At-risk students will be highlighted with clear visual indicators, and regular notifications will be sent to mentors and parents. The solution is designed to be simple, affordable, and easy to use, helping educators intervene on time without replacing their judgment."}, {"id": "DS-078", "title": "AI-Based Farmer Query Support and Advisory System", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Saqib Ul Sabha", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH14", "description": "Agriculture is one of the oldest and most essential professions in the world, serving as the foundation of food security and economic growth. However, in many rural and semi-urban regions, farmers continue to struggle with limited access to timely and accurate agricultural information. Modern farming requires continuous awareness of climate conditions, soil health, pest management, fertilizer use, and access to market data. Unfortunately, farmers often depend on manual advisory services, which are not always reliable or readily available. The AI-Based Farmer Query Support and Advisory System is designed to bridge this gap by leveraging the power of Artificial Intelligence (AI), Natural Language Processing (NLP), and Machine Learning (ML). The project aims to provide farmers with personalized, real-time, and easy-to-understand advisory services through both mobile and web applications. Farmers can ask their questions using text or voice in their regional language, and the system will analyze the queries to provide quick, actionable responses. By focusing on accessibility, multilingual support, and real-time insights, this system empowers farmers to make better decisions about crop selection, pest and disease control, irrigation scheduling, and government scheme utilization. The overall goal is not only to improve agricultural productivity but also to contribute to the vision of smart agriculture and Digital India."}, {"id": "DS-079", "title": "AI-Based Farmer Query Support and Advisory System", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Dr. Aarti", "sitting_place": "28-203-C2", "description": "Digital Krishi Officer is an AI-powered multilingual agricultural advisory system that assists farmers through text, voice, or image queries. Using NLP, computer vision, and contextual reasoning, it provides personalized, real-time recommendations on crop management, pest control, and government schemes, ensuring expert-level guidance and improved productivity. Project/Research Outcome An intelligent, adaptive, and multilingual AI platform for farmers offering personalized, real-time agricultural advice using NLP and AI models integrated with government and meteorological data."}, {"id": "DS-080", "title": "AI-Based Internship Recommendation Engine for PM Internship Scheme", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "National Education Policy 2020 & PM Internship Scheme (Government of India)", "supervisor": "Veerpal Kaur", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH8", "description": "This project proposes an AI-powered recommendation engine designed to match students with suitable internships under the PM Internship Scheme. The system uses Machine Learning algorithms to analyze students' profiles, academic performance, interests, and skillsets to generate personalized internship recommendations. The platform ensures fairness, transparency, and accessibility, improving internship allocation efficiency for students nationwide."}, {"id": "DS-081", "title": "AI-Enabled Public Health Chatbot for Early Detection, Personalized Alerts, and Epidemic Preparedness", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Ashu", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH6", "description": "This project aims to develop an intelligent public health chatbot that leverages Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Natural Language Processing (NLP) to provide real-time health support, awareness, and epidemic monitoring. The chatbot will interact with users in natural language to track symptoms, provide hyper-personalized health alerts, simulate potential epidemic spreads, and deliver preventive recommendations. We will use Machine Learning (ML), NLP, and cloud-based deployment technologies to ensure scalability, multi-language communication, and accessibility across devices (mobile/web). The chatbot will act as an early intervention tool that bridges the gap between healthcare services and the general population, especially in underserved areas."}, {"id": "DS-082", "title": "Al-Based Crop Recommendation for Farmers", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Dr. Aarti", "sitting_place": "28-203-C2", "description": "The document, \"An AI-Driven Intelligent Crop Advisory System for Sustainable and Profitable Farming,\" presents a detailed proposal and analysis of AgroIntel™, an advanced, AI-based crop recommendation system implemented as a web application to support data-driven and sustainable agriculture. This integrated solution aims to revolutionize the farming sector by moving it from a traditional, reactive business model to a proactive, intelligent, and sustainable one. The Need for Intelligent Advisory Systems The agricultural sector faces a crucial crisis: meeting the rising global food demand while simultaneously contending with limited natural resources, shifting climatic patterns, and the urgent need for environmental sustainability. Traditional farming methods, often relying on anecdotal or culturally appropriate advice, can be unscientific and lack the real-time adjustment needed to handle dynamic variables like non-stationary weather, varying soil conditions, or volatile market prices. This often results in inefficient resource use, low productivity, poor market linkage, economic losses, and unsustainable practices, especially for small-holding and marginal farmers in developing nations. To bridge this gap, the focus has shifted to leveraging advanced technologies like Artificial Intelligence (AI), the Internet of Things (IoT), and data analytics to facilitate precision agriculture and smart decision-making. AI-based crop recommendation systems, such as AgroIntel™, have emerged as a \"game-changing solution\" by providing personalized, data-driven recommendations to farmers."}, {"id": "DS-083", "title": "Al-Powered Crop Yield Prediction and Optimization", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Dr. Aarti", "sitting_place": "28-203-C2", "description": "The project titled \"AI-Based Crop Yield Prediction and Optimization \" focuses on developing an intelligent framework that leverages Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) to predict agricultural crop yields and support efficient farm management. The system analyzes multiple data sources, including soil parameters, weather conditions, and crop characteristics, to estimate yield outcomes and identify factors influencing productivity. Through advanced data analytics and predictive modeling, the platform assists farmers in making data-driven decisions regarding irrigation planning, fertilizer management, and optimal sowing periods. It aims to reduce dependency on manual estimation methods and improve both accuracy and resource utilization. The system also incorporates a user-friendly interface that allows farmers to visualize predictions and receive customized recommendations for improved yield performance. Additionally, the platform is designed to learn continuously from new agricultural data, improving its predictive accuracy over time. This initiative promotes sustainable and precision agriculture, ensuring better crop management, reduced resource wastage, and increased profitability for farmers. Overall, the project serves as a digital decision-support tool that combines technology and agriculture to enhance food security and environmental sustainability."}, {"id": "DS-084", "title": "Arogya Sahayak", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Ashu", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH6", "description": "Arogya Sahayak is an AI-based health chatbot made to help people in rural and semi-urban areas of India. It provides reliable health information about common diseases, symptoms, vaccinations, and preventive care. The chatbot works on WhatsApp and web, so users can easily access it on any device. It supports multiple Indian languages and includes a voice-to-text option for users who cannot type easily. It uses AI and trusted datasets to make sure the answers are both intelligent and accurate. The system is also built to work well even with low internet speed, helping users in remote areas. The project aims to make people more aware of their health, reduce misinformation, and build trust by providing answers based on verified government data."}, {"id": "DS-085", "title": "Assured Contract Farming System for Stable Market Access", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Veerpal Kaur", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH8", "description": "This project aims to create a simple digital platform that directly connects farmers with buyers through assured contract farming. It will work like a trusted bridge---farmers will get a guaranteed market for their crops, and buyers will find reliable suppliers. The platform will make the process clear and easy with open communication, digital contracts, fair price discussions, and secure payments. For farmers, this means stable income, freedom from middlemen, and timely payments. For buyers, it ensures a steady supply of quality produce with better traceability."}, {"id": "DS-086", "title": "Automated Attendance System for Rural Schools", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH 25012 : Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Arshiya", "sitting_place": "36-309-A-CH6", "description": "Automated Attendance System for Rural Schools -- Summary Overview: The Automated Attendance System for rural schools is an advanced AI-powered solution designed to simplify and automate the process of recording student attendance. Using technologies such as face recognition, RFID tags, or fingerprint scanning, the system captures attendance in real-time, ensuring accuracy and reliability. By reducing manual effort, the system frees up valuable teaching time, allowing educators to focus more on instruction and student engagement. Beyond mere attendance, the system provides actionable insights into student presence patterns, absenteeism trends, and classroom participation, enabling school administrators to make data-driven decisions to improve student accountability and overall academic outcomes. Problem Addressed: Manual attendance recording is time-consuming and prone to errors. Teachers spend significant classroom time on registers instead of teaching. Lack of real-time monitoring makes it difficult to track absenteeism or identify at-risk students. Rural schools often lack resources and staff to maintain accurate attendance records. Inefficient tracking leads to poor management and delayed interventions. Proposed Solution: The system automates attendance and school management through: Real-time attendance recording via face recognition, RFID, or fingerprint scanning. Instant notifications to teachers and parents regarding absentees. Automatic generation of daily, weekly, and monthly attendance reports. Analytics dashboards to track attendance trends and identify irregular patterns. Secure, scalable architecture suitable for deployment across multiple schools. Objectives: Streamline the attendance process to save teacher time. Ensure accurate, error-free attendance data. Provide real-time monitoring of student presence. Generate reports and analytics to enhance school management. Improve student accountability and reduce absenteeism. Enable scalable deployment in rural school networks with limited resources. Key Features: Automated attendance using biometric or image-based methods. Real-time absentee notifications for teachers and parents. Daily, weekly, and monthly attendance reports with analytics. Data-driven insights to monitor student presence and improve management. Secure, scalable, and user-friendly system suitable for rural environments. Expected Outcomes: Accurate, error-free attendance records. Reduced teacher workload and increased classroom efficiency. Improved student accountability and reduced absenteeism. Data-driven insights for school administrators to make informed decisions. Scalable deployment across multiple rural schools, enhancing efficiency and educational outcomes. Novelty: Integration of AI and biometric technologies in rural school environments. Real-time monitoring and absentee notifications. Attendance analytics to track trends and identify at-risk students. Scalable, secure, and easy-to-use platform for low-resource settings. Bridging the gap between technology and rural education management for better learning outcomes."}, {"id": "DS-087", "title": "Automated Timetable system for classrooms", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH 2025 (PROBLEM STATMENT NO. 25028)", "supervisor": "Dr. Amritpal Singh", "sitting_place": "28-204-C1", "description": "Timetable scheduling is developed to simplify the process of creating and organizing academic schedules for institutions. It gathers information about subjects, teachers, classrooms, and student batches to produce an ideal timetable. Using these rule-based procedures such as Graph and Greedy Algorithms, adequate allocation of classrooms, balanced faculty workload and efficient utilization of time are achieved. It will be developed in Node.js (server) and AngularJS (client-side) for real-time collaboration, timeline visualization and automatic conflicts resolution, with the goal to minimize human labor and mistakes."}, {"id": "DS-088", "title": "Comprehensive Crop Disease Detection and Classification using PlantDoc and Web-Sourced Datasets", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Big Data", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon", "supervisor": "Dr. Saqib Ul Sabha", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH14", "description": "This project will focus on developing an intelligent system for crop disease detection and crop classification using deep learning techniques. It will involve working with multiple datasets, including PlantDoc and web-sourced images, to build robust and accurate models. Various approaches such as convolutional neural networks, transfer learning, and data augmentation will be explored to improve performance. The project will also include comparative analysis to evaluate different methods and identify the most effective approach for real-world agricultural applications."}, {"id": "DS-089", "title": "Deep Learning for Automated cattle and Buffaloes Breed Recognition", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Saqib Ul Sabha", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH14", "description": "This project aims to develop an automated system for identifying cattle and buffalo breeds from images. Leveraging deep learning, particularly Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), the system will analyze visual traits such as coat patterns, body structure, and other phenotypic features. The objective is to build a robust and scalable tool that supports farmers, researchers, and livestock professionals in breed management, genetic studies, and livestock tracking, while minimizing the need for manual intervention."}, {"id": "DS-090", "title": "Deep Learning-Based Early Detection and Classification of Alzheimer's Disease Using Multimodal Neuroimaging Data", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Big Data", "nature": "Research", "source": "sih", "supervisor": "Dr. Saqib Ul Sabha", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH14", "description": "This dissertation focuses on developing advanced deep learning methodologies for the early detection and classification of Alzheimer's disease using multimodal neuroimaging data obtained from the OASIS-3 Dataset. Alzheimer's disease is a progressive neurological disorder that affects memory and cognitive abilities, and its early diagnosis remains a critical challenge due to subtle structural and functional brain changes. The research aims to leverage MRI imaging data to build robust and generalizable models using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and transfer learning architectures such as ResNet. Special emphasis will be placed on addressing challenges related to limited and imbalanced datasets, which are common in medical imaging, by incorporating advanced data augmentation strategies, contrastive learning, and class balancing techniques. Additionally, the study will explore longitudinal data analysis to understand disease progression over time. Explainable AI (XAI) methods such as Grad-CAM will be integrated to improve interpretability and trustworthiness of the model predictions. The proposed framework will be evaluated using standard performance metrics including accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score, and ROC-AUC."}, {"id": "DS-091", "title": "Detection and Mitigation of Hallucinations in Large Language Models Using Context-Aware Validation", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Big Data", "nature": "Research", "source": "Self", "supervisor": "Dr. Manpreet Singh Sehgal", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH4", "description": "To design a context-aware validation framework that: Detects hallucinated outputs in LLM-generated text Validates responses against external or contextual knowledge Applies mitigation strategies to improve factual correctness"}, {"id": "DS-092", "title": "Detection of Macronutrient Deficiency in Plants Using Image Processing", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Big Data", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Makul Mahajan", "sitting_place": "34-209-C1", "description": "Intelligent Detection of Macronutrient Deficiencies in Plants Using Image Processing Techniques is aimed at the creation of an automated system that can detect the nutrient deficiencies in plants (including nitrogen, phosphorus and potassium) by processing the images of the plant leaves. This study builds on the use of state-of-the-art image processing algorithms, including color analysis, texture analysis, and segmentation algorithms, and deep learning networks, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to identify visual cues. The goal is to substitute the traditional manual assessment systems with a more cost-effective and scalable precision agriculture system. This technology will have the power to categorize the deficiency types and determine the level of their intensity and therefore they can take immediate corrective action and improve the level of efficiency in the use of fertilizers. The results of this study can lead to the enhanced agricultural output, less use of resources and eco-friendly production of agricultural land."}, {"id": "DS-093", "title": "Development of Travel Related Software app that can be installed on Mobile phones that could capture trip related information", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Manpreet Singh Sehgal", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH4", "description": "Background NATPAC requires accurate data for transportation planning, but manual household surveys are time-consuming, tedious, and cover a very small percentage of the population, making the planning exercise inadequate. Description The objective is to develop a travel-related software application for mobile phones to capture trip information. With user consent, the app should automatically detect some travel details and nudge the user to fill in the rest. This will help establish a comprehensive travel activity and trip chain for individuals. Expected Solution A software application that captures complete trip details and saves them to a server/database accessible by NATPAC scientists for planning purposes. The app should be able to capture the following information: . Trip number . Origin (lat, long) and start time . Destination (lat, long) and end time . Mode used . Travel distance . Trip purpose . Number of companions during the trip . Frequency and cost incurred"}, {"id": "DS-094", "title": "Digital Health Record Management System for migrant workers", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Product", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Aryan Maan", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH17", "description": "The Digital Health Record Management System for migrant workers is a secure and scalable platform designed to ensure equitable healthcare access, improve continuity of care, and strengthen disease surveillance. Migrant populations often face challenges in maintaining consistent health records, resulting in fragmented care, delayed diagnoses, and increased risk of infectious disease transmission. This system enables the creation of portable digital health records accessible via mobile and web applications, with multilingual support and seamless integration with existing health systems. It supports vaccination tracking, lab results management, referrals, and privacy-preserving public health analytics. By addressing healthcare gaps for migrant populations, the project promotes better health outcomes, stronger surveillance, reduced inequalities, and progress toward multiple Sustainable Development Goals."}, {"id": "DS-095", "title": "EduCare-Intelligent Dropout Prediction and Counselling System for Education", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Ashu", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH6", "description": "Student dropout in higher education is a problem that has several underlying factors such as academic, economic, psychological, and behavioural and therefore requires early identification. This report offers a proposal of an artificial intelligence-based prediction and counselling system which combines attendance, assessments, LMS activity, fee records and behavioural data to label at-risk students. Integrating rule-based thresholds with latest ML models (Random Forest, Gradient Boosting, Neural Networks) the system will be able to deliver interpretable outputs and cover intricate disengagement trends. It has a user-friendly dashboard with alerts and visual trends that allow mentors, administrators and families to intervene in time. The platform, which was designed as a low-cost, scalable solution, focuses on quick intervention, empowering educators, and supporting student well-being, which helps build stronger relationships between students and their mentors and families."}, {"id": "DS-096", "title": "Fake News Detection System using Machine Learning and Natural Language Processing", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Ankit Galhotra", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH14", "description": "The idea originates from the growing concern over misinformation circulating on social media and online news platforms. It draws inspiration from recent studies published in IEEE and ACM digital libraries, as well as from datasets such as the ISOT Fake News Dataset, highlighting the need for reliable AI-driven solutions to detect and mitigate fake news. This project focuses on developing an intelligent Fake News Detection System that leverages Machine Learning and Natural Language Processing to automatically identify misleading or fabricated news articles. By analyzing textual patterns, linguistic cues, and contextual meanings, the system aims to differentiate authentic information from false content, helping to reduce the spread of misinformation online."}, {"id": "DS-097", "title": "IoT-Driven Real-Time Water Quality Monitoring and Anomaly Detection System", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Big Data", "nature": "Product", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Sanjeev Kumar", "sitting_place": "34-202-CH20", "description": "Access to clean water is one of the most pressing challenges of our time. Yet, in many parts of the world, contamination goes undetected simply because traditional monitoring methods are too slow, too expensive, and too dependent on human presence. Our project was built around one central question: what if water could tell us when something is wrong --- in real time, automatically, and from anywhere? We designed an IoT-based water quality monitoring system that continuously tracks key parameters --- including turbidity, dissolved oxygen, temperature, and electrical conductivity --- using a network of smart sensors deployed at water sources. These sensors feed live data to a cloud platform, where it is stored, processed, and made available through an interactive web dashboard. Anyone with access --- whether a water authority, a researcher, or a city official --- can monitor the status of multiple water sites remotely, at any time. What sets this system apart from a simple sensor setup is its intelligence. Rather than relying on fixed thresholds that only catch obvious violations, we integrated machine learning at the core of the system. An LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory) neural network analyzes historical sensor readings to forecast upcoming trends --- predicting a drop in dissolved oxygen or a temperature shift before it becomes a crisis. Alongside this, an Isolation Forest algorithm continuously scans live data for anomalies, flagging unusual readings that might indicate contamination, equipment failure, or sudden environmental changes. The hardware side of the project uses microcontrollers (Arduino/ESP32) to collect and transmit sensor data via Wi-Fi depending on the deployment environment. This makes the system flexible enough to work in urban water treatment plants, remote rivers, agricultural irrigation systems, and even aquaculture setups. When an anomaly is detected or a predicted trend crosses a safety threshold, the system automatically sends alerts via SMS or email to the relevant authorities. In short, this project transforms water monitoring from a reactive, manual process into a proactive, automated, and intelligent one --- making it possible to protect water quality at scale, with speed, and without constant human oversight."}, {"id": "DS-098", "title": "MedGPT Assist :A Retrieval-Augmented Generation System for Medical Knowledge Support", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Research", "source": "Research Papers", "supervisor": "Pardeep Kumar", "sitting_place": "28-203-CH3", "description": "MedGPT Assist is a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system designed to provide accurate and trustworthy medical knowledge. Traditional LLMs can produce outdated or incorrect responses and often lack source citations --- which can be risky in healthcare. To solve this, MedGPT Assist retrieves information from credible medical sources such as PubMed, WHO guidelines, and clinical textbooks before generating an answer. This ensures responses are reliable, evidence-based, and easy to understand for doctors, medical students, and patients."}, {"id": "DS-099", "title": "One-Stop Personalized Career & Education Advisor Platform", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Veerpal Kaur", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH8", "description": "The project aims to develop a lightweight web and mobile platform that guides students in choosing suitable career and education paths after Class 10/12. The system will provide aptitude-based stream suggestions, map courses to career opportunities, list nearby colleges, and track important details. Personalized recommendations will help students make informed choices easily."}, {"id": "DS-100", "title": "Real-Time Disaster Information Aggregation Software", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Big Data", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Komal Arora", "sitting_place": "27-205-CH6", "description": "It is a system designed to collect, process, and deliver up-to-date information about natural or man-made disasters from multiple sources in real time. Instead of scattered information floating like debris in a storm, this software builds a structured, real-time narrative that helps save lives and coordinate response efforts efficiently. Key Features • Data Aggregation: Gathers information from sources like social media, news feeds, government alerts, sensors, and satellite data. • Real-Time Processing: Uses streaming technologies to analyze incoming data instantly. • Filtering & Validation: Applies algorithms and sometimes AI to remove false or duplicate information. • Visualization: Displays alerts on dashboards, maps, or mobile apps for easy understanding. • Notification System: Sends timely alerts to authorities and the public. Purpose • Improve early warning systems • Enable quick decision-making for emergency responders • Provide accurate and timely updates to citizens"}, {"id": "DS-101", "title": "Real-Time Public Transport Tracking for Small Cities", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Ashu", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH6", "description": "This project focuses on developing a real-time tracking system for public transport in small cities, where organized transport management is often lacking. The system enables passengers to view the live location, estimated arrival time, and route of buses or other public vehicles using GPS and IoT integration. It also allows operators to monitor fleet movement and optimize routes based on traffic and demand."}, {"id": "DS-102", "title": "Scalable Real-Time Sentiment Analysis on Social Media Data Using Apache Spark Ecosystem", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Big Data", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2024", "supervisor": "Dr. Amritpal Singh", "sitting_place": "28-204-C1", "description": "This project proposes a real-time sentiment analysis system built on the Apache Spark ecosystem. Apache Spark provides a powerful distributed computing environment that enables fast and efficient processing of large-scale data. The system uses Spark Streaming to ingest continuous streams of social media data from APIs. This allows real-time data collection and processing with minimal latency. Once the data is ingested, preprocessing is performed using Spark's distributed DataFrame and SQL operations. This includes cleaning the text, removing noise such as stop words, tokenization, and transforming unstructured text into structured formats suitable for analysis. Feature extraction techniques such as TF-IDF are applied to convert text into numerical representations. For sentiment classification, machine learning models are developed using Spark MLlib. These models, such as Naive Bayes or Logistic Regression, classify the incoming data into sentiment categories like positive, negative, and neutral. The use of MLlib ensures that model training and prediction are scalable and distributed across clusters. The processed results are stored in a NoSQL database such as Apache Cassandra, which supports high availability and efficient handling of large datasets. This enables quick retrieval and long-term storage of sentiment data. Additionally, the system can be integrated with visualization tools to create dashboards that display sentiment trends, patterns, and real-time analytics. The proposed system offers key advantages such as scalability, fault tolerance, and real-time processing capabilities. It can handle large volumes of streaming data efficiently and provide timely insights. This makes it suitable for various applications including public opinion monitoring, brand reputation analysis, disaster response management, and policy evaluation."}, {"id": "DS-103", "title": "Smart Classroom & Timetable Scheduler", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH/25028", "supervisor": "Ankit Galhotra", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH14", "description": "The current scheduling mechanism in most higher education institutes/colleges relies on manual input via spreadsheets or basic tools. These fail to account for real-time availability of faculty, room capacity, teaching load norms, subject combinations, and student preferences. A solution is required that will accommodate the various parameters required for scheduling classes for UG and PG students and return an optimized timetable"}, {"id": "DS-104", "title": "Smart Curriculum Activity & Attendance App", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Manpreet Singh Sehgal", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH4", "description": "Problem Description Many educational institutions still depend on manual attendance systems, which are time-consuming and error-prone. Teachers spend a significant portion of class time marking attendance, reducing valuable instructional hours. Additionally, students often waste free periods with unproductive activities due to a lack of structured guidance. This leads to poor time management and reduced alignment with long-term academic or career goals. There is also a gap in personalized learning support during idle classroom hours. Institutions currently lack tools that integrate daily schedules with individual student planning and automated tracking. Impact / Why this problem needs to be solved This issue impacts both administrative efficiency and student development. Automating attendance saves teachers' time and ensures more accurate records. Additionally, providing students with structured personal development activities during free time helps improve productivity, goal clarity, and learning outcomes. Institutions can also gain better insight into student behavior and engagement, allowing for more targeted support. Expected Outcomes • Automatically marks student attendance based on the daily timetable using QR code, Bluetooth/Wi-Fi proximity, or face recognition. • Displays real-time attendance on a classroom screen. • Suggests personalized academic tasks during free periods based on the student's interests, strengths, and career goals. • Generates a daily routine combining class schedule, free time, and long-term personal goals. The app will require minimal infrastructure and be usable by both students and staff with basic training. Relevant Stakeholders / Beneficiaries • Students • Teachers • College administrators • Career counselors • Education departments Supporting Data • Surveys and reports on classroom time usage, student productivity, and NEP 2020 recommendations emphasizing personalized and experiential learning."}, {"id": "DS-105", "title": "Smart Mental Health and Psychological Support Platform for Students", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Dr. Ashu", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH6", "description": "This project aims to develop a web-based application that provides a comprehensive mental health and psychological support system tailored for students in higher education. The platform will allow users to self-assess their mental and emotional well-being, discuss their concerns anonymously, and receive personalized feedback. Based on the user's input, the system will suggest actionable strategies for improving mental health, such as lifestyle adjustments, stress management tips, and mindfulness exercises. For cases requiring professional attention, the platform will provide referrals to certified psychologists or counselors. The goal is to create a safe, accessible, and supportive environment for students to monitor and improve their mental health."}, {"id": "DS-106", "title": "Smart Tourist Safety Monitoring & Incident Response System using Al, Geo-Fencing, and Blockchain-based Digital ID", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH/25002", "supervisor": "Ankit Galhotra", "sitting_place": "34-209-CH14", "description": "A blockchain-based platform issuing secure digital IDs to tourists with KYC, itinerary, and emergency info valid for their visit. AI detects anomalies like inactivity or route deviation and alerts authorities. A real-time dashboard aids police with alerts, and E-FIRs. Optional IoT bands enable live tracking and SOS. Multilingual support (10+ languages) and end-to-end encryption ensure privacy and tamper-proof travel records."}, {"id": "DS-107", "title": "Smart Tourist Safety Monitoring & Incident Response System using Al, Geo-Fencing, and Blockchain-based Digital ID", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Application", "source": "SIH: Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Manpreet Singh Sehgal", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH4", "description": "Problem Statement This problem statement proposes the development of a Smart Tourist Safety Monitoring & Incident Response System that leverages AI, Blockchain, and Geo-Fencing technologies. The system should include: Digital Tourist ID Generation Platform • A secure blockchain-based system that issues digital IDs to tourists at entry points (airports, hotels, check-posts). • These IDs should include basic KYC (Aadhaar/passport), trip itinerary, and emergency contacts, and be valid only for the duration of the visit. Mobile Application for Tourists • Auto-assign a Tourist Safety Score based on travel patterns and area sensitivity. • Geo-fencing alerts when tourists enter high-risk or restricted zones. • Panic Button with live location sharing to nearest police unit and emergency contacts. • Optional real-time tracking feature (opt-in) for families and law enforcement. AI-Based Anomaly Detection • Detect sudden location drop-offs, prolonged inactivity, or deviation from planned routes. • Flag missing, silent, or distress behaviour for investigations. Tourism Department & Police Dashboard • Real-time visualizations of tourist clusters and heat maps of high-risk zones. • Access to digital ID records, alert history, and last known locations. • Automated E-FIR generation for missing person cases. IoT Integration (Optional) • Smart bands or tags for tourists in high-risk areas (e.g., caves, forests). • Continuous health/location signals and manual SOS feature. Multilingual Support • App and platform available in 10+ Indian languages and English. • Voice/text emergency access for elderly or disabled travellers. Data Privacy & Security • End-to-end encryption and compliance with data protection laws. • Blockchain ensures tamper-proof identity and travel records. Background In regions like the Northeast, where tourism is a key economic driver, ensuring the safety of visitors is paramount. Traditional policing and manual tracking methods are insufficient in remote and high-risk areas. There is a pressing need for a smart, technology-driven solution that ensures real-time monitoring, rapid response, and secure identity verification for tourists, while maintaining privacy and ease of travel. Expected Solution A robust digital ecosystem comprising: • Web portal and mobile app for tourists and authorities. • AI/ML models for behaviour tracking and predictive alerts. • Blockchain-based ID generation and verification. • Real-time dashboards for police/tourism departments. • Optional IoT wearable integration for enhanced safety. • Automated alert dispatch and evidence logging systems."}, {"id": "DS-108", "title": "The Synthetic Frontier and the Renaissance of Rigor: A Meta-Analytical Synthesis of the 2026 Artificial Intelligence Research Landscape", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Data Science and Big Data", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH", "supervisor": "Mani Shankar Tiwari( Left )", "sitting_place": "Not specified", "description": "This project presents a meta-analytical review of the 2026 Artificial Intelligence research landscape, examining major advancements in generative AI, multimodal systems, agentic AI, explainable AI, synthetic data, and trustworthy governance. It evaluates emerging trends, methodological rigor, ethical challenges, and future directions to understand how AI research is transitioning from rapid innovation toward more reliable, transparent, and scientifically grounded systems."}, {"id": "DS-109", "title": "Variety-Specific Rice Yield Prediction and Recommendation System", "category": "Data Science and Big Data", "area": "Database Systems", "nature": "Research", "source": "SIH:Smart India Hackathon 2025", "supervisor": "Dr. Saqib Ul Sabha", "sitting_place": "26-202-CH14", "description": "This project focuses exclusively on rice cultivation and aims to build an AI-powered decision support system that not only predicts yield for different rice varieties but also provides broader, varietyspecific insights to optimize cultivation. Unlike conventional yield forecasting models, this system accounts for the distinct agronomic characteristics of rice varieties such as grain type (e.g., long-grain Basmati, medium-grain Sona Masoori, short-grain IR64), maturity duration, soil adaptability, pest/disease resistance, and irrigation needs. The system will integrate multi-source datasets covering: ? Soil properties: pH, organic carbon, nitrogen, phosphorus, potassium, and moisture levels. ? Climatic conditions: rainfall, temperature, humidity, solar radiation, and seasonal variations. ? Agronomic practices: sowing dates, fertilizer application, irrigation schedules, and pest control methods. ? Variety-specific traits: growth duration, yield potential, tolerance to drought/flood, and market demand. By combining these features, advanced machine learning algorithms such as Random Forest, XGBoost, and LSTM networks will be trained to provide broader predictions that include: ? Variety-specific yield forecasts under given soil and climate conditions. ? Optimal planting and harvesting time windows for different rice varieties. ? Water and nutrient requirement estimations to prevent under or overutilization of resources. ? Risk assessment of yield loss due to climate variability (e.g., droughts, floods, or temperature fluctuations). ? Variety adaptability scoring, ranking rice types based on their suitability to specific regions and resource constraints. Beyond prediction, the system will include a recommendation engine that suggests the most suitable rice variety for a farmer's field, considering soil fertility, water availability, and climate resilience. For instance, in drought-prone regions, drought-tolerant varieties will be prioritized, whereas in flood-prone areas, submergence-tolerant varieties will be recommended."}];
